{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738219004,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"id":"prt_e9c44ca6a001Ylv7kt7pZnFbbX","messageID":"msg_e9c44b8f8001v2rOknVCFoX4el","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","type":"text","text":"I’m reading the proposal, command docs, and handler files now to ground the UX recommendations in the actual surfaces and output envelopes.","time":{"start":1780738214506,"end":1780738218996},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_076c916f5a177fda016a23e8a67b7c81918f5b30934bf1db84","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738219072,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OyVlQMurlWerr97fsELFXTKf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"caura-memclaw (MemClaw) — Sub-Packet Proposal for 027\"\n3: packet: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement\"\n4: researchPhase: \"research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings\"\n5: newChildProposed: 1\n6: newChildNumber: \"015-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening\"\n7: amendmentsProposed: 7\n8: created: \"2026-06-06T09:15:00Z\"\n9: status: \"proposal — not yet scaffolded (operator chose proposal-doc-only)\"\n10: concurrencyNote: \"Reconciled across the concurrent 006-peck (children 009-011) and 007-gem-team (children 012-014) runs; this proposal uses 015 for its new child.\"\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # caura-memclaw — Sub-Packet Proposal for 027\n14: \n15: Derived from the 20-iteration, adversarially-verified deep-research pass in `research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/` (see `research.md`). Evidence is `file:line` into `external/caura-memclaw-main` (Apache-2.0 — design inspiration only, no code copied).\n16: \n17: **The honest headline:** caura-memclaw is built for the *opposite* deployment shape (multi-tenant fleet memory). After adversarial verification, the bulk of its transferable signal **validates 027's existing children (002-006)** and supplies a short list of **hardening-grade sharpenings**. Its marquee feature — cross-agent self-improving memory — is **negative knowledge** for a single-user store, and its **direct, asymmetric feedback mutation is an anti-pattern that confirms 027/008's default-off, shadow-first stance is correct**. Only a small set of genuinely-new, cross-cutting items justify a new child.\n18: \n19: This proposal therefore has two parts:\n20: - **Part A — one new Level-2 child `015-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening`** for the cross-cutting items that do not fit an existing child's frozen scope.\n21: - **Part B — seven amendments** to existing children (the larger share of the value).\n22: \n23: > **⚠ Reconciliation with concurrent research (read first).** A concurrent run, `research/006-peck-source-deep-mining/`, proposes new children **009-peck-verification-discipline, 010-reviewer-prompt-benchmark-substrate, 011-acceptance-coverage-gate** (its `sub-packet-proposal.md`). To avoid a numbering collision, this proposal's new child is **`015-`** (reconciled: the next free slot after peck's `009-011` and the concurrent gem-team/007 proposals `012-014`; existing implementation children run `000`-`008`). If the operator does not adopt all of peck's 009-011, the new child can be compacted to the next actually-free slot at scaffold time (per the no-delete+recreate naming convention). (This research packet is folder-scoped with its own iteration sequence `001-020`, independent of the concurrent 006 run.)\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Headline recommendation\n28: \n29: | Recommendation | Type | Target | Verdict basis |\n30: |---|---|---|---|\n31: | Idempotency receipts for retryable memory writes | NEW | 015 (P1) | T1 ADAPT |\n32: | MCP tool-ownership map (37-tool surface) | NEW | 015 (P2) | T12 ADAPT |\n33: | Default-recall stale/status hard-exclusion audit | NEW | 015 (P3) | T13 ADAPT |\n34: | `source_kind` provenance + auto-cannot-overwrite-manual | AMEND | 002 | T2 validate+sharpen |\n35: | Advisory near-duplicate (deterministic, no LLM judge) | AMEND | 002 | T3 ADAPT |\n36: | First-timestamp-idempotent tombstone + active/purgeable index split + entity≠causal boundary | AMEND | 004 | T7/T8/T10 |\n37: | Natural-key idempotent edge promotion + provenance-skip-manual | AMEND | 005 | T9 validate |\n38: | **Scope 008 down: event-capture + diagnostics first; defer active reducers** | AMEND | 008 | T4/T5/T6 |\n39: | `last_dedup_checked_at` incremental marker; explicit fingerprint is *better* than MemClaw | AMEND (confirm) | 003 | T14 validate |\n40: | Compact append-only audit for automated mutations | AMEND | 002/004/008 | T11 |\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## PART A — Proposed new child\n45: \n46: ## Proposal 015: `015-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening` — Operational write/surface hardening\n47: \n48: **Scope summary**: Three cohesive, single-user-grounded hardening additions that cross-cut or fall outside existing children's frozen scope, each directly evidenced in MemClaw and surviving adversarial verification.\n49: \n50: 1. **P1 — Idempotency receipts (T1).** A minimal SQLite operation-receipt for retryable `memory_save`/`memory_update`: key on a server-derived `(operation_id | content_hash)` plus a request fingerprint; on identical retry, replay the prior result instead of inserting a duplicate; resolve \"same retry\" vs \"same content already exists\" distinctly. Deliberately **excludes** MemClaw's HTTP pending-sentinel/TTL/poll middleware — a local single-daemon needs only the receipt + one transaction. Evidence: `common/models/idempotency.py:30-53`; `core-api/src/core_api/middleware/idempotency.py:158-203`; `common/models/memory.py:96-105` (partial unique index `deleted_at IS NULL AND client_request_id IS NOT NULL` — the SQLite analog is a partial unique index on the receipt key).\n51: 2. **P2 — MCP tool-ownership map (T12).** A lightweight ownership/stability note for the 37-tool MCP surface (who owns each tool group, add-an-operation criteria, deprecation discipline). **Explicitly rejects** MemClaw's op-dispatch consolidation (it harms LLM tool discoverability — MemClaw only proves it on a 12-tool surface) and its public-SemVer governance (internal surface). Evidence: `docs/api-surfaces.md:1-74`; anti-evidence `core-api/src/core_api/mcp_server.py:735,1169`.\n52: 3. **P3 — Default-recall stale/status hard-exclusion audit (T13).** A verify-and-fix task confirming Spec Kit's default search does not silently hard-exclude deprecated-but-relevant memories. MemClaw itself hard-excludes `outdated`/`conflicted` unless `status_filter` is supplied — a self-inconsistency worth auditing against in Spec Kit. Evidence: `core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py:986,1022`.\n53: \n54: **Level estimate**: L2 (~150-350 LOC across receipt table + write-wrapper + audit script; P2 is docs-only).\n55: **Files (indicative)**: idempotency receipt schema + `memory_save`/`memory_update` wrapper in `mcp_server/handlers/save/**`; a `docs/` ownership map under the memory skill; one audit script.\n56: \n57: **Dependencies**:\n58: - Requires: existing memory write path + SQLite index.\n59: - Coordinates with: 002 (provenance), 006 (reconciliation/idempotency overlap), 008 (reserved-type provenance). **Independent of** the concurrent peck proposals 009-011.\n60: \n61: **Out of scope (negative knowledge guardrails)**: no multi-tenant scoping, no LLM-judge dedup, no HTTP idempotency middleware, no op-dispatch tool consolidation, no SemVer/release-please governance.\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## PART B — Amendments to existing children\n66: \n67: > These are validations + sharpenings, not new scope. Each child's frozen `spec.md` scope is respected; amendments are documented for the next time each child is planned/implemented.\n68: \n69: ### Amendment to 002 (memory-write-safety)\n70: - **T2 `source_kind` enum + auto-cannot-overwrite-manual** — add an explicit `source_kind` (`human|agent|system|import|feedback`) and enforce that automated writers (enrichment, promoters, reducers) may not overwrite human/constitutional fields. MemClaw's merge-only enrichment **validates** the direction but is *partial* (metadata keys are still enriched: `merge_enrichment_fields.py:28-50`) — Spec Kit should make the field-source rule explicit, not implicit.\n71: - **T3 advisory near-duplicate** — compute `near_duplicate_of` + similarity only when embeddings already exist; deterministic threshold; advisory, never hard-reject; no LLM judge / review queue. Evidence: `detect_near_duplicate.py:25-27,106` (adopt) vs `check_semantic_duplicate.py:7-10,193-210` (the hard-reject path = do NOT copy).\n72: - **T11 automated-mutation audit** — compact append-only audit rows for automated writes. Evidence: `common/models/audit.py:11-25`.\n73: \n74: ### Amendment to 003 (incremental-index-foundation)\n75: - **T14 (confirmation)** — MemClaw uses a single **global** `Vector(VECTOR_DIM)` with no per-row embedder version/fingerprint columns (`common/models/memory.py:24`); Spec Kit's planned explicit chunk fingerprint + embedder-tuple + derived-state **improves on** MemClaw. Keep the `last_dedup_checked_at` incremental-marker idea (`memory.py:75-77`). No scope change — this is positive confirmation that 003's design is sound.\n76: \n77: ### Amendment to 004 (causal-edge-tombstones)\n78: - **T7 first-timestamp-idempotent soft-delete** — preserve the first tombstone timestamp (COALESCE-style) so repeat deletes do not extend retention. MemClaw's `memory_soft_delete` *rewrites* `deleted_at` on repeat (`postgres_service.py:418-423`) — Spec Kit should improve on this.\n79: - **T8 active/purgeable partial-index split** — index active (`deleted_at IS NULL`) and purgeable (`deleted_at IS NOT NULL`) paths separately to keep both hot. Evidence: `memory.py:96-135`.\n80: - **T10 entity≠causal boundary** — keep any co-occurrence/entity signal as *low-weight recall evidence*, never as causal truth. MemClaw has **no** memory↔memory causal edges (only `supersedes_id` + entity relations: `memory.py:79-83`, `entity.py:27-62`); defer importing an entity graph absent measured need.\n81: \n82: ### Amendment to 005 (metadata-edge-promoter)\n83: - **T9 natural-key idempotent promotion + provenance** — make generated-edge promotion idempotent via a natural-key unique constraint, tag provenance, and skip already-wired manual links. MemClaw's entity `Relation` does exactly this (`uq_relations_natural_key`, migration `001_initial_schema.py:163-165`; `postgres_service.py:2983-3048`) — direct validation of 005's planned \"avoid duplicating manual metadata links.\"\n84: \n85: ### Amendment to 006 (write-path-reconciliation)\n86: - **T1 cross-reference** — the idempotency receipt (Proposal 015/P1) is the reconciliation primitive for retry-safe writes; 006's async post-insert-enrichment model is **validated** by MemClaw's decoupled embed/enrich (the *pattern*, not the Pub/Sub infra).\n87: \n88: ### Amendment to 007 (semantic-trigger-fallback)\n89: - **T13 cross-reference** — the stale/status hard-exclusion audit (Proposal 015/P3) protects the lexical-first fallback from silently dropping deprecated-but-relevant matches.\n90: \n91: ### Amendment to 008 (learning-feedback-reducers) — the central reframe\n92: MemClaw's `evolve`→`insights` loop is the closest analog to 008 and the most important lesson. After verification it is a **cautionary anti-pattern**, not a model:\n93: - It applies **direct, immediate, asymmetric** weight deltas (success `+0.10`, failure `-0.15`) to canonical weight (`evolve_service.py:147-165`; `constants.py:494-503`), persists LLM rules **active at confidence ≥ 0.5 with no shadow state** (`evolve_service.py:904-923`), and lets low weight feed stale-archival (`postgres_service.py:1606-1644`). In a sparse single-user corpus, one mis-attributed failure can demote a rare-but-correct memory irrecoverably.\n94: \n95: Recommended amendments (all *consistent with* 008's existing default-off/shadow-first plan — this sharpens, not redirects):\n96: - **T4 — scope 008 Phase-1 to event-capture + diagnostics only.** Land an append-only feedback-event log (audit/replay/diagnostics) and **defer all active reducers** (retrieval-score / retention / FSRS mutation) until measured ledger quality proves positive value. The fleet payoff that justifies MemClaw's aggressiveness does not exist for one user.\n97: - **T5 — reserve system-generated feedback artifact types** so the user-facing agent cannot forge learning signals once any reducer consumes them. Evidence: `common/enrichment/constants.py:97-110`; `routes/memories.py:101-131`; `mcp_server.py:281-310`.\n98: - **T6 — reject asymmetric damping.** Use symmetric/soft evidence accumulation, a rare-but-correct guard (high-tier/constitutional/user-confirmed/sparse-domain memories are protected from feedback-driven demotion or archival), and **constitutional immunity** (feedback may never demote or archive constitutional/protected memories). Evidence: `constants.py:494-503`; `evolve_service.py:340-375`.\n99: - Insight modes (failures/stale/patterns) survive only as **opt-in manual diagnostics** with minimum-corpus thresholds; **divergence does not transfer** (cross-agent only: `insights_service.py:419-454,1057-1061`).\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## Sequencing\n104: \n105: 1. **008 amendment first (documentation/scoping)** — record the scope-down + symmetric-damping/constitutional-immunity invariants before any 008 implementation work begins (cheapest, highest-leverage, prevents building the anti-pattern).\n106: 2. **002 amendments** — `source_kind` + automated-mutation audit are P0 provenance gates that 008's event log also depends on.\n107: 3. **015/P1 idempotency receipts** — small, isolated, validates 006.\n108: 4. **004/005 amendments** — fold into those children when next planned.\n109: 5. **015/P2 tool-ownership map + 015/P3 stale audit** — low-risk, independent, can land anytime.\n110: \n111: > Cross-run sequencing: this proposal is **orthogonal to** and **non-conflicting with** the concurrent peck proposals (009-011) — peck addresses verification discipline / reviewer-prompt benchmarking / acceptance-coverage; this addresses memory-store write/surface hardening + the 008 feedback reframe. They can be adopted independently.\n112: \n113: ## Provenance\n114: \n115: Source: `research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/research.md` §5 (surviving teachings T1-T14), §6 (negative-knowledge ledger), §7 (027-child mapping). 20 iterations (001-020), adversarially verified (017-020) and adjudicated against MemClaw ground truth. All MemClaw references are design inspiration only (Apache-2.0; no code copied).\n\n(End of file - total 115 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"caura-memclaw (MemClaw) — Sub-Packet Proposal for 027\"\npacket: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement\"\nresearchPhase: \"research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings\"\nnewChildProposed: 1\nnewChildNumber: \"015-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening\"\namendmentsProposed: 7\ncreated: \"2026-06-06T09:15:00Z\"\nstatus: \"proposal — not yet scaffolded (operator chose proposal-doc-only)\"\nconcurrencyNote: \"Reconciled across the concurrent 006-peck (children 009-011) and 007-gem-team (children 012-014) runs; this proposal uses 015 for its new child.\"\n---\n\n# caura-memclaw — Sub-Packet Proposal for 027\n\nDerived from the 20-iteration, adversarially-verified deep-research pass in `research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/` (see `research.md`). Evidence is `file:line` into `external/caura-memclaw-main` (Apache-2.0 — design inspiration only, no code copied).\n\n**The honest headline:** caura-memclaw is built for the *opposite* deployment shape (multi-tenant fleet memory). After adversarial verification, the bulk of its transferable signal **validates 027's existing children (002-006)** and supplies a short list of **hardening-grade sharpenings**. Its marquee feature — cross-agent self-improving memory — is **negative knowledge** for a single-user store, and its **direct, asymmetric feedback mutation is an anti-pattern that confirms 027/008's default-off, shadow-first stance is correct**. Only a small set of genuinely-new, cross-cutting items justify a new child.\n\nThis proposal therefore has two parts:\n- **Part A — one new Level-2 child `015-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening`** for the cross-cutting items that do not fit an existing child's frozen scope.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"caura-memclaw (MemClaw) — Sub-Packet Proposal for 027\"\npacket: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement\"\nresearchPhase: \"research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings\"\nnewChildProposed: 1\nnewChildNumber: \"015-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening\"\namendmentsProposed: 7\ncreated: \"2026-06-06T09:15:00Z\"\nstatus: \"proposal — not yet scaffolded (operator chose proposal-doc-only)\"\nconcurrencyNote: \"Reconciled across the concurrent 006-peck (children 009-011) and 007-gem-team (children 012-014) runs; this proposal uses 015 for its new child.\"\n---\n\n# caura-memclaw — Sub-Packet Proposal for 027\n\nDerived from the 20-iteration, adversarially-verified deep-research pass in `research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/` (see `research.md`). Evidence is `file:line` into `external/caura-memclaw-main` (Apache-2.0 — design inspiration only, no code copied).\n\n**The honest headline:** caura-memclaw is built for the *opposite* deployment shape (multi-tenant fleet memory). After adversarial verification, the bulk of its transferable signal **validates 027's existing children (002-006)** and supplies a short list of **hardening-grade sharpenings**. Its marquee feature — cross-agent self-improving memory — is **negative knowledge** for a single-user store, and its **direct, asymmetric feedback mutation is an anti-pattern that confirms 027/008's default-off, shadow-first stance is correct**. Only a small set of genuinely-new, cross-cutting items justify a new child.\n\nThis proposal therefore has two parts:\n- **Part A — one new Level-2 child `015-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening`** for the cross-cutting items that do not fit an existing child's frozen scope.\n- **Part B — seven amendments** to existing children (the larger share of the value).\n\n> **⚠ Reconciliation with concurrent research (read first).** A concurrent run, `research/006-peck-source-deep-mining/`, proposes new children **009-peck-verification-discipline, 010-reviewer-prompt-benchmark-substrate, 011-acceptance-coverage-gate** (its `sub-packet-proposal.md`). To avoid a numbering collision, this proposal's new child is **`015-`** (reconciled: the next free slot after peck's `009-011` and the concurrent gem-team/007 proposals `012-014`; existing implementation children run `000`-`008`). If the operator does not adopt all of peck's 009-011, the new child can be compacted to the next actually-free slot at scaffold time (per the no-delete+recreate naming convention). (This research packet is folder-scoped with its own iteration sequence `001-020`, independent of the concurrent 006 run.)\n\n---\n\n## Headline recommendation\n\n| Recommendation | Type | Target | Verdict basis |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Idempotency receipts for retryable memory writes | NEW | 015 (P1) | T1 ADAPT |\n| MCP tool-ownership map (37-tool surface) | NEW | 015 (P2) | T12 ADAPT |\n| Default-recall stale/status hard-exclusion audit | NEW | 015 (P3) | T13 ADAPT |\n| `source_kind` provenance + auto-cannot-overwrite-manual | AMEND | 002 | T2 validate+sharpen |\n| Advisory near-duplicate (deterministic, no LLM judge) | AMEND | 002 | T3 ADAPT |\n| First-timestamp-idempotent tombstone + active/purgeable index split + entity≠causal boundary | AMEND | 004 | T7/T8/T10 |\n| Natural-key idempotent edge promotion + provenance-skip-manual | AMEND | 005 | T9 validate |\n| **Scope 008 down: event-capture + diagnostics first; defer active reducers** | AMEND | 008 | T4/T5/T6 |\n| `last_dedup_checked_at` incremental marker; explicit fingerprint is *better* than MemClaw | AMEND (confirm) | 003 | T14 validate |\n| Compact append-only audit for automated mutations | AMEND | 002/004/008 | T11 |\n\n---\n\n## PART A — Proposed new child\n\n## Proposal 015: `015-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening` — Operational write/surface hardening\n\n**Scope summary**: Three cohesive, single-user-grounded hardening additions that cross-cut or fall outside existing children's frozen scope, each directly evidenced in MemClaw and surviving adversarial verification.\n\n1. **P1 — Idempotency receipts (T1).** A minimal SQLite operation-receipt for retryable `memory_save`/`memory_update`: key on a server-derived `(operation_id | content_hash)` plus a request fingerprint; on identical retry, replay the prior result instead of inserting a duplicate; resolve \"same retry\" vs \"same content already exists\" distinctly. Deliberately **excludes** MemClaw's HTTP pending-sentinel/TTL/poll middleware — a local single-daemon needs only the receipt + one transaction. Evidence: `common/models/idempotency.py:30-53`; `core-api/src/core_api/middleware/idempotency.py:158-203`; `common/models/memory.py:96-105` (partial unique index `deleted_at IS NULL AND client_request_id IS NOT NULL` — the SQLite analog is a partial unique index on the receipt key).\n2. **P2 — MCP tool-ownership map (T12).** A lightweight ownership/stability note for the 37-tool MCP surface (who owns each tool group, add-an-operation criteria, deprecation discipline). **Explicitly rejects** MemClaw's op-dispatch consolidation (it harms LLM tool discoverability — MemClaw only proves it on a 12-tool surface) and its public-SemVer governance (internal surface). Evidence: `docs/api-surfaces.md:1-74`; anti-evidence `core-api/src/core_api/mcp_server.py:735,1169`.\n3. **P3 — Default-recall stale/status hard-exclusion audit (T13).** A verify-and-fix task confirming Spec Kit's default search does not silently hard-exclude deprecated-but-relevant memories. MemClaw itself hard-excludes `outdated`/`conflicted` unless `status_filter` is supplied — a self-inconsistency worth auditing against in Spec Kit. Evidence: `core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py:986,1022`.\n\n**Level estimate**: L2 (~150-350 LOC across receipt table + write-wrapper + audit script; P2 is docs-only).\n**Files (indicative)**: idempotency receipt schema + `memory_save`/`memory_update` wrapper in `mcp_server/handlers/save/**`; a `docs/` ownership map under the memory skill; one audit script.\n\n**Dependencies**:\n- Requires: existing memory write path + SQLite index.\n- Coordinates with: 002 (provenance), 006 (reconciliation/idempotency overlap), 008 (reserved-type provenance). **Independent of** the concurrent peck proposals 009-011.\n\n**Out of scope (negative knowledge guardrails)**: no multi-tenant scoping, no LLM-judge dedup, no HTTP idempotency middleware, no op-dispatch tool consolidation, no SemVer/release-please governance.\n\n---\n\n## PART B — Amendments to existing children\n\n> These are validations + sharpenings, not new scope. Each child's frozen `spec.md` scope is respected; amendments are documented for the next time each child is planned/implemented.\n\n### Amendment to 002 (memory-write-safety)\n- **T2 `source_kind` enum + auto-cannot-overwrite-manual** — add an explicit `source_kind` (`human|agent|system|import|feedback`) and enforce that automated writers (enrichment, promoters, reducers) may not overwrite human/constitutional fields. MemClaw's merge-only enrichment **validates** the direction but is *partial* (metadata keys are still enriched: `merge_enrichment_fields.py:28-50`) — Spec Kit should make the field-source rule explicit, not implicit.\n- **T3 advisory near-duplicate** — compute `near_duplicate_of` + similarity only when embeddings already exist; deterministic threshold; advisory, never hard-reject; no LLM judge / review queue. Evidence: `detect_near_duplicate.py:25-27,106` (adopt) vs `check_semantic_duplicate.py:7-10,193-210` (the hard-reject path = do NOT copy).\n- **T11 automated-mutation audit** — compact append-only audit rows for automated writes. Evidence: `common/models/audit.py:11-25`.\n\n### Amendment to 003 (incremental-index-foundation)\n- **T14 (confirmation)** — MemClaw uses a single **global** `Vector(VECTOR_DIM)` with no per-row embedder version/fingerprint columns (`common/models/memory.py:24`); Spec Kit's planned explicit chunk fingerprint + embedder-tuple + derived-state **improves on** MemClaw. Keep the `last_dedup_checked_at` incremental-marker idea (`memory.py:75-77`). No scope change — this is positive confirmation that 003's design is sound.\n\n### Amendment to 004 (causal-edge-tombstones)\n- **T7 first-timestamp-idempotent soft-delete** — preserve the first tombstone timestamp (COALESCE-style) so repeat deletes do not extend retention. MemClaw's `memory_soft_delete` *rewrites* `deleted_at` on repeat (`postgres_service.py:418-423`) — Spec Kit should improve on this.\n- **T8 active/purgeable partial-index split** — index active (`deleted_at IS NULL`) and purgeable (`deleted_at IS NOT NULL`) paths separately to keep both hot. Evidence: `memory.py:96-135`.\n- **T10 entity≠causal boundary** — keep any co-occurrence/entity signal as *low-weight recall evidence*, never as causal truth. MemClaw has **no** memory↔memory causal edges (only `supersedes_id` + entity relations: `memory.py:79-83`, `entity.py:27-62`); defer importing an entity graph absent measured need.\n\n### Amendment to 005 (metadata-edge-promoter)\n- **T9 natural-key idempotent promotion + provenance** — make generated-edge promotion idempotent via a natural-key unique constraint, tag provenance, and skip already-wired manual links. MemClaw's entity `Relation` does exactly this (`uq_relations_natural_key`, migration `001_initial_schema.py:163-165`; `postgres_service.py:2983-3048`) — direct validation of 005's planned \"avoid duplicating manual metadata links.\"\n\n### Amendment to 006 (write-path-reconciliation)\n- **T1 cross-reference** — the idempotency receipt (Proposal 015/P1) is the reconciliation primitive for retry-safe writes; 006's async post-insert-enrichment model is **validated** by MemClaw's decoupled embed/enrich (the *pattern*, not the Pub/Sub infra).\n\n### Amendment to 007 (semantic-trigger-fallback)\n- **T13 cross-reference** — the stale/status hard-exclusion audit (Proposal 015/P3) protects the lexical-first fallback from silently dropping deprecated-but-relevant matches.\n\n### Amendment to 008 (learning-feedback-reducers) — the central reframe\nMemClaw's `evolve`→`insights` loop is the closest analog to 008 and the most important lesson. After verification it is a **cautionary anti-pattern**, not a model:\n- It applies **direct, immediate, asymmetric** weight deltas (success `+0.10`, failure `-0.15`) to canonical weight (`evolve_service.py:147-165`; `constants.py:494-503`), persists LLM rules **active at confidence ≥ 0.5 with no shadow state** (`evolve_service.py:904-923`), and lets low weight feed stale-archival (`postgres_service.py:1606-1644`). In a sparse single-user corpus, one mis-attributed failure can demote a rare-but-correct memory irrecoverably.\n\nRecommended amendments (all *consistent with* 008's existing default-off/shadow-first plan — this sharpens, not redirects):\n- **T4 — scope 008 Phase-1 to event-capture + diagnostics only.** Land an append-only feedback-event log (audit/replay/diagnostics) and **defer all active reducers** (retrieval-score / retention / FSRS mutation) until measured ledger quality proves positive value. The fleet payoff that justifies MemClaw's aggressiveness does not exist for one user.\n- **T5 — reserve system-generated feedback artifact types** so the user-facing agent cannot forge learning signals once any reducer consumes them. Evidence: `common/enrichment/constants.py:97-110`; `routes/memories.py:101-131`; `mcp_server.py:281-310`.\n- **T6 — reject asymmetric damping.** Use symmetric/soft evidence accumulation, a rare-but-correct guard (high-tier/constitutional/user-confirmed/sparse-domain memories are protected from feedback-driven demotion or archival), and **constitutional immunity** (feedback may never demote or archive constitutional/protected memories). Evidence: `constants.py:494-503`; `evolve_service.py:340-375`.\n- Insight modes (failures/stale/patterns) survive only as **opt-in manual diagnostics** with minimum-corpus thresholds; **divergence does not transfer** (cross-agent only: `insights_service.py:419-454,1057-1061`).\n\n---\n\n## Sequencing\n\n1. **008 amendment first (documentation/scoping)** — record the scope-down + symmetric-damping/constitutional-immunity invariants before any 008 implementation work begins (cheapest, highest-leverage, prevents building the anti-pattern).\n2. **002 amendments** — `source_kind` + automated-mutation audit are P0 provenance gates that 008's event log also depends on.\n3. **015/P1 idempotency receipts** — small, isolated, validates 006.\n4. **004/005 amendments** — fold into those children when next planned.\n5. **015/P2 tool-ownership map + 015/P3 stale audit** — low-risk, independent, can land anytime.\n\n> Cross-run sequencing: this proposal is **orthogonal to** and **non-conflicting with** the concurrent peck proposals (009-011) — peck addresses verification discipline / reviewer-prompt benchmarking / acceptance-coverage; this addresses memory-store write/surface hardening + the 008 feedback reframe. They can be adopted independently.\n\n## Provenance\n\nSource: `research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/research.md` §5 (surviving teachings T1-T14), §6 (negative-knowledge ledger), §7 (027-child mapping). 20 iterations (001-020), adversarially verified (017-020) and adjudicated against MemClaw ground truth. All MemClaw references are design inspiration only (Apache-2.0; no code copied).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":115,"totalLines":115,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md","time":{"start":1780738219062,"end":1780738219070}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_076c916f5a177fda016a23e8aaf31081919d9a528566d5ed8a"}},"id":"prt_e9c44dbf7001Owihg3xlhotPE4","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","messageID":"msg_e9c44b8f8001v2rOknVCFoX4el"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738219105,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_H8Vb0vm7g4QziqnJVXcF8mRW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\n3: argument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - SPEC FOLDER RESOLUTION\n8: \n9: **BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, resolve `target_folder`:**\n10: \n11: ```text\n12: IF $ARGUMENTS contains a spec folder path:\n13:     → Validate folder exists\n14:     → Store as target_folder\n15:     → Continue reading this file\n16: \n17: IF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n18:     → Run AUTO-DETECTION (Tier 1 → Tier 2 → Tier 3):\n19: \n20:     TIER 1: Gate 3 Carry-Over (highest confidence - no confirmation needed)\n21:     - Check if a spec folder was established via Gate 3 earlier in this conversation\n22:     - If yes → use it directly as target_folder (per CLAUDE.md Memory Save Rule)\n23:     - Announce: \"Using active spec folder from this session: [folder]\"\n24: \n25:     TIER 2: Conversation Signal Analysis (high confidence - confirm)\n26:     - Scan files modified/read during this conversation\n27:     - Map file paths to spec folders:\n28:       * Files under specs/NNN-name/ or its children\n29:       * Files referenced in a spec folder's description.json\n30:       * Supporting docs (feature_catalog, manual_testing_playbook) linked via symlinks to a spec tree\n31:     - If ALL modified files map to a single spec folder (or one parent and its children):\n32:       → Propose: \"Based on this session's work, the target folder is [folder]. Saving there. [Y/n]\"\n33:       → If user confirms or does not object → store as target_folder\n34:     - If modified files span multiple unrelated spec folders → proceed to Tier 3\n35: \n36:     TIER 3: Guided Selection (fallback - must ask)\n37:     - List the spec folders touched in this conversation, ranked by file-edit count\n38:     - ASK: \"Multiple spec folders were touched. Which one should this context be saved to?\"\n39:     - If no spec folders detected at all → list recent/related spec folders and ask\n40:     - WAIT for user response → store as target_folder\n41: ```\n42: \n43: **CRITICAL RULES:**\n44: - Tier 1 (Gate 3 carry-over) proceeds without confirmation per CLAUDE.md Memory Save Rule\n45: - Tier 2 proposals MUST show the detected folder and ask for brief confirmation\n46: - Tier 3 MUST wait for explicit user response before proceeding\n47: - When ambiguous (files in multiple unrelated spec folders), ALWAYS ask - do not guess\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: # /memory:save\n52: \n53: > Save current conversation context into the packet's canonical continuity surfaces with semantic indexing.\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 1. INSTRUCTIONS\n58: \n59: Resolve the target spec folder first, build structured JSON from the session evidence, then run the save workflow below. Prefer canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity` over any legacy supporting artifacts.\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 2. PURPOSE\n64: \n65: Save the current conversation context, including session summary, key decisions, modified files, and trigger phrases, into the packet's canonical continuity surfaces so `/speckit:resume` and `/memory:search` read the same source of truth.\n66: \n67: **Key difference from `/memory:learn`:**\n68: - `/memory:save` = Session context routed into canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity`\n69: - `/memory:learn` = Constitutional rules saved to `constitutional/` (always-surface tier)\n70: \n71: ### Canonical Routing Model\n72: \n73: - `handover.md` remains the top recovery document for active-session state and pending work.\n74: - `_memory.continuity` stores the compact continuity block used by `/speckit:resume`.\n75: - AI may directly edit `_memory.continuity` frontmatter blocks in `implementation-summary.md` when only those doc-local continuity hints need updating.\n76: - Canonical spec docs such as `implementation-summary.md` and `decision-record.md` receive the durable narrative content when the route applies.\n77: - `generate-context.js` remains the primary save mechanism when the workflow also needs DB indexing, embedding generation, `description.json` refresh, `graph-metadata.json` refresh, or anchor-managed compatibility output.\n78: - Canonical save requests now default to **planner-first** behavior: return the routed target, proposed edit summary, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions before any mutation-first apply path is requested.\n79: - Explicit fallback remains available with `plannerMode: \"full-auto\"` or CLI `--full-auto` when an operator wants the legacy atomic writer behavior.\n80: - Standalone spec-doc markdown is not the primary operator-facing destination for this command.\n81: - Retention cleanup is outside save scope. When saved records expire under governance metadata, use `/memory:manage retention-sweep`, which routes to `memory_retention_sweep` (`tool-schemas.ts:330`).\n82: - `/memory:*` commands are markdown-owned contracts. They intentionally do not\n83:   have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\n84:   operating-mode blocks plus the markdown workflow steps.\n85: \n86: ### Handover Document Maintenance\n87: \n88: `/memory:save` is the canonical maintainer for `handover.md` through `handover_state` routing. When a packet does not already contain `handover.md`, create it from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/handover.md`, then merge subsequent stop-state updates into `handover.md::session-log` while keeping `_memory.continuity` aligned for `/speckit:resume`.\n89: \n90: ### Routed Save Categories\n91: \n92: The canonical save router works with 8 categories:\n93: \n94: | Category | Typical target | Notes |\n95: | -------- | -------------- | ----- |\n96: | `narrative_progress` | `implementation-summary.md::what-built` | What changed in the system or packet |\n97: | `narrative_delivery` | `implementation-summary.md::how-delivered` | Sequencing, gating, rollout, and verification story |\n98: | `decision` | `decision-record.md::adr-NNN` on L3/L3+ or `implementation-summary.md::decisions` on L1/L2 | Choice, tradeoff, rationale |\n99: | `handover_state` | `handover.md::session-log` | Stop-state, blockers, recent action, next safe action. Use `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/handover.md` for initial creation when `handover.md` does not exist. |\n100: | `research_finding` | `research/research.md::findings` | Evidence, investigation result, cited upstream behavior |\n101: | `task_update` | `tasks.md::<phase-anchor>` | Checklist/task status mutation |\n102: | `metadata_only` | `_memory.continuity` in frontmatter | Machine-owned continuity payloads |\n103: | `drop` | `scratch/pending-route-<hash>.json` via refusal | Non-canonical transcript/tooling noise; never auto-merged |\n104: \n105: Routing tiers:\n106: \n107: - Tier 1 handles structured routes and strong heuristics.\n108: - Tier 2 uses prototype similarity against the frozen routing library.\n109: - Tier 3 is part of the live save handler by default. When `LLM_REFORMULATION_ENDPOINT` is reachable and returns a usable decision, it participates automatically; if that endpoint is unavailable or unusable, the save path falls back to Tier 2 with a confidence penalty when safe, otherwise it refuses the merge.\n110: \n111: Boundary rules:\n112: \n113: - Delivery cues are now stronger when the chunk mentions sequencing, gating, rollout, or verification.\n114: - Handover keeps state-first stop/resume notes even if they mention soft operational commands like `git diff`, `list spec-doc records`, or `force re-index`.\n115: - Hard transcript, telemetry, and wrapper scaffolding still route to `drop`.\n116: \n117: Override and context rules:\n118: \n119: - `routeAs` can force any of the 8 categories. The router preserves the natural decision for audit and warns if an override is accepted against a natural `drop`.\n120: - Router context passes `packet_kind` derived from spec metadata first (`type`, `title`, `description`), with parent-phase fallback only when the metadata is silent.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 3. CONTRACT\n125: \n126: | Field   | Value                                                                                        |\n127: | ------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n128: | Input   | Spec folder path (from Gate 3 or `$ARGUMENTS`) + AI-composed JSON data                       |\n129: | Output  | Canonical spec-doc continuity updates + indexed continuity data. Also refreshes `graph-metadata.json` derived fields in the spec folder: `trigger_phrases` are deduplicated and capped at 12, `key_files` are sanitized before storage, `entities` are deduplicated with canonical-path preference, and `status` is checklist-aware and normalized to lowercase. |\n130: | Script  | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`               |\n131: | Primary | **JSON mode:** `generate-context.js <json-data-path>` (e.g. a path under `$TMPDIR` or `/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json`) or `--json '<data>'` |\n132: | Trigger | \"save context\", \"save memory\", `/memory:save`                                                |\n133: \n134: Planner behavior:\n135: - Default: `plan-only` for canonical save requests, with explicit follow-up actions such as `apply`, `refresh-graph`, and `reindex`\n136: - Fallback: `full-auto` restores the legacy mutation-first canonical writer\n137: - Deferred freshness actions: graph refresh and spec-doc reindex are surfaced as follow-ups instead of assumed default side effects\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 4. QUICK REFERENCE\n142: \n143: | Usage                                                  | Behavior                                                |\n144: | ------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n145: | `/memory:save`                                         | Auto-detect the active packet, confirm if needed, then route into canonical continuity targets |\n146: | `/memory:save 011-memory`                              | Save to a specific spec folder                          |\n147: | `/memory:save specs/006-semantic-memory/003-debugging` | Save to a nested spec folder                            |\n148: | `node .../generate-context.js --full-auto ...`         | Opt back into the legacy full-auto canonical apply path |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 5. VALIDATION\n153: \n154: ### Pre-Flight Checks (Phase 0)\n155: \n156: Execute BEFORE folder validation to prevent data quality issues. All checks must pass.\n157: \n158: #### Check 1: Anchor Format Validation\n159: \n160: - Scan conversation for existing canonical spec-doc references\n161: - If any canonical spec documents (`decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `handover.md`, `resource-map.md`) were read during the session, verify they contain BOTH opening AND closing ANCHOR tags\n162: - Pattern: `<!-- ANCHOR:id --> ... <!-- /ANCHOR:id -->`\n163: - If missing closing tags → WARN user before proceeding\n164: - Why: Broken anchors break section-specific retrieval (93% token waste)\n165: \n166: #### Check 2: Token Budget Validation\n167: \n168: - Estimate conversation size: `message_count * avg_tokens_per_message`\n169: - If estimated > 50,000 tokens:\n170:   - WARN: \"Large conversation detected\"\n171:   - OPTIONS: `[C]ontinue anyway | [S]plit save | [E]dit scope`\n172:   - WAIT for response\n173: \n174: #### Check 3: Spec Folder Existence\n175: \n176: - If `$ARGUMENTS` contains folder → validate exists, store as `pending_folder`\n177: - If `$ARGUMENTS` empty → defer to Phase 1\n178: \n179: #### Check 4: Stop Hook Awareness\n180: \n181: - Confirm whether recent hook-driven context preservation evidence exists for this session\n182: - Current limitation: no dedicated `pendingStopSave` field is shipped in the hook state, so `/memory:save` must not claim a guaranteed auto-save merge marker\n183: - If no recent hook-save evidence can be established: PASSED (proceed normally)\n184: \n185: **Phase 0 Output:**\n186: ```text\n187: anchor_validation: PASSED | WARNED\n188: token_budget:      PASSED | SPLIT_REQUESTED\n189: folder_existence:  PASSED\n190: stop_hook_check:   PASSED\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### Spec Folder Validation (Phase 1)\n194: \n195: ```text\n196: IF target_folder already set (from $ARGUMENTS or Tier 1/2 auto-detection):\n197:   → Validate folder exists → Proceed to Content Alignment Check\n198: IF target_folder not yet set (Tier 3 pending):\n199:   → WAIT for user response → Validate → Proceed\n200: IF folder invalid:\n201:   → Show available folders → ASK user → WAIT\n202: ```\n203: \n204: **HARD STOP:** Do NOT proceed to save workflow until `target_folder` is set and validated.\n205: \n206: #### Content Alignment Check\n207: \n208: After Phase 1, validate the conversation topic matches the target folder:\n209: \n210: - Extract conversation topic (subject, files modified, problem being solved)\n211: - Compare to `target_folder` name\n212: - If clear match → PASS\n213: - If mismatch → WARN with alternatives:\n214:   - Show: \"Conversation topic: [topic]\" / \"Selected folder: [target_folder]\"\n215:   - Suggest top 3 alternative folders\n216:   - ASK: `[C]ontinue | [1][2][3] alternatives | [N]ew folder`\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## 6. WORKFLOW\n221: \n222: ### Step 1: Folder Detection\n223: \n224: Use the `target_folder` value from Phase 1.\n225: \n226: ### Step 2: Context Analysis (AI MUST PERFORM)\n227: \n228: **CRITICAL:** The AI agent MUST analyze the conversation and extract this data. The script does NOT auto-extract: the AI constructs this manually.\n229: \n230: Extract from the current conversation:\n231: - **Session summary**: 2-4 sentences describing what was accomplished\n232: - **Key decisions**: Array of choices with rationale (format: \"Decision: [choice] because [reason]\")\n233: - **Files modified**: Full paths to all files created/edited during session\n234: - **Trigger phrases**: 5-10 keywords/phrases for future semantic search retrieval\n235: - **Technical context**: Key technical details, patterns used, or implementation notes\n236: \n237: ### Step 3: Anchor Generation (MANDATORY)\n238: \n239: Every generated canonical spec document MUST include anchors for section-specific retrieval (enables 93% token savings).\n240: \n241: **Anchor Format:**\n242: ```html\n243: <!-- ANCHOR:anchor-id -->\n244: Content for this section...\n245: <!-- /ANCHOR:anchor-id -->\n246: ```\n247: \n248: **Rules:**\n249: - Use UPPERCASE `ANCHOR` (recommended, though lowercase works)\n250: - **MUST include BOTH opening AND closing tags**: closing tag is REQUIRED\n251: - No space after colon: `ANCHOR:id` not `ANCHOR: id`\n252: - Without closing tag, extraction fails silently\n253: \n254: **Anti-Pattern:**\n255: ```html\n256: <!-- WRONG: No closing tag = anchor extraction fails -->\n257: <!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n258: Content...\n259: <!-- Missing closing tag! -->\n260: \n261: <!-- CORRECT: Both tags present -->\n262: <!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n263: Content...\n264: <!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n265: ```\n266: \n267: **Anchor ID Pattern:** `[context-type]-[keywords]-[spec-number]`\n268: \n269: | Context Type     | Use For                  | Example                             |\n270: | ---------------- | ------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |\n271: | `implementation` | Code patterns, solutions | `implementation-oauth-callback-049` |\n272: | `decision`       | Architecture choices     | `decision-database-schema-005`      |\n273: | `research`       | Investigation findings   | `research-lenis-scroll-006`         |\n274: | `discovery`      | Learnings, insights      | `discovery-api-limits-011`          |\n275: | `general`        | Mixed content            | `general-session-summary-049`       |\n276: \n277: **Minimum Anchors:** 1 required (primary section). Recommended: 2+ (summary + decisions/implementation).\n278: \n279: **Standard Anchor Set:**\n280: ```markdown\n281: <!-- ANCHOR:summary-[spec#] -->\n282: ## Session Summary\n283: ...\n284: <!-- /ANCHOR:summary-[spec#] -->\n285: \n286: <!-- ANCHOR:decision-[topic]-[spec#] -->\n287: ## Key Decisions\n288: ...\n289: <!-- /ANCHOR:decision-[topic]-[spec#] -->\n290: \n291: <!-- ANCHOR:files-[spec#] -->\n292: ## Files Modified\n293: ...\n294: <!-- /ANCHOR:files-[spec#] -->\n295: ```\n296: \n297: ### Step 4: Create JSON Data (AI CONSTRUCTS THIS)\n298: \n299: **CRITICAL:** The AI MUST construct this JSON from Step 2 analysis. The script requires proper JSON input to produce high-quality canonical spec-doc updates across decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, and handover.md.\n300: \n301: **Required JSON Structure:**\n302: ```json\n303: {\n304:   \"specFolder\": \"005-memory/010-feature-name\",\n305:   \"sessionSummary\": \"Comprehensive description of what was accomplished. Include problem solved, approach taken, outcome achieved. 100+ chars.\",\n306:   \"keyDecisions\": [\n307:     \"Decision 1: Chose X because Y - provides Z benefit\",\n308:     \"Decision 2: Selected A over B due to performance\"\n309:   ],\n310:   \"filesModified\": [\n311:     \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js\",\n312:     \"specs/005-memory/010-feature-name/spec.md\"\n313:   ],\n314:   \"triggerPhrases\": [\n315:     \"generate-context\", \"memory save\", \"JSON input\",\n316:     \"context preservation\", \"session capture\"\n317:   ],\n318:   \"technicalContext\": {\n319:     \"rootCause\": \"Description of the problem's root cause\",\n320:     \"solution\": \"How it was solved\",\n321:     \"patterns\": \"Key patterns or approaches used\"\n322:   },\n323:   \"toolCalls\": [\n324:     { \"tool\": \"Read\", \"inputSummary\": \"Read scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js\", \"outputSummary\": \"Runtime CLI entry point verified for JSON-mode saves\", \"status\": \"success\", \"durationEstimate\": \"fast\" },\n325:     { \"tool\": \"Edit\", \"inputSummary\": \"Updated Memory Save Rule in CLAUDE.md\", \"outputSummary\": \"Changed JSON-primary wording\", \"status\": \"success\" }\n326:   ],\n327:   \"exchanges\": [\n328:     { \"userInput\": \"Implement the JSON-primary plan\", \"assistantResponse\": \"Updated CLAUDE.md, SKILL.md, session-types.ts, data-loader.ts with JSON-primary changes\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z\" }\n329:   ]\n330: }\n331: ```\n332: \n333: **Field Guidelines:**\n334: \n335: | Field              | Min Length | Purpose                                              |\n336: | ------------------ | ---------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n337: | `sessionSummary`   | 100+ chars | Becomes OVERVIEW: be comprehensive                   |\n338: | `keyDecisions`     | 1+ items   | Each decision with rationale                         |\n339: | `filesModified`    | 0+ items   | Actual paths modified                                |\n340: | `triggerPhrases`   | 5-12 items | Keywords for semantic search. Parser-enforced cap at 12. |\n341: | `technicalContext` | Optional   | Additional technical details                         |\n342: | `toolCalls`        | Optional   | AI-summarized tool calls (richer than DB extraction) |\n343: | `exchanges`        | Optional   | Key user-assistant exchanges during session          |\n344: \n345: ### Step 5: Produce Plan or Execute Processing Script\n346: \n347: Default `/memory:save` behavior is plan-only. Stop after producing the routed\n348: target, proposed edits, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions unless the\n349: caller explicitly selects an apply action, `plannerMode:\"full-auto\"`, or the CLI\n350: `--full-auto` path.\n351: \n352: | Mode                              | Command                                                           | Use When                                     |\n353: | --------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |\n354: | **Plan-only** (default)           | Return routed target, proposed edits, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions | Canonical save request without explicit apply approval |\n355: | **JSON File** (explicit apply)    | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js ${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/save-context-data.json <spec-folder>` | Rich context with decisions, files, triggers after apply or full-auto selection |\n356: \n357: > **Why JSON mode:** The AI has strictly better information about its own session than any database query can reconstruct. JSON mode eliminates wrong-session capture, multi-session ambiguity, and exchange pairing bugs.\n358: \n359: > **026 Memory Quality (Post-Save Review):** After `generate-context.js` completes, it outputs a POST-SAVE QUALITY REVIEW. HIGH-severity issues (stale titles, weak trigger phrases, wrong importance tier) MUST be patched via Edit tool immediately. MEDIUM issues should be patched when practical. Trigger phrases are sanitized: generic phrases (e.g., \"context\", \"session\") are flagged for replacement with domain-specific terms per 026-003-009/010 trigger sanitization rules.\n360: \n361: > **Graph metadata refresh:** The same save pass refreshes `graph-metadata.json` with checklist-aware status fallback (`implementation-summary.md` presence + checklist completion), lowercase status normalization, sanitized `key_files`, deduplicated entities, and a 12-item cap on derived trigger phrases.\n362: \n363: > **Auto-index of touched files (Step 11.5):** After the canonical save updates packet docs and `graph-metadata.json`, the workflow re-indexes touched canonical spec docs only when the standalone process is the sole SQLite writer. If the mk-spec-memory daemon is down, `generate-context.js` may run the direct incremental spec-doc index path. If the daemon is up, Step 11.5 must not open a second better-sqlite3 writer on `context-index.sqlite`; finish freshness through the daemon-owned MCP tool instead:\n364: >\n365: > ```javascript\n366: > mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({\n367: >   specFolder: \"<target-folder>\",\n368: >   includeSpecDocs: true,\n369: >   force: false\n370: > })\n371: > ```\n372: >\n373: > The save itself is durable before indexing. When Step 11.5 skips because the daemon is running, docs are not lost; retrieval remains stale until the MCP scan runs. The re-index covers canonical spec docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `handover.md`, `research/research.md`, `resource-map.md`) and `graph-metadata.json` modified earlier in the session. Incremental mode skips unchanged files cheaply via mtime + content-hash checks.\n374: >\n375: > Kill switches: `SPECKIT_AUTO_INDEX_TOUCHED=false` (targeted opt-out) or `SPECKIT_INDEX_SPEC_DOCS=false` (existing global opt-out) disables Step 11.5. The backend has a 51s cooldown between scans; when a save fires during cooldown, Step 11.5 logs `skipped (scan cooldown active; retry on next save)` and continues — the index catches up on the next save.\n376: \n377: > **Cross-Platform Note:** `${TMPDIR:-/tmp}` uses the system temp directory. On macOS/Linux this resolves to `/tmp` or `$TMPDIR`. On Windows (Git Bash/WSL), use `$TEMP` or `%TEMP%`.\n378: \n379: > SECURITY: When using heredoc or --stdin, ensure JSON content is properly escaped. Prefer --json flag with single-quoted inline JSON or write to /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json via Write tool first (exception to the Write tool exclusion: writing the intermediate JSON data file is permitted).\n380: \n381: Write to `/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json` (Write tool exception: intermediate JSON data file only) or use `--json`/`--stdin`, then execute:\n382: ```bash\n383: TEMP_FILE=\"${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/save-context-data.json\"\n384: \n385: # 1. Write JSON data to the temp file\n386: cat > \"$TEMP_FILE\" << 'EOF'\n387: { \"specFolder\": \"...\", \"sessionSummary\": \"...\", ... }\n388: EOF\n389: \n390: # 2. Execute the script\n391: node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js \"$TEMP_FILE\" specs/###-folder/\n392: \n393: # 3. Clean up\n394: rm \"$TEMP_FILE\"\n395: ```\n396: \n397: **Expected Output (Success):**\n398: ```text\n399: ✓ Loaded conversation data\n400: ✓ Transformed manual format to MCP-compatible structure\n401: ✓ Found N messages\n402: ✓ Found N decisions\n403: ✓ Routed canonical targets prepared\n404: ✓ Continuity surfaces updated\n405: ✓ Indexed continuity data\n406: ```\n407: \n408: ### File Output\n409: \n410: **Primary result:** canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity` are updated in-place for the selected spec folder.\n411: \n412: **Typical targets:**\n413: - `handover.md`\n414: - `implementation-summary.md`\n415: - `decision-record.md`\n416: - frontmatter `_memory.continuity`\n417: - `graph-metadata.json`\n418: \n419: If compatibility artifacts are emitted during migration cleanup, they remain secondary to the canonical packet update and should not be treated as the source of truth.\n420: \n421: ### Step 6: Report Results\n422: \n423: Display the completion report (see Section 6).\n424: \n425: ---\n426: \n427: ## 7. COMPLETION REPORT\n428: \n429: ### Structured Response Envelope\n430: \n431: ```json\n432: {\n433:   \"summary\": \"Context saved successfully into the canonical continuity surfaces for specs/011-memory\",\n434:   \"data\": {\n435:     \"status\": \"OK\",\n436:     \"spec_folder\": \"011-memory\",\n437:     \"targets_updated\": [\n438:       \"handover.md\",\n439:       \"implementation-summary.md\",\n440:       \"_memory.continuity\"\n441:     ],\n442:     \"indexing_status\": \"indexed\",\n443:     \"anchors_updated\": [\"summary-011\", \"decision-vector-search-011\", \"files-011\"],\n444:     \"trigger_phrases\": [\"semantic search\", \"vector embeddings\", \"memory retrieval\"],\n445:     \"timestamp\": \"2026-02-01T14:30:00Z\"\n446:   },\n447:   \"hints\": [\n448:     \"Use /memory:search to find the updated packet context later\",\n449:     \"Anchors enable 93% token savings when loading specific sections\"\n450:   ],\n451:   \"meta\": {\n452:     \"command\": \"/memory:save\",\n453:     \"duration_ms\": 1247,\n454:     \"mcp_available\": true,\n455:     \"deferred_indexing\": false\n456:   }\n457: }\n458: ```\n459: \n460: **Key Fields:**\n461: \n462: | Field                    | Type     | Description                              |\n463: | ------------------------ | -------- | ---------------------------------------- |\n464: | `data.status`            | string   | \"OK\" or \"FAIL\"                           |\n465: | `data.targets_updated`   | string[] | Canonical packet targets updated         |\n466: | `data.indexing_status`   | string   | \"indexed\", \"deferred\", or \"failed\"       |\n467: | `data.anchors_updated`   | string[] | List of anchor IDs updated or created    |\n468: | `meta.deferred_indexing` | boolean  | Whether indexing was deferred to restart |\n469: \n470: ### Human-Friendly Display\n471: \n472: ```text\n473: MEMORY:SAVE\n474: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n475: \n476:   Folder      <spec_folder>\n477:   Targets     <target_1>, <target_2>, <target_3>\n478:   Indexing    <indexing_status>\n479: \n480: → Anchors ─────────────────────────────────── <count> updated\n481:   <anchor1>\n482:   <anchor2>\n483:   <anchor3>\n484: \n485: → Triggers ──────────────────────────────────────────\n486:   <phrase1> · <phrase2> · <phrase3> · ...\n487: \n488: ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n489: [t] edit triggers    [d] done\n490: \n491: STATUS=OK TARGETS=<count> ANCHORS=<count>\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ### Post-Save Actions\n495: \n496: | Input | Action                                            |\n497: | ----- | ------------------------------------------------- |\n498: | t     | Edit trigger phrases for this spec-doc record (add/remove) |\n499: | d     | Done, exit save workflow                          |\n500: \n501: ### Trigger Edit (if selected)\n502: \n503: ```text\n504: MEMORY:TRIGGERS\n505: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n506: \n507:   Record      #<id> \"<spec_doc_title>\"\n508: \n509: → Current Triggers ─────────────────────────────────\n510:   1) <phrase1>\n511:   2) <phrase2>\n512:   3) <phrase3>\n513: \n514: ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n515: [a] add    [r] remove #    [s] save    [d] done\n516: \n517: STATUS=OK ID=<id> TRIGGERS=<count>\n518: ```\n519: \n520: ---\n521: \n522: ## 8. ERROR HANDLING\n523: \n524: | Condition               | Action                                          |\n525: | ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |\n526: | No spec folder found    | Prompt user to create one                       |\n527: | Folder not found        | Show available folders, ask user                |\n528: | Topic-folder mismatch   | Warn, suggest alternatives, ask to confirm      |\n529: | Empty conversation      | Return `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"No context to save\"` |\n530: | Script execution fails  | Show error, suggest manual save                 |\n531: | Embedding fails         | Canonical docs updated, will auto-index on MCP restart |\n532: | MCP unavailable         | Canonical docs updated, indexing deferred to restart   |\n533: | JSON not loaded         | Check temp file path and content format          |\n534: \n535: ---\n536: \n537: ## 9. NEXT STEPS\n538: \n539: | Condition                    | Suggested Command                          | Reason                        |\n540: | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------- |\n541: | Context saved, continue work | Return to previous task                    | Memory preserved, continue    |\n542: | Ending session               | `/memory:save [spec-folder-path]`           | Update `handover.md` through `handover_state` routing |\n543: | Search indexed continuity    | `/memory:search [query]`                | Find related context          |\n544: | Start new work               | `/speckit:complete [feature-description]` | Begin new feature             |\n545: \n546: **ALWAYS** end with: \"Context saved. What would you like to do next?\"\n547: \n548: ---\n549: \n550: ## 10. RELATED COMMANDS\n551: \n552: - `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools\n553: - `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest\n554: - `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules\n555: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation\n556: \n557: ---\n558: <!-- APPENDIX: Reference material for AI agent implementation -->\n559: \n560: ## APPENDIX A: MCP TOOL REFERENCE\n561: \n562: > **Tool Restriction (Memory Save Rule - HARD BLOCK):** `Write` remains intentionally excluded. `Edit` is allowed only for direct `_memory.continuity` frontmatter updates inside `implementation-summary.md`. Use `generate-context.js` for indexed saves, embedding generation, `description.json` refresh, `graph-metadata.json` refresh, and anchor-managed canonical spec-doc routing. Standalone `memory/*.md` files are retired and the runtime rejects them. See AGENTS.md Memory Save Rule.\n563: \n564: > **Mutation Ledger & Artifact Routing:** Every save operation is now recorded in the mutation ledger, an append-only audit trail that captures the file path, spec folder, timestamp, and indexing outcome. Artifact metadata associated with the saved spec-doc record may also be classified via artifact-class routing before indexing, ensuring consistent type tagging across the database.\n565: \n566: ### Enforcement Matrix\n567: \n568: ```text\n569: STEP            REQUIRED CALLS                            ON FAILURE\n570: ─────────────── ───────────────────────────────────────── ──────────────\n571: FOLDER DETECT   Bash (ls, CLI argument)                   Prompt user\n572: CONTEXT SAVE    Bash (node generate-context.js)           Show error msg\n573: IMMEDIATE INDEX mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan (optional) Show error msg\n574: ```\n575: \n576: **Script Location:** `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`\n577: \n578: **Immediate indexing:** Canonical spec-doc surfaces participate in spec-doc indexing. If you need fresh retrieval immediately after a save, run a targeted index scan:\n579: \n580: ```javascript\n581: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({\n582:   specFolder: \"011-memory\",\n583:   includeSpecDocs: true,\n584:   force: true\n585: })\n586: ```\n587: \n588: `memory_update({ id, triggerPhrases })`: Update trigger phrases on an existing indexed spec-doc record. Used by the `[t]` edit triggers action in the post-save review.\n589: \n590: ---\n591: \n592: ## APPENDIX B: ADVANCED REFERENCE\n593: \n594: ### Indexing Options\n595: \n596: Four indexing methods are available: auto-indexing on MCP startup (default), `generate-context.js` (standard save workflow), `memory_save` (single file), and `memory_index_scan` (bulk). See full parameter references below.\n597: \n598: #### Normalization Before Bulk Rebuild\n599: \n600: When corpus-wide markdown metadata has changed, run normalization before force re-index:\n601: \n602: ```bash\n603: # Dry-run normalization\n604: node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/backfill-frontmatter.js --dry-run --include-archive\n605: \n606: # Apply normalization\n607: node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/backfill-frontmatter.js --apply --include-archive\n608: \n609: # Rebuild index after normalization\n610: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ force: true })\n611: ```\n612: \n613: Recommended order: **normalize → verify → rebuild**.\n614: \n615: #### Deferred Indexing (Graceful Degradation)\n616: \n617: When MCP is unavailable or embedding fails, the canonical document update still lands on disk. Follow with a targeted `memory_index_scan` after MCP recovery so the updated spec docs and continuity anchors are discoverable across retrieval channels.\n618: \n619: **Manual Retry:**\n620: ```javascript\n621: // Entire folder\n622: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ specFolder: \"011-memory\", force: true })\n623: ```\n624: \n625: **Recovery Options:**\n626: \n627: | Issue                  | Recovery                                                                                                                       |\n628: | ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n629: | MCP server unreachable | Restart OpenCode to restart MCP server. Post-026: run `memory_health()` after restart to verify all retrieval channels (graph, vector, FTS5) are operational |\n630: | Embedding timeout      | Use `memory_index_scan` with smaller batch                                                                                     |\n631: | Corrupted file         | Read file, verify ANCHOR tags, re-save with corrections                                                                        |\n632: | Database locked        | For database recovery, use `/memory:manage health` to diagnose issues and `/memory:manage checkpoint restore` to recover from a known-good state. Avoid manual file deletion. |\n633: \n634: #### Full Parameter Reference: memory_save\n635: \n636: | Parameter        | Type    | Default    | Description                                         |\n637: | ---------------- | ------- | ---------- | --------------------------------------------------- |\n638: | `filePath`       | string  | *required* | Absolute path to the generated canonical spec document |\n639: | `force`          | boolean | false      | Force re-index even if content hash unchanged       |\n640: | `dryRun`         | boolean | false      | Validate only without saving                        |\n641: | `skipPreflight`  | boolean | false      | Skip pre-flight validation checks (not recommended) |\n642: | `asyncEmbedding` | boolean | false      | Defer embedding generation for non-blocking saves   |\n643: \n644: #### Full Parameter Reference: memory_index_scan\n645: \n646: | Parameter               | Type    | Default | Description                        |\n647: | ----------------------- | ------- | ------- | ---------------------------------- |\n648: | `force`                 | boolean | false   | Force re-index all files           |\n649: | `specFolder`            | string  | -       | Limit scan to specific spec folder |\n650: | `includeSpecDocs`       | boolean | true    | Include spec folder documents      |\n651: | `includeConstitutional` | boolean | true    | Include constitutional rule files  |\n652: | `incremental`           | boolean | true    | Skip unchanged files (mtime check) |\n653: \n654: ### Sub-Agent Delegation\n655: \n656: The save workflow delegates execution to a sub-agent for token efficiency. The main agent handles folder validation and user interaction; the sub-agent handles context analysis and file generation.\n657: \n658: #### Architecture\n659: \n660: ```text\n661: Main Agent (reads command):\n662: ├── PHASE 0-1: Pre-flight + Spec Folder Validation\n663: ├── DISPATCH: Task tool with sub-agent\n664: │   ├── Sub-agent analyzes conversation\n665: │   ├── Sub-agent generates JSON data\n666: │   ├── Sub-agent executes generate-context.js\n667: │   └── Sub-agent returns result\n668: ├── FALLBACK (if Task unavailable):\n669: │   └── Execute Steps 2-5 directly\n670: └── Step 6: Report Results (always main agent)\n671: ```\n672: \n673: #### Sub-Agent Dispatch\n674: \n675: When phases pass, dispatch via Task tool:\n676: \n677: - **subagent_type:** `general`\n678: - **description:** \"Save continuity context\"\n679: - **prompt:** Include:\n680:   1. `target_folder` and `alignment_validated` from phases\n681:   2. Instructions for Steps 2-5 (context analysis → anchor generation → JSON construction → script execution)\n682:   3. Expected return format: `{ status, file_path, memory_id, anchors_created, trigger_phrases, spec_folder }`\n683: \n684: #### Fallback Logic\n685: \n686: Fallback triggers if Task tool returns error, times out, or sub-agent returns `status: FAIL`.\n687: \n688: **Fallback behavior:** Execute Steps 2-5 directly in the main agent context, then continue to Step 6.\n689: \n690: | Benefit               | Description                                           |\n691: | --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |\n692: | Token efficiency      | Heavy context extraction happens in sub-agent context |\n693: | Main agent responsive | Validation and reporting stay lightweight             |\n694: | Fallback safety       | Commands always work, even without Task tool          |\n695: \n696: ### Governance, Provenance & Retention\n697: \n698: The `memory_save` tool schema advertises advanced governance parameters for multi-tenant, multi-agent, and compliance-aware deployments. These parameters take effect only when governance guardrails are enabled.\n699: \n700: #### Governance Scoping\n701: \n702: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n703: |-----------|------|-------------|\n704: | `tenantId` | string | Tenant boundary for governed ingest |\n705: | `userId` | string | User boundary for governed ingest |\n706: | `agentId` | string | Agent boundary for governed ingest |\n707: | `sessionId` | string | Session boundary for governed ingest |\n708: \n709: #### Provenance\n710: \n711: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n712: |-----------|------|-------------|\n713: | `provenanceSource` | string | Required provenance source when governance guardrails are enabled |\n714: | `provenanceActor` | string | Required provenance actor when governance guardrails are enabled |\n715: | `governedAt` | string | ISO timestamp for governed ingest. Defaults to now when omitted |\n716: \n717: #### Retention\n718: \n719: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n720: |-----------|------|-------------|\n721: | `retentionPolicy` | string | Retention class: `keep` (permanent), `ephemeral` (short-lived), `shared` (reserved compatibility value) |\n722: | `deleteAfter` | string | Optional ISO timestamp after which retention sweep may delete the spec-doc record |\n723: \n724: > **Note:** Governance parameters (tenantId, userId, agentId, sessionId) are validated by the memorySaveSchema when provided. All governance fields must pass schema validation.\n725: \n726: #### Async Bulk Ingestion\n727: \n728: For ingesting multiple files at once without blocking, use `/memory:manage ingest` instead:\n729: \n730: ```bash\n731: # Start async ingestion of multiple files\n732: /memory:manage ingest start /path/to/file1.md /path/to/file2.md --folder 007-auth\n733: \n734: # Check progress\n735: /memory:manage ingest status <jobId>\n736: ```\n737: \n738: See `/memory:manage ingest` for the full async ingestion workflow.\n\n(End of file - total 738 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n---\n\n# MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - SPEC FOLDER RESOLUTION\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, resolve `target_folder`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS contains a spec folder path:\n    → Validate folder exists\n    → Store as target_folder\n    → Continue reading this file\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → Run AUTO-DETECTION (Tier 1 → Tier 2 → Tier 3):\n\n    TIER 1: Gate 3 Carry-Over (highest confidence - no confirmation needed)","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md","text":"---\ndescription: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n---\n\n# MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - SPEC FOLDER RESOLUTION\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, resolve `target_folder`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS contains a spec folder path:\n    → Validate folder exists\n    → Store as target_folder\n    → Continue reading this file\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → Run AUTO-DETECTION (Tier 1 → Tier 2 → Tier 3):\n\n    TIER 1: Gate 3 Carry-Over (highest confidence - no confirmation needed)\n    - Check if a spec folder was established via Gate 3 earlier in this conversation\n    - If yes → use it directly as target_folder (per CLAUDE.md Memory Save Rule)\n    - Announce: \"Using active spec folder from this session: [folder]\"\n\n    TIER 2: Conversation Signal Analysis (high confidence - confirm)\n    - Scan files modified/read during this conversation\n    - Map file paths to spec folders:\n      * Files under specs/NNN-name/ or its children\n      * Files referenced in a spec folder's description.json\n      * Supporting docs (feature_catalog, manual_testing_playbook) linked via symlinks to a spec tree\n    - If ALL modified files map to a single spec folder (or one parent and its children):\n      → Propose: \"Based on this session's work, the target folder is [folder]. Saving there. [Y/n]\"\n      → If user confirms or does not object → store as target_folder\n    - If modified files span multiple unrelated spec folders → proceed to Tier 3\n\n    TIER 3: Guided Selection (fallback - must ask)\n    - List the spec folders touched in this conversation, ranked by file-edit count\n    - ASK: \"Multiple spec folders were touched. Which one should this context be saved to?\"\n    - If no spec folders detected at all → list recent/related spec folders and ask\n    - WAIT for user response → store as target_folder\n```\n\n**CRITICAL RULES:**\n- Tier 1 (Gate 3 carry-over) proceeds without confirmation per CLAUDE.md Memory Save Rule\n- Tier 2 proposals MUST show the detected folder and ask for brief confirmation\n- Tier 3 MUST wait for explicit user response before proceeding\n- When ambiguous (files in multiple unrelated spec folders), ALWAYS ask - do not guess\n\n---\n\n# /memory:save\n\n> Save current conversation context into the packet's canonical continuity surfaces with semantic indexing.\n\n---\n\n## 1. INSTRUCTIONS\n\nResolve the target spec folder first, build structured JSON from the session evidence, then run the save workflow below. Prefer canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity` over any legacy supporting artifacts.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PURPOSE\n\nSave the current conversation context, including session summary, key decisions, modified files, and trigger phrases, into the packet's canonical continuity surfaces so `/speckit:resume` and `/memory:search` read the same source of truth.\n\n**Key difference from `/memory:learn`:**\n- `/memory:save` = Session context routed into canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity`\n- `/memory:learn` = Constitutional rules saved to `constitutional/` (always-surface tier)\n\n### Canonical Routing Model\n\n- `handover.md` remains the top recovery document for active-session state and pending work.\n- `_memory.continuity` stores the compact continuity block used by `/speckit:resume`.\n- AI may directly edit `_memory.continuity` frontmatter blocks in `implementation-summary.md` when only those doc-local continuity hints need updating.\n- Canonical spec docs such as `implementation-summary.md` and `decision-record.md` receive the durable narrative content when the route applies.\n- `generate-context.js` remains the primary save mechanism when the workflow also needs DB indexing, embedding generation, `description.json` refresh, `graph-metadata.json` refresh, or anchor-managed compatibility output.\n- Canonical save requests now default to **planner-first** behavior: return the routed target, proposed edit summary, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions before any mutation-first apply path is requested.\n- Explicit fallback remains available with `plannerMode: \"full-auto\"` or CLI `--full-auto` when an operator wants the legacy atomic writer behavior.\n- Standalone spec-doc markdown is not the primary operator-facing destination for this command.\n- Retention cleanup is outside save scope. When saved records expire under governance metadata, use `/memory:manage retention-sweep`, which routes to `memory_retention_sweep` (`tool-schemas.ts:330`).\n- `/memory:*` commands are markdown-owned contracts. They intentionally do not\n  have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\n  operating-mode blocks plus the markdown workflow steps.\n\n### Handover Document Maintenance\n\n`/memory:save` is the canonical maintainer for `handover.md` through `handover_state` routing. When a packet does not already contain `handover.md`, create it from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/handover.md`, then merge subsequent stop-state updates into `handover.md::session-log` while keeping `_memory.continuity` aligned for `/speckit:resume`.\n\n### Routed Save Categories\n\nThe canonical save router works with 8 categories:\n\n| Category | Typical target | Notes |\n| -------- | -------------- | ----- |\n| `narrative_progress` | `implementation-summary.md::what-built` | What changed in the system or packet |\n| `narrative_delivery` | `implementation-summary.md::how-delivered` | Sequencing, gating, rollout, and verification story |\n| `decision` | `decision-record.md::adr-NNN` on L3/L3+ or `implementation-summary.md::decisions` on L1/L2 | Choice, tradeoff, rationale |\n| `handover_state` | `handover.md::session-log` | Stop-state, blockers, recent action, next safe action. Use `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/handover.md` for initial creation when `handover.md` does not exist. |\n| `research_finding` | `research/research.md::findings` | Evidence, investigation result, cited upstream behavior |\n| `task_update` | `tasks.md::<phase-anchor>` | Checklist/task status mutation |\n| `metadata_only` | `_memory.continuity` in frontmatter | Machine-owned continuity payloads |\n| `drop` | `scratch/pending-route-<hash>.json` via refusal | Non-canonical transcript/tooling noise; never auto-merged |\n\nRouting tiers:\n\n- Tier 1 handles structured routes and strong heuristics.\n- Tier 2 uses prototype similarity against the frozen routing library.\n- Tier 3 is part of the live save handler by default. When `LLM_REFORMULATION_ENDPOINT` is reachable and returns a usable decision, it participates automatically; if that endpoint is unavailable or unusable, the save path falls back to Tier 2 with a confidence penalty when safe, otherwise it refuses the merge.\n\nBoundary rules:\n\n- Delivery cues are now stronger when the chunk mentions sequencing, gating, rollout, or verification.\n- Handover keeps state-first stop/resume notes even if they mention soft operational commands like `git diff`, `list spec-doc records`, or `force re-index`.\n- Hard transcript, telemetry, and wrapper scaffolding still route to `drop`.\n\nOverride and context rules:\n\n- `routeAs` can force any of the 8 categories. The router preserves the natural decision for audit and warns if an override is accepted against a natural `drop`.\n- Router context passes `packet_kind` derived from spec metadata first (`type`, `title`, `description`), with parent-phase fallback only when the metadata is silent.\n\n---\n\n## 3. CONTRACT\n\n| Field   | Value                                                                                        |\n| ------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Input   | Spec folder path (from Gate 3 or `$ARGUMENTS`) + AI-composed JSON data                       |\n| Output  | Canonical spec-doc continuity updates + indexed continuity data. Also refreshes `graph-metadata.json` derived fields in the spec folder: `trigger_phrases` are deduplicated and capped at 12, `key_files` are sanitized before storage, `entities` are deduplicated with canonical-path preference, and `status` is checklist-aware and normalized to lowercase. |\n| Script  | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`               |\n| Primary | **JSON mode:** `generate-context.js <json-data-path>` (e.g. a path under `$TMPDIR` or `/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json`) or `--json '<data>'` |\n| Trigger | \"save context\", \"save memory\", `/memory:save`                                                |\n\nPlanner behavior:\n- Default: `plan-only` for canonical save requests, with explicit follow-up actions such as `apply`, `refresh-graph`, and `reindex`\n- Fallback: `full-auto` restores the legacy mutation-first canonical writer\n- Deferred freshness actions: graph refresh and spec-doc reindex are surfaced as follow-ups instead of assumed default side effects\n\n---\n\n## 4. QUICK REFERENCE\n\n| Usage                                                  | Behavior                                                |\n| ------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `/memory:save`                                         | Auto-detect the active packet, confirm if needed, then route into canonical continuity targets |\n| `/memory:save 011-memory`                              | Save to a specific spec folder                          |\n| `/memory:save specs/006-semantic-memory/003-debugging` | Save to a nested spec folder                            |\n| `node .../generate-context.js --full-auto ...`         | Opt back into the legacy full-auto canonical apply path |\n\n---\n\n## 5. VALIDATION\n\n### Pre-Flight Checks (Phase 0)\n\nExecute BEFORE folder validation to prevent data quality issues. All checks must pass.\n\n#### Check 1: Anchor Format Validation\n\n- Scan conversation for existing canonical spec-doc references\n- If any canonical spec documents (`decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `handover.md`, `resource-map.md`) were read during the session, verify they contain BOTH opening AND closing ANCHOR tags\n- Pattern: `<!-- ANCHOR:id --> ... <!-- /ANCHOR:id -->`\n- If missing closing tags → WARN user before proceeding\n- Why: Broken anchors break section-specific retrieval (93% token waste)\n\n#### Check 2: Token Budget Validation\n\n- Estimate conversation size: `message_count * avg_tokens_per_message`\n- If estimated > 50,000 tokens:\n  - WARN: \"Large conversation detected\"\n  - OPTIONS: `[C]ontinue anyway | [S]plit save | [E]dit scope`\n  - WAIT for response\n\n#### Check 3: Spec Folder Existence\n\n- If `$ARGUMENTS` contains folder → validate exists, store as `pending_folder`\n- If `$ARGUMENTS` empty → defer to Phase 1\n\n#### Check 4: Stop Hook Awareness\n\n- Confirm whether recent hook-driven context preservation evidence exists for this session\n- Current limitation: no dedicated `pendingStopSave` field is shipped in the hook state, so `/memory:save` must not claim a guaranteed auto-save merge marker\n- If no recent hook-save evidence can be established: PASSED (proceed normally)\n\n**Phase 0 Output:**\n```text\nanchor_validation: PASSED | WARNED\ntoken_budget:      PASSED | SPLIT_REQUESTED\nfolder_existence:  PASSED\nstop_hook_check:   PASSED\n```\n\n### Spec Folder Validation (Phase 1)\n\n```text\nIF target_folder already set (from $ARGUMENTS or Tier 1/2 auto-detection):\n  → Validate folder exists → Proceed to Content Alignment Check\nIF target_folder not yet set (Tier 3 pending):\n  → WAIT for user response → Validate → Proceed\nIF folder invalid:\n  → Show available folders → ASK user → WAIT\n```\n\n**HARD STOP:** Do NOT proceed to save workflow until `target_folder` is set and validated.\n\n#### Content Alignment Check\n\nAfter Phase 1, validate the conversation topic matches the target folder:\n\n- Extract conversation topic (subject, files modified, problem being solved)\n- Compare to `target_folder` name\n- If clear match → PASS\n- If mismatch → WARN with alternatives:\n  - Show: \"Conversation topic: [topic]\" / \"Selected folder: [target_folder]\"\n  - Suggest top 3 alternative folders\n  - ASK: `[C]ontinue | [1][2][3] alternatives | [N]ew folder`\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW\n\n### Step 1: Folder Detection\n\nUse the `target_folder` value from Phase 1.\n\n### Step 2: Context Analysis (AI MUST PERFORM)\n\n**CRITICAL:** The AI agent MUST analyze the conversation and extract this data. The script does NOT auto-extract: the AI constructs this manually.\n\nExtract from the current conversation:\n- **Session summary**: 2-4 sentences describing what was accomplished\n- **Key decisions**: Array of choices with rationale (format: \"Decision: [choice] because [reason]\")\n- **Files modified**: Full paths to all files created/edited during session\n- **Trigger phrases**: 5-10 keywords/phrases for future semantic search retrieval\n- **Technical context**: Key technical details, patterns used, or implementation notes\n\n### Step 3: Anchor Generation (MANDATORY)\n\nEvery generated canonical spec document MUST include anchors for section-specific retrieval (enables 93% token savings).\n\n**Anchor Format:**\n```html\n<!-- ANCHOR:anchor-id -->\nContent for this section...\n<!-- /ANCHOR:anchor-id -->\n```\n\n**Rules:**\n- Use UPPERCASE `ANCHOR` (recommended, though lowercase works)\n- **MUST include BOTH opening AND closing tags**: closing tag is REQUIRED\n- No space after colon: `ANCHOR:id` not `ANCHOR: id`\n- Without closing tag, extraction fails silently\n\n**Anti-Pattern:**\n```html\n<!-- WRONG: No closing tag = anchor extraction fails -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\nContent...\n<!-- Missing closing tag! -->\n\n<!-- CORRECT: Both tags present -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\nContent...\n<!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n```\n\n**Anchor ID Pattern:** `[context-type]-[keywords]-[spec-number]`\n\n| Context Type     | Use For                  | Example                             |\n| ---------------- | ------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |\n| `implementation` | Code patterns, solutions | `implementation-oauth-callback-049` |\n| `decision`       | Architecture choices     | `decision-database-schema-005`      |\n| `research`       | Investigation findings   | `research-lenis-scroll-006`         |\n| `discovery`      | Learnings, insights      | `discovery-api-limits-011`          |\n| `general`        | Mixed content            | `general-session-summary-049`       |\n\n**Minimum Anchors:** 1 required (primary section). Recommended: 2+ (summary + decisions/implementation).\n\n**Standard Anchor Set:**\n```markdown\n<!-- ANCHOR:summary-[spec#] -->\n## Session Summary\n...\n<!-- /ANCHOR:summary-[spec#] -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:decision-[topic]-[spec#] -->\n## Key Decisions\n...\n<!-- /ANCHOR:decision-[topic]-[spec#] -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:files-[spec#] -->\n## Files Modified\n...\n<!-- /ANCHOR:files-[spec#] -->\n```\n\n### Step 4: Create JSON Data (AI CONSTRUCTS THIS)\n\n**CRITICAL:** The AI MUST construct this JSON from Step 2 analysis. The script requires proper JSON input to produce high-quality canonical spec-doc updates across decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, and handover.md.\n\n**Required JSON Structure:**\n```json\n{\n  \"specFolder\": \"005-memory/010-feature-name\",\n  \"sessionSummary\": \"Comprehensive description of what was accomplished. Include problem solved, approach taken, outcome achieved. 100+ chars.\",\n  \"keyDecisions\": [\n    \"Decision 1: Chose X because Y - provides Z benefit\",\n    \"Decision 2: Selected A over B due to performance\"\n  ],\n  \"filesModified\": [\n    \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js\",\n    \"specs/005-memory/010-feature-name/spec.md\"\n  ],\n  \"triggerPhrases\": [\n    \"generate-context\", \"memory save\", \"JSON input\",\n    \"context preservation\", \"session capture\"\n  ],\n  \"technicalContext\": {\n    \"rootCause\": \"Description of the problem's root cause\",\n    \"solution\": \"How it was solved\",\n    \"patterns\": \"Key patterns or approaches used\"\n  },\n  \"toolCalls\": [\n    { \"tool\": \"Read\", \"inputSummary\": \"Read scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js\", \"outputSummary\": \"Runtime CLI entry point verified for JSON-mode saves\", \"status\": \"success\", \"durationEstimate\": \"fast\" },\n    { \"tool\": \"Edit\", \"inputSummary\": \"Updated Memory Save Rule in CLAUDE.md\", \"outputSummary\": \"Changed JSON-primary wording\", \"status\": \"success\" }\n  ],\n  \"exchanges\": [\n    { \"userInput\": \"Implement the JSON-primary plan\", \"assistantResponse\": \"Updated CLAUDE.md, SKILL.md, session-types.ts, data-loader.ts with JSON-primary changes\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Field Guidelines:**\n\n| Field              | Min Length | Purpose                                              |\n| ------------------ | ---------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n| `sessionSummary`   | 100+ chars | Becomes OVERVIEW: be comprehensive                   |\n| `keyDecisions`     | 1+ items   | Each decision with rationale                         |\n| `filesModified`    | 0+ items   | Actual paths modified                                |\n| `triggerPhrases`   | 5-12 items | Keywords for semantic search. Parser-enforced cap at 12. |\n| `technicalContext` | Optional   | Additional technical details                         |\n| `toolCalls`        | Optional   | AI-summarized tool calls (richer than DB extraction) |\n| `exchanges`        | Optional   | Key user-assistant exchanges during session          |\n\n### Step 5: Produce Plan or Execute Processing Script\n\nDefault `/memory:save` behavior is plan-only. Stop after producing the routed\ntarget, proposed edits, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions unless the\ncaller explicitly selects an apply action, `plannerMode:\"full-auto\"`, or the CLI\n`--full-auto` path.\n\n| Mode                              | Command                                                           | Use When                                     |\n| --------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |\n| **Plan-only** (default)           | Return routed target, proposed edits, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions | Canonical save request without explicit apply approval |\n| **JSON File** (explicit apply)    | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js ${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/save-context-data.json <spec-folder>` | Rich context with decisions, files, triggers after apply or full-auto selection |\n\n> **Why JSON mode:** The AI has strictly better information about its own session than any database query can reconstruct. JSON mode eliminates wrong-session capture, multi-session ambiguity, and exchange pairing bugs.\n\n> **026 Memory Quality (Post-Save Review):** After `generate-context.js` completes, it outputs a POST-SAVE QUALITY REVIEW. HIGH-severity issues (stale titles, weak trigger phrases, wrong importance tier) MUST be patched via Edit tool immediately. MEDIUM issues should be patched when practical. Trigger phrases are sanitized: generic phrases (e.g., \"context\", \"session\") are flagged for replacement with domain-specific terms per 026-003-009/010 trigger sanitization rules.\n\n> **Graph metadata refresh:** The same save pass refreshes `graph-metadata.json` with checklist-aware status fallback (`implementation-summary.md` presence + checklist completion), lowercase status normalization, sanitized `key_files`, deduplicated entities, and a 12-item cap on derived trigger phrases.\n\n> **Auto-index of touched files (Step 11.5):** After the canonical save updates packet docs and `graph-metadata.json`, the workflow re-indexes touched canonical spec docs only when the standalone process is the sole SQLite writer. If the mk-spec-memory daemon is down, `generate-context.js` may run the direct incremental spec-doc index path. If the daemon is up, Step 11.5 must not open a second better-sqlite3 writer on `context-index.sqlite`; finish freshness through the daemon-owned MCP tool instead:\n>\n> ```javascript\n> mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({\n>   specFolder: \"<target-folder>\",\n>   includeSpecDocs: true,\n>   force: false\n> })\n> ```\n>\n> The save itself is durable before indexing. When Step 11.5 skips because the daemon is running, docs are not lost; retrieval remains stale until the MCP scan runs. The re-index covers canonical spec docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `handover.md`, `research/research.md`, `resource-map.md`) and `graph-metadata.json` modified earlier in the session. Incremental mode skips unchanged files cheaply via mtime + content-hash checks.\n>\n> Kill switches: `SPECKIT_AUTO_INDEX_TOUCHED=false` (targeted opt-out) or `SPECKIT_INDEX_SPEC_DOCS=false` (existing global opt-out) disables Step 11.5. The backend has a 51s cooldown between scans; when a save fires during cooldown, Step 11.5 logs `skipped (scan cooldown active; retry on next save)` and continues — the index catches up on the next save.\n\n> **Cross-Platform Note:** `${TMPDIR:-/tmp}` uses the system temp directory. On macOS/Linux this resolves to `/tmp` or `$TMPDIR`. On Windows (Git Bash/WSL), use `$TEMP` or `%TEMP%`.\n\n> SECURITY: When using heredoc or --stdin, ensure JSON content is properly escaped. Prefer --json flag with single-quoted inline JSON or write to /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json via Write tool first (exception to the Write tool exclusion: writing the intermediate JSON data file is permitted).\n\nWrite to `/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json` (Write tool exception: intermediate JSON data file only) or use `--json`/`--stdin`, then execute:\n```bash\nTEMP_FILE=\"${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/save-context-data.json\"\n\n# 1. Write JSON data to the temp file\ncat > \"$TEMP_FILE\" << 'EOF'\n{ \"specFolder\": \"...\", \"sessionSummary\": \"...\", ... }\nEOF\n\n# 2. Execute the script\nnode .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js \"$TEMP_FILE\" specs/###-folder/\n\n# 3. Clean up\nrm \"$TEMP_FILE\"\n```\n\n**Expected Output (Success):**\n```text\n✓ Loaded conversation data\n✓ Transformed manual format to MCP-compatible structure\n✓ Found N messages\n✓ Found N decisions\n✓ Routed canonical targets prepared\n✓ Continuity surfaces updated\n✓ Indexed continuity data\n```\n\n### File Output\n\n**Primary result:** canonical packet docs and `_memory.continuity` are updated in-place for the selected spec folder.\n\n**Typical targets:**\n- `handover.md`\n- `implementation-summary.md`\n- `decision-record.md`\n- frontmatter `_memory.continuity`\n- `graph-metadata.json`\n\nIf compatibility artifacts are emitted during migration cleanup, they remain secondary to the canonical packet update and should not be treated as the source of truth.\n\n### Step 6: Report Results\n\nDisplay the completion report (see Section 6).\n\n---\n\n## 7. COMPLETION REPORT\n\n### Structured Response Envelope\n\n```json\n{\n  \"summary\": \"Context saved successfully into the canonical continuity surfaces for specs/011-memory\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"status\": \"OK\",\n    \"spec_folder\": \"011-memory\",\n    \"targets_updated\": [\n      \"handover.md\",\n      \"implementation-summary.md\",\n      \"_memory.continuity\"\n    ],\n    \"indexing_status\": \"indexed\",\n    \"anchors_updated\": [\"summary-011\", \"decision-vector-search-011\", \"files-011\"],\n    \"trigger_phrases\": [\"semantic search\", \"vector embeddings\", \"memory retrieval\"],\n    \"timestamp\": \"2026-02-01T14:30:00Z\"\n  },\n  \"hints\": [\n    \"Use /memory:search to find the updated packet context later\",\n    \"Anchors enable 93% token savings when loading specific sections\"\n  ],\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"command\": \"/memory:save\",\n    \"duration_ms\": 1247,\n    \"mcp_available\": true,\n    \"deferred_indexing\": false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Fields:**\n\n| Field                    | Type     | Description                              |\n| ------------------------ | -------- | ---------------------------------------- |\n| `data.status`            | string   | \"OK\" or \"FAIL\"                           |\n| `data.targets_updated`   | string[] | Canonical packet targets updated         |\n| `data.indexing_status`   | string   | \"indexed\", \"deferred\", or \"failed\"       |\n| `data.anchors_updated`   | string[] | List of anchor IDs updated or created    |\n| `meta.deferred_indexing` | boolean  | Whether indexing was deferred to restart |\n\n### Human-Friendly Display\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SAVE\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Folder      <spec_folder>\n  Targets     <target_1>, <target_2>, <target_3>\n  Indexing    <indexing_status>\n\n→ Anchors ─────────────────────────────────── <count> updated\n  <anchor1>\n  <anchor2>\n  <anchor3>\n\n→ Triggers ──────────────────────────────────────────\n  <phrase1> · <phrase2> · <phrase3> · ...\n\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n[t] edit triggers    [d] done\n\nSTATUS=OK TARGETS=<count> ANCHORS=<count>\n```\n\n### Post-Save Actions\n\n| Input | Action                                            |\n| ----- | ------------------------------------------------- |\n| t     | Edit trigger phrases for this spec-doc record (add/remove) |\n| d     | Done, exit save workflow                          |\n\n### Trigger Edit (if selected)\n\n```text\nMEMORY:TRIGGERS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Record      #<id> \"<spec_doc_title>\"\n\n→ Current Triggers ─────────────────────────────────\n  1) <phrase1>\n  2) <phrase2>\n  3) <phrase3>\n\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n[a] add    [r] remove #    [s] save    [d] done\n\nSTATUS=OK ID=<id> TRIGGERS=<count>\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. ERROR HANDLING\n\n| Condition               | Action                                          |\n| ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |\n| No spec folder found    | Prompt user to create one                       |\n| Folder not found        | Show available folders, ask user                |\n| Topic-folder mismatch   | Warn, suggest alternatives, ask to confirm      |\n| Empty conversation      | Return `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"No context to save\"` |\n| Script execution fails  | Show error, suggest manual save                 |\n| Embedding fails         | Canonical docs updated, will auto-index on MCP restart |\n| MCP unavailable         | Canonical docs updated, indexing deferred to restart   |\n| JSON not loaded         | Check temp file path and content format          |\n\n---\n\n## 9. NEXT STEPS\n\n| Condition                    | Suggested Command                          | Reason                        |\n| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------- |\n| Context saved, continue work | Return to previous task                    | Memory preserved, continue    |\n| Ending session               | `/memory:save [spec-folder-path]`           | Update `handover.md` through `handover_state` routing |\n| Search indexed continuity    | `/memory:search [query]`                | Find related context          |\n| Start new work               | `/speckit:complete [feature-description]` | Begin new feature             |\n\n**ALWAYS** end with: \"Context saved. What would you like to do next?\"\n\n---\n\n## 10. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools\n- `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest\n- `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation\n\n---\n<!-- APPENDIX: Reference material for AI agent implementation -->\n\n## APPENDIX A: MCP TOOL REFERENCE\n\n> **Tool Restriction (Memory Save Rule - HARD BLOCK):** `Write` remains intentionally excluded. `Edit` is allowed only for direct `_memory.continuity` frontmatter updates inside `implementation-summary.md`. Use `generate-context.js` for indexed saves, embedding generation, `description.json` refresh, `graph-metadata.json` refresh, and anchor-managed canonical spec-doc routing. Standalone `memory/*.md` files are retired and the runtime rejects them. See AGENTS.md Memory Save Rule.\n\n> **Mutation Ledger & Artifact Routing:** Every save operation is now recorded in the mutation ledger, an append-only audit trail that captures the file path, spec folder, timestamp, and indexing outcome. Artifact metadata associated with the saved spec-doc record may also be classified via artifact-class routing before indexing, ensuring consistent type tagging across the database.\n\n### Enforcement Matrix\n\n```text\nSTEP            REQUIRED CALLS                            ON FAILURE\n─────────────── ───────────────────────────────────────── ──────────────\nFOLDER DETECT   Bash (ls, CLI argument)                   Prompt user\nCONTEXT SAVE    Bash (node generate-context.js)           Show error msg\nIMMEDIATE INDEX mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan (optional) Show error msg\n```\n\n**Script Location:** `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`\n\n**Immediate indexing:** Canonical spec-doc surfaces participate in spec-doc indexing. If you need fresh retrieval immediately after a save, run a targeted index scan:\n\n```javascript\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({\n  specFolder: \"011-memory\",\n  includeSpecDocs: true,\n  force: true\n})\n```\n\n`memory_update({ id, triggerPhrases })`: Update trigger phrases on an existing indexed spec-doc record. Used by the `[t]` edit triggers action in the post-save review.\n\n---\n\n## APPENDIX B: ADVANCED REFERENCE\n\n### Indexing Options\n\nFour indexing methods are available: auto-indexing on MCP startup (default), `generate-context.js` (standard save workflow), `memory_save` (single file), and `memory_index_scan` (bulk). See full parameter references below.\n\n#### Normalization Before Bulk Rebuild\n\nWhen corpus-wide markdown metadata has changed, run normalization before force re-index:\n\n```bash\n# Dry-run normalization\nnode .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/backfill-frontmatter.js --dry-run --include-archive\n\n# Apply normalization\nnode .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/backfill-frontmatter.js --apply --include-archive\n\n# Rebuild index after normalization\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ force: true })\n```\n\nRecommended order: **normalize → verify → rebuild**.\n\n#### Deferred Indexing (Graceful Degradation)\n\nWhen MCP is unavailable or embedding fails, the canonical document update still lands on disk. Follow with a targeted `memory_index_scan` after MCP recovery so the updated spec docs and continuity anchors are discoverable across retrieval channels.\n\n**Manual Retry:**\n```javascript\n// Entire folder\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ specFolder: \"011-memory\", force: true })\n```\n\n**Recovery Options:**\n\n| Issue                  | Recovery                                                                                                                       |\n| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n| MCP server unreachable | Restart OpenCode to restart MCP server. Post-026: run `memory_health()` after restart to verify all retrieval channels (graph, vector, FTS5) are operational |\n| Embedding timeout      | Use `memory_index_scan` with smaller batch                                                                                     |\n| Corrupted file         | Read file, verify ANCHOR tags, re-save with corrections                                                                        |\n| Database locked        | For database recovery, use `/memory:manage health` to diagnose issues and `/memory:manage checkpoint restore` to recover from a known-good state. Avoid manual file deletion. |\n\n#### Full Parameter Reference: memory_save\n\n| Parameter        | Type    | Default    | Description                                         |\n| ---------------- | ------- | ---------- | --------------------------------------------------- |\n| `filePath`       | string  | *required* | Absolute path to the generated canonical spec document |\n| `force`          | boolean | false      | Force re-index even if content hash unchanged       |\n| `dryRun`         | boolean | false      | Validate only without saving                        |\n| `skipPreflight`  | boolean | false      | Skip pre-flight validation checks (not recommended) |\n| `asyncEmbedding` | boolean | false      | Defer embedding generation for non-blocking saves   |\n\n#### Full Parameter Reference: memory_index_scan\n\n| Parameter               | Type    | Default | Description                        |\n| ----------------------- | ------- | ------- | ---------------------------------- |\n| `force`                 | boolean | false   | Force re-index all files           |\n| `specFolder`            | string  | -       | Limit scan to specific spec folder |\n| `includeSpecDocs`       | boolean | true    | Include spec folder documents      |\n| `includeConstitutional` | boolean | true    | Include constitutional rule files  |\n| `incremental`           | boolean | true    | Skip unchanged files (mtime check) |\n\n### Sub-Agent Delegation\n\nThe save workflow delegates execution to a sub-agent for token efficiency. The main agent handles folder validation and user interaction; the sub-agent handles context analysis and file generation.\n\n#### Architecture\n\n```text\nMain Agent (reads command):\n├── PHASE 0-1: Pre-flight + Spec Folder Validation\n├── DISPATCH: Task tool with sub-agent\n│   ├── Sub-agent analyzes conversation\n│   ├── Sub-agent generates JSON data\n│   ├── Sub-agent executes generate-context.js\n│   └── Sub-agent returns result\n├── FALLBACK (if Task unavailable):\n│   └── Execute Steps 2-5 directly\n└── Step 6: Report Results (always main agent)\n```\n\n#### Sub-Agent Dispatch\n\nWhen phases pass, dispatch via Task tool:\n\n- **subagent_type:** `general`\n- **description:** \"Save continuity context\"\n- **prompt:** Include:\n  1. `target_folder` and `alignment_validated` from phases\n  2. Instructions for Steps 2-5 (context analysis → anchor generation → JSON construction → script execution)\n  3. Expected return format: `{ status, file_path, memory_id, anchors_created, trigger_phrases, spec_folder }`\n\n#### Fallback Logic\n\nFallback triggers if Task tool returns error, times out, or sub-agent returns `status: FAIL`.\n\n**Fallback behavior:** Execute Steps 2-5 directly in the main agent context, then continue to Step 6.\n\n| Benefit               | Description                                           |\n| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |\n| Token efficiency      | Heavy context extraction happens in sub-agent context |\n| Main agent responsive | Validation and reporting stay lightweight             |\n| Fallback safety       | Commands always work, even without Task tool          |\n\n### Governance, Provenance & Retention\n\nThe `memory_save` tool schema advertises advanced governance parameters for multi-tenant, multi-agent, and compliance-aware deployments. These parameters take effect only when governance guardrails are enabled.\n\n#### Governance Scoping\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `tenantId` | string | Tenant boundary for governed ingest |\n| `userId` | string | User boundary for governed ingest |\n| `agentId` | string | Agent boundary for governed ingest |\n| `sessionId` | string | Session boundary for governed ingest |\n\n#### Provenance\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `provenanceSource` | string | Required provenance source when governance guardrails are enabled |\n| `provenanceActor` | string | Required provenance actor when governance guardrails are enabled |\n| `governedAt` | string | ISO timestamp for governed ingest. Defaults to now when omitted |\n\n#### Retention\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `retentionPolicy` | string | Retention class: `keep` (permanent), `ephemeral` (short-lived), `shared` (reserved compatibility value) |\n| `deleteAfter` | string | Optional ISO timestamp after which retention sweep may delete the spec-doc record |\n\n> **Note:** Governance parameters (tenantId, userId, agentId, sessionId) are validated by the memorySaveSchema when provided. All governance fields must pass schema validation.\n\n#### Async Bulk Ingestion\n\nFor ingesting multiple files at once without blocking, use `/memory:manage ingest` instead:\n\n```bash\n# Start async ingestion of multiple files\n/memory:manage ingest start /path/to/file1.md /path/to/file2.md --folder 007-auth\n\n# Check progress\n/memory:manage ingest status <jobId>\n```\n\nSee `/memory:manage ingest` for the full async ingestion workflow.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":738,"totalLines":738,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/save.md","time":{"start":1780738219091,"end":1780738219099}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_076c916f5a177fda016a23e8aaf32881919f493a6a7197c6ce"}},"id":"prt_e9c44dc3a001aSql2lgtOolGU8","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","messageID":"msg_e9c44b8f8001v2rOknVCFoX4el"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738219105,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OOzCZnAZYW3VEdPtZSHtRGxZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\n3: argument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n5: ---\n6: \n7: > **Code Graph bridge:** Structural routing may call stable `code_graph_*` MCP tools; the code-graph implementation and docs are owned by `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n8: \n9: # 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n10: \n11: **BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, CHECK `$ARGUMENTS`:**\n12: \n13: ```text\n14: IF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n15:     → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n16:     → Present the user with this question:\n17:         question: \"What would you like to retrieve context for?\"\n18:         options:\n19:           - label: \"Add feature\"\n20:             description: \"Context for implementing a new feature\"\n21:           - label: \"Fix bug\"\n22:             description: \"Context for debugging and fixing an issue\"\n23:           - label: \"Refactor\"\n24:             description: \"Context for code restructuring\"\n25:           - label: \"Security audit\"\n26:             description: \"Context for security review\"\n27:           - label: \"Understand\"\n28:             description: \"Context for learning existing code\"\n29:           - label: \"Find spec\"\n30:             description: \"Context for spec document retrieval\"\n31:           - label: \"Find decision\"\n32:             description: \"Context for decision rationale lookup\"\n33:           - label: \"Analysis tools\"\n34:             description: \"Epistemic baselines, memory causal graph, ablation, dashboards\"\n35:     → WAIT for user response\n36:     → If \"Analysis tools\" selected → Display ANALYSIS OVERVIEW (Section 8)\n37:     → Otherwise → Use their response to determine the intent and query\n38:     → If the AskUserQuestion response is a custom answer rather than one of the listed options,\n39:       treat that custom answer as the literal retrieval query and route it through RETRIEVAL MODE\n40:     → Only THEN continue with this workflow\n41: \n42: IF $ARGUMENTS starts with a KNOWN ANALYSIS SUBCOMMAND (Section 3):\n43:     → Route to ANALYSIS MODE (Section 5)\n44: \n45: IF $ARGUMENTS contains a query (any other text):\n46:     → Route to RETRIEVAL MODE (Section 4)\n47: ```\n48: \n49: **CRITICAL RULES:**\n50: - **DO NOT** infer query from conversation context\n51: - **DO NOT** assume the user's intent without explicit input\n52: - **DO NOT** proceed past this point without explicit query from user\n53: - The query and intent MUST come from `$ARGUMENTS` or user's answer above\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: # Memory Search Command\n58: \n59: Unified entry point for knowledge retrieval and analysis. Combines intent-aware context search (retrieval mode) with epistemic measurement, memory causal graph tools, and evaluation dashboards (analysis mode).\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 0. INSTRUCTIONS\n64: \n65: Start by classifying `$ARGUMENTS` into retrieval mode or analysis mode. Follow the routing contract below, prefer canonical packet sources in retrieval mode, and only invoke the analysis subcommands that match the user's explicit request.\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ```yaml\n70: role: Retrieval & Analysis Specialist\n71: purpose: Unified entry point combining intent-aware retrieval with epistemic measurement, memory causal graph, and evaluation tools\n72: action: Route through retrieval or analysis mode based on argument pattern\n73: \n74: operating_mode:\n75:   workflow: argument_routing\n76:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n77:   approvals: none_required\n78:   tracking: intent_classification\n79: ```\n80: \n81: This is a markdown-owned command contract. `/memory:*` commands intentionally do\n82: not have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\n83: operating-mode block and markdown workflow steps.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 1. PURPOSE\n88: \n89: > **L1 Orchestration + L6 Analysis**: This command operates at both the L1 retrieval layer (orchestrating lower-level context-retrieval operations) and the L6 analysis layer (epistemic baselines, memory causal graph, evaluation). It provides a single entry point for all knowledge-related context-retrieval operations.\n90: \n91: Provide a unified entry point that:\n92: \n93: **Retrieval mode** (default):\n94: - Automatically detects task intent from the query\n95: - Applies task-specific weights for search optimization\n96: - Combines search + load in a single operation\n97: - Returns context with relevance explanation\n98: - Enforces L1 token budget constraints (target: ~2000 tokens per call)\n99: - Handles session deduplication for cross-session queries\n100: - Targets canonical packet sources first: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, then the packet spec docs\n101: \n102: **Analysis mode** (subcommand-triggered):\n103: - Epistemic measurement: Capture knowledge baselines before and after tasks (`task_preflight`, `task_postflight`)\n104: - Memory causal graph: Trace decision lineage, create/remove causal links, view graph stats (`memory_drift_why`, `memory_causal_link`, `memory_causal_unlink`, `memory_causal_stats`)\n105: - Evaluation: Run channel ablation studies and view reporting dashboards (`eval_run_ablation`, `eval_reporting_dashboard`)\n106: - Learning history: View PREFLIGHT/POSTFLIGHT records and Learning Index trends (`memory_get_learning_history`)\n107: \n108: **Lifecycle note:** Retrieval does not delete expired records. Use `/memory:manage retention-sweep` for the `memory_retention_sweep` tool when governed records need retention cleanup (`tool-schemas.ts:330`).\n109: \n110: ### Hybrid Retrieval Runtime (Retrieval Mode)\n111: \n112: The unified context tool runs a hybrid retrieval pipeline with **graph-first routing** (026):\n113: \n114: - **Structural code graph channel has priority** in the fusion strategy: structural queries (callers, imports, dependencies) are routed to `code_graph_query` first, before semantic or lexical channels\n115: - Tri-channel retrieval (graph + vector/semantic + FTS5/BM25) with graph results given precedence in the fusion merge\n116: - Code Graph structural queries plus exact-text Grep integrates as the vector/semantic channel, providing natural-language code discovery alongside indexed-continuity vector search\n117: - When graph and semantic channels miss or return weak results, a 3-tier FTS fallback activates: FTS5 full-text → BM25 keyword scoring → Grep/Glob filesystem search. Post-026 FTS5 remediation improved BM25 tokenization and ranking accuracy\n118: - Intent-adaptive fusion and reranking (weights adapt when `SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION` is enabled, including the internal continuity profile: semantic `0.52`, keyword `0.18`, recency `0.07`, graph `0.23`)\n119: - MMR diversity pruning to reduce redundant chunks, with continuity-oriented Stage 3 passes using a dedicated lambda of `0.65`\n120: - Stage 3 applies MMR diversity reranking plus MPAB chunk collapse; `applyLengthPenalty` remains on the API surface for compatibility but currently resolves to a neutral `1.0` multiplier for every document\n121: - Deep-mode query expansion for broader lexical coverage\n122: - Evidence-gap detection (026) to flag low-confidence retrievals with explicit gap warnings, enabling downstream reasoning to remain cautious and avoid acting on sparse evidence\n123: \n124: ### Canonical Retrieval Order\n125: \n126: - `/speckit:resume` is the recovery surface for session continuation.\n127: - Resume-oriented retrieval follows `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`.\n128: - Packet-oriented retrieval may additionally use indexed `document_type='graph_metadata'` rows for dependency, supersession, related-packet, and key-file signals.\n129: - `find_spec` and `find_decision` should resolve against canonical spec docs and anchors, not against standalone continuity artifacts.\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## 2. CONTRACT\n134: \n135: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS`: Query with optional intent override, OR analysis subcommand with parameters\n136: **Outputs:** Context with relevance scores and intent explanation, OR `STATUS=<OK|FAIL>` with subcommand-specific output\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ## 3. QUICK REFERENCE\n141: \n142: ### Retrieval Mode (default)\n143: \n144: | Command | Result |\n145: |---------|--------|\n146: | `/memory:search \"implement auth\"` | Auto-detect add_feature, apply weights |\n147: | `/memory:search \"auth bug\" --intent:fix_bug` | Explicit fix_bug intent |\n148: | `/memory:search \"how does auth work?\"` | Auto-detect understand intent |\n149: | `/memory:search \"optimize auth code\"` | Auto-detect refactor intent |\n150: | `/memory:search \"auth security review\"` | Auto-detect security_audit intent |\n151: | `/memory:search \"find the spec for auth\"` | Auto-detect find_spec intent |\n152: | `/memory:search \"why did we choose JWT\"` | Auto-detect find_decision intent |\n153: \n154: ### Analysis Mode (subcommand-triggered)\n155: \n156: | Command | Result |\n157: |---------|--------|\n158: | `/memory:search preflight specs/007-auth T1` | Capture epistemic baseline |\n159: | `/memory:search postflight specs/007-auth T1` | Calculate learning delta |\n160: | `/memory:search history specs/007-auth` | View learning history |\n161: | `/memory:search causal 42` | Trace causal chain for memory #42 |\n162: | `/memory:search link 42 43 caused` | Link memory #42 → #43 as caused |\n163: | `/memory:search unlink 5` | Remove causal edge #5 |\n164: | `/memory:search causal-stats` | View memory causal graph statistics |\n165: | `/memory:search ablation` | Run channel ablation study |\n166: | `/memory:search dashboard` | View reporting dashboard |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## 4. ARGUMENT ROUTING\n171: \n172: ```text\n173: $ARGUMENTS\n174:     │\n175:     ├─ Empty (no args)                        → INTERACTIVE PROMPT (see gate above)\n176:     │\n177:     ├─ ANALYSIS SUBCOMMAND DETECTED?\n178:     │   First token matches one of:\n179:     │   \"preflight\", \"postflight\", \"history\",\n180:     │   \"causal\", \"link\", \"unlink\",\n181:     │   \"causal-stats\", \"ablation\", \"dashboard\"\n182:     │   └─► YES → ANALYSIS MODE (Section 5)\n183:     │\n184:     └─ OTHERWISE (any other text)\n185:         └─► RETRIEVAL MODE (Section 4A)\n186:             Parse: <query> [--intent:<type>]\n187: ```\n188: \n189: **Routing logic:** If the first argument token exactly matches a known analysis subcommand keyword → route to analysis mode. Otherwise → treat entire input as a retrieval query (with optional `--intent:` flag).\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n194: <!-- SECTION 4A: RETRIEVAL MODE                                     -->\n195: <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n196: \n197: ## 4A. RETRIEVAL MODE\n198: \n199: ### Intent Types and Weights\n200: \n201: #### Intent Classification\n202: \n203: The system detects one of seven intent types:\n204: \n205: | Intent Type | Description | Weight Adjustments |\n206: |-------------|-------------|--------------------|\n207: | **add_feature** | Implementing new functionality | implementation: 1.5x, architecture: 1.3x, patterns: 1.2x |\n208: | **fix_bug** | Debugging and fixing issues | decisions: 1.4x, implementation: 1.3x, errors: 1.5x |\n209: | **refactor** | Code restructuring | architecture: 1.5x, patterns: 1.4x, decisions: 1.2x |\n210: | **security_audit** | Security review | decisions: 1.4x, implementation: 1.3x, security: 1.5x |\n211: | **understand** | Learning existing code | architecture: 1.4x, decisions: 1.3x, overview: 1.5x |\n212: | **find_spec** | Canonical spec document retrieval | spec-doc: 1.5x, architecture: 1.3x, overview: 1.2x |\n213: | **find_decision** | Decision rationale lookup from canonical docs | decisions: 1.5x, rationale: 1.4x, architecture: 1.2x |\n214: \n215: #### Detection Logic\n216: \n217: Intent is detected via keyword matching against the query. Keywords are phrase-based to avoid false positives:\n218: \n219: | Intent | Keywords |\n220: |--------|----------|\n221: | `add_feature` | 'implement', 'add feature', 'add new', 'add a', 'create new', 'build new' |\n222: | `fix_bug` | 'bug', 'error', 'fix', 'broken', 'issue', 'debug' |\n223: | `refactor` | 'refactor', 'restructure', 'improve', 'clean up', 'optimize' |\n224: | `security_audit` | 'security', 'vulnerability', 'auth', 'sanitize', 'xss', 'csrf' |\n225: | `understand` | 'how', 'why', 'what', 'explain', 'understand', 'learn' |\n226: | `find_spec` | 'spec', 'specification', 'spec folder', 'spec document', 'find spec' |\n227: | `find_decision` | 'decision', 'rationale', 'why did we', 'chose', 'decision record' |\n228: \n229: **Default fallback:** If no keywords match, defaults to `understand`.\n230: \n231: #### Anchor Mapping by Intent\n232: \n233: | Intent | Primary Anchors | Secondary Anchors | Why These? |\n234: |--------|----------------|-------------------|------------|\n235: | **add_feature** | implementation, architecture, patterns | decisions, code-examples | Need existing patterns + structure |\n236: | **fix_bug** | decisions, implementation, errors | debugging, troubleshooting | Need decision history + error context |\n237: | **refactor** | architecture, patterns, decisions | technical-specs, code-quality | Need structure understanding + rationale |\n238: | **security_audit** | decisions, implementation, security | validation, auth, sanitization | Need security decisions + validation patterns |\n239: | **understand** | architecture, decisions, summary | overview, context, background | Need high-level understanding first |\n240: | **find_spec** | spec-doc, architecture, overview | specification, structure | Need canonical spec document content + structure |\n241: | **find_decision** | decisions, rationale, architecture | context, background, history | Need decision records and rationale from canonical docs |\n242: \n243: #### Example: add_feature Intent\n244: \n245: ```text\n246: Query: \"implement oauth token refresh\"\n247: Intent: add_feature (detected)\n248: \n249: Anchors Selected:\n250:   1. implementation (1.5x weight)\n251:   2. architecture (1.3x weight)\n252:   3. patterns (1.2x weight)\n253: \n254: Reasoning:\n255:   - Need existing OAuth implementation patterns\n256:   - Need architecture understanding for integration points\n257:   - Need code examples for token handling\n258: ```\n259: \n260: ### Retrieval Workflow\n261: \n262: #### Step 1: Parse Query and Detect Intent\n263: \n264: ```text\n265: Input: $ARGUMENTS\n266:     ↓\n267: Extract Query + Intent Override (if --intent: flag)\n268:     ↓\n269: IF intent override provided:\n270:     → Use explicit intent\n271: ELSE:\n272:     → Auto-detect via keyword matching\n273:     ↓\n274: Store: query, intent\n275: ```\n276: \n277: #### Step 2: Apply Intent-Specific Weights\n278: \n279: ```text\n280: Based on detected intent:\n281:     ↓\n282: Select appropriate anchors:\n283:     - add_feature: ['implementation', 'architecture', 'patterns']\n284:     - fix_bug: ['decisions', 'implementation', 'errors', 'debugging']\n285:     - refactor: ['architecture', 'patterns', 'decisions']\n286:     - security_audit: ['decisions', 'implementation', 'security']\n287:     - understand: ['architecture', 'decisions', 'summary', 'overview']\n288:     - find_spec: ['spec-doc', 'architecture', 'overview', 'specification']\n289:     - find_decision: ['decisions', 'rationale', 'architecture', 'context']\n290:     ↓\n291: Adjust search parameters:\n292:     - Weight boost for relevant context types\n293:     - Anchor filtering for targeted retrieval\n294: ```\n295: \n296: #### Step 3: Execute Search with Optimizations\n297: \n298: ```javascript\n299: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({\n300:   input: query,\n301:   intent: intent,\n302:   mode: \"auto\",                 // use \"deep\" for expanded multi-query retrieval\n303:   anchors: intentAnchors[intent],\n304:   limit: 10,\n305:   includeContent: true,\n306:   enableDedup: true\n307: });\n308: ```\n309: \n310: #### Step 4: Return Context with Explanation\n311: \n312: Format response:\n313: \n314: ```text\n315: MEMORY:SEARCH  \"<query>\"  <detected-intent>  <N> found\n316: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n317: \n318:   <leaf-folder>/\n319:     <score>  #<id>  <title>\n320: \n321:   <leaf-folder>/\n322:     <score>  #<id>  <title>\n323:     <score>  #<id>  <title>\n324:     <score>  #<id>  <title>\n325: \n326:   <leaf-folder>/\n327:     <score>  #<id>  <title>\n328:     <score>  #<id>  <title>\n329: \n330: STATUS=OK RESULTS=<count>\n331: ```\n332: \n333: **Folder display rules:**\n334: - Results grouped by spec folder\n335: - **Leaf folder name only** as group header (last path segment, e.g., `010-search-retrieval-quality-fixes/`)\n336: - Drop all parent path prefixes (`system-spec-kit/023-esm-module-compliance/` etc.)\n337: - Top-level folders (like `system-spec-kit/`) shown as-is\n338: - If two leaf names collide, prefix with parent number: `023/010-search-quality/`\n339: - Results indented under their folder group\n340: - Each result shows only: score, ID, title\n341: - No other metadata (no type, bars, previews, weights, or token budget)\n342: \n343: #### Step 4b: Empty-Results Fallback (RESULTS=0 with TRIGGERED>0 or CONSTITUTIONAL>0)\n344: \n345: When semantic + lexical search return zero direct matches but the trigger-phrase matcher OR constitutional-rule surfacer returned spec-doc records, render them under explicit canonical labels — never invent ad-hoc wording like \"Auto-triggered memories\":\n346: \n347: ```text\n348: MEMORY:SEARCH  \"<query>\"  <detected-intent>  0 found\n349: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n350: \n351: No spec-doc records matched this query via semantic or lexical search.\n352: \n353: Trigger-matched spec-doc records (matched on phrase \"<keyword>\"):\n354:   <leaf-folder>/\n355:     #<id>  <title>\n356:   <leaf-folder>/\n357:     #<id>  <title>\n358: \n359: Constitutional rules (always-surface tier):\n360:   #<id>  <title>\n361: \n362: STATUS=OK  RESULTS=0  TRIGGERED=<n>  CONSTITUTIONAL=<n>\n363: ```\n364: \n365: **Vocabulary rules for this fallback:**\n366: - Use `Trigger-matched spec-doc records` — NOT `Auto-triggered memories`, `Triggered memories`, or `Memories`\n367: - Use `Constitutional rules` — NOT `Constitutional memories`\n368: - The phrase that triggered the match is shown in quotes in the section heading\n369: - Drop the score column (trigger matches are categorical, not scored)\n370: - After the formatted output, the assistant MAY ask one clarifying follow-up question if the query was ambiguous (≤2 lines), but the canonical block above must come first.\n371: \n372: ##### Forbidden Phrase Enforcement (REQ-003 / Cluster 3)\n373: \n374: The following phrases MUST NOT appear anywhere in any `/memory:search` rendering — empty-result fallback, full-result render, or analysis subcommand output. This list is authoritative; treat any occurrence as a P0 contract violation.\n375: \n376: | Forbidden Phrase | Required Replacement |\n377: |------------------|---------------------|\n378: | `Auto-triggered memories` | `Trigger-matched spec-doc records` |\n379: | `Auto-triggered memory` | `Trigger-matched spec-doc record` |\n380: | `Triggered memories` | `Trigger-matched spec-doc records` |\n381: | `Triggered memory` | `Trigger-matched spec-doc record` |\n382: | `Memories` (as a section header on its own) | `Spec-doc records` |\n383: | `Memory` (as a result-class label) | `Spec-doc record` |\n384: | `Constitutional memories` | `Constitutional rules` |\n385: | `Constitutional memory` | `Constitutional rule` |\n386: | `auto-triggered` (any case) | `trigger-matched` |\n387: \n388: Pre-render gate (assistant MUST run before emitting the response block):\n389: 1. Build the candidate output text.\n390: 2. Case-insensitively scan for every forbidden phrase above.\n391: 3. On any match: rewrite using the replacement column. Do not emit the original.\n392: 4. After rewrite, verify the candidate is greppable-clean for the forbidden list.\n393: \n394: Verification (regression-safe):\n395: - `grep -Eci 'auto-triggered|triggered memories|triggered memory|constitutional memor(y|ies)'` against the rendered block MUST return `0`.\n396: - The rendered block uses only `Trigger-matched spec-doc records`, `Constitutional rules`, and `Spec-doc record(s)` for these concepts.\n397: \n398: ### Token Budget Enforcement\n399: \n400: **memory_context L1 Budget:** ~2000 tokens total (mode-managed)\n401: \n402: #### Budget Guidance by Mode\n403: \n404: | Mode | Target Budget | Typical Use |\n405: |------|---------------|-------------|\n406: | `quick` | ~800 | Fast trigger/context lookup |\n407: | `focused` | ~1500 | Intent-optimized retrieval (`fix_bug`, etc.) |\n408: | `resume` | ~1200 | Session recovery (`state`, `next-steps`) |\n409: | `deep` | ~2000 | Broader context for complex work |\n410: | `auto` | mode-routed | Server selects mode from detected intent |\n411: \n412: #### Truncation Logic\n413: \n414: When results exceed token budget:\n415: 1. Sort results by intent-specific relevance score\n416: 2. Include results until budget reached\n417: 3. If last result causes overage but >90% budget used, truncate to fit remaining budget\n418: 4. Output includes: `Token Budget: ~<tokens> / <budget> tokens (<percentage>% used)` and `Truncation: <none|partial|significant>`\n419: \n420: ### Session Deduplication\n421: \n422: #### Purpose\n423: \n424: Prevent duplicate context when the same query spans multiple sessions or when overlapping sessions contain redundant information.\n425: \n426: #### Strategy\n427: \n428: - Content hashing: Each result is hashed; duplicates with same hash are merged (keeping most recent version)\n429: - Cross-session detection via `sessionId` metadata and content hash comparison\n430: - Timestamp-based recency preference when duplicates found\n431: - When the caller omits `sessionId`, the server uses a memory-specific runtime session identifier for `memory_context`; this keeps trigger and constitutional channel dedup stable within the MCP process without broadening global session state.\n432: - Dedup applies to standard retrieval results, trigger-derived context, and constitutional-tier injections before the response is budgeted.\n433: \n434: #### Deduplication Metadata\n435: \n436: When deduplication occurs, the response includes:\n437: \n438: ```yaml\n439: deduplication:\n440:   enabled: true\n441:   original_count: <N>\n442:   deduplicated_count: <M>\n443:   duplicates_removed: <N - M>\n444:   session_dedup_applied: true\n445: ```\n446: \n447: ---\n448: \n449: <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n450: <!-- SECTION 5: ANALYSIS MODE                                       -->\n451: <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n452: \n453: ## 5. ANALYSIS MODE\n454: \n455: ### Analysis Subcommand Routing\n456: \n457: ```text\n458: $ARGUMENTS (first token is a known subcommand)\n459:     │\n460:     ├─ \"preflight <specFolder> <taskId>\"      → EPISTEMIC MEASUREMENT (Section 5A)\n461:     ├─ \"postflight <specFolder> <taskId>\"     → EPISTEMIC MEASUREMENT (Section 5A)\n462:     ├─ \"history <specFolder>\"                 → EPISTEMIC MEASUREMENT (Section 5A)\n463:     ├─ \"causal <memoryId>\"                    → CAUSAL GRAPH (Section 5B)\n464:     ├─ \"link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation>\"→ CAUSAL GRAPH (Section 5B)\n465:     ├─ \"unlink <edgeId>\"                      → CAUSAL GRAPH (Section 5B)\n466:     ├─ \"causal-stats\"                         → CAUSAL GRAPH (Section 5B)\n467:     ├─ \"ablation\"                             → EVALUATION (Section 5C)\n468:     └─ \"dashboard\"                            → EVALUATION (Section 5C)\n469: ```\n470: \n471: ---\n472: \n473: ### 5A. Epistemic Measurement\n474: \n475: #### Preflight\n476: \n477: **Trigger:** `/memory:search preflight <specFolder> <taskId>`\n478: \n479: Captures epistemic baseline before implementation. Records knowledge, uncertainty, and context scores for later comparison with postflight.\n480: \n481: ##### Parameters\n482: \n483: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n484: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n485: | `specFolder` | string | Yes | Spec folder path (e.g., `specs/003-memory/077-upgrade`) |\n486: | `taskId` | string | Yes | Task identifier (e.g., `T1`, `implementation`) |\n487: | `knowledgeScore` | number | Yes | Knowledge level 0-100 |\n488: | `uncertaintyScore` | number | Yes | Uncertainty level 0-100 |\n489: | `contextScore` | number | Yes | Context completeness 0-100 |\n490: | `knowledgeGaps` | string[] | No | Identified knowledge gaps |\n491: | `sessionId` | string | No | Session identifier |\n492: \n493: ##### Workflow\n494: \n495: 1. Parse `specFolder` and `taskId` from arguments\n496: 2. Assess current epistemic state (knowledge, uncertainty, context)\n497: 3. Call `task_preflight()` with scores\n498: 4. Display baseline confirmation\n499: \n500: ##### Output\n501: \n502: ```text\n503: MEMORY:SEARCH PREFLIGHT\n504: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n505: \n506:   Spec        <specFolder>\n507:   Task        <taskId>\n508: \n509: → Epistemic Baseline ─────────────────────────────\n510:   Knowledge     <score>/100\n511:   Uncertainty   <score>/100\n512:   Context       <score>/100\n513: \n514: → Knowledge Gaps ─────────────────────────────────\n515:   <gap1>\n516:   <gap2>\n517: \n518: STATUS=OK ACTION=preflight\n519: ```\n520: \n521: #### Postflight\n522: \n523: **Trigger:** `/memory:search postflight <specFolder> <taskId>`\n524: \n525: Captures post-task epistemic state and calculates Learning Index. The `specFolder` and `taskId` must match a prior preflight record.\n526: \n527: **Learning Index:** `LI = (KnowledgeDelta × 0.4) + (UncertaintyReduction × 0.35) + (ContextImprovement × 0.25)`\n528: \n529: ##### Parameters\n530: \n531: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n532: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n533: | `specFolder` | string | Yes | Spec folder path (must match preflight) |\n534: | `taskId` | string | Yes | Task identifier (must match preflight) |\n535: | `knowledgeScore` | number | Yes | Post-task knowledge level 0-100 |\n536: | `uncertaintyScore` | number | Yes | Post-task uncertainty level 0-100 |\n537: | `contextScore` | number | Yes | Post-task context completeness 0-100 |\n538: | `gapsClosed` | string[] | No | Knowledge gaps closed during task |\n539: | `newGapsDiscovered` | string[] | No | New gaps discovered during task |\n540: \n541: ##### Learning Index Interpretation\n542: \n543: | Range | Meaning |\n544: |-------|---------|\n545: | 40+ | Significant learning |\n546: | 15-40 | Moderate learning |\n547: | 5-15 | Incremental learning |\n548: | <5 | Execution-focused (minimal learning) |\n549: | Negative | Regression, investigate |\n550: \n551: ##### Output\n552: \n553: ```text\n554: MEMORY:SEARCH POSTFLIGHT\n555: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n556: \n557:   Spec        <specFolder>\n558:   Task        <taskId>\n559: \n560: → Epistemic State (Final) ────────────────────────\n561:   Knowledge     <pre> → <post>  (Δ <delta>)\n562:   Uncertainty   <pre> → <post>  (Δ <delta>)\n563:   Context       <pre> → <post>  (Δ <delta>)\n564: \n565: → Learning Index ─────────────────────────────────\n566:   ████████░░  <LI>/10  (<interpretation>)\n567: \n568: → Gaps Closed ────────────────────────────────────\n569:   <gap1>\n570:   <gap2>\n571: \n572: STATUS=OK ACTION=postflight LI=<value>\n573: ```\n574: \n575: #### Learning History\n576: \n577: **Trigger:** `/memory:search history <specFolder>`\n578: \n579: View learning history (PREFLIGHT/POSTFLIGHT records) for a spec folder. Shows knowledge improvement deltas and Learning Index trends. Completes the epistemic lifecycle: capture (preflight) -> complete (postflight) -> review (history).\n580: \n581: ##### Parameters\n582: \n583: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n584: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n585: | `specFolder` | string | Yes | Spec folder path (e.g., `specs/007-auth`) |\n586: | `sessionId` | string | No | Filter by session ID |\n587: | `limit` | number | No | Maximum records (default: 10, max: 100) |\n588: | `onlyComplete` | boolean | No | Only return records with both PREFLIGHT and POSTFLIGHT (default: false) |\n589: | `includeSummary` | boolean | No | Include summary statistics and trends (default: true) |\n590: \n591: ##### Output\n592: \n593: ```text\n594: MEMORY:SEARCH HISTORY\n595: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n596: \n597:   Spec        <specFolder>\n598:   Records     <N>\n599: \n600: → Learning History ───────────────────────────────\n601:   <taskId>  K: <pre>→<post>  U: <pre>→<post>  C: <pre>→<post>  LI: <value>\n602:   <taskId>  K: <pre>→<post>  U: <pre>→<post>  C: <pre>→<post>  LI: <value>\n603: \n604: → Summary ────────────────────────────────────────\n605:   Avg LI      <value>\n606:   Trend       <improving|stable|declining>\n607: \n608: STATUS=OK ACTION=history\n609: ```\n610: \n611: ---\n612: \n613: ### 5B. Memory Causal Graph\n614: \n615: #### Causal Trace\n616: \n617: **Trigger:** `/memory:search causal <memoryId>`\n618: \n619: Traces the causal chain for a spec-doc record to answer \"why was this decision made?\" Traverses causal edges up to `maxDepth` hops.\n620: \n621: ##### Parameters\n622: \n623: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n624: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n625: | `memoryId` | number or string | Yes | Memory ID to trace |\n626: | `maxDepth` | number | No | Max traversal depth (default: 3, max: 10) |\n627: | `direction` | string | No | `outgoing`, `incoming`, or `both` (default: `both`) |\n628: | `relations` | string[] | No | Filter by: `caused`, `enabled`, `supersedes`, `contradicts`, `derived_from`, `supports` |\n629: | `includeMemoryDetails` | boolean | No | Include full spec-doc record details (default: true) |\n630: \n631: ##### Output\n632: \n633: ```text\n634: MEMORY:SEARCH CAUSAL\n635: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n636: \n637:   Record      #<id> \"<title>\"\n638:   Depth       <maxDepth>\n639:   Direction   <direction>\n640: \n641: → Causal Chain ───────────────────────────────────\n642:   #<id> \"<title>\"\n643:     ├─ caused → #<id2> \"<title2>\"\n644:     │   └─ enabled → #<id3> \"<title3>\"\n645:     └─ supersedes → #<id4> \"<title4>\"\n646: \n647: STATUS=OK ACTION=causal EDGES=<count>\n648: ```\n649: \n650: #### Causal Link\n651: \n652: **Trigger:** `/memory:search link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation>`\n653: \n654: Creates a causal relationship between two spec-doc records.\n655: \n656: ##### Parameters\n657: \n658: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n659: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n660: | `sourceId` | number or string | Yes | Source memory ID |\n661: | `targetId` | number or string | Yes | Target memory ID |\n662: | `relation` | string | Yes | `caused`, `enabled`, `supersedes`, `contradicts`, `derived_from`, `supports` |\n663: | `strength` | number | No | Relationship strength 0.0-1.0 (default: 1.0) |\n664: | `evidence` | string | No | Evidence or reason for the relationship |\n665: \n666: ##### Output\n667: \n668: ```text\n669: MEMORY:SEARCH LINK\n670: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n671: \n672:   Source      #<sourceId> \"<title>\"\n673:   Target      #<targetId> \"<title>\"\n674:   Relation    <relation>\n675:   Strength    <strength>\n676: \n677: STATUS=OK ACTION=link\n678: ```\n679: \n680: #### Causal Unlink\n681: \n682: **Trigger:** `/memory:search unlink <edgeId>`\n683: \n684: Removes a causal relationship by edge ID. Use `/memory:search causal <memoryId>` first to find edge IDs.\n685: \n686: ##### Parameters\n687: \n688: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n689: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n690: | `edgeId` | number | Yes | Edge ID to delete |\n691: \n692: ##### Output\n693: \n694: ```text\n695: MEMORY:SEARCH UNLINK\n696: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n697: \n698:   Removed     Edge #<edgeId>\n699: \n700: STATUS=OK ACTION=unlink\n701: ```\n702: \n703: #### Causal Stats\n704: \n705: **Trigger:** `/memory:search causal-stats`\n706: \n707: Shows statistics about the causal spec-doc graph. No parameters required.\n708: \n709: Target: 60% of spec-doc records linked (CHK-065).\n710: \n711: ##### Output\n712: \n713: ```text\n714: MEMORY:SEARCH CAUSAL-STATS\n715: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n716: \n717:   Total Edges     <N>\n718:   Coverage        <pct>% (<linked>/<total> spec-doc records)\n719: \n720: → By Relation ────────────────────────────────────\n721:   caused          ██████░░░░  <N>\n722:   enabled         ████░░░░░░  <N>\n723:   supersedes      ██░░░░░░░░  <N>\n724:   contradicts     █░░░░░░░░░  <N>\n725:   derived_from    ███░░░░░░░  <N>\n726:   supports        █████░░░░░  <N>\n727: \n728: STATUS=OK ACTION=causal-stats COVERAGE=<pct>%\n729: ```\n730: \n731: ---\n732: \n733: ### 5C. Evaluation\n734: \n735: #### Ablation Study\n736: \n737: **Trigger:** `/memory:search ablation`\n738: \n739: Runs a controlled channel ablation study (R13-S3). Requires `SPECKIT_ABLATION=true` environment variable.\n740: \n741: ##### Parameters\n742: \n743: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n744: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n745: | `mode` | string | No | Evaluation mode. Defaults to `ablation`; use `k_sensitivity` for raw pre-fusion RRF K analysis |\n746: | `channels` | string[] | No | Channels to ablate: `vector`, `bm25`, `fts5`, `graph`, `trigger` (default: all) |\n747: | `groundTruthQueryIds` | number[] | No | Subset of ground truth query IDs to evaluate |\n748: | `recallK` | number | No | Recall cutoff K (default: 20) |\n749: | `storeResults` | boolean | No | Persist metrics to eval_metric_snapshots (default: true) |\n750: | `includeFormattedReport` | boolean | No | Include human-readable markdown report (default: true) |\n751: \n752: ##### Behavior Notes\n753: \n754: - Missing `groundTruthQueryIds` now produce a warning and the run continues with the remaining IDs that exist in the static dataset.\n755: - If the report includes `Token budget overflow` and fewer than `recallK` candidates were evaluated, treat the run as investigation-only rather than a reliable Recall@K verdict.\n756: - After a DB rebuild or eval DB swap, rerun `scripts/evals/map-ground-truth-ids.ts` before comparing baselines or channel deltas.\n757: \n758: ##### Output\n759: \n760: ```text\n761: MEMORY:SEARCH ABLATION\n762: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n763: \n764: → Recall@<K> Deltas ──────────────────────────────\n765:   -vector     Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n766:   -bm25       Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n767:   -fts5       Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n768:   -graph      Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n769:   -trigger    Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n770: \n771:   Stored      <yes|no>\n772: \n773: STATUS=OK ACTION=ablation\n774: ```\n775: \n776: #### Reporting Dashboard\n777: \n778: **Trigger:** `/memory:search dashboard`\n779: \n780: Generates R13-S3 reporting dashboard output with sprint/channel trend aggregation.\n781: \n782: ##### Parameters\n783: \n784: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n785: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n786: | `sprintFilter` | string[] | No | Sprint label filters |\n787: | `channelFilter` | string[] | No | Channel filters |\n788: | `metricFilter` | string[] | No | Metric-name filters |\n789: | `limit` | number | No | Max sprint groups to return |\n790: | `format` | string | No | `text` (default) or `json` |\n791: \n792: ##### Output\n793: \n794: ```text\n795: MEMORY:SEARCH DASHBOARD\n796: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n797: \n798: → Sprint Trends ──────────────────────────────────\n799:   <sprint>    Recall@20: <value>  MRR: <value>\n800:   <sprint>    Recall@20: <value>  MRR: <value>\n801: \n802: → Channel Performance ───────────────────────────\n803:   vector      ████████░░  <value>\n804:   bm25        ██████░░░░  <value>\n805:   fts5        █████░░░░░  <value>\n806: \n807: STATUS=OK ACTION=dashboard\n808: ```\n809: \n810: ---\n811: \n812: ## 6. ERROR HANDLING\n813: \n814: | Condition | Response |\n815: |-----------|----------|\n816: | Query empty | Ask user for query or subcommand (see gate at top) |\n817: | Intent invalid | Default to 'understand' with warning |\n818: | No results | Suggest broader query or different intent |\n819: | Search fails | Fall back to unweighted search |\n820: | Unknown subcommand | `STATUS=FAIL`, list valid subcommands |\n821: | Missing required parameter | `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Missing <param> for <subcommand>\"` |\n822: | Preflight/postflight specFolder mismatch | `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"specFolder must match preflight record\"` |\n823: | SPECKIT_ABLATION not enabled | `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Requires SPECKIT_ABLATION=true\"` |\n824: | Ablation warns about missing IDs | Continue with available IDs, then correct `groundTruthQueryIds` or rerun `scripts/evals/map-ground-truth-ids.ts` |\n825: | Ablation reports `Token budget overflow` below `recallK` | Report the run as investigation-only and fix truncation before using Recall@K as evidence |\n826: | No causal edges found | Display empty graph message |\n827: | Spec-doc record ID not found | `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Memory #<id> not found\"` (runtime string preserved verbatim) |\n828: | No learning history records | Suggest using `preflight` before tasks |\n829: \n830: ---\n831: \n832: ## 7. RELATED COMMANDS\n833: \n834: - `/memory:save`: Save conversation context\n835: - `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest\n836: - `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules\n837: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation\n838: \n839: ---\n840: <!-- APPENDIX: Reference material for AI agent implementation -->\n841: \n842: ## APPENDIX A: MCP TOOL REFERENCE\n843: \n844: **CRITICAL:** Use the correct MCP tools for each step. This command owns 13 tools across L1, L2, L6, and L7 layers.\n845: \n846: ### Enforcement Matrix\n847: \n848: | MODE | REQUIRED CALLS | PATTERN | ON FAILURE |\n849: |------|----------------|---------|------------|\n850: | RETRIEVAL (default) | | | |\n851: | Intent detect | Parse query, match keywords | LOCAL | Default to 'understand' |\n852: | Context (preferred) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({ input, ... })` | SINGLE | Fall back to manual search |\n853: | Quick search (optional) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search({ query, ... })` | SINGLE | Fall back to preferred/manual retrieval |\n854: | Trigger check | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers({ prompt: query })` | OPTIONAL | Continue without |\n855: | Search (manual) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search({ query, anchors, includeContent: true })` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n856: | ANALYSIS | | | |\n857: | Preflight | `task_preflight()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n858: | Postflight | `task_postflight()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n859: | Memory causal trace | `memory_drift_why()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n860: | Memory causal link | `memory_causal_link()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n861: | Memory causal unlink | `memory_causal_unlink()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n862: | Memory causal stats | `memory_causal_stats()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n863: | Ablation | `eval_run_ablation()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n864: | Dashboard | `eval_reporting_dashboard()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n865: | History | `memory_get_learning_history()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n866: \n867: ### Tool Signatures\n868: \n869: > **Note:** The dedicated `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context()` tool provides unified intent-aware retrieval server-side. It accepts `input`, `mode`, `intent`, `specFolder`, governed retrieval params (`tenantId`, `userId`, `agentId`), `limit`, `sessionId`, `enableDedup`, `includeContent`, `includeTrace`, `tokenUsage`, and `anchors`. `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search()` also supports governed retrieval via `tenantId`, `userId`, and `agentId`. This is the recommended unified approach. The manual orchestration below is for advanced use cases requiring fine-grained control.\n870: \n871: > **Adaptive Fusion, Hybrid Routing & Telemetry:** Retrieval combines vector, FTS5/BM25, and structural code graph channels, then applies intent-adaptive fusion and reranking. Results may be routed through artifact-class classification before scoring. When `SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION` is enabled, weights adapt dynamically by intent, including the internal continuity profile (`0.52 / 0.18 / 0.07 / 0.23`) used for resume-style retrieval. When `SPECKIT_EXTENDED_TELEMETRY` is enabled, extended telemetry is captured (query timing, score distributions, fusion decisions) and written to the telemetry log.\n872: >\n873: > **MMR and Evidence Gap Prevention:** Post-fusion MMR reduces redundant context chunks, and low-confidence retrieval can trigger an early evidence-gap warning so sparse results are treated cautiously.\n874: \n875: ```javascript\n876: // ─── Retrieval tools ───────────────────────────────────────────\n877: \n878: // Option 1: Dedicated context tool (preferred - single call)\n879: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({\n880:   input: \"<query>\",\n881:   intent: \"<add_feature|fix_bug|refactor|security_audit|understand|find_spec|find_decision>\",  // Optional, auto-detected if omitted\n882:   specFolder: \"<folder>\",  // Optional\n883:   tenantId: \"<tenant-id>\", // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n884:   userId: \"<user-id>\",     // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n885:   agentId: \"<agent-id>\",   // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n886:   includeContent: true,\n887:   anchors: [\"<anchor1>\", \"<anchor2>\"],  // Intent-specific\n888: })\n889: \n890: // Option 2: Simplified search for fast query-only retrieval\n891: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search({\n892:   query: \"<query>\",\n893:   limit: 10,                // Optional\n894:   specFolder: \"<folder>\",   // Optional\n895:   tenantId: \"<tenant-id>\",  // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n896:   userId: \"<user-id>\",      // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n897:   agentId: \"<agent-id>\",    // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n898: })\n899: \n900: // Option 3: Manual search with anchors (advanced - fine-grained control)\n901: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search({\n902:   query: \"<query>\",\n903:   anchors: [\"<anchor1>\", \"<anchor2>\", ...],  // Intent-specific\n904:   limit: 10,\n905:   includeContent: true,  // Single call, no separate load\n906:   useDecay: true,\n907:   contextType: \"<type>\",  // e.g., \"implementation\", \"decision\"\n908: })\n909: \n910: // ─── Analysis tools ───────────────────────────────────────────\n911: \n912: // Epistemic measurement\n913: mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight({ specFolder, taskId, knowledgeScore, uncertaintyScore, contextScore, knowledgeGaps, sessionId })\n914: mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight({ specFolder, taskId, knowledgeScore, uncertaintyScore, contextScore, gapsClosed, newGapsDiscovered })\n915: \n916: // Memory causal graph\n917: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why({ memoryId, maxDepth, direction, relations, includeMemoryDetails })\n918: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link({ sourceId, targetId, relation, strength, evidence })\n919: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink({ edgeId })\n920: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats({})\n921: \n922: // Evaluation\n923: mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation({ mode: \"ablation\", channels, groundTruthQueryIds, recallK, storeResults: true, includeFormattedReport: true })\n924: mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard({ sprintFilter, channelFilter, metricFilter, limit, format })\n925: mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history({ specFolder, sessionId, limit, onlyComplete, includeSummary })\n926: ```\n927: \n928: ### Tool Coverage\n929: \n930: | # | Tool | Layer | Mode | Subcommand |\n931: |---|------|-------|------|------------|\n932: | 1 | `memory_context` | L1 | Retrieval | (default) |\n933: | 2 | `memory_quick_search` | L2 | Retrieval | (default) |\n934: | 3 | `memory_search` | L2 | Retrieval | (default) |\n935: | 4 | `memory_match_triggers` | L2 | Retrieval | (default) |\n936: | 5 | `task_preflight` | L6 | Analysis | `preflight` |\n937: | 6 | `task_postflight` | L6 | Analysis | `postflight` |\n938: | 7 | `memory_drift_why` | L6 | Analysis | `causal` |\n939: | 8 | `memory_causal_link` | L6 | Analysis | `link` |\n940: | 9 | `memory_causal_stats` | L6 | Analysis | `causal-stats` |\n941: | 10 | `memory_causal_unlink` | L6 | Analysis | `unlink` |\n942: | 11 | `eval_run_ablation` | L6 | Analysis | `ablation` |\n943: | 12 | `eval_reporting_dashboard` | L6 | Analysis | `dashboard` |\n944: | 13 | `memory_get_learning_history` | L7 | Analysis | `history` |\n945: \n946: ---\n947: \n948: ## APPENDIX B: ADVANCED PARAMETERS\n949: \n950: ### memory_context: Full Parameters\n951: \n952: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n953: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n954: | `input` | string | *required* | Query, prompt, or context description |\n955: | `mode` | string | `auto` | `auto`, `quick`, `deep`, `focused`, `resume` |\n956: | `intent` | string | auto-detect | `add_feature`, `fix_bug`, `refactor`, `security_audit`, `understand`, `find_spec`, `find_decision` |\n957: | `specFolder` | string | - | Limit context to specific spec folder |\n958: | `limit` | number | mode-specific | Maximum results (1-100) |\n959: | `sessionId` | string | ephemeral | Caller-supplied session identifier |\n960: | `enableDedup` | boolean | true | Enable session deduplication |\n961: | `includeContent` | boolean | false | Include full file content in results |\n962: | `includeTrace` | boolean | false | Include provenance-rich trace data (scores, source, trace) in results when underlying `memory_search` is called |\n963: | `tokenUsage` | number | - | Caller token usage ratio (0.0-1.0). Helps the server budget-aware pruning when the caller is near context limits |\n964: | `anchors` | string[] | - | Filter content to specific anchors (e.g., `[\"state\", \"next-steps\"]` for resume mode) |\n965: \n966: ### memory_search: Advanced Parameters\n967: \n968: The full `memory_search` parameter surface is available when using Option 3 (manual search). Key advanced parameters:\n969: \n970: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n971: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n972: | `query` | string | - | Natural language search query (required unless `concepts` provided) |\n973: | `concepts` | string[] | - | 2-5 concept strings for multi-concept AND search (required unless `query` provided) |\n974: | `specFolder` | string | - | Limit search to specific spec folder |\n975: | `tier` | string | - | Filter by importance tier |\n976: | `contextType` | string | - | Filter by context type |\n977: | `useDecay` | boolean | true | Apply temporal decay scoring |\n978: | `includeContiguity` | boolean | false | Include adjacent/contiguous spec-doc records |\n979: | `includeConstitutional` | boolean | true | Include constitutional-tier spec-doc records at top |\n980: | `enableSessionBoost` | boolean | env flag | Enable session-based score boost from working_memory attention signals |\n981: | `enableCausalBoost` | boolean | env flag | Enable causal-neighbor boost (2-hop traversal on causal_edges) |\n982: | `min_quality_score` | number | - | Minimum quality score threshold (0.0-1.0) |\n983: | `minQualityScore` | number | - | **Deprecated alias** for `min_quality_score`. Prefer the snake_case parameter name |\n984: | `bypassCache` | boolean | false | Skip tool cache and force fresh search |\n985: | `rerank` | boolean | true | Enable MMR diversity reranking |\n986: | `applyLengthPenalty` | boolean | true | Compatibility-only length-penalty option; always resolves to a neutral `1.0` multiplier |\n987: | `applyStateLimits` | boolean | false | Enforce per-tier quantity limits for result diversity |\n988: | `minState` | string | `WARM` | Minimum active spec-doc state: `HOT`, `WARM`, `COLD`, `DORMANT` |\n989: | `autoDetectIntent` | boolean | true | Auto-detect intent from query if not explicitly set |\n990: | `trackAccess` | boolean | false | Write FSRS strengthening updates on read (off by default to avoid write-on-read) |\n991: | `mode` | string | `auto` | `auto` (standard) or `deep` (multi-query expansion). Note: deep mode does not guarantee expansion for simple queries |\n992: | `includeTrace` | boolean | false | Include provenance-rich scores/source/trace fields in each result |\n993: \n994: > **Governance scoping:** `tenantId`, `userId`, and `agentId` are advertised in the tool schema for governed retrieval. When scope enforcement is active, results are isolated to the specified boundaries.\n995: \n996: ### memory_match_triggers: Cognitive Parameters\n997: \n998: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n999: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n1000: | `prompt` | string | *required* | User prompt or text to match against trigger phrases |\n1001: | `limit` | number | 3 | Maximum matching spec-doc records to return |\n1002: | `session_id` | string | - | Session identifier for cognitive features. Enables attention decay and tiered content injection |\n1003: | `turnNumber` | number | - | Current conversation turn number. Used with `session_id` for decay calculations |\n1004: | `include_cognitive` | boolean | true | Enable cognitive features (decay, tiers, co-activation). Requires `session_id` |\n1005: \n1006: When cognitive features are enabled (`session_id` + `include_cognitive`), trigger matching uses attention-based decay and tiered content injection: HOT spec-doc records return full content, WARM spec-doc records return summaries, with co-activation of related spec-doc records.\n1007: \n1008: ---\n1009: \n1010: ## 8. ANALYSIS OVERVIEW DASHBOARD\n1011: \n1012: When the user selects \"Analysis tools\" from the empty-arguments prompt, or when context warrants showing available analysis capabilities:\n1013: \n1014: ```text\n1015: MEMORY:SEARCH - ANALYSIS TOOLS\n1016: ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n1017: \n1018: → Available Subcommands ──────────────────────────\n1019: \n1020:   Epistemic Measurement\n1021:   [preflight]   Capture knowledge baseline before task\n1022:   [postflight]  Capture post-task state and learning delta\n1023:   [history]     View learning history for a spec folder\n1024: \n1025:   Memory Causal Graph\n1026:   [causal]        Trace decision lineage for a spec-doc record\n1027:   [link]          Create causal relationship\n1028:   [unlink]        Remove causal relationship\n1029:   [causal-stats]  View memory causal graph coverage statistics\n1030: \n1031:   Evaluation\n1032:   [ablation]    Run channel ablation study\n1033:   [dashboard]   View reporting dashboard\n1034: \n1035: STATUS=OK ACTION=overview\n1036: ```\n\n(End of file - total 1036 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\nargument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n---\n\n> **Code Graph bridge:** Structural routing may call stable `code_graph_*` MCP tools; the code-graph implementation and docs are owned by `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n# 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, CHECK `$ARGUMENTS`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n    → Present the user with this question:\n        question: \"What would you like to retrieve context for?\"\n        options:\n          - label: \"Add feature\"\n            description: \"Context for implementing a new feature\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md","text":"---\ndescription: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\nargument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n---\n\n> **Code Graph bridge:** Structural routing may call stable `code_graph_*` MCP tools; the code-graph implementation and docs are owned by `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n# 🚨 MANDATORY FIRST ACTION - DO NOT SKIP\n\n**BEFORE READING ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS FILE, CHECK `$ARGUMENTS`:**\n\n```text\nIF $ARGUMENTS is empty, undefined, or contains only whitespace:\n    → STOP IMMEDIATELY\n    → Present the user with this question:\n        question: \"What would you like to retrieve context for?\"\n        options:\n          - label: \"Add feature\"\n            description: \"Context for implementing a new feature\"\n          - label: \"Fix bug\"\n            description: \"Context for debugging and fixing an issue\"\n          - label: \"Refactor\"\n            description: \"Context for code restructuring\"\n          - label: \"Security audit\"\n            description: \"Context for security review\"\n          - label: \"Understand\"\n            description: \"Context for learning existing code\"\n          - label: \"Find spec\"\n            description: \"Context for spec document retrieval\"\n          - label: \"Find decision\"\n            description: \"Context for decision rationale lookup\"\n          - label: \"Analysis tools\"\n            description: \"Epistemic baselines, memory causal graph, ablation, dashboards\"\n    → WAIT for user response\n    → If \"Analysis tools\" selected → Display ANALYSIS OVERVIEW (Section 8)\n    → Otherwise → Use their response to determine the intent and query\n    → If the AskUserQuestion response is a custom answer rather than one of the listed options,\n      treat that custom answer as the literal retrieval query and route it through RETRIEVAL MODE\n    → Only THEN continue with this workflow\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS starts with a KNOWN ANALYSIS SUBCOMMAND (Section 3):\n    → Route to ANALYSIS MODE (Section 5)\n\nIF $ARGUMENTS contains a query (any other text):\n    → Route to RETRIEVAL MODE (Section 4)\n```\n\n**CRITICAL RULES:**\n- **DO NOT** infer query from conversation context\n- **DO NOT** assume the user's intent without explicit input\n- **DO NOT** proceed past this point without explicit query from user\n- The query and intent MUST come from `$ARGUMENTS` or user's answer above\n\n---\n\n# Memory Search Command\n\nUnified entry point for knowledge retrieval and analysis. Combines intent-aware context search (retrieval mode) with epistemic measurement, memory causal graph tools, and evaluation dashboards (analysis mode).\n\n---\n\n## 0. INSTRUCTIONS\n\nStart by classifying `$ARGUMENTS` into retrieval mode or analysis mode. Follow the routing contract below, prefer canonical packet sources in retrieval mode, and only invoke the analysis subcommands that match the user's explicit request.\n\n---\n\n```yaml\nrole: Retrieval & Analysis Specialist\npurpose: Unified entry point combining intent-aware retrieval with epistemic measurement, memory causal graph, and evaluation tools\naction: Route through retrieval or analysis mode based on argument pattern\n\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: argument_routing\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  approvals: none_required\n  tracking: intent_classification\n```\n\nThis is a markdown-owned command contract. `/memory:*` commands intentionally do\nnot have external YAML assets; validators and reviewers should check the inline\noperating-mode block and markdown workflow steps.\n\n---\n\n## 1. PURPOSE\n\n> **L1 Orchestration + L6 Analysis**: This command operates at both the L1 retrieval layer (orchestrating lower-level context-retrieval operations) and the L6 analysis layer (epistemic baselines, memory causal graph, evaluation). It provides a single entry point for all knowledge-related context-retrieval operations.\n\nProvide a unified entry point that:\n\n**Retrieval mode** (default):\n- Automatically detects task intent from the query\n- Applies task-specific weights for search optimization\n- Combines search + load in a single operation\n- Returns context with relevance explanation\n- Enforces L1 token budget constraints (target: ~2000 tokens per call)\n- Handles session deduplication for cross-session queries\n- Targets canonical packet sources first: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, then the packet spec docs\n\n**Analysis mode** (subcommand-triggered):\n- Epistemic measurement: Capture knowledge baselines before and after tasks (`task_preflight`, `task_postflight`)\n- Memory causal graph: Trace decision lineage, create/remove causal links, view graph stats (`memory_drift_why`, `memory_causal_link`, `memory_causal_unlink`, `memory_causal_stats`)\n- Evaluation: Run channel ablation studies and view reporting dashboards (`eval_run_ablation`, `eval_reporting_dashboard`)\n- Learning history: View PREFLIGHT/POSTFLIGHT records and Learning Index trends (`memory_get_learning_history`)\n\n**Lifecycle note:** Retrieval does not delete expired records. Use `/memory:manage retention-sweep` for the `memory_retention_sweep` tool when governed records need retention cleanup (`tool-schemas.ts:330`).\n\n### Hybrid Retrieval Runtime (Retrieval Mode)\n\nThe unified context tool runs a hybrid retrieval pipeline with **graph-first routing** (026):\n\n- **Structural code graph channel has priority** in the fusion strategy: structural queries (callers, imports, dependencies) are routed to `code_graph_query` first, before semantic or lexical channels\n- Tri-channel retrieval (graph + vector/semantic + FTS5/BM25) with graph results given precedence in the fusion merge\n- Code Graph structural queries plus exact-text Grep integrates as the vector/semantic channel, providing natural-language code discovery alongside indexed-continuity vector search\n- When graph and semantic channels miss or return weak results, a 3-tier FTS fallback activates: FTS5 full-text → BM25 keyword scoring → Grep/Glob filesystem search. Post-026 FTS5 remediation improved BM25 tokenization and ranking accuracy\n- Intent-adaptive fusion and reranking (weights adapt when `SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION` is enabled, including the internal continuity profile: semantic `0.52`, keyword `0.18`, recency `0.07`, graph `0.23`)\n- MMR diversity pruning to reduce redundant chunks, with continuity-oriented Stage 3 passes using a dedicated lambda of `0.65`\n- Stage 3 applies MMR diversity reranking plus MPAB chunk collapse; `applyLengthPenalty` remains on the API surface for compatibility but currently resolves to a neutral `1.0` multiplier for every document\n- Deep-mode query expansion for broader lexical coverage\n- Evidence-gap detection (026) to flag low-confidence retrievals with explicit gap warnings, enabling downstream reasoning to remain cautious and avoid acting on sparse evidence\n\n### Canonical Retrieval Order\n\n- `/speckit:resume` is the recovery surface for session continuation.\n- Resume-oriented retrieval follows `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`.\n- Packet-oriented retrieval may additionally use indexed `document_type='graph_metadata'` rows for dependency, supersession, related-packet, and key-file signals.\n- `find_spec` and `find_decision` should resolve against canonical spec docs and anchors, not against standalone continuity artifacts.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONTRACT\n\n**Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS`: Query with optional intent override, OR analysis subcommand with parameters\n**Outputs:** Context with relevance scores and intent explanation, OR `STATUS=<OK|FAIL>` with subcommand-specific output\n\n---\n\n## 3. QUICK REFERENCE\n\n### Retrieval Mode (default)\n\n| Command | Result |\n|---------|--------|\n| `/memory:search \"implement auth\"` | Auto-detect add_feature, apply weights |\n| `/memory:search \"auth bug\" --intent:fix_bug` | Explicit fix_bug intent |\n| `/memory:search \"how does auth work?\"` | Auto-detect understand intent |\n| `/memory:search \"optimize auth code\"` | Auto-detect refactor intent |\n| `/memory:search \"auth security review\"` | Auto-detect security_audit intent |\n| `/memory:search \"find the spec for auth\"` | Auto-detect find_spec intent |\n| `/memory:search \"why did we choose JWT\"` | Auto-detect find_decision intent |\n\n### Analysis Mode (subcommand-triggered)\n\n| Command | Result |\n|---------|--------|\n| `/memory:search preflight specs/007-auth T1` | Capture epistemic baseline |\n| `/memory:search postflight specs/007-auth T1` | Calculate learning delta |\n| `/memory:search history specs/007-auth` | View learning history |\n| `/memory:search causal 42` | Trace causal chain for memory #42 |\n| `/memory:search link 42 43 caused` | Link memory #42 → #43 as caused |\n| `/memory:search unlink 5` | Remove causal edge #5 |\n| `/memory:search causal-stats` | View memory causal graph statistics |\n| `/memory:search ablation` | Run channel ablation study |\n| `/memory:search dashboard` | View reporting dashboard |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ARGUMENT ROUTING\n\n```text\n$ARGUMENTS\n    │\n    ├─ Empty (no args)                        → INTERACTIVE PROMPT (see gate above)\n    │\n    ├─ ANALYSIS SUBCOMMAND DETECTED?\n    │   First token matches one of:\n    │   \"preflight\", \"postflight\", \"history\",\n    │   \"causal\", \"link\", \"unlink\",\n    │   \"causal-stats\", \"ablation\", \"dashboard\"\n    │   └─► YES → ANALYSIS MODE (Section 5)\n    │\n    └─ OTHERWISE (any other text)\n        └─► RETRIEVAL MODE (Section 4A)\n            Parse: <query> [--intent:<type>]\n```\n\n**Routing logic:** If the first argument token exactly matches a known analysis subcommand keyword → route to analysis mode. Otherwise → treat entire input as a retrieval query (with optional `--intent:` flag).\n\n---\n\n<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<!-- SECTION 4A: RETRIEVAL MODE                                     -->\n<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n\n## 4A. RETRIEVAL MODE\n\n### Intent Types and Weights\n\n#### Intent Classification\n\nThe system detects one of seven intent types:\n\n| Intent Type | Description | Weight Adjustments |\n|-------------|-------------|--------------------|\n| **add_feature** | Implementing new functionality | implementation: 1.5x, architecture: 1.3x, patterns: 1.2x |\n| **fix_bug** | Debugging and fixing issues | decisions: 1.4x, implementation: 1.3x, errors: 1.5x |\n| **refactor** | Code restructuring | architecture: 1.5x, patterns: 1.4x, decisions: 1.2x |\n| **security_audit** | Security review | decisions: 1.4x, implementation: 1.3x, security: 1.5x |\n| **understand** | Learning existing code | architecture: 1.4x, decisions: 1.3x, overview: 1.5x |\n| **find_spec** | Canonical spec document retrieval | spec-doc: 1.5x, architecture: 1.3x, overview: 1.2x |\n| **find_decision** | Decision rationale lookup from canonical docs | decisions: 1.5x, rationale: 1.4x, architecture: 1.2x |\n\n#### Detection Logic\n\nIntent is detected via keyword matching against the query. Keywords are phrase-based to avoid false positives:\n\n| Intent | Keywords |\n|--------|----------|\n| `add_feature` | 'implement', 'add feature', 'add new', 'add a', 'create new', 'build new' |\n| `fix_bug` | 'bug', 'error', 'fix', 'broken', 'issue', 'debug' |\n| `refactor` | 'refactor', 'restructure', 'improve', 'clean up', 'optimize' |\n| `security_audit` | 'security', 'vulnerability', 'auth', 'sanitize', 'xss', 'csrf' |\n| `understand` | 'how', 'why', 'what', 'explain', 'understand', 'learn' |\n| `find_spec` | 'spec', 'specification', 'spec folder', 'spec document', 'find spec' |\n| `find_decision` | 'decision', 'rationale', 'why did we', 'chose', 'decision record' |\n\n**Default fallback:** If no keywords match, defaults to `understand`.\n\n#### Anchor Mapping by Intent\n\n| Intent | Primary Anchors | Secondary Anchors | Why These? |\n|--------|----------------|-------------------|------------|\n| **add_feature** | implementation, architecture, patterns | decisions, code-examples | Need existing patterns + structure |\n| **fix_bug** | decisions, implementation, errors | debugging, troubleshooting | Need decision history + error context |\n| **refactor** | architecture, patterns, decisions | technical-specs, code-quality | Need structure understanding + rationale |\n| **security_audit** | decisions, implementation, security | validation, auth, sanitization | Need security decisions + validation patterns |\n| **understand** | architecture, decisions, summary | overview, context, background | Need high-level understanding first |\n| **find_spec** | spec-doc, architecture, overview | specification, structure | Need canonical spec document content + structure |\n| **find_decision** | decisions, rationale, architecture | context, background, history | Need decision records and rationale from canonical docs |\n\n#### Example: add_feature Intent\n\n```text\nQuery: \"implement oauth token refresh\"\nIntent: add_feature (detected)\n\nAnchors Selected:\n  1. implementation (1.5x weight)\n  2. architecture (1.3x weight)\n  3. patterns (1.2x weight)\n\nReasoning:\n  - Need existing OAuth implementation patterns\n  - Need architecture understanding for integration points\n  - Need code examples for token handling\n```\n\n### Retrieval Workflow\n\n#### Step 1: Parse Query and Detect Intent\n\n```text\nInput: $ARGUMENTS\n    ↓\nExtract Query + Intent Override (if --intent: flag)\n    ↓\nIF intent override provided:\n    → Use explicit intent\nELSE:\n    → Auto-detect via keyword matching\n    ↓\nStore: query, intent\n```\n\n#### Step 2: Apply Intent-Specific Weights\n\n```text\nBased on detected intent:\n    ↓\nSelect appropriate anchors:\n    - add_feature: ['implementation', 'architecture', 'patterns']\n    - fix_bug: ['decisions', 'implementation', 'errors', 'debugging']\n    - refactor: ['architecture', 'patterns', 'decisions']\n    - security_audit: ['decisions', 'implementation', 'security']\n    - understand: ['architecture', 'decisions', 'summary', 'overview']\n    - find_spec: ['spec-doc', 'architecture', 'overview', 'specification']\n    - find_decision: ['decisions', 'rationale', 'architecture', 'context']\n    ↓\nAdjust search parameters:\n    - Weight boost for relevant context types\n    - Anchor filtering for targeted retrieval\n```\n\n#### Step 3: Execute Search with Optimizations\n\n```javascript\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({\n  input: query,\n  intent: intent,\n  mode: \"auto\",                 // use \"deep\" for expanded multi-query retrieval\n  anchors: intentAnchors[intent],\n  limit: 10,\n  includeContent: true,\n  enableDedup: true\n});\n```\n\n#### Step 4: Return Context with Explanation\n\nFormat response:\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH  \"<query>\"  <detected-intent>  <N> found\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  <leaf-folder>/\n    <score>  #<id>  <title>\n\n  <leaf-folder>/\n    <score>  #<id>  <title>\n    <score>  #<id>  <title>\n    <score>  #<id>  <title>\n\n  <leaf-folder>/\n    <score>  #<id>  <title>\n    <score>  #<id>  <title>\n\nSTATUS=OK RESULTS=<count>\n```\n\n**Folder display rules:**\n- Results grouped by spec folder\n- **Leaf folder name only** as group header (last path segment, e.g., `010-search-retrieval-quality-fixes/`)\n- Drop all parent path prefixes (`system-spec-kit/023-esm-module-compliance/` etc.)\n- Top-level folders (like `system-spec-kit/`) shown as-is\n- If two leaf names collide, prefix with parent number: `023/010-search-quality/`\n- Results indented under their folder group\n- Each result shows only: score, ID, title\n- No other metadata (no type, bars, previews, weights, or token budget)\n\n#### Step 4b: Empty-Results Fallback (RESULTS=0 with TRIGGERED>0 or CONSTITUTIONAL>0)\n\nWhen semantic + lexical search return zero direct matches but the trigger-phrase matcher OR constitutional-rule surfacer returned spec-doc records, render them under explicit canonical labels — never invent ad-hoc wording like \"Auto-triggered memories\":\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH  \"<query>\"  <detected-intent>  0 found\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\nNo spec-doc records matched this query via semantic or lexical search.\n\nTrigger-matched spec-doc records (matched on phrase \"<keyword>\"):\n  <leaf-folder>/\n    #<id>  <title>\n  <leaf-folder>/\n    #<id>  <title>\n\nConstitutional rules (always-surface tier):\n  #<id>  <title>\n\nSTATUS=OK  RESULTS=0  TRIGGERED=<n>  CONSTITUTIONAL=<n>\n```\n\n**Vocabulary rules for this fallback:**\n- Use `Trigger-matched spec-doc records` — NOT `Auto-triggered memories`, `Triggered memories`, or `Memories`\n- Use `Constitutional rules` — NOT `Constitutional memories`\n- The phrase that triggered the match is shown in quotes in the section heading\n- Drop the score column (trigger matches are categorical, not scored)\n- After the formatted output, the assistant MAY ask one clarifying follow-up question if the query was ambiguous (≤2 lines), but the canonical block above must come first.\n\n##### Forbidden Phrase Enforcement (REQ-003 / Cluster 3)\n\nThe following phrases MUST NOT appear anywhere in any `/memory:search` rendering — empty-result fallback, full-result render, or analysis subcommand output. This list is authoritative; treat any occurrence as a P0 contract violation.\n\n| Forbidden Phrase | Required Replacement |\n|------------------|---------------------|\n| `Auto-triggered memories` | `Trigger-matched spec-doc records` |\n| `Auto-triggered memory` | `Trigger-matched spec-doc record` |\n| `Triggered memories` | `Trigger-matched spec-doc records` |\n| `Triggered memory` | `Trigger-matched spec-doc record` |\n| `Memories` (as a section header on its own) | `Spec-doc records` |\n| `Memory` (as a result-class label) | `Spec-doc record` |\n| `Constitutional memories` | `Constitutional rules` |\n| `Constitutional memory` | `Constitutional rule` |\n| `auto-triggered` (any case) | `trigger-matched` |\n\nPre-render gate (assistant MUST run before emitting the response block):\n1. Build the candidate output text.\n2. Case-insensitively scan for every forbidden phrase above.\n3. On any match: rewrite using the replacement column. Do not emit the original.\n4. After rewrite, verify the candidate is greppable-clean for the forbidden list.\n\nVerification (regression-safe):\n- `grep -Eci 'auto-triggered|triggered memories|triggered memory|constitutional memor(y|ies)'` against the rendered block MUST return `0`.\n- The rendered block uses only `Trigger-matched spec-doc records`, `Constitutional rules`, and `Spec-doc record(s)` for these concepts.\n\n### Token Budget Enforcement\n\n**memory_context L1 Budget:** ~2000 tokens total (mode-managed)\n\n#### Budget Guidance by Mode\n\n| Mode | Target Budget | Typical Use |\n|------|---------------|-------------|\n| `quick` | ~800 | Fast trigger/context lookup |\n| `focused` | ~1500 | Intent-optimized retrieval (`fix_bug`, etc.) |\n| `resume` | ~1200 | Session recovery (`state`, `next-steps`) |\n| `deep` | ~2000 | Broader context for complex work |\n| `auto` | mode-routed | Server selects mode from detected intent |\n\n#### Truncation Logic\n\nWhen results exceed token budget:\n1. Sort results by intent-specific relevance score\n2. Include results until budget reached\n3. If last result causes overage but >90% budget used, truncate to fit remaining budget\n4. Output includes: `Token Budget: ~<tokens> / <budget> tokens (<percentage>% used)` and `Truncation: <none|partial|significant>`\n\n### Session Deduplication\n\n#### Purpose\n\nPrevent duplicate context when the same query spans multiple sessions or when overlapping sessions contain redundant information.\n\n#### Strategy\n\n- Content hashing: Each result is hashed; duplicates with same hash are merged (keeping most recent version)\n- Cross-session detection via `sessionId` metadata and content hash comparison\n- Timestamp-based recency preference when duplicates found\n- When the caller omits `sessionId`, the server uses a memory-specific runtime session identifier for `memory_context`; this keeps trigger and constitutional channel dedup stable within the MCP process without broadening global session state.\n- Dedup applies to standard retrieval results, trigger-derived context, and constitutional-tier injections before the response is budgeted.\n\n#### Deduplication Metadata\n\nWhen deduplication occurs, the response includes:\n\n```yaml\ndeduplication:\n  enabled: true\n  original_count: <N>\n  deduplicated_count: <M>\n  duplicates_removed: <N - M>\n  session_dedup_applied: true\n```\n\n---\n\n<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<!-- SECTION 5: ANALYSIS MODE                                       -->\n<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n\n## 5. ANALYSIS MODE\n\n### Analysis Subcommand Routing\n\n```text\n$ARGUMENTS (first token is a known subcommand)\n    │\n    ├─ \"preflight <specFolder> <taskId>\"      → EPISTEMIC MEASUREMENT (Section 5A)\n    ├─ \"postflight <specFolder> <taskId>\"     → EPISTEMIC MEASUREMENT (Section 5A)\n    ├─ \"history <specFolder>\"                 → EPISTEMIC MEASUREMENT (Section 5A)\n    ├─ \"causal <memoryId>\"                    → CAUSAL GRAPH (Section 5B)\n    ├─ \"link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation>\"→ CAUSAL GRAPH (Section 5B)\n    ├─ \"unlink <edgeId>\"                      → CAUSAL GRAPH (Section 5B)\n    ├─ \"causal-stats\"                         → CAUSAL GRAPH (Section 5B)\n    ├─ \"ablation\"                             → EVALUATION (Section 5C)\n    └─ \"dashboard\"                            → EVALUATION (Section 5C)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5A. Epistemic Measurement\n\n#### Preflight\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:search preflight <specFolder> <taskId>`\n\nCaptures epistemic baseline before implementation. Records knowledge, uncertainty, and context scores for later comparison with postflight.\n\n##### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `specFolder` | string | Yes | Spec folder path (e.g., `specs/003-memory/077-upgrade`) |\n| `taskId` | string | Yes | Task identifier (e.g., `T1`, `implementation`) |\n| `knowledgeScore` | number | Yes | Knowledge level 0-100 |\n| `uncertaintyScore` | number | Yes | Uncertainty level 0-100 |\n| `contextScore` | number | Yes | Context completeness 0-100 |\n| `knowledgeGaps` | string[] | No | Identified knowledge gaps |\n| `sessionId` | string | No | Session identifier |\n\n##### Workflow\n\n1. Parse `specFolder` and `taskId` from arguments\n2. Assess current epistemic state (knowledge, uncertainty, context)\n3. Call `task_preflight()` with scores\n4. Display baseline confirmation\n\n##### Output\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH PREFLIGHT\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Spec        <specFolder>\n  Task        <taskId>\n\n→ Epistemic Baseline ─────────────────────────────\n  Knowledge     <score>/100\n  Uncertainty   <score>/100\n  Context       <score>/100\n\n→ Knowledge Gaps ─────────────────────────────────\n  <gap1>\n  <gap2>\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=preflight\n```\n\n#### Postflight\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:search postflight <specFolder> <taskId>`\n\nCaptures post-task epistemic state and calculates Learning Index. The `specFolder` and `taskId` must match a prior preflight record.\n\n**Learning Index:** `LI = (KnowledgeDelta × 0.4) + (UncertaintyReduction × 0.35) + (ContextImprovement × 0.25)`\n\n##### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `specFolder` | string | Yes | Spec folder path (must match preflight) |\n| `taskId` | string | Yes | Task identifier (must match preflight) |\n| `knowledgeScore` | number | Yes | Post-task knowledge level 0-100 |\n| `uncertaintyScore` | number | Yes | Post-task uncertainty level 0-100 |\n| `contextScore` | number | Yes | Post-task context completeness 0-100 |\n| `gapsClosed` | string[] | No | Knowledge gaps closed during task |\n| `newGapsDiscovered` | string[] | No | New gaps discovered during task |\n\n##### Learning Index Interpretation\n\n| Range | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| 40+ | Significant learning |\n| 15-40 | Moderate learning |\n| 5-15 | Incremental learning |\n| <5 | Execution-focused (minimal learning) |\n| Negative | Regression, investigate |\n\n##### Output\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH POSTFLIGHT\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Spec        <specFolder>\n  Task        <taskId>\n\n→ Epistemic State (Final) ────────────────────────\n  Knowledge     <pre> → <post>  (Δ <delta>)\n  Uncertainty   <pre> → <post>  (Δ <delta>)\n  Context       <pre> → <post>  (Δ <delta>)\n\n→ Learning Index ─────────────────────────────────\n  ████████░░  <LI>/10  (<interpretation>)\n\n→ Gaps Closed ────────────────────────────────────\n  <gap1>\n  <gap2>\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=postflight LI=<value>\n```\n\n#### Learning History\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:search history <specFolder>`\n\nView learning history (PREFLIGHT/POSTFLIGHT records) for a spec folder. Shows knowledge improvement deltas and Learning Index trends. Completes the epistemic lifecycle: capture (preflight) -> complete (postflight) -> review (history).\n\n##### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `specFolder` | string | Yes | Spec folder path (e.g., `specs/007-auth`) |\n| `sessionId` | string | No | Filter by session ID |\n| `limit` | number | No | Maximum records (default: 10, max: 100) |\n| `onlyComplete` | boolean | No | Only return records with both PREFLIGHT and POSTFLIGHT (default: false) |\n| `includeSummary` | boolean | No | Include summary statistics and trends (default: true) |\n\n##### Output\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH HISTORY\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Spec        <specFolder>\n  Records     <N>\n\n→ Learning History ───────────────────────────────\n  <taskId>  K: <pre>→<post>  U: <pre>→<post>  C: <pre>→<post>  LI: <value>\n  <taskId>  K: <pre>→<post>  U: <pre>→<post>  C: <pre>→<post>  LI: <value>\n\n→ Summary ────────────────────────────────────────\n  Avg LI      <value>\n  Trend       <improving|stable|declining>\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=history\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5B. Memory Causal Graph\n\n#### Causal Trace\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:search causal <memoryId>`\n\nTraces the causal chain for a spec-doc record to answer \"why was this decision made?\" Traverses causal edges up to `maxDepth` hops.\n\n##### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `memoryId` | number or string | Yes | Memory ID to trace |\n| `maxDepth` | number | No | Max traversal depth (default: 3, max: 10) |\n| `direction` | string | No | `outgoing`, `incoming`, or `both` (default: `both`) |\n| `relations` | string[] | No | Filter by: `caused`, `enabled`, `supersedes`, `contradicts`, `derived_from`, `supports` |\n| `includeMemoryDetails` | boolean | No | Include full spec-doc record details (default: true) |\n\n##### Output\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH CAUSAL\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Record      #<id> \"<title>\"\n  Depth       <maxDepth>\n  Direction   <direction>\n\n→ Causal Chain ───────────────────────────────────\n  #<id> \"<title>\"\n    ├─ caused → #<id2> \"<title2>\"\n    │   └─ enabled → #<id3> \"<title3>\"\n    └─ supersedes → #<id4> \"<title4>\"\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=causal EDGES=<count>\n```\n\n#### Causal Link\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:search link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation>`\n\nCreates a causal relationship between two spec-doc records.\n\n##### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `sourceId` | number or string | Yes | Source memory ID |\n| `targetId` | number or string | Yes | Target memory ID |\n| `relation` | string | Yes | `caused`, `enabled`, `supersedes`, `contradicts`, `derived_from`, `supports` |\n| `strength` | number | No | Relationship strength 0.0-1.0 (default: 1.0) |\n| `evidence` | string | No | Evidence or reason for the relationship |\n\n##### Output\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH LINK\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Source      #<sourceId> \"<title>\"\n  Target      #<targetId> \"<title>\"\n  Relation    <relation>\n  Strength    <strength>\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=link\n```\n\n#### Causal Unlink\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:search unlink <edgeId>`\n\nRemoves a causal relationship by edge ID. Use `/memory:search causal <memoryId>` first to find edge IDs.\n\n##### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `edgeId` | number | Yes | Edge ID to delete |\n\n##### Output\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH UNLINK\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Removed     Edge #<edgeId>\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=unlink\n```\n\n#### Causal Stats\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:search causal-stats`\n\nShows statistics about the causal spec-doc graph. No parameters required.\n\nTarget: 60% of spec-doc records linked (CHK-065).\n\n##### Output\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH CAUSAL-STATS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n  Total Edges     <N>\n  Coverage        <pct>% (<linked>/<total> spec-doc records)\n\n→ By Relation ────────────────────────────────────\n  caused          ██████░░░░  <N>\n  enabled         ████░░░░░░  <N>\n  supersedes      ██░░░░░░░░  <N>\n  contradicts     █░░░░░░░░░  <N>\n  derived_from    ███░░░░░░░  <N>\n  supports        █████░░░░░  <N>\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=causal-stats COVERAGE=<pct>%\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5C. Evaluation\n\n#### Ablation Study\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:search ablation`\n\nRuns a controlled channel ablation study (R13-S3). Requires `SPECKIT_ABLATION=true` environment variable.\n\n##### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `mode` | string | No | Evaluation mode. Defaults to `ablation`; use `k_sensitivity` for raw pre-fusion RRF K analysis |\n| `channels` | string[] | No | Channels to ablate: `vector`, `bm25`, `fts5`, `graph`, `trigger` (default: all) |\n| `groundTruthQueryIds` | number[] | No | Subset of ground truth query IDs to evaluate |\n| `recallK` | number | No | Recall cutoff K (default: 20) |\n| `storeResults` | boolean | No | Persist metrics to eval_metric_snapshots (default: true) |\n| `includeFormattedReport` | boolean | No | Include human-readable markdown report (default: true) |\n\n##### Behavior Notes\n\n- Missing `groundTruthQueryIds` now produce a warning and the run continues with the remaining IDs that exist in the static dataset.\n- If the report includes `Token budget overflow` and fewer than `recallK` candidates were evaluated, treat the run as investigation-only rather than a reliable Recall@K verdict.\n- After a DB rebuild or eval DB swap, rerun `scripts/evals/map-ground-truth-ids.ts` before comparing baselines or channel deltas.\n\n##### Output\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH ABLATION\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n→ Recall@<K> Deltas ──────────────────────────────\n  -vector     Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n  -bm25       Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n  -fts5       Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n  -graph      Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n  -trigger    Δ <delta>  (baseline: <base>)\n\n  Stored      <yes|no>\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=ablation\n```\n\n#### Reporting Dashboard\n\n**Trigger:** `/memory:search dashboard`\n\nGenerates R13-S3 reporting dashboard output with sprint/channel trend aggregation.\n\n##### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `sprintFilter` | string[] | No | Sprint label filters |\n| `channelFilter` | string[] | No | Channel filters |\n| `metricFilter` | string[] | No | Metric-name filters |\n| `limit` | number | No | Max sprint groups to return |\n| `format` | string | No | `text` (default) or `json` |\n\n##### Output\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH DASHBOARD\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n→ Sprint Trends ──────────────────────────────────\n  <sprint>    Recall@20: <value>  MRR: <value>\n  <sprint>    Recall@20: <value>  MRR: <value>\n\n→ Channel Performance ───────────────────────────\n  vector      ████████░░  <value>\n  bm25        ██████░░░░  <value>\n  fts5        █████░░░░░  <value>\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=dashboard\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. ERROR HANDLING\n\n| Condition | Response |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Query empty | Ask user for query or subcommand (see gate at top) |\n| Intent invalid | Default to 'understand' with warning |\n| No results | Suggest broader query or different intent |\n| Search fails | Fall back to unweighted search |\n| Unknown subcommand | `STATUS=FAIL`, list valid subcommands |\n| Missing required parameter | `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Missing <param> for <subcommand>\"` |\n| Preflight/postflight specFolder mismatch | `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"specFolder must match preflight record\"` |\n| SPECKIT_ABLATION not enabled | `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Requires SPECKIT_ABLATION=true\"` |\n| Ablation warns about missing IDs | Continue with available IDs, then correct `groundTruthQueryIds` or rerun `scripts/evals/map-ground-truth-ids.ts` |\n| Ablation reports `Token budget overflow` below `recallK` | Report the run as investigation-only and fix truncation before using Recall@K as evidence |\n| No causal edges found | Display empty graph message |\n| Spec-doc record ID not found | `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Memory #<id> not found\"` (runtime string preserved verbatim) |\n| No learning history records | Suggest using `preflight` before tasks |\n\n---\n\n## 7. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:save`: Save conversation context\n- `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest\n- `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation\n\n---\n<!-- APPENDIX: Reference material for AI agent implementation -->\n\n## APPENDIX A: MCP TOOL REFERENCE\n\n**CRITICAL:** Use the correct MCP tools for each step. This command owns 13 tools across L1, L2, L6, and L7 layers.\n\n### Enforcement Matrix\n\n| MODE | REQUIRED CALLS | PATTERN | ON FAILURE |\n|------|----------------|---------|------------|\n| RETRIEVAL (default) | | | |\n| Intent detect | Parse query, match keywords | LOCAL | Default to 'understand' |\n| Context (preferred) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({ input, ... })` | SINGLE | Fall back to manual search |\n| Quick search (optional) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search({ query, ... })` | SINGLE | Fall back to preferred/manual retrieval |\n| Trigger check | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers({ prompt: query })` | OPTIONAL | Continue without |\n| Search (manual) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search({ query, anchors, includeContent: true })` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| ANALYSIS | | | |\n| Preflight | `task_preflight()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| Postflight | `task_postflight()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| Memory causal trace | `memory_drift_why()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| Memory causal link | `memory_causal_link()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| Memory causal unlink | `memory_causal_unlink()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| Memory causal stats | `memory_causal_stats()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| Ablation | `eval_run_ablation()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| Dashboard | `eval_reporting_dashboard()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| History | `memory_get_learning_history()` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n\n### Tool Signatures\n\n> **Note:** The dedicated `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context()` tool provides unified intent-aware retrieval server-side. It accepts `input`, `mode`, `intent`, `specFolder`, governed retrieval params (`tenantId`, `userId`, `agentId`), `limit`, `sessionId`, `enableDedup`, `includeContent`, `includeTrace`, `tokenUsage`, and `anchors`. `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search()` also supports governed retrieval via `tenantId`, `userId`, and `agentId`. This is the recommended unified approach. The manual orchestration below is for advanced use cases requiring fine-grained control.\n\n> **Adaptive Fusion, Hybrid Routing & Telemetry:** Retrieval combines vector, FTS5/BM25, and structural code graph channels, then applies intent-adaptive fusion and reranking. Results may be routed through artifact-class classification before scoring. When `SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION` is enabled, weights adapt dynamically by intent, including the internal continuity profile (`0.52 / 0.18 / 0.07 / 0.23`) used for resume-style retrieval. When `SPECKIT_EXTENDED_TELEMETRY` is enabled, extended telemetry is captured (query timing, score distributions, fusion decisions) and written to the telemetry log.\n>\n> **MMR and Evidence Gap Prevention:** Post-fusion MMR reduces redundant context chunks, and low-confidence retrieval can trigger an early evidence-gap warning so sparse results are treated cautiously.\n\n```javascript\n// ─── Retrieval tools ───────────────────────────────────────────\n\n// Option 1: Dedicated context tool (preferred - single call)\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({\n  input: \"<query>\",\n  intent: \"<add_feature|fix_bug|refactor|security_audit|understand|find_spec|find_decision>\",  // Optional, auto-detected if omitted\n  specFolder: \"<folder>\",  // Optional\n  tenantId: \"<tenant-id>\", // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n  userId: \"<user-id>\",     // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n  agentId: \"<agent-id>\",   // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n  includeContent: true,\n  anchors: [\"<anchor1>\", \"<anchor2>\"],  // Intent-specific\n})\n\n// Option 2: Simplified search for fast query-only retrieval\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search({\n  query: \"<query>\",\n  limit: 10,                // Optional\n  specFolder: \"<folder>\",   // Optional\n  tenantId: \"<tenant-id>\",  // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n  userId: \"<user-id>\",      // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n  agentId: \"<agent-id>\",    // Optional governed retrieval boundary\n})\n\n// Option 3: Manual search with anchors (advanced - fine-grained control)\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search({\n  query: \"<query>\",\n  anchors: [\"<anchor1>\", \"<anchor2>\", ...],  // Intent-specific\n  limit: 10,\n  includeContent: true,  // Single call, no separate load\n  useDecay: true,\n  contextType: \"<type>\",  // e.g., \"implementation\", \"decision\"\n})\n\n// ─── Analysis tools ───────────────────────────────────────────\n\n// Epistemic measurement\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight({ specFolder, taskId, knowledgeScore, uncertaintyScore, contextScore, knowledgeGaps, sessionId })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight({ specFolder, taskId, knowledgeScore, uncertaintyScore, contextScore, gapsClosed, newGapsDiscovered })\n\n// Memory causal graph\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why({ memoryId, maxDepth, direction, relations, includeMemoryDetails })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link({ sourceId, targetId, relation, strength, evidence })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink({ edgeId })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats({})\n\n// Evaluation\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation({ mode: \"ablation\", channels, groundTruthQueryIds, recallK, storeResults: true, includeFormattedReport: true })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard({ sprintFilter, channelFilter, metricFilter, limit, format })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history({ specFolder, sessionId, limit, onlyComplete, includeSummary })\n```\n\n### Tool Coverage\n\n| # | Tool | Layer | Mode | Subcommand |\n|---|------|-------|------|------------|\n| 1 | `memory_context` | L1 | Retrieval | (default) |\n| 2 | `memory_quick_search` | L2 | Retrieval | (default) |\n| 3 | `memory_search` | L2 | Retrieval | (default) |\n| 4 | `memory_match_triggers` | L2 | Retrieval | (default) |\n| 5 | `task_preflight` | L6 | Analysis | `preflight` |\n| 6 | `task_postflight` | L6 | Analysis | `postflight` |\n| 7 | `memory_drift_why` | L6 | Analysis | `causal` |\n| 8 | `memory_causal_link` | L6 | Analysis | `link` |\n| 9 | `memory_causal_stats` | L6 | Analysis | `causal-stats` |\n| 10 | `memory_causal_unlink` | L6 | Analysis | `unlink` |\n| 11 | `eval_run_ablation` | L6 | Analysis | `ablation` |\n| 12 | `eval_reporting_dashboard` | L6 | Analysis | `dashboard` |\n| 13 | `memory_get_learning_history` | L7 | Analysis | `history` |\n\n---\n\n## APPENDIX B: ADVANCED PARAMETERS\n\n### memory_context: Full Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `input` | string | *required* | Query, prompt, or context description |\n| `mode` | string | `auto` | `auto`, `quick`, `deep`, `focused`, `resume` |\n| `intent` | string | auto-detect | `add_feature`, `fix_bug`, `refactor`, `security_audit`, `understand`, `find_spec`, `find_decision` |\n| `specFolder` | string | - | Limit context to specific spec folder |\n| `limit` | number | mode-specific | Maximum results (1-100) |\n| `sessionId` | string | ephemeral | Caller-supplied session identifier |\n| `enableDedup` | boolean | true | Enable session deduplication |\n| `includeContent` | boolean | false | Include full file content in results |\n| `includeTrace` | boolean | false | Include provenance-rich trace data (scores, source, trace) in results when underlying `memory_search` is called |\n| `tokenUsage` | number | - | Caller token usage ratio (0.0-1.0). Helps the server budget-aware pruning when the caller is near context limits |\n| `anchors` | string[] | - | Filter content to specific anchors (e.g., `[\"state\", \"next-steps\"]` for resume mode) |\n\n### memory_search: Advanced Parameters\n\nThe full `memory_search` parameter surface is available when using Option 3 (manual search). Key advanced parameters:\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `query` | string | - | Natural language search query (required unless `concepts` provided) |\n| `concepts` | string[] | - | 2-5 concept strings for multi-concept AND search (required unless `query` provided) |\n| `specFolder` | string | - | Limit search to specific spec folder |\n| `tier` | string | - | Filter by importance tier |\n| `contextType` | string | - | Filter by context type |\n| `useDecay` | boolean | true | Apply temporal decay scoring |\n| `includeContiguity` | boolean | false | Include adjacent/contiguous spec-doc records |\n| `includeConstitutional` | boolean | true | Include constitutional-tier spec-doc records at top |\n| `enableSessionBoost` | boolean | env flag | Enable session-based score boost from working_memory attention signals |\n| `enableCausalBoost` | boolean | env flag | Enable causal-neighbor boost (2-hop traversal on causal_edges) |\n| `min_quality_score` | number | - | Minimum quality score threshold (0.0-1.0) |\n| `minQualityScore` | number | - | **Deprecated alias** for `min_quality_score`. Prefer the snake_case parameter name |\n| `bypassCache` | boolean | false | Skip tool cache and force fresh search |\n| `rerank` | boolean | true | Enable MMR diversity reranking |\n| `applyLengthPenalty` | boolean | true | Compatibility-only length-penalty option; always resolves to a neutral `1.0` multiplier |\n| `applyStateLimits` | boolean | false | Enforce per-tier quantity limits for result diversity |\n| `minState` | string | `WARM` | Minimum active spec-doc state: `HOT`, `WARM`, `COLD`, `DORMANT` |\n| `autoDetectIntent` | boolean | true | Auto-detect intent from query if not explicitly set |\n| `trackAccess` | boolean | false | Write FSRS strengthening updates on read (off by default to avoid write-on-read) |\n| `mode` | string | `auto` | `auto` (standard) or `deep` (multi-query expansion). Note: deep mode does not guarantee expansion for simple queries |\n| `includeTrace` | boolean | false | Include provenance-rich scores/source/trace fields in each result |\n\n> **Governance scoping:** `tenantId`, `userId`, and `agentId` are advertised in the tool schema for governed retrieval. When scope enforcement is active, results are isolated to the specified boundaries.\n\n### memory_match_triggers: Cognitive Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string | *required* | User prompt or text to match against trigger phrases |\n| `limit` | number | 3 | Maximum matching spec-doc records to return |\n| `session_id` | string | - | Session identifier for cognitive features. Enables attention decay and tiered content injection |\n| `turnNumber` | number | - | Current conversation turn number. Used with `session_id` for decay calculations |\n| `include_cognitive` | boolean | true | Enable cognitive features (decay, tiers, co-activation). Requires `session_id` |\n\nWhen cognitive features are enabled (`session_id` + `include_cognitive`), trigger matching uses attention-based decay and tiered content injection: HOT spec-doc records return full content, WARM spec-doc records return summaries, with co-activation of related spec-doc records.\n\n---\n\n## 8. ANALYSIS OVERVIEW DASHBOARD\n\nWhen the user selects \"Analysis tools\" from the empty-arguments prompt, or when context warrants showing available analysis capabilities:\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SEARCH - ANALYSIS TOOLS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n→ Available Subcommands ──────────────────────────\n\n  Epistemic Measurement\n  [preflight]   Capture knowledge baseline before task\n  [postflight]  Capture post-task state and learning delta\n  [history]     View learning history for a spec folder\n\n  Memory Causal Graph\n  [causal]        Trace decision lineage for a spec-doc record\n  [link]          Create causal relationship\n  [unlink]        Remove causal relationship\n  [causal-stats]  View memory causal graph coverage statistics\n\n  Evaluation\n  [ablation]    Run channel ablation study\n  [dashboard]   View reporting dashboard\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=overview\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":1036,"totalLines":1036,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/search.md","time":{"start":1780738219094,"end":1780738219101}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_076c916f5a177fda016a23e8aaf3348191b16a51c21c0c8cf4"}},"id":"prt_e9c44dc54001pIETbc8dQGrcDI","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","messageID":"msg_e9c44b8f8001v2rOknVCFoX4el"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738219167,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jSc2ud46kx3dpau4oWJL5w89","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: // MODULE: Memory Save Handler\n3: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: /* --- 1. DEPENDENCIES --- */\n5: \n6: // Node built-ins\n7: import { createHash, randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\n8: import * as fs from 'node:fs';\n9: import path from 'path';\n10: \n11: // Shared packages\n12: import { validateFilePath } from '@spec-kit/shared/utils/path-security';\n13: import {\n14:   evaluateMemorySufficiency,\n15:   MEMORY_SUFFICIENCY_REJECTION_CODE,\n16:   type MemorySufficiencyResult,\n17: } from '@spec-kit/shared/parsing/memory-sufficiency';\n18: import {\n19:   validateMemoryTemplateContract,\n20:   type MemoryTemplateContractResult,\n21: } from '@spec-kit/shared/parsing/memory-template-contract';\n22: import {\n23:   evaluateSpecDocHealth,\n24:   type SpecDocHealthResult,\n25: } from '@spec-kit/shared/parsing/spec-doc-health';\n26: \n27: // Internal modules\n28: import { ALLOWED_BASE_PATHS, checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\n29: import { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\n30: import { createFilePathValidator } from '../utils/validators.js';\n31: import * as memoryParser from '../lib/parsing/memory-parser.js';\n32: import * as transactionManager from '../lib/storage/transaction-manager.js';\n33: import * as checkpoints from '../lib/storage/checkpoints.js';\n34: import * as preflight from '../lib/validation/preflight.js';\n35: import { requireDb } from '../utils/index.js';\n36: import type { MCPResponse } from './types.js';\n37: import { createAppendOnlyMemoryRecord, recordLineageVersion, retirePredecessorForActiveReindex } from '../lib/storage/lineage-state.js';\n38: import { determineAction } from '../lib/storage/reconsolidation.js';\n39: import * as causalEdges from '../lib/storage/causal-edges.js';\n40: \n41: import { runQualityGate, isQualityGateEnabled } from '../lib/validation/save-quality-gate.js';\n42: import {\n43:   isPostInsertEnrichmentEnabled,\n44:   isPostInsertEnrichmentAsync,\n45:   isSaveQualityGateEnabled,\n46:   isSaveReconsolidationEnabled,\n47:   resolveSavePlannerMode,\n48: } from '../lib/search/search-flags.js';\n49: import { invalidateEntityDensityCache } from '../lib/search/entity-density.js';\n50: \n51: import { getCanonicalPathKey, resolveCanonicalPath } from '../lib/utils/canonical-path.js';\n52: import { isIndexableConstitutionalMemoryPath, shouldIndexForMemory } from '../lib/utils/index-scope.js';\n53: import { findSimilarMemories } from './pe-gating.js';\n54: import { runPostMutationHooks } from './mutation-hooks.js';\n55: import { buildMutationHookFeedback } from '../hooks/mutation-feedback.js';\n56: import { indexChunkedMemoryFile, shouldUseChunkedIndexing } from './chunking-orchestrator.js';\n57: import { applyPostInsertMetadata } from './save/db-helpers.js';\n58: import {\n59:   createMemoryRecord,\n60:   findSamePathExistingMemory,\n61:   type CreateRecordIdentityHints,\n62:   type MemoryScopeMatch,\n63: } from './save/create-record.js';\n64: import {\n65:   buildGovernanceLogicalKey,\n66:   buildGovernancePostInsertFields,\n67:   ensureGovernanceRuntime,\n68:   recordGovernanceAudit,\n69:   recordTierDowngradeAudit,\n70:   validateGovernedIngest,\n71:   type GovernanceDecision,\n72: } from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\n73: import { delete_memory_from_database } from '../lib/search/vector-index-mutations.js';\n74: import {\n75:   runQualityLoop,\n76: } from './quality-loop.js';\n77: import type {\n78:   QualityLoopResult,\n79: } from './quality-loop.js';\n80: \n81: // O2-5/O2-12: V-rule validation (previously only in workflow path)\n82: import {\n83:   validateMemoryQualityContent,\n84:   determineValidationDisposition,\n85: } from './v-rule-bridge.js';\n86: \n87: // Save pipeline modules\n88: import type {\n89:   IndexResult,\n90:   RouteCategory,\n91:   MergeModeHint,\n92:   SaveArgs,\n93:   AtomicSaveParams,\n94:   AtomicSaveOptions,\n95:   AtomicSaveResult,\n96:   PlannerAdvisory,\n97:   PlannerBlocker,\n98:   PlannerFollowUpAction,\n99:   PlannerRouteTarget,\n100: } from './save/index.js';\n101: import { checkExistingRow, checkContentHashDedup } from './save/dedup.js';\n102: import { generateOrCacheEmbedding, persistPendingEmbeddingCacheWrite } from './save/embedding-pipeline.js';\n103: import { evaluateAndApplyPeDecision } from './save/pe-orchestration.js';\n104: import {\n105:   findScopeFilteredCandidates,\n106:   getRequestedScope,\n107:   runReconsolidationIfEnabled,\n108: } from './save/reconsolidation-bridge.js';\n109: import {\n110:   runPostInsertEnrichmentIfEnabled,\n111:   runPostInsertEnrichment,\n112:   shouldRunPostInsertEnrichment,\n113:   buildDeferredEnrichmentResult,\n114: } from './save/post-insert.js';\n115: import type { PostInsertEnrichmentResult } from './save/post-insert.js';\n116: import {\n117:   markEnrichmentPending,\n118:   needsEnrichmentRepair,\n119:   POST_INSERT_ENRICHMENT_VERSION,\n120:   recordEnrichmentResult,\n121:   repairEnrichmentOnReplay,\n122: } from './save/enrichment-state.js';\n123: import {\n124:   buildIndexResult,\n125:   buildPlannerResponse,\n126:   buildSaveResponse,\n127:   classifySaveErrorCode,\n128:   extractSaveErrorDetails,\n129:   serializePlannerAdvisory,\n130:   serializePlannerBlocker,\n131:   serializePlannerFollowUpAction,\n132:   serializePlannerProposedEdit,\n133:   serializePlannerRouteTarget,\n134: } from './save/response-builder.js';\n135: import type {\n136:   IndexingOrigin,\n137:   ReconsolidationFailureReason,\n138:   ReconsolidationOperationState,\n139: } from './save/types.js';\n140: import { atomicIndexMemory } from './save/atomic-index-memory.js';\n141: import { createMCPErrorResponse } from '../lib/response/envelope.js';\n142: import {\n143:   buildTier3Prompt,\n144:   createContentRouter,\n145:   getTier3Contract,\n146:   isTier3RoutingEnabled,\n147:   InMemoryRouterCache,\n148:   TIER2_FALLBACK_PENALTY,\n149:   TIER3_THRESHOLD,\n150:   type RoutingDecision,\n151:   type Tier3ClassifierInput,\n152:   type Tier3RawResponse,\n153: } from '../lib/routing/content-router.js';\n154: import { anchorMergeOperation } from '../lib/merge/anchor-merge-operation.js';\n155: import {\n156:   readThinContinuityRecord,\n157:   upsertThinContinuityInMarkdown,\n158:   type ThinContinuityRecord,\n159: } from '../lib/continuity/thin-continuity-record.js';\n160: import {\n161:   runSpecDocStructureRule,\n162:   type ContaminationPlan,\n163:   type MergePlan,\n164:   type PostSavePlan,\n165: } from '../lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.js';\n166: import { detectSpecLevelFromParsed } from './handler-utils.js';\n167: \n168: // Extracted sub-modules\n169: import { withSpecFolderLock } from './save/spec-folder-mutex.js';\n170: import { buildParsedMemoryEvidenceSnapshot } from './save/markdown-evidence-builder.js';\n171: import {\n172:   applyInsufficiencyMetadata,\n173:   buildInsufficiencyRejectionResult,\n174:   buildTemplateContractRejectionResult,\n175:   buildDryRunSummary,\n176:   buildPlannerAdvisory,\n177:   buildPlannerBlocker,\n178: } from './save/validation-responses.js';\n179: \n180: import { markMemorySuperseded } from './pe-gating.js';\n181: import { resolveMemoryReference } from './causal-links-processor.js';\n182: import { refreshAutoEntitiesForMemory } from '../lib/extraction/entity-extractor.js';\n183: \n184: // Feature catalog: Memory indexing (memory_save)\n185: // Feature catalog: Verify-fix-verify memory quality loop\n186: // Feature catalog: Dry-run preflight for memory_save\n187: // Feature catalog: Prediction-error save arbitration\n188: \n189: \n190: // Create local path validator\n191: const validateFilePathLocal = createFilePathValidator(ALLOWED_BASE_PATHS, validateFilePath);\n192: const MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION = 'manual-fallback' as const;\n193: export const MEMORY_INDEX_SCOPE_EXCLUDED_ERROR_CODE = 'E_MEMORY_INDEX_SCOPE_EXCLUDED';\n194: const ROUTED_CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID = '_memory.continuity';\n195: const tier3RoutingCache = new InMemoryRouterCache();\n196: let warnedEntityDensityInvalidationFailure = false;\n197: \n198: function invalidateEntityDensityCacheAfterSave(): void {\n199:   try {\n200:     invalidateEntityDensityCache();\n201:   } catch (err: unknown) {\n202:     if (warnedEntityDensityInvalidationFailure) {\n203:       return;\n204:     }\n205:     warnedEntityDensityInvalidationFailure = true;\n206:     const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n207:     console.warn(`[memory-save] Entity-density cache invalidation failed after save: ${message}`);\n208:   }\n209: }\n210: \n211: async function repairReplayEnrichmentIfNeeded(\n212:   database: Parameters<typeof needsEnrichmentRepair>[0],\n213:   memoryId: number | undefined,\n214:   parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n215: ): Promise<void> {\n216:   if (memoryId == null || !needsEnrichmentRepair(database, memoryId)) {\n217:     return;\n218:   }\n219: \n220:   await repairEnrichmentOnReplay({\n221:     database,\n222:     parsed,\n223:     plannerMode: 'full-auto',\n224:   }, memoryId);\n225: }\n226: \n227: interface PreparedParsedMemory {\n228:   parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>;\n229:   validation: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.validateParsedMemory>;\n230:   qualityLoopResult: QualityLoopResult;\n231:   sufficiencyResult: MemorySufficiencyResult;\n232:   templateContract: MemoryTemplateContractResult;\n233:   specDocHealth: SpecDocHealthResult | null;\n234:   finalizedFileContent: string | null;\n235:   sourceClassification: 'template-generated' | typeof MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION;\n236: }\n237: \n238: function createIndexScopeExcludedResponse(\n239:   requestId: string,\n240:   canonicalPath: string,\n241:   originalPath: string,\n242: ): MCPResponse {\n243:   return createMCPErrorResponse({\n244:     tool: 'memory_save',\n245:     error: `Memory indexing excluded for path: ${canonicalPath}`,\n246:     code: MEMORY_INDEX_SCOPE_EXCLUDED_ERROR_CODE,\n247:     details: {\n248:       requestId,\n249:       canonicalPath,\n250:       filePath: originalPath,\n251:     },\n252:     recovery: {\n253:       hint: 'Move the file into an indexable spec folder or constitutional rule path before retrying.',\n254:       actions: ['Verify the path is not under z_future/ or external/'],\n255:       severity: 'warning',\n256:     },\n257:   });\n258: }\n259: \n260: type ParsedMemoryWithIndexHints = ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile> & {\n261:   _skipIndex?: boolean;\n262:   _vRuleIndexBlockIds?: string[];\n263: };\n264: \n265: interface RoutedSaveOptions extends CreateRecordIdentityHints {\n266:   routeAs?: RouteCategory;\n267:   mergeModeHint?: MergeModeHint;\n268: }\n269: \n270: interface RoutedRecordIdentity {\n271:   targetDocPath: string;\n272:   canonicalFilePath: string;\n273:   targetAnchorId: string | null;\n274:   routeAs: RouteCategory | null;\n275:   continuitySourceKey: string | null;\n276: }\n277: \n278: type CanonicalPacketLevel = 'L1' | 'L2' | 'L3' | 'L3+';\n279: type CanonicalPacketKind = 'feature' | 'phase' | 'remediation' | 'research' | 'unknown';\n280: \n281: interface CanonicalAtomicValidatorPlan {\n282:   folder: string;\n283:   level: string;\n284:   mergePlan: MergePlan | null;\n285:   contaminationPlan: ContaminationPlan | null;\n286:   postSavePlan: PostSavePlan | null;\n287: }\n288: \n289: interface CanonicalAtomicPrepared {\n290:   preparedMemory: PreparedParsedMemory;\n291:   routing: RoutedSaveOptions;\n292:   validatorPlan: CanonicalAtomicValidatorPlan | null;\n293: }\n294: \n295: const STANDARD_MEMORY_TEMPLATE_MARKERS = [\n296:   '## continue session',\n297:   '## recovery hints',\n298:   '<!-- memory metadata -->',\n299: ];\n300: const CANONICAL_SPEC_DOCUMENT_TYPES = new Set([\n301:   'spec',\n302:   'plan',\n303:   'tasks',\n304:   'checklist',\n305:   'decision_record',\n306:   'implementation_summary',\n307:   'research',\n308:   'handover',\n309:   'resource_map',\n310: ]);\n311: const ROUTE_CATEGORIES = new Set<RouteCategory>([\n312:   'narrative_progress',\n313:   'narrative_delivery',\n314:   'decision',\n315:   'handover_state',\n316:   'research_finding',\n317:   'task_update',\n318:   'metadata_only',\n319:   'drop',\n320: ]);\n321: \n322: class VRuleUnavailableError extends Error {\n323:   constructor(message: string) {\n324:     super(message);\n325:     this.name = 'VRuleUnavailableError';\n326:   }\n327: }\n328: \n329: function isVRuleUnavailableResult(value: unknown): value is {\n330:   passed: false;\n331:   status: 'error' | 'warning';\n332:   message: string;\n333:   _unavailable: true;\n334: } {\n335:   return typeof value === 'object'\n336:     && value !== null\n337:     && 'passed' in value\n338:     && (value as { passed?: unknown }).passed === false\n339:     && 'status' in value\n340:     && typeof (value as { status?: unknown }).status === 'string'\n341:     && 'message' in value\n342:     && typeof (value as { message?: unknown }).message === 'string';\n343: }\n344: \n345: function classifyMemorySaveSource(\n346:   content: string,\n347: ): 'template-generated' | typeof MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION {\n348:   const normalizedContent = content.toLowerCase();\n349:   const hasAnyStandardMarker = STANDARD_MEMORY_TEMPLATE_MARKERS.some((marker) => normalizedContent.includes(marker));\n350:   return hasAnyStandardMarker ? 'template-generated' : MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION;\n351: }\n352: \n353: // Files that are structural metadata for graph traversal and continuity, not\n354: // semantic-search corpus. The memory-sufficiency gate is built around markdown\n355: // anchors and prose evidence; pure-JSON structural files cannot satisfy it by\n356: // construction. We exempt them from the sufficiency floor so they index with\n357: // whatever flattened text the indexer produces — graph traversal already reads\n358: // these files directly from disk for parent/child/status, so the embedding is\n359: // best-effort, not load-bearing.\n360: const STRUCTURAL_METADATA_FILENAMES = new Set<string>(['graph-metadata.json']);\n361: \n362: function isStructuralMetadataFile(filePath: string): boolean {\n363:   return STRUCTURAL_METADATA_FILENAMES.has(path.basename(filePath));\n364: }\n365: \n366: function shouldBypassTemplateContract(\n367:   sourceClassification: PreparedParsedMemory['sourceClassification'],\n368:   sufficiencyResult: MemorySufficiencyResult,\n369:   templateContract: MemoryTemplateContractResult,\n370:   specDocHealth?: SpecDocHealthResult | null,\n371:   documentType?: string,\n372: ): boolean {\n373:   const isValidCanonicalSpecDoc = Boolean(\n374:     documentType\n375:       && CANONICAL_SPEC_DOCUMENT_TYPES.has(documentType)\n376:       && specDocHealth?.pass === true,\n377:   );\n378: \n379:   return sourceClassification === MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION\n380:     && sufficiencyResult.pass\n381:     && !templateContract.valid\n382:     && (\n383:       isValidCanonicalSpecDoc\n384:       || (\n385:         sufficiencyResult.evidenceCounts.primary === 0\n386:         && sufficiencyResult.evidenceCounts.support >= 3\n387:         && sufficiencyResult.evidenceCounts.anchors >= 1\n388:       )\n389:     );\n390: }\n391: \n392: function buildQualityLoopMetadata(\n393:   parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n394:   database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n395: ): Record<string, unknown> {\n396:   return {\n397:     title: parsed.title ?? '',\n398:     triggerPhrases: parsed.triggerPhrases,\n399:     specFolder: parsed.specFolder,\n400:     contextType: parsed.contextType,\n401:     importanceTier: parsed.importanceTier,\n402:     causalLinks: parsed.causalLinks,\n403:     filePath: parsed.filePath,\n404:     lastModified: parsed.lastModified,\n405:     resolveReference: (reference: string) => resolveMemoryReference(database, reference) !== null,\n406:   };\n407: }\n408: \n409: function prepareParsedMemoryForIndexing(\n410:   parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n411:   database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n412:   options: {\n413:     emitEvalMetrics?: boolean;\n414:     qualityLoopMode?: 'advisory' | 'full-auto';\n415:   } = {},\n416: ): PreparedParsedMemory {\n417:   // Resolve to the canonical path before applying memory-index governance.\n418:   const canonicalFilePath = resolveCanonicalPath(path.resolve(parsed.filePath));\n419:   if (!shouldIndexForMemory(canonicalFilePath)) {\n420:     throw new Error(`Memory indexing excluded for path: ${parsed.filePath}`);\n421:   }\n422:   if (parsed.importanceTier === 'constitutional' && !isIndexableConstitutionalMemoryPath(canonicalFilePath)) {\n423:     console.warn('[memory-save] importance_tier=constitutional rejected for non-constitutional path; downgrading to important', {\n424:       file_path: parsed.filePath,\n425:     });\n426:     try {\n427:       recordTierDowngradeAudit(database, {\n428:         logicalKey: buildGovernanceLogicalKey(parsed.specFolder, canonicalFilePath, null),\n429:         requestedTier: 'constitutional',\n430:         nextTier: 'important',\n431:         source: 'memory_save',\n432:         filePath: parsed.filePath,\n433:         canonicalFilePath,\n434:       });\n435:     } catch (error: unknown) {\n436:       console.warn(\n437:         '[memory-save] governance_audit insert failed for tier downgrade:',\n438:         error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error),\n439:       );\n440:     }\n441:     parsed.importanceTier = 'important';\n442:   }\n443: \n444:   const validation = memoryParser.validateParsedMemory(parsed);\n445:   if (validation.warnings && validation.warnings.length > 0) {\n446:     console.warn(`[memory] Warning for ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}:`);\n447:     validation.warnings.forEach((warning: string) => console.warn(`[memory]   - ${warning}`));\n448:   }\n449: \n450:   // O2-5/O2-12: Run V-rule validation (previously only in workflow path)\n451:   const vRuleResult = validateMemoryQualityContent(parsed.content, { filePath: parsed.filePath });\n452:   if (isVRuleUnavailableResult(vRuleResult) && vRuleResult.status === 'error') {\n453:     throw new VRuleUnavailableError(vRuleResult.message);\n454:   }\n455:   if (vRuleResult && '_unavailable' in vRuleResult) {\n456:     validation.warnings.push('V-rule validator module unavailable — quality gate bypassed. Save proceeds without V-rule enforcement.');\n457:   }\n458:   if (vRuleResult && !isVRuleUnavailableResult(vRuleResult) && !vRuleResult.valid) {\n459:     const vRuleDisposition = determineValidationDisposition(\n460:       vRuleResult.failedRules,\n461:       parsed.memoryTypeSource || null,\n462:     );\n463:     if (vRuleDisposition && vRuleDisposition.disposition === 'abort_write') {\n464:       const failedRuleIds = vRuleDisposition.blockingRuleIds;\n465:       console.error(`[memory-save] V-rule hard block for ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}: ${failedRuleIds.join(', ')}`);\n466:       // Return early with a rejected quality loop result so callers see the block\n467:       const rejectScore = { total: 0, breakdown: { triggers: 0, anchors: 0, budget: 0, coherence: 0 }, issues: [`V-rule hard block: ${failedRuleIds.join(', ')}`] };\n468:       return {\n469:         parsed,\n470:         validation,\n471:         qualityLoopResult: {\n472:           passed: false,\n473:           score: rejectScore,\n474:           attempts: 0,\n475:           fixes: [],\n476:           rejected: true,\n477:           rejectionReason: `V-rule hard block: ${failedRuleIds.join(', ')}`,\n478:         },\n479:         sufficiencyResult: {\n480:           pass: false,\n481:           rejectionCode: MEMORY_SUFFICIENCY_REJECTION_CODE,\n482:           score: 0,\n483:           reasons: [`V-rule hard block: ${failedRuleIds.join(', ')}`],\n484:           evidenceCounts: { primary: 0, support: 0, total: 0, semanticChars: 0, uniqueWords: 0, anchors: 0, triggerPhrases: 0 },\n485:         },\n486:         templateContract: { valid: true, violations: [], missingAnchors: [], unexpectedTemplateArtifacts: [] } as MemoryTemplateContractResult,\n487:         specDocHealth: null,\n488:         finalizedFileContent: null,\n489:         sourceClassification: 'template-generated',\n490:       };\n491:     }\n492:     if (vRuleDisposition && vRuleDisposition.disposition === 'write_skip_index') {\n493:       console.warn(`[memory-save] V-rule index block for ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}: ${vRuleDisposition.indexBlockingRuleIds.join(', ')}`);\n494:       validation.warnings.push(`V-rule index block: ${vRuleDisposition.indexBlockingRuleIds.join(', ')}`);\n495:       // F07-002: Flag to skip indexing for write_skip_index disposition\n496:       const parsedWithIndexHints = parsed as ParsedMemoryWithIndexHints;\n497:       parsedWithIndexHints._skipIndex = true;\n498:       parsedWithIndexHints._vRuleIndexBlockIds = vRuleDisposition.indexBlockingRuleIds;\n499:     }\n500:   }\n501: \n502:   const qualityLoopResult = runQualityLoop(parsed.content, buildQualityLoopMetadata(parsed, database), {\n503:     emitEvalMetrics: options.emitEvalMetrics,\n504:     mode: options.qualityLoopMode ?? 'advisory',\n505:   });\n506:   parsed.qualityScore = qualityLoopResult.score.total;\n507:   parsed.qualityFlags = Array.from(new Set([\n508:     ...(parsed.qualityFlags ?? []),\n509:     ...qualityLoopResult.score.issues,\n510:   ]));\n511:   if (qualityLoopResult.fixedTriggerPhrases) {\n512:     parsed.triggerPhrases = qualityLoopResult.fixedTriggerPhrases;\n513:   }\n514:   const finalizedFileContent = qualityLoopResult.fixedContent\n515:     && qualityLoopResult.passed\n516:     ? qualityLoopResult.fixedContent\n517:     : null;\n518:   if (finalizedFileContent) {\n519:     parsed.content = finalizedFileContent;\n520:     parsed.contentHash = memoryParser.computeContentHash(parsed.content);\n521:   }\n522: \n523:   const sourceClassification = classifyMemorySaveSource(parsed.content);\n524:   if (sourceClassification === MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION) {\n525:     const warning = 'Manual fallback save mode detected; standard generate-context template markers are missing.';\n526:     console.warn(`[memory-save] ${warning} ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}`);\n527:     validation.warnings.push(warning);\n528:   }\n529: \n530:   const sufficiencyResult = evaluateMemorySufficiency(\n531:     {\n532:       ...buildParsedMemoryEvidenceSnapshot(parsed),\n533:       sourceClassification,\n534:     },\n535:   );\n536:   applyInsufficiencyMetadata(parsed, sufficiencyResult);\n537:   const templateContract = validateMemoryTemplateContract(parsed.content);\n538: \n539:   // Non-blocking spec doc health annotation\n540:   // Canonical saves land directly in the spec folder (e.g. .../NNN-name/decision-record.md),\n541:   // so the immediate parent is usually the spec folder itself.\n542:   let specDocHealth: SpecDocHealthResult | null = null;\n543:   if (parsed.specFolder && parsed.filePath) {\n544:     try {\n545:       const absFilePath = path.resolve(parsed.filePath);\n546:       const immediateParent = path.dirname(absFilePath);\n547:       const candidates = [immediateParent, path.dirname(immediateParent)];\n548:       for (const candidate of candidates) {\n549:         if (fs.existsSync(path.join(candidate, 'spec.md'))) {\n550:           specDocHealth = evaluateSpecDocHealth(candidate);\n551:           break;\n552:         }\n553:       }\n554:     } catch (error: unknown) {\n555:       const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n556:       console.warn(\n557:         `[memory-save] spec-doc-health annotation skipped for ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}: ${message}`\n558:       );\n559:     }\n560:   }\n561: \n562:   return {\n563:     parsed,\n564:     validation,\n565:     qualityLoopResult,\n566:     sufficiencyResult,\n567:     templateContract,\n568:     specDocHealth,\n569:     finalizedFileContent,\n570:     sourceClassification,\n571:   };\n572: }\n573: \n574: async function finalizeMemoryFileContent(\n575:   filePath: string,\n576:   content: string,\n577: ): Promise<void> {\n578:   const backupPath = `${filePath}.${randomUUID().slice(0, 8)}.bak`;\n579:   const tempPath = `${filePath}.${randomUUID().slice(0, 8)}.tmp`;\n580:   let backupCreated = false;\n581:   let tempCreated = false;\n582: \n583:   try {\n584:     try {\n585:       await fs.promises.copyFile(filePath, backupPath);\n586:       backupCreated = true;\n587:     } catch (backupErr: unknown) {\n588:       const errCode = typeof backupErr === 'object' && backupErr !== null && 'code' in backupErr\n589:         ? String((backupErr as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code)\n590:         : '';\n591:       if (errCode !== 'ENOENT') {\n592:         throw backupErr;\n593:       }\n594:     }\n595: \n596:     await fs.promises.writeFile(tempPath, content, 'utf-8');\n597:     tempCreated = true;\n598:     await fs.promises.rename(tempPath, filePath);\n599:     tempCreated = false;\n600:   } catch (writeErr: unknown) {\n601:     if (tempCreated) {\n602:       try {\n603:         await fs.promises.unlink(tempPath);\n604:       } catch {\n605:         // Best-effort cleanup only.\n606:       }\n607:     }\n608:     if (backupCreated) {\n609:       try {\n610:         await fs.promises.copyFile(backupPath, filePath);\n611:       } catch (restoreErr: unknown) {\n612:         console.warn(\n613:           '[memory-save] Auto-fix file restore failed after finalize error:',\n614:           restoreErr instanceof Error ? restoreErr.message : String(restoreErr),\n615:         );\n616:       }\n617:     }\n618:     throw writeErr;\n619:   } finally {\n620:     if (tempCreated) {\n621:       try {\n622:         await fs.promises.unlink(tempPath);\n623:       } catch {\n624:         // Best-effort cleanup only.\n625:       }\n626:     }\n627:     if (backupCreated) {\n628:       try {\n629:         await fs.promises.unlink(backupPath);\n630:       } catch {\n631:         // Best-effort cleanup only.\n632:       }\n633:     }\n634:   }\n635: }\n636: \n637: function appendResultWarning<T extends Record<string, unknown>>(result: T, warning: string | null): T {\n638:   if (!warning) {\n639:     return result;\n640:   }\n641: \n642:   const r = result as Record<string, unknown>;\n643:   const warnings = Array.isArray(r.warnings)\n644:     ? [...(r.warnings as string[])]\n645:     : [];\n646:   warnings.push(warning);\n647:   r.warnings = warnings;\n648:   return result;\n649: }\n650: \n651: class SaveTimeReconsolidationAbort extends Error {\n652:   readonly result: {\n653:     status: 'failed';\n654:     reason: ReconsolidationFailureReason;\n655:     warnings?: string[];\n656:     persistedState?: ReconsolidationOperationState;\n657:   };\n658: \n659:   constructor(result: SaveTimeReconsolidationAbort['result']) {\n660:     super(result.reason);\n661:     this.name = 'SaveTimeReconsolidationAbort';\n662:     this.result = result;\n663:   }\n664: }\n665: \n666: function buildSaveTimeReconsolidationFailureResult(args: {\n667:   parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>;\n668:   validation: { warnings: string[] };\n669:   reconWarnings: string[];\n670:   failure: SaveTimeReconsolidationAbort['result'];\n671:   message?: string;\n672: }): IndexResult {\n673:   const warnings = [\n674:     ...args.validation.warnings,\n675:     ...args.reconWarnings,\n676:     ...(args.failure.warnings ?? []),\n677:   ];\n678: \n679:   return {\n680:     status: 'error',\n681:     id: 0,\n682:     specFolder: args.parsed.specFolder,\n683:     title: args.parsed.title ?? '',\n684:     triggerPhrases: args.parsed.triggerPhrases,\n685:     contextType: args.parsed.contextType,\n686:     importanceTier: args.parsed.importanceTier,\n687:     memoryType: args.parsed.memoryType,\n688:     memoryTypeSource: args.parsed.memoryTypeSource,\n689:     qualityScore: args.parsed.qualityScore,\n690:     qualityFlags: args.parsed.qualityFlags,\n691:     warnings,\n692:     error: args.message ?? `Save-time reconsolidation failed: ${args.failure.reason}`,\n693:     message: args.message ?? `Save-time reconsolidation failed: ${args.failure.reason}`,\n694:     saveTimeReconsolidation: args.failure,\n695:   };\n696: }\n697: \n698: function recordCrossPathPeSupersedes(\n699:   database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n700:   memoryId: number,\n701:   supersededMemoryId: number | null,\n702:   samePathMemoryId: number | null,\n703:   reason: string | null | undefined,\n704: ): void {\n705:   if (supersededMemoryId == null || supersededMemoryId === samePathMemoryId) {\n706:     return;\n707:   }\n708: \n709:   causalEdges.init(database);\n710:   const evidence = reason && reason.trim().length > 0\n711:     ? reason.trim()\n712:     : 'Prediction-error contradiction across different file paths';\n713:   causalEdges.insertEdge(\n714:     String(memoryId),\n715:     String(supersededMemoryId),\n716:     causalEdges.RELATION_TYPES.SUPERSEDES,\n717:     1.0,\n718:     evidence,\n719:     true,\n720:     'auto',\n721:   );\n722: }\n723: \n724: interface ChunkedInsertTracker {\n725:   parentId: number | null;\n726:   childIds: Set<number>;\n727: }\n728: \n729: function createChunkedInsertTracker(): ChunkedInsertTracker {\n730:   return {\n731:     parentId: null,\n732:     childIds: new Set<number>(),\n733:   };\n734: }\n735: \n736: function trackChunkedInsert(\n737:   tracker: ChunkedInsertTracker,\n738:   memoryId: number,\n739:   fields: Record<string, unknown>,\n740: ): void {\n741:   if (typeof fields.chunk_index === 'number') {\n742:     tracker.childIds.add(memoryId);\n743:     return;\n744:   }\n745: \n746:   if (tracker.parentId == null) {\n747:     tracker.parentId = memoryId;\n748:   }\n749: }\n750: \n751: function rollbackCreatedChunkTree(\n752:   database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n753:   tracker: ChunkedInsertTracker,\n754: ): { attempted: boolean; cleaned: boolean; error?: string } {\n755:   if (tracker.parentId == null) {\n756:     return { attempted: false, cleaned: false };\n757:   }\n758: \n759:   const childIds = new Set<number>(tracker.childIds);\n760:   try {\n761:     const persistedChildRows = database.prepare(`\n762:       SELECT id\n763:       FROM memory_index\n764:       WHERE parent_id = ?\n765:     `).all(tracker.parentId) as Array<{ id: number }>;\n766:     for (const row of persistedChildRows) {\n767:       childIds.add(row.id);\n768:     }\n769:   } catch {\n770:     // Best-effort lookup only. Tracked IDs remain authoritative for cleanup.\n771:   }\n772: \n773:   const cleanupErrors: string[] = [];\n774:   for (const childId of childIds) {\n775:     try {\n776:       if (!delete_memory_from_database(database, childId)) {\n777:         cleanupErrors.push(`Chunk ${childId} was not deleted`);\n778:       }\n779:     } catch (error: unknown) {\n780:       cleanupErrors.push(`Chunk ${childId} cleanup failed: ${getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error)}`);\n781:     }\n782:   }\n783: \n784:   try {\n785:     if (!delete_memory_from_database(database, tracker.parentId)) {\n786:       cleanupErrors.push(`Parent ${tracker.parentId} was not deleted`);\n787:     }\n788:   } catch (error: unknown) {\n789:     cleanupErrors.push(`Parent ${tracker.parentId} cleanup failed: ${getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error)}`);\n790:   }\n791: \n792:   if (cleanupErrors.length > 0) {\n793:     return {\n794:       attempted: true,\n795:       cleaned: false,\n796:       error: cleanupErrors.join('; '),\n797:     };\n798:   }\n799: \n800:   return { attempted: true, cleaned: true };\n801: }\n802: \n803: function captureAtomicSaveOriginalState(filePath: string): { existed: boolean; content: string | null } {\n804:   if (!fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n805:     return { existed: false, content: null };\n806:   }\n807: \n808:   return {\n809:     existed: true,\n810:     content: fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8'),\n811:   };\n812: }\n813: \n814: function getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error: unknown): string {\n815:   return error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n816: }\n817: \n818: function deleteAtomicSaveFile(filePath: string): { deleted: boolean; existed: boolean; error?: string } {\n819:   const existed = fs.existsSync(filePath);\n820:   if (!existed) {\n821:     return { deleted: false, existed: false };\n822:   }\n823: \n824:   try {\n825:     fs.unlinkSync(filePath);\n826:     return { deleted: true, existed: true };\n827:   } catch (error: unknown) {\n828:     return {\n829:       deleted: false,\n830:       existed: true,\n831:       error: getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error),\n832:     };\n833:   }\n834: }\n835: \n836: function restoreAtomicSaveOriginalState(\n837:   filePath: string,\n838:   originalState: { existed: boolean; content: string | null },\n839: ): { restored: boolean; error?: string } {\n840:   try {\n841:     if (!originalState.existed) {\n842:       const deleteResult = deleteAtomicSaveFile(filePath);\n843:       if (!deleteResult.existed || deleteResult.deleted) {\n844:         return { restored: true };\n845:       }\n846:       return {\n847:         restored: false,\n848:         error: deleteResult.error ?? `Failed to remove promoted file at ${filePath}`,\n849:       };\n850:     }\n851: \n852:     if (typeof originalState.content !== 'string') {\n853:       return { restored: false, error: 'Original file content is unavailable for rollback' };\n854:     }\n855: \n856:     fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(filePath), { recursive: true });\n857:     fs.writeFileSync(filePath, originalState.content, 'utf-8');\n858:     return { restored: true };\n859:   } catch (error: unknown) {\n860:     return {\n861:       restored: false,\n862:       error: getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error),\n863:     };\n864:   }\n865: }\n866: \n867: function cleanupAtomicSavePendingFile(\n868:   pendingPath: string,\n869: ): { cleaned: boolean; existed: boolean; error?: string } {\n870:   try {\n871:     const deleteResult = deleteAtomicSaveFile(pendingPath);\n872:     if (!deleteResult.existed || deleteResult.deleted) {\n873:       return {\n874:         cleaned: true,\n875:         existed: deleteResult.existed,\n876:       };\n877:     }\n878:     return {\n879:       cleaned: false,\n880:       existed: deleteResult.existed,\n881:       error: deleteResult.error ?? `Failed to remove pending file at ${pendingPath}`,\n882:     };\n883:   } catch (error: unknown) {\n884:     return {\n885:       cleaned: false,\n886:       existed: true,\n887:       error: getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error),\n888:     };\n889:   }\n890: }\n891: \n892: function applyRoutedSaveHints(\n893:   parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n894:   routing: RoutedSaveOptions,\n895: ): ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile> {\n896:   const parsedWithHints = parsed as ParsedMemoryWithIndexHints & Record<string, unknown>;\n897:   if (routing.targetDocPath) {\n898:     parsedWithHints.targetDocPath = routing.targetDocPath;\n899:     parsedWithHints.target_doc_path = routing.targetDocPath;\n900:   }\n901:   if (routing.targetAnchorId) {\n902:     parsedWithHints.targetAnchorId = routing.targetAnchorId;\n903:     parsedWithHints.target_anchor_id = routing.targetAnchorId;\n904:     parsedWithHints.anchorId = routing.targetAnchorId;\n905:     parsedWithHints.anchor_id = routing.targetAnchorId;\n906:   }\n907:   if (routing.routeAs) {\n908:     parsedWithHints.routeAs = routing.routeAs;\n909:     parsedWithHints.route_as = routing.routeAs;\n910:   }\n911:   if (routing.continuitySourceKey) {\n912:     parsedWithHints.continuitySourceKey = routing.continuitySourceKey;\n913:     parsedWithHints.continuity_source_key = routing.continuitySourceKey;\n914:   }\n915:   return parsedWithHints;\n916: }\n917: \n918: function buildRoutedSaveOptions(\n919:   filePath: string,\n920:   routeAs?: RouteCategory,\n921:   mergeModeHint?: MergeModeHint,\n922:   targetAnchorId?: string,\n923: ): RoutedSaveOptions | undefined {\n924:   if (!routeAs && !mergeModeHint && !targetAnchorId) {\n925:     return undefined;\n926:   }\n927: \n928:   return {\n929:     targetDocPath: filePath,\n930:     ...(routeAs ? { routeAs } : {}),\n931:     ...(mergeModeHint ? { mergeModeHint } : {}),\n932:     ...(targetAnchorId ? { targetAnchorId } : {}),\n933:   };\n934: }\n935: \n936: function shouldUseCanonicalRouting(_params: Pick<AtomicSaveParams, 'routeAs' | 'mergeModeHint' | 'targetAnchorId'>): boolean {\n937:   // Test-only bypass: allows the atomic-save failure-injection suite\n938:   // to exercise the legacy prepareParsedMemoryForIndexing path without\n939:   // setting up full Tier 3 classifier fixtures.\n940:   if (process.env.SPECKIT_TEST_DISABLE_CANONICAL_ROUTING === 'true') return false;\n941:   return true; // Canonical routing is always enabled (Tier 3 LLM routing on by default)\n942: }\n943: \n944: function pickRoutedIdentityValue(value: unknown): string | null {\n945:   return typeof value === 'string' && value.trim().length > 0 ? value.trim() : null;\n946: }\n947: \n948: function pickRouteCategory(value: unknown): RouteCategory | null {\n949:   const normalized = pickRoutedIdentityValue(value);\n950:   if (!normalized || !ROUTE_CATEGORIES.has(normalized as RouteCategory)) {\n951:     return null;\n952:   }\n953:   return normalized as RouteCategory;\n954: }\n955: \n956: function isMergeModeHint(value: unknown): value is MergeModeHint {\n957:   return value === 'append-as-paragraph'\n958:     || value === 'insert-new-adr'\n959:     || value === 'append-table-row'\n960:     || value === 'update-in-place'\n961:     || value === 'append-section';\n962: }\n963: \n964: function resolveRoutedRecordIdentity(\n965:   parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n966:   routedFilePath: string,\n967:   routing: RoutedSaveOptions,\n968: ): RoutedRecordIdentity {\n969:   const routedRecord = parsed as unknown as Record<string, unknown>;\n970:   const routeAs = pickRouteCategory(routing.routeAs ?? routedRecord.routeAs ?? routedRecord.route_as);\n971:   const continuitySourceKey = pickRoutedIdentityValue(\n972:     routing.continuitySourceKey\n973:     ?? routedRecord.continuitySourceKey\n974:     ?? routedRecord.continuity_source_key\n975:     ?? routedRecord.sourceKey\n976:     ?? routedRecord.source_key,\n977:   );\n978:   const explicitTargetAnchorId = pickRoutedIdentityValue(\n979:     routing.targetAnchorId\n980:     ?? routedRecord.targetAnchorId\n981:     ?? routedRecord.target_anchor_id\n982:     ?? routedRecord.anchorId\n983:     ?? routedRecord.anchor_id,\n984:   );\n985: \n986:   return {\n987:     targetDocPath: routing.targetDocPath ?? routedFilePath,\n988:     canonicalFilePath: routing.canonicalFilePath ?? getCanonicalPathKey(routing.targetDocPath ?? routedFilePath),\n989:     targetAnchorId: explicitTargetAnchorId ?? ((routeAs === 'metadata_only' || continuitySourceKey !== null) ? ROUTED_CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID : null),\n990:     routeAs,\n991:     continuitySourceKey,\n992:   };\n993: }\n994: \n995: function toCanonicalPacketLevel(level: number | null): CanonicalPacketLevel {\n996:   if (level === 1) return 'L1';\n997:   if (level === 2) return 'L2';\n998:   if (level === 3) return 'L3';\n999:   return 'L3+';\n1000: }\n1001: \n1002: function toValidatorLevel(packetLevel: CanonicalPacketLevel): string {\n1003:   return packetLevel.replace(/^L/u, '');\n1004: }\n1005: \n1006: function normalizeForFingerprint(content: string): string {\n1007:   return content\n1008:     .replace(/\\r\\n/g, '\\n')\n1009:     .replace(/[ \\t]+$/gm, '');\n1010: }\n1011: \n1012: function buildContinuityFingerprint(content: string): string {\n1013:   return `sha256:${createHash('sha256').update(normalizeForFingerprint(content), 'utf8').digest('hex')}`;\n1014: }\n1015: \n1016: function normalizePhaseAnchor(value: string | null | undefined): string | null {\n1017:   if (typeof value !== 'string') {\n1018:     return null;\n1019:   }\n1020:   const trimmed = value.trim();\n1021:   const match = trimmed.match(/^phase(?:[\\s_-]+)?(\\d+)$/iu);\n1022:   return match ? `phase-${match[1]}` : null;\n1023: }\n1024: \n1025: function inferPhaseAnchorFromText(text: string): string | null {\n1026:   const match = text.match(/\\bphase(?:[\\s_-]+)?(\\d+)\\b/iu);\n1027:   return match ? `phase-${match[1]}` : null;\n1028: }\n1029: \n1030: function inferPhaseAnchorFromSpecFolder(specFolder: string): string | null {\n1031:   return inferPhaseAnchorFromText(specFolder.replace(/\\//g, ' '));\n1032: }\n1033: \n1034: function deriveLikelyPhaseAnchorForCanonicalRouting(params: {\n1035:   routingChunkText: string;\n1036:   specFolder: string;\n1037:   targetAnchorId?: string;\n1038: }): string | null {\n1039:   return normalizePhaseAnchor(params.targetAnchorId)\n1040:     ?? inferPhaseAnchorFromText(params.routingChunkText)\n1041:     ?? inferPhaseAnchorFromSpecFolder(params.specFolder);\n1042: }\n1043: \n1044: function stripMarkdownFrontmatter(markdown: string): string {\n1045:   return markdown.replace(/^(?:\\uFEFF)?---\\r?\\n[\\s\\S]*?\\r?\\n---(?:\\r?\\n)?/u, '');\n1046: }\n1047: \n1048: function normalizeRoutingChunkText(markdown: string): string {\n1049:   return stripMarkdownFrontmatter(markdown)\n1050:     .replace(/<!--[\\s\\S]*?-->/g, ' ')\n1051:     .replace(/\\r\\n/g, '\\n')\n1052:     .replace(/\\n{3,}/g, '\\n\\n')\n1053:     .trim();\n1054: }\n1055: \n1056: function extractFrontmatterScalar(markdown: string, key: string): string | null {\n1057:   const frontmatterMatch = markdown.match(/^(?:\\uFEFF)?---\\r?\\n([\\s\\S]*?)\\r?\\n---(?:\\r?\\n)?/u);\n1058:   if (!frontmatterMatch?.[1]) {\n1059:     return null;\n1060:   }\n1061: \n1062:   const escapedKey = key.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\\]\\\\]/g, '\\\\$&');\n1063:   const scalarMatch = frontmatterMatch[1].match(\n1064:     new RegExp(`^\\\\s*${escapedKey}:\\\\s*[\"']?([^\"'\\r\\n]+)[\"']?\\\\s*$`, 'imu'),\n1065:   );\n1066:   return scalarMatch?.[1]?.trim() ?? null;\n1067: }\n1068: \n1069: function hasNumericSpecFolderName(folderPath: string): boolean {\n1070:   return /^\\d{3}(?:[-_].+)?$/u.test(path.basename(folderPath));\n1071: }\n1072: \n1073: function hasChildSpecFolders(specFolderAbsolute: string): boolean {\n1074:   try {\n1075:     const entries = fs.readdirSync(specFolderAbsolute, { withFileTypes: true });\n1076:     return entries.some((entry) => {\n1077:       if (!entry.isDirectory() || !hasNumericSpecFolderName(entry.name)) {\n1078:         return false;\n1079:       }\n1080:       return fs.existsSync(path.join(specFolderAbsolute, entry.name, 'spec.md'));\n1081:     });\n1082:   } catch {\n1083:     return false;\n1084:   }\n1085: }\n1086: \n1087: function deriveCanonicalPacketKind(\n1088:   specFolderAbsolute: string,\n1089:   specFolderKey: string,\n1090: ): CanonicalPacketKind {\n1091:   const specMdPath = path.join(specFolderAbsolute, 'spec.md');\n1092:   let specContent = '';\n1093:   try {\n1094:     specContent = fs.readFileSync(specMdPath, 'utf8');\n1095:   } catch {\n1096:     specContent = '';\n1097:   }\n1098: \n1099:   const packetType = extractFrontmatterScalar(specContent, 'type')?.toLowerCase() ?? '';\n1100:   const title = extractFrontmatterScalar(specContent, 'title')?.toLowerCase() ?? '';\n1101:   const description = extractFrontmatterScalar(specContent, 'description')?.toLowerCase() ?? '';\n1102:   const folderName = path.basename(specFolderAbsolute).toLowerCase();\n1103:   const semanticHint = `${folderName} ${title} ${description}`;\n1104: \n1105:   if (packetType === 'research') {\n1106:     return 'research';\n1107:   }\n1108:   if (/\\bremediation\\b/u.test(semanticHint)) {\n1109:     return 'remediation';\n1110:   }\n1111: \n1112:   const parentFolder = path.dirname(specFolderAbsolute);\n1113:   const hasNumericParentPacket = hasNumericSpecFolderName(parentFolder)\n1114:     && fs.existsSync(path.join(parentFolder, 'spec.md'));\n1115:   if (!hasChildSpecFolders(specFolderAbsolute) && hasNumericParentPacket) {\n1116:     return 'phase';\n1117:   }\n1118: \n1119:   const normalizedSpecFolder = specFolderKey.replace(/^specs\\//u, '');\n1120:   const depth = normalizedSpecFolder.split('/').filter(Boolean).length;\n1121:   if (depth <= 2) {\n1122:     return 'feature';\n1123:   }\n1124: \n1125:   return hasNumericParentPacket ? 'phase' : 'feature';\n1126: }\n1127: \n1128: function getTier3RoutingEndpoint(): string | null {\n1129:   const endpoint = process.env.LLM_REFORMULATION_ENDPOINT?.trim();\n1130:   return endpoint ? endpoint.replace(/\\/+$/u, '') : null;\n1131: }\n1132: \n1133: function extractTier3MessageText(content: unknown): string | null {\n1134:   if (typeof content === 'string') {\n1135:     const trimmed = content.trim();\n1136:     return trimmed.length > 0 ? trimmed : null;\n1137:   }\n1138:   if (Array.isArray(content)) {\n1139:     const text = content\n1140:       .map((entry) => {\n1141:         if (!entry || typeof entry !== 'object') {\n1142:           return '';\n1143:         }\n1144:         const textValue = (entry as { text?: unknown }).text;\n1145:         return typeof textValue === 'string' ? textValue : '';\n1146:       })\n1147:       .join('')\n1148:       .trim();\n1149:     return text.length > 0 ? text : null;\n1150:   }\n1151:   return null;\n1152: }\n1153: \n1154: function isTier3RawResponseShape(parsed: unknown): parsed is Tier3RawResponse {\n1155:   if (!parsed || typeof parsed !== 'object') {\n1156:     return false;\n1157:   }\n1158: \n1159:   const record = parsed as Record<string, unknown>;\n1160:   return typeof record.category === 'string'\n1161:     && typeof record.confidence === 'number'\n1162:     && typeof record.target_doc === 'string'\n1163:     && typeof record.target_anchor === 'string'\n1164:     && typeof record.merge_mode === 'string'\n1165:     && typeof record.reasoning === 'string';\n1166: }\n1167: \n1168: function parseTier3ClassifierResponse(rawText: string): Tier3RawResponse | null {\n1169:   try {\n1170:     const parsed = JSON.parse(rawText) as Record<string, unknown>;\n1171:     if (!parsed || typeof parsed !== 'object') {\n1172:       return null;\n1173:     }\n1174:     return isTier3RawResponseShape(parsed) ? parsed : null;\n1175:   } catch {\n1176:     return null;\n1177:   }\n1178: }\n1179: \n1180: async function classifyWithTier3Llm(input: Tier3ClassifierInput): Promise<Tier3RawResponse | null> {\n1181:   const endpoint = getTier3RoutingEndpoint();\n1182:   if (!endpoint) {\n1183:     return null;\n1184:   }\n1185: \n1186:   const apiKey = process.env.LLM_REFORMULATION_API_KEY?.trim() ?? '';\n1187:   const contract = getTier3Contract();\n1188:   const prompt = buildTier3Prompt(input);\n1189:   const controller = new AbortController();\n1190:   const timeoutId = setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), contract.timeoutMs);\n1191: \n1192:   try {\n1193:     const response = await fetch(`${endpoint}/chat/completions`, {\n1194:       method: 'POST',\n1195:       headers: {\n1196:         'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n1197:         ...(apiKey ? { Authorization: `Bearer ${apiKey}` } : {}),\n1198:       },\n1199:       body: JSON.stringify({\n1200:         model: contract.model,\n1201:         messages: [\n1202:           { role: 'system', content: prompt.system },\n1203:           { role: 'user', content: prompt.user },\n1204:         ],\n1205:         reasoning_effort: contract.reasoningEffort,\n1206:         temperature: contract.temperature,\n1207:         max_tokens: contract.maxOutputTokens,\n1208:         response_format: { type: 'json_object' },\n1209:       }),\n1210:       signal: controller.signal,\n1211:     });\n1212: \n1213:     clearTimeout(timeoutId);\n1214: \n1215:     if (!response.ok) {\n1216:       return null;\n1217:     }\n1218: \n1219:     const data = await response.json() as {\n1220:       choices?: Array<{\n1221:         message?: {\n1222:           content?: unknown;\n1223:         };\n1224:       }>;\n1225:     };\n1226:     const rawText = extractTier3MessageText(data.choices?.[0]?.message?.content);\n1227:     return rawText ? parseTier3ClassifierResponse(rawText) : null;\n1228:   } catch {\n1229:     clearTimeout(timeoutId);\n1230:     return null;\n1231:   }\n1232: }\n1233: \n1234: function buildCanonicalRouter(options: { tier3Enabled?: boolean } = {}) {\n1235:   return createContentRouter({\n1236:     classifyWithTier3: classifyWithTier3Llm,\n1237:     cache: tier3RoutingCache,\n1238:     tier3Enabled: options.tier3Enabled,\n1239:   });\n1240: }\n1241: \n1242: function collapseInlineWhitespace(value: string): string {\n1243:   return value.replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n1244: }\n1245: \n1246: function clipInlineText(value: string, maxLength = 96): string {\n1247:   const normalized = collapseInlineWhitespace(value);\n1248:   return normalized.length <= maxLength ? normalized : `${normalized.slice(0, maxLength - 3).trimEnd()}...`;\n1249: }\n1250: \n1251: function extractParagraphs(markdown: string): string[] {\n1252:   return normalizeRoutingChunkText(markdown)\n1253:     .split(/\\n\\s*\\n/g)\n1254:     .map((entry) => collapseInlineWhitespace(entry))\n1255:     .filter(Boolean);\n1256: }\n1257: \n1258: function extractListItems(markdown: string): string[] {\n1259:   return normalizeRoutingChunkText(markdown)\n1260:     .split(/\\r?\\n/g)\n1261:     .map((line) => line.match(/^\\s*(?:[-*+]|\\d+\\.)\\s+(.+)$/u)?.[1] ?? '')\n1262:     .map((line) => clipInlineText(line, 120))\n1263:     .filter(Boolean);\n1264: }\n1265: \n1266: function resolveSpecFolderAbsoluteFromFilePath(filePath: string, specFolder: string): string {\n1267:   const normalizedFilePath = filePath.replace(/\\\\/g, '/');\n1268:   const normalizedSpecFolder = specFolder.replace(/^specs\\//u, '');\n1269:   const markers = [\n1270:     `/specs/${normalizedSpecFolder}/`,\n1271:     `/specs/${specFolder}/`,\n1272:   ];\n1273: \n1274:   for (const marker of markers) {\n1275:     const markerIndex = normalizedFilePath.lastIndexOf(marker);\n1276:     if (markerIndex >= 0) {\n1277:       return path.normalize(`${normalizedFilePath.slice(0, markerIndex)}${marker.slice(0, -1)}`);\n1278:     }\n1279:   }\n1280: \n1281:   return path.resolve(path.dirname(filePath), '..');\n1282: }\n1283: \n1284: function resolveMetadataHostDocPath(specFolderAbsolute: string): string {\n1285:   const implementationSummaryPath = path.join(specFolderAbsolute, 'implementation-summary.md');\n1286:   if (fs.existsSync(implementationSummaryPath)) {\n1287:     return implementationSummaryPath;\n1288:   }\n1289: \n1290:   return path.join(specFolderAbsolute, 'spec.md');\n1291: }\n1292: \n1293: function resolveCanonicalTargetDocPath(\n1294:   specFolderAbsolute: string,\n1295:   routedDocPath: string,\n1296: ): string {\n1297:   if (routedDocPath === 'spec-frontmatter' || routedDocPath === 'implementation-summary.md') {\n1298:     return resolveMetadataHostDocPath(specFolderAbsolute);\n1299:   }\n1300:   return path.join(specFolderAbsolute, routedDocPath);\n1301: }\n1302: \n1303: function clampRoutingConfidence(value: number): number {\n1304:   return Math.min(1, Math.max(0, value));\n1305: }\n1306: \n1307: function selectTier2FailOpenFallback(\n1308:   specFolderAbsolute: string,\n1309:   decision: RoutingDecision,\n1310: ): {\n1311:   category: RouteCategory;\n1312:   confidence: number;\n1313:   targetDocPath: string;\n1314:   routedDocPath: string;\n1315:   targetAnchorId: string;\n1316:   mergeMode: RoutingDecision['target']['mergeMode'];\n1317:   warningMessage: string;\n1318: } | null {\n1319:   if (decision.tierUsed !== 3) {\n1320:     return null;\n1321:   }\n1322: \n1323:   for (const hit of decision.tier2TopK) {\n1324:     if (hit.category === 'drop') {\n1325:       continue;\n1326:     }\n1327:     const fallbackConfidence = clampRoutingConfidence(hit.similarity - TIER2_FALLBACK_PENALTY);\n1328:     if (fallbackConfidence < TIER3_THRESHOLD) {\n1329:       continue;\n1330:     }\n1331: \n1332:     const targetDocPath = resolveCanonicalTargetDocPath(specFolderAbsolute, hit.target_doc);\n1333:     if (!fs.existsSync(targetDocPath)) {\n1334:       continue;\n1335:     }\n1336: \n1337:     return {\n1338:       category: hit.category as RouteCategory,\n1339:       confidence: fallbackConfidence,\n1340:       targetDocPath,\n1341:       routedDocPath: hit.target_doc,\n1342:       targetAnchorId: hit.target_anchor,\n1343:       mergeMode: hit.merge_intent,\n1344:       warningMessage: `Tier 3 routing was unusable; fell back to Tier 2 prototype match ${hit.category}.`,\n1345:     };\n1346:   }\n1347: \n1348:   return null;\n1349: }\n1350: \n1351: function buildFallbackContinuityRecord(params: {\n1352:   parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>;\n1353:   routeCategory: RouteCategory;\n1354:   targetDocPath: string;\n1355:   specFolderAbsolute: string;\n1356:   currentContent: string;\n1357: }): ThinContinuityRecord {\n1358:   const { parsed, routeCategory, targetDocPath, specFolderAbsolute, currentContent } = params;\n1359:   const relativeTargetPath = path.relative(specFolderAbsolute, targetDocPath).replace(/\\\\/g, '/');\n1360:   const absoluteSpecFolder = specFolderAbsolute.replace(/\\\\/g, '/');\n1361:   const packetPointerFromPath = absoluteSpecFolder.includes('/specs/')\n1362:     ? absoluteSpecFolder.split('/specs/')[1]\n1363:     : parsed.specFolder.replace(/^specs\\//u, '');\n1364:   const title = clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? (normalizeRoutingChunkText(currentContent) || 'Updated canonical continuity'));\n1365:   const nextActionByRoute: Record<RouteCategory, string> = {\n1366:     narrative_progress: 'Review routed update',\n1367:     narrative_delivery: 'Verify delivery route',\n1368:     decision: 'Review ADR follow-up',\n1369:     handover_state: 'Resume routed handover',\n1370:     research_finding: 'Review cited finding',\n1371:     task_update: 'Verify task alignment',\n1372:     metadata_only: 'Refresh continuity',\n1373:     drop: 'Inspect refused route',\n1374:   };\n1375: \n1376:   return {\n1377:     packet_pointer: packetPointerFromPath,\n1378:     last_updated_at: new Date().toISOString().replace(/\\.\\d{3}Z$/u, 'Z'),\n1379:     last_updated_by: 'memory-save',\n1380:     recent_action: title,\n1381:     next_safe_action: nextActionByRoute[routeCategory],\n1382:     blockers: [],\n1383:     key_files: relativeTargetPath ? [relativeTargetPath] : [],\n1384:     session_dedup: {\n1385:       fingerprint: buildContinuityFingerprint(currentContent),\n1386:       session_id: 'memory-save',\n1387:       parent_session_id: null,\n1388:     },\n1389:     completion_pct: 0,\n1390:     open_questions: [],\n1391:     answered_questions: [],\n1392:   };\n1393: }\n1394: \n1395: function buildCanonicalMergePayload(params: {\n1396:   parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>;\n1397:   routeCategory: RouteCategory;\n1398:   mergeMode: MergeModeHint;\n1399:   content: string;\n1400: }): Record<string, unknown> {\n1401:   const { parsed, routeCategory, mergeMode, content } = params;\n1402:   const paragraphs = extractParagraphs(content);\n1403:   const firstParagraph = paragraphs[0] ?? clipInlineText(content, 160);\n1404:   const secondParagraph = paragraphs[1] ?? firstParagraph;\n1405:   const listItems = extractListItems(content);\n1406: \n1407:   switch (mergeMode) {\n1408:     case 'append-as-paragraph':\n1409:       return { paragraph: firstParagraph };\n1410:     case 'append-section':\n1411:       return {\n1412:         title: clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? `${routeCategory.replace(/_/g, ' ')} update`, 72),\n1413:         body: normalizeRoutingChunkText(content) || firstParagraph,\n1414:       };\n1415:     case 'insert-new-adr':\n1416:       return {\n1417:         title: clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? 'Captured canonical decision', 80),\n1418:         context: firstParagraph,\n1419:         decision: secondParagraph,\n1420:         consequences: listItems.slice(0, 3),\n1421:       };\n1422:     case 'update-in-place': {\n1423:       const targetId = content.match(/\\b(?:T\\d{3}|CHK-\\d{3})\\b/u)?.[0];\n1424:       if (!targetId) {\n1425:         throw new Error(`Canonical task update could not find a target task/checklist id in routed content.`);\n1426:       }\n1427:       const checked = /\\[[xX]\\]/u.test(content)\n1428:         ? true\n1429:         : (/\\[[ ]\\]/u.test(content) ? false : undefined);\n1430:       return {\n1431:         targetId,\n1432:         ...(checked === undefined ? {} : { checked }),\n1433:         evidence: clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? firstParagraph, 96),\n1434:       };\n1435:     }\n1436:     case 'append-table-row':\n1437:       return {\n1438:         cells: [\n1439:           clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? routeCategory, 48),\n1440:           'Updated',\n1441:           clipInlineText(firstParagraph, 96),\n1442:         ],\n1443:         dedupeColumn: 0,\n1444:       };\n1445:     default:\n1446:       return { paragraph: firstParagraph };\n1447:   }\n1448: }\n1449: \n1450: async function buildCanonicalAtomicPreparedSave(\n1451:   params: AtomicSaveParams,\n1452:   database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n1453: ): Promise<{ status: 'ready'; prepared: CanonicalAtomicPrepared; persistedContent: string; persistedFilePath: string } | { status: 'abort'; result: AtomicSaveResult }> {\n1454:   const preparedMemory = prepareParsedMemoryForIndexing(\n1455:     memoryParser.parseMemoryContent(params.file_path, params.content),\n1456:     database,\n1457:     {\n1458:       qualityLoopMode: params.plannerMode === 'full-auto' ? 'full-auto' : 'advisory',\n1459:     },\n1460:   );\n1461:   if (!preparedMemory.validation.valid) {\n1462:     return {\n1463:       status: 'abort',\n1464:       result: {\n1465:         success: false,\n1466:         filePath: params.file_path,\n1467:         status: 'error',\n1468:         summary: 'Atomic save preflight failed',\n1469:         message: 'Parsed content failed validation before canonical atomic save',\n1470:         error: `Validation failed: ${preparedMemory.validation.errors.join(', ')}`,\n1471:       },\n1472:     };\n1473:   }\n1474: \n1475:   if (preparedMemory.qualityLoopResult.fixes.length > 0 && preparedMemory.qualityLoopResult.passed && preparedMemory.qualityLoopResult.fixedContent) {\n1476:     console.error(`[memory-save] Quality loop applied ${preparedMemory.qualityLoopResult.fixes.length} auto-fix(es) for ${path.basename(params.file_path)} before canonical pending-file promotion`);\n1477:   }\n1478: \n1479:   const specFolderAbsolute = resolveSpecFolderAbsoluteFromFilePath(params.file_path, preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder);\n1480:   const packetLevel = toCanonicalPacketLevel(detectSpecLevelFromParsed(path.join(specFolderAbsolute, 'spec.md')));\n1481:   const packetKind = deriveCanonicalPacketKind(specFolderAbsolute, preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder);\n1482:   const saveMode = params.routeAs ? 'route-as' : 'natural';\n1483:   const tier3Enabled = isTier3RoutingEnabled();\n1484:   const router = buildCanonicalRouter({ tier3Enabled });\n1485:   const routingChunkText = normalizeRoutingChunkText(params.content);\n1486:   const likelyPhaseAnchor = deriveLikelyPhaseAnchorForCanonicalRouting({\n1487:     routingChunkText,\n1488:     specFolder: preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder,\n1489:     targetAnchorId: params.targetAnchorId,\n1490:   });\n1491:   const decision = await router.classifyContent(\n1492:     {\n1493:       id: path.basename(params.file_path),\n1494:       text: routingChunkText,\n1495:       sourceField: params.routeAs === 'metadata_only' ? 'preflight' : 'observations',\n1496:       routeAs: params.routeAs,\n1497:       metadata: params.targetAnchorId ? { targetAnchorId: params.targetAnchorId } : undefined,\n1498:     },\n1499:     {\n1500:       specFolder: preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder,\n1501:       packetLevel,\n1502:       sessionMeta: {\n1503:         spec_folder: preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder,\n1504:         packet_level: packetLevel,\n1505:         packet_kind: packetKind,\n1506:         save_mode: saveMode,\n1507:         recent_docs_touched: [],\n1508:         recent_anchors_touched: [],\n1509:         likely_phase_anchor: likelyPhaseAnchor,\n1510:       },\n1511:     },\n1512:   );\n1513: \n1514:   let effectiveDecision = decision;\n1515:   const applyTier2FailOpenFallback = (): boolean => {\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1515. Use offset=1516 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Save Handler\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n/* --- 1. DEPENDENCIES --- */\n\n// Node built-ins\nimport { createHash, randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\nimport * as fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'path';\n\n// Shared packages\nimport { validateFilePath } from '@spec-kit/shared/utils/path-security';\nimport {\n  evaluateMemorySufficiency,\n  MEMORY_SUFFICIENCY_REJECTION_CODE,\n  type MemorySufficiencyResult,\n} from '@spec-kit/shared/parsing/memory-sufficiency';\nimport {\n  validateMemoryTemplateContract,\n  type MemoryTemplateContractResult,","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts","text":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Save Handler\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n/* --- 1. DEPENDENCIES --- */\n\n// Node built-ins\nimport { createHash, randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\nimport * as fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'path';\n\n// Shared packages\nimport { validateFilePath } from '@spec-kit/shared/utils/path-security';\nimport {\n  evaluateMemorySufficiency,\n  MEMORY_SUFFICIENCY_REJECTION_CODE,\n  type MemorySufficiencyResult,\n} from '@spec-kit/shared/parsing/memory-sufficiency';\nimport {\n  validateMemoryTemplateContract,\n  type MemoryTemplateContractResult,\n} from '@spec-kit/shared/parsing/memory-template-contract';\nimport {\n  evaluateSpecDocHealth,\n  type SpecDocHealthResult,\n} from '@spec-kit/shared/parsing/spec-doc-health';\n\n// Internal modules\nimport { ALLOWED_BASE_PATHS, checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\nimport { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\nimport { createFilePathValidator } from '../utils/validators.js';\nimport * as memoryParser from '../lib/parsing/memory-parser.js';\nimport * as transactionManager from '../lib/storage/transaction-manager.js';\nimport * as checkpoints from '../lib/storage/checkpoints.js';\nimport * as preflight from '../lib/validation/preflight.js';\nimport { requireDb } from '../utils/index.js';\nimport type { MCPResponse } from './types.js';\nimport { createAppendOnlyMemoryRecord, recordLineageVersion, retirePredecessorForActiveReindex } from '../lib/storage/lineage-state.js';\nimport { determineAction } from '../lib/storage/reconsolidation.js';\nimport * as causalEdges from '../lib/storage/causal-edges.js';\n\nimport { runQualityGate, isQualityGateEnabled } from '../lib/validation/save-quality-gate.js';\nimport {\n  isPostInsertEnrichmentEnabled,\n  isPostInsertEnrichmentAsync,\n  isSaveQualityGateEnabled,\n  isSaveReconsolidationEnabled,\n  resolveSavePlannerMode,\n} from '../lib/search/search-flags.js';\nimport { invalidateEntityDensityCache } from '../lib/search/entity-density.js';\n\nimport { getCanonicalPathKey, resolveCanonicalPath } from '../lib/utils/canonical-path.js';\nimport { isIndexableConstitutionalMemoryPath, shouldIndexForMemory } from '../lib/utils/index-scope.js';\nimport { findSimilarMemories } from './pe-gating.js';\nimport { runPostMutationHooks } from './mutation-hooks.js';\nimport { buildMutationHookFeedback } from '../hooks/mutation-feedback.js';\nimport { indexChunkedMemoryFile, shouldUseChunkedIndexing } from './chunking-orchestrator.js';\nimport { applyPostInsertMetadata } from './save/db-helpers.js';\nimport {\n  createMemoryRecord,\n  findSamePathExistingMemory,\n  type CreateRecordIdentityHints,\n  type MemoryScopeMatch,\n} from './save/create-record.js';\nimport {\n  buildGovernanceLogicalKey,\n  buildGovernancePostInsertFields,\n  ensureGovernanceRuntime,\n  recordGovernanceAudit,\n  recordTierDowngradeAudit,\n  validateGovernedIngest,\n  type GovernanceDecision,\n} from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\nimport { delete_memory_from_database } from '../lib/search/vector-index-mutations.js';\nimport {\n  runQualityLoop,\n} from './quality-loop.js';\nimport type {\n  QualityLoopResult,\n} from './quality-loop.js';\n\n// O2-5/O2-12: V-rule validation (previously only in workflow path)\nimport {\n  validateMemoryQualityContent,\n  determineValidationDisposition,\n} from './v-rule-bridge.js';\n\n// Save pipeline modules\nimport type {\n  IndexResult,\n  RouteCategory,\n  MergeModeHint,\n  SaveArgs,\n  AtomicSaveParams,\n  AtomicSaveOptions,\n  AtomicSaveResult,\n  PlannerAdvisory,\n  PlannerBlocker,\n  PlannerFollowUpAction,\n  PlannerRouteTarget,\n} from './save/index.js';\nimport { checkExistingRow, checkContentHashDedup } from './save/dedup.js';\nimport { generateOrCacheEmbedding, persistPendingEmbeddingCacheWrite } from './save/embedding-pipeline.js';\nimport { evaluateAndApplyPeDecision } from './save/pe-orchestration.js';\nimport {\n  findScopeFilteredCandidates,\n  getRequestedScope,\n  runReconsolidationIfEnabled,\n} from './save/reconsolidation-bridge.js';\nimport {\n  runPostInsertEnrichmentIfEnabled,\n  runPostInsertEnrichment,\n  shouldRunPostInsertEnrichment,\n  buildDeferredEnrichmentResult,\n} from './save/post-insert.js';\nimport type { PostInsertEnrichmentResult } from './save/post-insert.js';\nimport {\n  markEnrichmentPending,\n  needsEnrichmentRepair,\n  POST_INSERT_ENRICHMENT_VERSION,\n  recordEnrichmentResult,\n  repairEnrichmentOnReplay,\n} from './save/enrichment-state.js';\nimport {\n  buildIndexResult,\n  buildPlannerResponse,\n  buildSaveResponse,\n  classifySaveErrorCode,\n  extractSaveErrorDetails,\n  serializePlannerAdvisory,\n  serializePlannerBlocker,\n  serializePlannerFollowUpAction,\n  serializePlannerProposedEdit,\n  serializePlannerRouteTarget,\n} from './save/response-builder.js';\nimport type {\n  IndexingOrigin,\n  ReconsolidationFailureReason,\n  ReconsolidationOperationState,\n} from './save/types.js';\nimport { atomicIndexMemory } from './save/atomic-index-memory.js';\nimport { createMCPErrorResponse } from '../lib/response/envelope.js';\nimport {\n  buildTier3Prompt,\n  createContentRouter,\n  getTier3Contract,\n  isTier3RoutingEnabled,\n  InMemoryRouterCache,\n  TIER2_FALLBACK_PENALTY,\n  TIER3_THRESHOLD,\n  type RoutingDecision,\n  type Tier3ClassifierInput,\n  type Tier3RawResponse,\n} from '../lib/routing/content-router.js';\nimport { anchorMergeOperation } from '../lib/merge/anchor-merge-operation.js';\nimport {\n  readThinContinuityRecord,\n  upsertThinContinuityInMarkdown,\n  type ThinContinuityRecord,\n} from '../lib/continuity/thin-continuity-record.js';\nimport {\n  runSpecDocStructureRule,\n  type ContaminationPlan,\n  type MergePlan,\n  type PostSavePlan,\n} from '../lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.js';\nimport { detectSpecLevelFromParsed } from './handler-utils.js';\n\n// Extracted sub-modules\nimport { withSpecFolderLock } from './save/spec-folder-mutex.js';\nimport { buildParsedMemoryEvidenceSnapshot } from './save/markdown-evidence-builder.js';\nimport {\n  applyInsufficiencyMetadata,\n  buildInsufficiencyRejectionResult,\n  buildTemplateContractRejectionResult,\n  buildDryRunSummary,\n  buildPlannerAdvisory,\n  buildPlannerBlocker,\n} from './save/validation-responses.js';\n\nimport { markMemorySuperseded } from './pe-gating.js';\nimport { resolveMemoryReference } from './causal-links-processor.js';\nimport { refreshAutoEntitiesForMemory } from '../lib/extraction/entity-extractor.js';\n\n// Feature catalog: Memory indexing (memory_save)\n// Feature catalog: Verify-fix-verify memory quality loop\n// Feature catalog: Dry-run preflight for memory_save\n// Feature catalog: Prediction-error save arbitration\n\n\n// Create local path validator\nconst validateFilePathLocal = createFilePathValidator(ALLOWED_BASE_PATHS, validateFilePath);\nconst MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION = 'manual-fallback' as const;\nexport const MEMORY_INDEX_SCOPE_EXCLUDED_ERROR_CODE = 'E_MEMORY_INDEX_SCOPE_EXCLUDED';\nconst ROUTED_CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID = '_memory.continuity';\nconst tier3RoutingCache = new InMemoryRouterCache();\nlet warnedEntityDensityInvalidationFailure = false;\n\nfunction invalidateEntityDensityCacheAfterSave(): void {\n  try {\n    invalidateEntityDensityCache();\n  } catch (err: unknown) {\n    if (warnedEntityDensityInvalidationFailure) {\n      return;\n    }\n    warnedEntityDensityInvalidationFailure = true;\n    const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n    console.warn(`[memory-save] Entity-density cache invalidation failed after save: ${message}`);\n  }\n}\n\nasync function repairReplayEnrichmentIfNeeded(\n  database: Parameters<typeof needsEnrichmentRepair>[0],\n  memoryId: number | undefined,\n  parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n): Promise<void> {\n  if (memoryId == null || !needsEnrichmentRepair(database, memoryId)) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  await repairEnrichmentOnReplay({\n    database,\n    parsed,\n    plannerMode: 'full-auto',\n  }, memoryId);\n}\n\ninterface PreparedParsedMemory {\n  parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>;\n  validation: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.validateParsedMemory>;\n  qualityLoopResult: QualityLoopResult;\n  sufficiencyResult: MemorySufficiencyResult;\n  templateContract: MemoryTemplateContractResult;\n  specDocHealth: SpecDocHealthResult | null;\n  finalizedFileContent: string | null;\n  sourceClassification: 'template-generated' | typeof MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION;\n}\n\nfunction createIndexScopeExcludedResponse(\n  requestId: string,\n  canonicalPath: string,\n  originalPath: string,\n): MCPResponse {\n  return createMCPErrorResponse({\n    tool: 'memory_save',\n    error: `Memory indexing excluded for path: ${canonicalPath}`,\n    code: MEMORY_INDEX_SCOPE_EXCLUDED_ERROR_CODE,\n    details: {\n      requestId,\n      canonicalPath,\n      filePath: originalPath,\n    },\n    recovery: {\n      hint: 'Move the file into an indexable spec folder or constitutional rule path before retrying.',\n      actions: ['Verify the path is not under z_future/ or external/'],\n      severity: 'warning',\n    },\n  });\n}\n\ntype ParsedMemoryWithIndexHints = ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile> & {\n  _skipIndex?: boolean;\n  _vRuleIndexBlockIds?: string[];\n};\n\ninterface RoutedSaveOptions extends CreateRecordIdentityHints {\n  routeAs?: RouteCategory;\n  mergeModeHint?: MergeModeHint;\n}\n\ninterface RoutedRecordIdentity {\n  targetDocPath: string;\n  canonicalFilePath: string;\n  targetAnchorId: string | null;\n  routeAs: RouteCategory | null;\n  continuitySourceKey: string | null;\n}\n\ntype CanonicalPacketLevel = 'L1' | 'L2' | 'L3' | 'L3+';\ntype CanonicalPacketKind = 'feature' | 'phase' | 'remediation' | 'research' | 'unknown';\n\ninterface CanonicalAtomicValidatorPlan {\n  folder: string;\n  level: string;\n  mergePlan: MergePlan | null;\n  contaminationPlan: ContaminationPlan | null;\n  postSavePlan: PostSavePlan | null;\n}\n\ninterface CanonicalAtomicPrepared {\n  preparedMemory: PreparedParsedMemory;\n  routing: RoutedSaveOptions;\n  validatorPlan: CanonicalAtomicValidatorPlan | null;\n}\n\nconst STANDARD_MEMORY_TEMPLATE_MARKERS = [\n  '## continue session',\n  '## recovery hints',\n  '<!-- memory metadata -->',\n];\nconst CANONICAL_SPEC_DOCUMENT_TYPES = new Set([\n  'spec',\n  'plan',\n  'tasks',\n  'checklist',\n  'decision_record',\n  'implementation_summary',\n  'research',\n  'handover',\n  'resource_map',\n]);\nconst ROUTE_CATEGORIES = new Set<RouteCategory>([\n  'narrative_progress',\n  'narrative_delivery',\n  'decision',\n  'handover_state',\n  'research_finding',\n  'task_update',\n  'metadata_only',\n  'drop',\n]);\n\nclass VRuleUnavailableError extends Error {\n  constructor(message: string) {\n    super(message);\n    this.name = 'VRuleUnavailableError';\n  }\n}\n\nfunction isVRuleUnavailableResult(value: unknown): value is {\n  passed: false;\n  status: 'error' | 'warning';\n  message: string;\n  _unavailable: true;\n} {\n  return typeof value === 'object'\n    && value !== null\n    && 'passed' in value\n    && (value as { passed?: unknown }).passed === false\n    && 'status' in value\n    && typeof (value as { status?: unknown }).status === 'string'\n    && 'message' in value\n    && typeof (value as { message?: unknown }).message === 'string';\n}\n\nfunction classifyMemorySaveSource(\n  content: string,\n): 'template-generated' | typeof MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION {\n  const normalizedContent = content.toLowerCase();\n  const hasAnyStandardMarker = STANDARD_MEMORY_TEMPLATE_MARKERS.some((marker) => normalizedContent.includes(marker));\n  return hasAnyStandardMarker ? 'template-generated' : MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION;\n}\n\n// Files that are structural metadata for graph traversal and continuity, not\n// semantic-search corpus. The memory-sufficiency gate is built around markdown\n// anchors and prose evidence; pure-JSON structural files cannot satisfy it by\n// construction. We exempt them from the sufficiency floor so they index with\n// whatever flattened text the indexer produces — graph traversal already reads\n// these files directly from disk for parent/child/status, so the embedding is\n// best-effort, not load-bearing.\nconst STRUCTURAL_METADATA_FILENAMES = new Set<string>(['graph-metadata.json']);\n\nfunction isStructuralMetadataFile(filePath: string): boolean {\n  return STRUCTURAL_METADATA_FILENAMES.has(path.basename(filePath));\n}\n\nfunction shouldBypassTemplateContract(\n  sourceClassification: PreparedParsedMemory['sourceClassification'],\n  sufficiencyResult: MemorySufficiencyResult,\n  templateContract: MemoryTemplateContractResult,\n  specDocHealth?: SpecDocHealthResult | null,\n  documentType?: string,\n): boolean {\n  const isValidCanonicalSpecDoc = Boolean(\n    documentType\n      && CANONICAL_SPEC_DOCUMENT_TYPES.has(documentType)\n      && specDocHealth?.pass === true,\n  );\n\n  return sourceClassification === MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION\n    && sufficiencyResult.pass\n    && !templateContract.valid\n    && (\n      isValidCanonicalSpecDoc\n      || (\n        sufficiencyResult.evidenceCounts.primary === 0\n        && sufficiencyResult.evidenceCounts.support >= 3\n        && sufficiencyResult.evidenceCounts.anchors >= 1\n      )\n    );\n}\n\nfunction buildQualityLoopMetadata(\n  parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n  database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n): Record<string, unknown> {\n  return {\n    title: parsed.title ?? '',\n    triggerPhrases: parsed.triggerPhrases,\n    specFolder: parsed.specFolder,\n    contextType: parsed.contextType,\n    importanceTier: parsed.importanceTier,\n    causalLinks: parsed.causalLinks,\n    filePath: parsed.filePath,\n    lastModified: parsed.lastModified,\n    resolveReference: (reference: string) => resolveMemoryReference(database, reference) !== null,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction prepareParsedMemoryForIndexing(\n  parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n  database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n  options: {\n    emitEvalMetrics?: boolean;\n    qualityLoopMode?: 'advisory' | 'full-auto';\n  } = {},\n): PreparedParsedMemory {\n  // Resolve to the canonical path before applying memory-index governance.\n  const canonicalFilePath = resolveCanonicalPath(path.resolve(parsed.filePath));\n  if (!shouldIndexForMemory(canonicalFilePath)) {\n    throw new Error(`Memory indexing excluded for path: ${parsed.filePath}`);\n  }\n  if (parsed.importanceTier === 'constitutional' && !isIndexableConstitutionalMemoryPath(canonicalFilePath)) {\n    console.warn('[memory-save] importance_tier=constitutional rejected for non-constitutional path; downgrading to important', {\n      file_path: parsed.filePath,\n    });\n    try {\n      recordTierDowngradeAudit(database, {\n        logicalKey: buildGovernanceLogicalKey(parsed.specFolder, canonicalFilePath, null),\n        requestedTier: 'constitutional',\n        nextTier: 'important',\n        source: 'memory_save',\n        filePath: parsed.filePath,\n        canonicalFilePath,\n      });\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      console.warn(\n        '[memory-save] governance_audit insert failed for tier downgrade:',\n        error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error),\n      );\n    }\n    parsed.importanceTier = 'important';\n  }\n\n  const validation = memoryParser.validateParsedMemory(parsed);\n  if (validation.warnings && validation.warnings.length > 0) {\n    console.warn(`[memory] Warning for ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}:`);\n    validation.warnings.forEach((warning: string) => console.warn(`[memory]   - ${warning}`));\n  }\n\n  // O2-5/O2-12: Run V-rule validation (previously only in workflow path)\n  const vRuleResult = validateMemoryQualityContent(parsed.content, { filePath: parsed.filePath });\n  if (isVRuleUnavailableResult(vRuleResult) && vRuleResult.status === 'error') {\n    throw new VRuleUnavailableError(vRuleResult.message);\n  }\n  if (vRuleResult && '_unavailable' in vRuleResult) {\n    validation.warnings.push('V-rule validator module unavailable — quality gate bypassed. Save proceeds without V-rule enforcement.');\n  }\n  if (vRuleResult && !isVRuleUnavailableResult(vRuleResult) && !vRuleResult.valid) {\n    const vRuleDisposition = determineValidationDisposition(\n      vRuleResult.failedRules,\n      parsed.memoryTypeSource || null,\n    );\n    if (vRuleDisposition && vRuleDisposition.disposition === 'abort_write') {\n      const failedRuleIds = vRuleDisposition.blockingRuleIds;\n      console.error(`[memory-save] V-rule hard block for ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}: ${failedRuleIds.join(', ')}`);\n      // Return early with a rejected quality loop result so callers see the block\n      const rejectScore = { total: 0, breakdown: { triggers: 0, anchors: 0, budget: 0, coherence: 0 }, issues: [`V-rule hard block: ${failedRuleIds.join(', ')}`] };\n      return {\n        parsed,\n        validation,\n        qualityLoopResult: {\n          passed: false,\n          score: rejectScore,\n          attempts: 0,\n          fixes: [],\n          rejected: true,\n          rejectionReason: `V-rule hard block: ${failedRuleIds.join(', ')}`,\n        },\n        sufficiencyResult: {\n          pass: false,\n          rejectionCode: MEMORY_SUFFICIENCY_REJECTION_CODE,\n          score: 0,\n          reasons: [`V-rule hard block: ${failedRuleIds.join(', ')}`],\n          evidenceCounts: { primary: 0, support: 0, total: 0, semanticChars: 0, uniqueWords: 0, anchors: 0, triggerPhrases: 0 },\n        },\n        templateContract: { valid: true, violations: [], missingAnchors: [], unexpectedTemplateArtifacts: [] } as MemoryTemplateContractResult,\n        specDocHealth: null,\n        finalizedFileContent: null,\n        sourceClassification: 'template-generated',\n      };\n    }\n    if (vRuleDisposition && vRuleDisposition.disposition === 'write_skip_index') {\n      console.warn(`[memory-save] V-rule index block for ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}: ${vRuleDisposition.indexBlockingRuleIds.join(', ')}`);\n      validation.warnings.push(`V-rule index block: ${vRuleDisposition.indexBlockingRuleIds.join(', ')}`);\n      // F07-002: Flag to skip indexing for write_skip_index disposition\n      const parsedWithIndexHints = parsed as ParsedMemoryWithIndexHints;\n      parsedWithIndexHints._skipIndex = true;\n      parsedWithIndexHints._vRuleIndexBlockIds = vRuleDisposition.indexBlockingRuleIds;\n    }\n  }\n\n  const qualityLoopResult = runQualityLoop(parsed.content, buildQualityLoopMetadata(parsed, database), {\n    emitEvalMetrics: options.emitEvalMetrics,\n    mode: options.qualityLoopMode ?? 'advisory',\n  });\n  parsed.qualityScore = qualityLoopResult.score.total;\n  parsed.qualityFlags = Array.from(new Set([\n    ...(parsed.qualityFlags ?? []),\n    ...qualityLoopResult.score.issues,\n  ]));\n  if (qualityLoopResult.fixedTriggerPhrases) {\n    parsed.triggerPhrases = qualityLoopResult.fixedTriggerPhrases;\n  }\n  const finalizedFileContent = qualityLoopResult.fixedContent\n    && qualityLoopResult.passed\n    ? qualityLoopResult.fixedContent\n    : null;\n  if (finalizedFileContent) {\n    parsed.content = finalizedFileContent;\n    parsed.contentHash = memoryParser.computeContentHash(parsed.content);\n  }\n\n  const sourceClassification = classifyMemorySaveSource(parsed.content);\n  if (sourceClassification === MANUAL_FALLBACK_SOURCE_CLASSIFICATION) {\n    const warning = 'Manual fallback save mode detected; standard generate-context template markers are missing.';\n    console.warn(`[memory-save] ${warning} ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}`);\n    validation.warnings.push(warning);\n  }\n\n  const sufficiencyResult = evaluateMemorySufficiency(\n    {\n      ...buildParsedMemoryEvidenceSnapshot(parsed),\n      sourceClassification,\n    },\n  );\n  applyInsufficiencyMetadata(parsed, sufficiencyResult);\n  const templateContract = validateMemoryTemplateContract(parsed.content);\n\n  // Non-blocking spec doc health annotation\n  // Canonical saves land directly in the spec folder (e.g. .../NNN-name/decision-record.md),\n  // so the immediate parent is usually the spec folder itself.\n  let specDocHealth: SpecDocHealthResult | null = null;\n  if (parsed.specFolder && parsed.filePath) {\n    try {\n      const absFilePath = path.resolve(parsed.filePath);\n      const immediateParent = path.dirname(absFilePath);\n      const candidates = [immediateParent, path.dirname(immediateParent)];\n      for (const candidate of candidates) {\n        if (fs.existsSync(path.join(candidate, 'spec.md'))) {\n          specDocHealth = evaluateSpecDocHealth(candidate);\n          break;\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n      console.warn(\n        `[memory-save] spec-doc-health annotation skipped for ${path.basename(parsed.filePath)}: ${message}`\n      );\n    }\n  }\n\n  return {\n    parsed,\n    validation,\n    qualityLoopResult,\n    sufficiencyResult,\n    templateContract,\n    specDocHealth,\n    finalizedFileContent,\n    sourceClassification,\n  };\n}\n\nasync function finalizeMemoryFileContent(\n  filePath: string,\n  content: string,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const backupPath = `${filePath}.${randomUUID().slice(0, 8)}.bak`;\n  const tempPath = `${filePath}.${randomUUID().slice(0, 8)}.tmp`;\n  let backupCreated = false;\n  let tempCreated = false;\n\n  try {\n    try {\n      await fs.promises.copyFile(filePath, backupPath);\n      backupCreated = true;\n    } catch (backupErr: unknown) {\n      const errCode = typeof backupErr === 'object' && backupErr !== null && 'code' in backupErr\n        ? String((backupErr as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code)\n        : '';\n      if (errCode !== 'ENOENT') {\n        throw backupErr;\n      }\n    }\n\n    await fs.promises.writeFile(tempPath, content, 'utf-8');\n    tempCreated = true;\n    await fs.promises.rename(tempPath, filePath);\n    tempCreated = false;\n  } catch (writeErr: unknown) {\n    if (tempCreated) {\n      try {\n        await fs.promises.unlink(tempPath);\n      } catch {\n        // Best-effort cleanup only.\n      }\n    }\n    if (backupCreated) {\n      try {\n        await fs.promises.copyFile(backupPath, filePath);\n      } catch (restoreErr: unknown) {\n        console.warn(\n          '[memory-save] Auto-fix file restore failed after finalize error:',\n          restoreErr instanceof Error ? restoreErr.message : String(restoreErr),\n        );\n      }\n    }\n    throw writeErr;\n  } finally {\n    if (tempCreated) {\n      try {\n        await fs.promises.unlink(tempPath);\n      } catch {\n        // Best-effort cleanup only.\n      }\n    }\n    if (backupCreated) {\n      try {\n        await fs.promises.unlink(backupPath);\n      } catch {\n        // Best-effort cleanup only.\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nfunction appendResultWarning<T extends Record<string, unknown>>(result: T, warning: string | null): T {\n  if (!warning) {\n    return result;\n  }\n\n  const r = result as Record<string, unknown>;\n  const warnings = Array.isArray(r.warnings)\n    ? [...(r.warnings as string[])]\n    : [];\n  warnings.push(warning);\n  r.warnings = warnings;\n  return result;\n}\n\nclass SaveTimeReconsolidationAbort extends Error {\n  readonly result: {\n    status: 'failed';\n    reason: ReconsolidationFailureReason;\n    warnings?: string[];\n    persistedState?: ReconsolidationOperationState;\n  };\n\n  constructor(result: SaveTimeReconsolidationAbort['result']) {\n    super(result.reason);\n    this.name = 'SaveTimeReconsolidationAbort';\n    this.result = result;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction buildSaveTimeReconsolidationFailureResult(args: {\n  parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>;\n  validation: { warnings: string[] };\n  reconWarnings: string[];\n  failure: SaveTimeReconsolidationAbort['result'];\n  message?: string;\n}): IndexResult {\n  const warnings = [\n    ...args.validation.warnings,\n    ...args.reconWarnings,\n    ...(args.failure.warnings ?? []),\n  ];\n\n  return {\n    status: 'error',\n    id: 0,\n    specFolder: args.parsed.specFolder,\n    title: args.parsed.title ?? '',\n    triggerPhrases: args.parsed.triggerPhrases,\n    contextType: args.parsed.contextType,\n    importanceTier: args.parsed.importanceTier,\n    memoryType: args.parsed.memoryType,\n    memoryTypeSource: args.parsed.memoryTypeSource,\n    qualityScore: args.parsed.qualityScore,\n    qualityFlags: args.parsed.qualityFlags,\n    warnings,\n    error: args.message ?? `Save-time reconsolidation failed: ${args.failure.reason}`,\n    message: args.message ?? `Save-time reconsolidation failed: ${args.failure.reason}`,\n    saveTimeReconsolidation: args.failure,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction recordCrossPathPeSupersedes(\n  database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n  memoryId: number,\n  supersededMemoryId: number | null,\n  samePathMemoryId: number | null,\n  reason: string | null | undefined,\n): void {\n  if (supersededMemoryId == null || supersededMemoryId === samePathMemoryId) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  causalEdges.init(database);\n  const evidence = reason && reason.trim().length > 0\n    ? reason.trim()\n    : 'Prediction-error contradiction across different file paths';\n  causalEdges.insertEdge(\n    String(memoryId),\n    String(supersededMemoryId),\n    causalEdges.RELATION_TYPES.SUPERSEDES,\n    1.0,\n    evidence,\n    true,\n    'auto',\n  );\n}\n\ninterface ChunkedInsertTracker {\n  parentId: number | null;\n  childIds: Set<number>;\n}\n\nfunction createChunkedInsertTracker(): ChunkedInsertTracker {\n  return {\n    parentId: null,\n    childIds: new Set<number>(),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction trackChunkedInsert(\n  tracker: ChunkedInsertTracker,\n  memoryId: number,\n  fields: Record<string, unknown>,\n): void {\n  if (typeof fields.chunk_index === 'number') {\n    tracker.childIds.add(memoryId);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  if (tracker.parentId == null) {\n    tracker.parentId = memoryId;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction rollbackCreatedChunkTree(\n  database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n  tracker: ChunkedInsertTracker,\n): { attempted: boolean; cleaned: boolean; error?: string } {\n  if (tracker.parentId == null) {\n    return { attempted: false, cleaned: false };\n  }\n\n  const childIds = new Set<number>(tracker.childIds);\n  try {\n    const persistedChildRows = database.prepare(`\n      SELECT id\n      FROM memory_index\n      WHERE parent_id = ?\n    `).all(tracker.parentId) as Array<{ id: number }>;\n    for (const row of persistedChildRows) {\n      childIds.add(row.id);\n    }\n  } catch {\n    // Best-effort lookup only. Tracked IDs remain authoritative for cleanup.\n  }\n\n  const cleanupErrors: string[] = [];\n  for (const childId of childIds) {\n    try {\n      if (!delete_memory_from_database(database, childId)) {\n        cleanupErrors.push(`Chunk ${childId} was not deleted`);\n      }\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      cleanupErrors.push(`Chunk ${childId} cleanup failed: ${getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error)}`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  try {\n    if (!delete_memory_from_database(database, tracker.parentId)) {\n      cleanupErrors.push(`Parent ${tracker.parentId} was not deleted`);\n    }\n  } catch (error: unknown) {\n    cleanupErrors.push(`Parent ${tracker.parentId} cleanup failed: ${getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error)}`);\n  }\n\n  if (cleanupErrors.length > 0) {\n    return {\n      attempted: true,\n      cleaned: false,\n      error: cleanupErrors.join('; '),\n    };\n  }\n\n  return { attempted: true, cleaned: true };\n}\n\nfunction captureAtomicSaveOriginalState(filePath: string): { existed: boolean; content: string | null } {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n    return { existed: false, content: null };\n  }\n\n  return {\n    existed: true,\n    content: fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8'),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error: unknown): string {\n  return error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n}\n\nfunction deleteAtomicSaveFile(filePath: string): { deleted: boolean; existed: boolean; error?: string } {\n  const existed = fs.existsSync(filePath);\n  if (!existed) {\n    return { deleted: false, existed: false };\n  }\n\n  try {\n    fs.unlinkSync(filePath);\n    return { deleted: true, existed: true };\n  } catch (error: unknown) {\n    return {\n      deleted: false,\n      existed: true,\n      error: getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error),\n    };\n  }\n}\n\nfunction restoreAtomicSaveOriginalState(\n  filePath: string,\n  originalState: { existed: boolean; content: string | null },\n): { restored: boolean; error?: string } {\n  try {\n    if (!originalState.existed) {\n      const deleteResult = deleteAtomicSaveFile(filePath);\n      if (!deleteResult.existed || deleteResult.deleted) {\n        return { restored: true };\n      }\n      return {\n        restored: false,\n        error: deleteResult.error ?? `Failed to remove promoted file at ${filePath}`,\n      };\n    }\n\n    if (typeof originalState.content !== 'string') {\n      return { restored: false, error: 'Original file content is unavailable for rollback' };\n    }\n\n    fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(filePath), { recursive: true });\n    fs.writeFileSync(filePath, originalState.content, 'utf-8');\n    return { restored: true };\n  } catch (error: unknown) {\n    return {\n      restored: false,\n      error: getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error),\n    };\n  }\n}\n\nfunction cleanupAtomicSavePendingFile(\n  pendingPath: string,\n): { cleaned: boolean; existed: boolean; error?: string } {\n  try {\n    const deleteResult = deleteAtomicSaveFile(pendingPath);\n    if (!deleteResult.existed || deleteResult.deleted) {\n      return {\n        cleaned: true,\n        existed: deleteResult.existed,\n      };\n    }\n    return {\n      cleaned: false,\n      existed: deleteResult.existed,\n      error: deleteResult.error ?? `Failed to remove pending file at ${pendingPath}`,\n    };\n  } catch (error: unknown) {\n    return {\n      cleaned: false,\n      existed: true,\n      error: getAtomicSaveErrorMessage(error),\n    };\n  }\n}\n\nfunction applyRoutedSaveHints(\n  parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n  routing: RoutedSaveOptions,\n): ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile> {\n  const parsedWithHints = parsed as ParsedMemoryWithIndexHints & Record<string, unknown>;\n  if (routing.targetDocPath) {\n    parsedWithHints.targetDocPath = routing.targetDocPath;\n    parsedWithHints.target_doc_path = routing.targetDocPath;\n  }\n  if (routing.targetAnchorId) {\n    parsedWithHints.targetAnchorId = routing.targetAnchorId;\n    parsedWithHints.target_anchor_id = routing.targetAnchorId;\n    parsedWithHints.anchorId = routing.targetAnchorId;\n    parsedWithHints.anchor_id = routing.targetAnchorId;\n  }\n  if (routing.routeAs) {\n    parsedWithHints.routeAs = routing.routeAs;\n    parsedWithHints.route_as = routing.routeAs;\n  }\n  if (routing.continuitySourceKey) {\n    parsedWithHints.continuitySourceKey = routing.continuitySourceKey;\n    parsedWithHints.continuity_source_key = routing.continuitySourceKey;\n  }\n  return parsedWithHints;\n}\n\nfunction buildRoutedSaveOptions(\n  filePath: string,\n  routeAs?: RouteCategory,\n  mergeModeHint?: MergeModeHint,\n  targetAnchorId?: string,\n): RoutedSaveOptions | undefined {\n  if (!routeAs && !mergeModeHint && !targetAnchorId) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  return {\n    targetDocPath: filePath,\n    ...(routeAs ? { routeAs } : {}),\n    ...(mergeModeHint ? { mergeModeHint } : {}),\n    ...(targetAnchorId ? { targetAnchorId } : {}),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction shouldUseCanonicalRouting(_params: Pick<AtomicSaveParams, 'routeAs' | 'mergeModeHint' | 'targetAnchorId'>): boolean {\n  // Test-only bypass: allows the atomic-save failure-injection suite\n  // to exercise the legacy prepareParsedMemoryForIndexing path without\n  // setting up full Tier 3 classifier fixtures.\n  if (process.env.SPECKIT_TEST_DISABLE_CANONICAL_ROUTING === 'true') return false;\n  return true; // Canonical routing is always enabled (Tier 3 LLM routing on by default)\n}\n\nfunction pickRoutedIdentityValue(value: unknown): string | null {\n  return typeof value === 'string' && value.trim().length > 0 ? value.trim() : null;\n}\n\nfunction pickRouteCategory(value: unknown): RouteCategory | null {\n  const normalized = pickRoutedIdentityValue(value);\n  if (!normalized || !ROUTE_CATEGORIES.has(normalized as RouteCategory)) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return normalized as RouteCategory;\n}\n\nfunction isMergeModeHint(value: unknown): value is MergeModeHint {\n  return value === 'append-as-paragraph'\n    || value === 'insert-new-adr'\n    || value === 'append-table-row'\n    || value === 'update-in-place'\n    || value === 'append-section';\n}\n\nfunction resolveRoutedRecordIdentity(\n  parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>,\n  routedFilePath: string,\n  routing: RoutedSaveOptions,\n): RoutedRecordIdentity {\n  const routedRecord = parsed as unknown as Record<string, unknown>;\n  const routeAs = pickRouteCategory(routing.routeAs ?? routedRecord.routeAs ?? routedRecord.route_as);\n  const continuitySourceKey = pickRoutedIdentityValue(\n    routing.continuitySourceKey\n    ?? routedRecord.continuitySourceKey\n    ?? routedRecord.continuity_source_key\n    ?? routedRecord.sourceKey\n    ?? routedRecord.source_key,\n  );\n  const explicitTargetAnchorId = pickRoutedIdentityValue(\n    routing.targetAnchorId\n    ?? routedRecord.targetAnchorId\n    ?? routedRecord.target_anchor_id\n    ?? routedRecord.anchorId\n    ?? routedRecord.anchor_id,\n  );\n\n  return {\n    targetDocPath: routing.targetDocPath ?? routedFilePath,\n    canonicalFilePath: routing.canonicalFilePath ?? getCanonicalPathKey(routing.targetDocPath ?? routedFilePath),\n    targetAnchorId: explicitTargetAnchorId ?? ((routeAs === 'metadata_only' || continuitySourceKey !== null) ? ROUTED_CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID : null),\n    routeAs,\n    continuitySourceKey,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction toCanonicalPacketLevel(level: number | null): CanonicalPacketLevel {\n  if (level === 1) return 'L1';\n  if (level === 2) return 'L2';\n  if (level === 3) return 'L3';\n  return 'L3+';\n}\n\nfunction toValidatorLevel(packetLevel: CanonicalPacketLevel): string {\n  return packetLevel.replace(/^L/u, '');\n}\n\nfunction normalizeForFingerprint(content: string): string {\n  return content\n    .replace(/\\r\\n/g, '\\n')\n    .replace(/[ \\t]+$/gm, '');\n}\n\nfunction buildContinuityFingerprint(content: string): string {\n  return `sha256:${createHash('sha256').update(normalizeForFingerprint(content), 'utf8').digest('hex')}`;\n}\n\nfunction normalizePhaseAnchor(value: string | null | undefined): string | null {\n  if (typeof value !== 'string') {\n    return null;\n  }\n  const trimmed = value.trim();\n  const match = trimmed.match(/^phase(?:[\\s_-]+)?(\\d+)$/iu);\n  return match ? `phase-${match[1]}` : null;\n}\n\nfunction inferPhaseAnchorFromText(text: string): string | null {\n  const match = text.match(/\\bphase(?:[\\s_-]+)?(\\d+)\\b/iu);\n  return match ? `phase-${match[1]}` : null;\n}\n\nfunction inferPhaseAnchorFromSpecFolder(specFolder: string): string | null {\n  return inferPhaseAnchorFromText(specFolder.replace(/\\//g, ' '));\n}\n\nfunction deriveLikelyPhaseAnchorForCanonicalRouting(params: {\n  routingChunkText: string;\n  specFolder: string;\n  targetAnchorId?: string;\n}): string | null {\n  return normalizePhaseAnchor(params.targetAnchorId)\n    ?? inferPhaseAnchorFromText(params.routingChunkText)\n    ?? inferPhaseAnchorFromSpecFolder(params.specFolder);\n}\n\nfunction stripMarkdownFrontmatter(markdown: string): string {\n  return markdown.replace(/^(?:\\uFEFF)?---\\r?\\n[\\s\\S]*?\\r?\\n---(?:\\r?\\n)?/u, '');\n}\n\nfunction normalizeRoutingChunkText(markdown: string): string {\n  return stripMarkdownFrontmatter(markdown)\n    .replace(/<!--[\\s\\S]*?-->/g, ' ')\n    .replace(/\\r\\n/g, '\\n')\n    .replace(/\\n{3,}/g, '\\n\\n')\n    .trim();\n}\n\nfunction extractFrontmatterScalar(markdown: string, key: string): string | null {\n  const frontmatterMatch = markdown.match(/^(?:\\uFEFF)?---\\r?\\n([\\s\\S]*?)\\r?\\n---(?:\\r?\\n)?/u);\n  if (!frontmatterMatch?.[1]) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const escapedKey = key.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\\]\\\\]/g, '\\\\$&');\n  const scalarMatch = frontmatterMatch[1].match(\n    new RegExp(`^\\\\s*${escapedKey}:\\\\s*[\"']?([^\"'\\r\\n]+)[\"']?\\\\s*$`, 'imu'),\n  );\n  return scalarMatch?.[1]?.trim() ?? null;\n}\n\nfunction hasNumericSpecFolderName(folderPath: string): boolean {\n  return /^\\d{3}(?:[-_].+)?$/u.test(path.basename(folderPath));\n}\n\nfunction hasChildSpecFolders(specFolderAbsolute: string): boolean {\n  try {\n    const entries = fs.readdirSync(specFolderAbsolute, { withFileTypes: true });\n    return entries.some((entry) => {\n      if (!entry.isDirectory() || !hasNumericSpecFolderName(entry.name)) {\n        return false;\n      }\n      return fs.existsSync(path.join(specFolderAbsolute, entry.name, 'spec.md'));\n    });\n  } catch {\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction deriveCanonicalPacketKind(\n  specFolderAbsolute: string,\n  specFolderKey: string,\n): CanonicalPacketKind {\n  const specMdPath = path.join(specFolderAbsolute, 'spec.md');\n  let specContent = '';\n  try {\n    specContent = fs.readFileSync(specMdPath, 'utf8');\n  } catch {\n    specContent = '';\n  }\n\n  const packetType = extractFrontmatterScalar(specContent, 'type')?.toLowerCase() ?? '';\n  const title = extractFrontmatterScalar(specContent, 'title')?.toLowerCase() ?? '';\n  const description = extractFrontmatterScalar(specContent, 'description')?.toLowerCase() ?? '';\n  const folderName = path.basename(specFolderAbsolute).toLowerCase();\n  const semanticHint = `${folderName} ${title} ${description}`;\n\n  if (packetType === 'research') {\n    return 'research';\n  }\n  if (/\\bremediation\\b/u.test(semanticHint)) {\n    return 'remediation';\n  }\n\n  const parentFolder = path.dirname(specFolderAbsolute);\n  const hasNumericParentPacket = hasNumericSpecFolderName(parentFolder)\n    && fs.existsSync(path.join(parentFolder, 'spec.md'));\n  if (!hasChildSpecFolders(specFolderAbsolute) && hasNumericParentPacket) {\n    return 'phase';\n  }\n\n  const normalizedSpecFolder = specFolderKey.replace(/^specs\\//u, '');\n  const depth = normalizedSpecFolder.split('/').filter(Boolean).length;\n  if (depth <= 2) {\n    return 'feature';\n  }\n\n  return hasNumericParentPacket ? 'phase' : 'feature';\n}\n\nfunction getTier3RoutingEndpoint(): string | null {\n  const endpoint = process.env.LLM_REFORMULATION_ENDPOINT?.trim();\n  return endpoint ? endpoint.replace(/\\/+$/u, '') : null;\n}\n\nfunction extractTier3MessageText(content: unknown): string | null {\n  if (typeof content === 'string') {\n    const trimmed = content.trim();\n    return trimmed.length > 0 ? trimmed : null;\n  }\n  if (Array.isArray(content)) {\n    const text = content\n      .map((entry) => {\n        if (!entry || typeof entry !== 'object') {\n          return '';\n        }\n        const textValue = (entry as { text?: unknown }).text;\n        return typeof textValue === 'string' ? textValue : '';\n      })\n      .join('')\n      .trim();\n    return text.length > 0 ? text : null;\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction isTier3RawResponseShape(parsed: unknown): parsed is Tier3RawResponse {\n  if (!parsed || typeof parsed !== 'object') {\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  const record = parsed as Record<string, unknown>;\n  return typeof record.category === 'string'\n    && typeof record.confidence === 'number'\n    && typeof record.target_doc === 'string'\n    && typeof record.target_anchor === 'string'\n    && typeof record.merge_mode === 'string'\n    && typeof record.reasoning === 'string';\n}\n\nfunction parseTier3ClassifierResponse(rawText: string): Tier3RawResponse | null {\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(rawText) as Record<string, unknown>;\n    if (!parsed || typeof parsed !== 'object') {\n      return null;\n    }\n    return isTier3RawResponseShape(parsed) ? parsed : null;\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nasync function classifyWithTier3Llm(input: Tier3ClassifierInput): Promise<Tier3RawResponse | null> {\n  const endpoint = getTier3RoutingEndpoint();\n  if (!endpoint) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const apiKey = process.env.LLM_REFORMULATION_API_KEY?.trim() ?? '';\n  const contract = getTier3Contract();\n  const prompt = buildTier3Prompt(input);\n  const controller = new AbortController();\n  const timeoutId = setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), contract.timeoutMs);\n\n  try {\n    const response = await fetch(`${endpoint}/chat/completions`, {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n        ...(apiKey ? { Authorization: `Bearer ${apiKey}` } : {}),\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        model: contract.model,\n        messages: [\n          { role: 'system', content: prompt.system },\n          { role: 'user', content: prompt.user },\n        ],\n        reasoning_effort: contract.reasoningEffort,\n        temperature: contract.temperature,\n        max_tokens: contract.maxOutputTokens,\n        response_format: { type: 'json_object' },\n      }),\n      signal: controller.signal,\n    });\n\n    clearTimeout(timeoutId);\n\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    const data = await response.json() as {\n      choices?: Array<{\n        message?: {\n          content?: unknown;\n        };\n      }>;\n    };\n    const rawText = extractTier3MessageText(data.choices?.[0]?.message?.content);\n    return rawText ? parseTier3ClassifierResponse(rawText) : null;\n  } catch {\n    clearTimeout(timeoutId);\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction buildCanonicalRouter(options: { tier3Enabled?: boolean } = {}) {\n  return createContentRouter({\n    classifyWithTier3: classifyWithTier3Llm,\n    cache: tier3RoutingCache,\n    tier3Enabled: options.tier3Enabled,\n  });\n}\n\nfunction collapseInlineWhitespace(value: string): string {\n  return value.replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n}\n\nfunction clipInlineText(value: string, maxLength = 96): string {\n  const normalized = collapseInlineWhitespace(value);\n  return normalized.length <= maxLength ? normalized : `${normalized.slice(0, maxLength - 3).trimEnd()}...`;\n}\n\nfunction extractParagraphs(markdown: string): string[] {\n  return normalizeRoutingChunkText(markdown)\n    .split(/\\n\\s*\\n/g)\n    .map((entry) => collapseInlineWhitespace(entry))\n    .filter(Boolean);\n}\n\nfunction extractListItems(markdown: string): string[] {\n  return normalizeRoutingChunkText(markdown)\n    .split(/\\r?\\n/g)\n    .map((line) => line.match(/^\\s*(?:[-*+]|\\d+\\.)\\s+(.+)$/u)?.[1] ?? '')\n    .map((line) => clipInlineText(line, 120))\n    .filter(Boolean);\n}\n\nfunction resolveSpecFolderAbsoluteFromFilePath(filePath: string, specFolder: string): string {\n  const normalizedFilePath = filePath.replace(/\\\\/g, '/');\n  const normalizedSpecFolder = specFolder.replace(/^specs\\//u, '');\n  const markers = [\n    `/specs/${normalizedSpecFolder}/`,\n    `/specs/${specFolder}/`,\n  ];\n\n  for (const marker of markers) {\n    const markerIndex = normalizedFilePath.lastIndexOf(marker);\n    if (markerIndex >= 0) {\n      return path.normalize(`${normalizedFilePath.slice(0, markerIndex)}${marker.slice(0, -1)}`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return path.resolve(path.dirname(filePath), '..');\n}\n\nfunction resolveMetadataHostDocPath(specFolderAbsolute: string): string {\n  const implementationSummaryPath = path.join(specFolderAbsolute, 'implementation-summary.md');\n  if (fs.existsSync(implementationSummaryPath)) {\n    return implementationSummaryPath;\n  }\n\n  return path.join(specFolderAbsolute, 'spec.md');\n}\n\nfunction resolveCanonicalTargetDocPath(\n  specFolderAbsolute: string,\n  routedDocPath: string,\n): string {\n  if (routedDocPath === 'spec-frontmatter' || routedDocPath === 'implementation-summary.md') {\n    return resolveMetadataHostDocPath(specFolderAbsolute);\n  }\n  return path.join(specFolderAbsolute, routedDocPath);\n}\n\nfunction clampRoutingConfidence(value: number): number {\n  return Math.min(1, Math.max(0, value));\n}\n\nfunction selectTier2FailOpenFallback(\n  specFolderAbsolute: string,\n  decision: RoutingDecision,\n): {\n  category: RouteCategory;\n  confidence: number;\n  targetDocPath: string;\n  routedDocPath: string;\n  targetAnchorId: string;\n  mergeMode: RoutingDecision['target']['mergeMode'];\n  warningMessage: string;\n} | null {\n  if (decision.tierUsed !== 3) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  for (const hit of decision.tier2TopK) {\n    if (hit.category === 'drop') {\n      continue;\n    }\n    const fallbackConfidence = clampRoutingConfidence(hit.similarity - TIER2_FALLBACK_PENALTY);\n    if (fallbackConfidence < TIER3_THRESHOLD) {\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    const targetDocPath = resolveCanonicalTargetDocPath(specFolderAbsolute, hit.target_doc);\n    if (!fs.existsSync(targetDocPath)) {\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    return {\n      category: hit.category as RouteCategory,\n      confidence: fallbackConfidence,\n      targetDocPath,\n      routedDocPath: hit.target_doc,\n      targetAnchorId: hit.target_anchor,\n      mergeMode: hit.merge_intent,\n      warningMessage: `Tier 3 routing was unusable; fell back to Tier 2 prototype match ${hit.category}.`,\n    };\n  }\n\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction buildFallbackContinuityRecord(params: {\n  parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>;\n  routeCategory: RouteCategory;\n  targetDocPath: string;\n  specFolderAbsolute: string;\n  currentContent: string;\n}): ThinContinuityRecord {\n  const { parsed, routeCategory, targetDocPath, specFolderAbsolute, currentContent } = params;\n  const relativeTargetPath = path.relative(specFolderAbsolute, targetDocPath).replace(/\\\\/g, '/');\n  const absoluteSpecFolder = specFolderAbsolute.replace(/\\\\/g, '/');\n  const packetPointerFromPath = absoluteSpecFolder.includes('/specs/')\n    ? absoluteSpecFolder.split('/specs/')[1]\n    : parsed.specFolder.replace(/^specs\\//u, '');\n  const title = clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? (normalizeRoutingChunkText(currentContent) || 'Updated canonical continuity'));\n  const nextActionByRoute: Record<RouteCategory, string> = {\n    narrative_progress: 'Review routed update',\n    narrative_delivery: 'Verify delivery route',\n    decision: 'Review ADR follow-up',\n    handover_state: 'Resume routed handover',\n    research_finding: 'Review cited finding',\n    task_update: 'Verify task alignment',\n    metadata_only: 'Refresh continuity',\n    drop: 'Inspect refused route',\n  };\n\n  return {\n    packet_pointer: packetPointerFromPath,\n    last_updated_at: new Date().toISOString().replace(/\\.\\d{3}Z$/u, 'Z'),\n    last_updated_by: 'memory-save',\n    recent_action: title,\n    next_safe_action: nextActionByRoute[routeCategory],\n    blockers: [],\n    key_files: relativeTargetPath ? [relativeTargetPath] : [],\n    session_dedup: {\n      fingerprint: buildContinuityFingerprint(currentContent),\n      session_id: 'memory-save',\n      parent_session_id: null,\n    },\n    completion_pct: 0,\n    open_questions: [],\n    answered_questions: [],\n  };\n}\n\nfunction buildCanonicalMergePayload(params: {\n  parsed: ReturnType<typeof memoryParser.parseMemoryFile>;\n  routeCategory: RouteCategory;\n  mergeMode: MergeModeHint;\n  content: string;\n}): Record<string, unknown> {\n  const { parsed, routeCategory, mergeMode, content } = params;\n  const paragraphs = extractParagraphs(content);\n  const firstParagraph = paragraphs[0] ?? clipInlineText(content, 160);\n  const secondParagraph = paragraphs[1] ?? firstParagraph;\n  const listItems = extractListItems(content);\n\n  switch (mergeMode) {\n    case 'append-as-paragraph':\n      return { paragraph: firstParagraph };\n    case 'append-section':\n      return {\n        title: clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? `${routeCategory.replace(/_/g, ' ')} update`, 72),\n        body: normalizeRoutingChunkText(content) || firstParagraph,\n      };\n    case 'insert-new-adr':\n      return {\n        title: clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? 'Captured canonical decision', 80),\n        context: firstParagraph,\n        decision: secondParagraph,\n        consequences: listItems.slice(0, 3),\n      };\n    case 'update-in-place': {\n      const targetId = content.match(/\\b(?:T\\d{3}|CHK-\\d{3})\\b/u)?.[0];\n      if (!targetId) {\n        throw new Error(`Canonical task update could not find a target task/checklist id in routed content.`);\n      }\n      const checked = /\\[[xX]\\]/u.test(content)\n        ? true\n        : (/\\[[ ]\\]/u.test(content) ? false : undefined);\n      return {\n        targetId,\n        ...(checked === undefined ? {} : { checked }),\n        evidence: clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? firstParagraph, 96),\n      };\n    }\n    case 'append-table-row':\n      return {\n        cells: [\n          clipInlineText(parsed.title ?? routeCategory, 48),\n          'Updated',\n          clipInlineText(firstParagraph, 96),\n        ],\n        dedupeColumn: 0,\n      };\n    default:\n      return { paragraph: firstParagraph };\n  }\n}\n\nasync function buildCanonicalAtomicPreparedSave(\n  params: AtomicSaveParams,\n  database: ReturnType<typeof requireDb>,\n): Promise<{ status: 'ready'; prepared: CanonicalAtomicPrepared; persistedContent: string; persistedFilePath: string } | { status: 'abort'; result: AtomicSaveResult }> {\n  const preparedMemory = prepareParsedMemoryForIndexing(\n    memoryParser.parseMemoryContent(params.file_path, params.content),\n    database,\n    {\n      qualityLoopMode: params.plannerMode === 'full-auto' ? 'full-auto' : 'advisory',\n    },\n  );\n  if (!preparedMemory.validation.valid) {\n    return {\n      status: 'abort',\n      result: {\n        success: false,\n        filePath: params.file_path,\n        status: 'error',\n        summary: 'Atomic save preflight failed',\n        message: 'Parsed content failed validation before canonical atomic save',\n        error: `Validation failed: ${preparedMemory.validation.errors.join(', ')}`,\n      },\n    };\n  }\n\n  if (preparedMemory.qualityLoopResult.fixes.length > 0 && preparedMemory.qualityLoopResult.passed && preparedMemory.qualityLoopResult.fixedContent) {\n    console.error(`[memory-save] Quality loop applied ${preparedMemory.qualityLoopResult.fixes.length} auto-fix(es) for ${path.basename(params.file_path)} before canonical pending-file promotion`);\n  }\n\n  const specFolderAbsolute = resolveSpecFolderAbsoluteFromFilePath(params.file_path, preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder);\n  const packetLevel = toCanonicalPacketLevel(detectSpecLevelFromParsed(path.join(specFolderAbsolute, 'spec.md')));\n  const packetKind = deriveCanonicalPacketKind(specFolderAbsolute, preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder);\n  const saveMode = params.routeAs ? 'route-as' : 'natural';\n  const tier3Enabled = isTier3RoutingEnabled();\n  const router = buildCanonicalRouter({ tier3Enabled });\n  const routingChunkText = normalizeRoutingChunkText(params.content);\n  const likelyPhaseAnchor = deriveLikelyPhaseAnchorForCanonicalRouting({\n    routingChunkText,\n    specFolder: preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder,\n    targetAnchorId: params.targetAnchorId,\n  });\n  const decision = await router.classifyContent(\n    {\n      id: path.basename(params.file_path),\n      text: routingChunkText,\n      sourceField: params.routeAs === 'metadata_only' ? 'preflight' : 'observations',\n      routeAs: params.routeAs,\n      metadata: params.targetAnchorId ? { targetAnchorId: params.targetAnchorId } : undefined,\n    },\n    {\n      specFolder: preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder,\n      packetLevel,\n      sessionMeta: {\n        spec_folder: preparedMemory.parsed.specFolder,\n        packet_level: packetLevel,\n        packet_kind: packetKind,\n        save_mode: saveMode,\n        recent_docs_touched: [],\n        recent_anchors_touched: [],\n        likely_phase_anchor: likelyPhaseAnchor,\n      },\n    },\n  );\n\n  let effectiveDecision = decision;\n  const applyTier2FailOpenFallback = (): boolean => {","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":1515,"totalLines":1516,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts","time":{"start":1780738219132,"end":1780738219162}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_076c916f5a177fda016a23e8aaf34881918435baec645f2c64"}},"id":"prt_e9c44dc5f001Akmn0pos7q4KTM","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","messageID":"msg_e9c44b8f8001v2rOknVCFoX4el"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738219168,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_DhmVssgYPWngbFS66Tu3SKCv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: // MODULE: Memory Search\n3: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n5:    1. DEPENDENCIES\n6: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n7: \n8: import * as toolCache from '../lib/cache/tool-cache.js';\n9: import * as causalEdges from '../lib/storage/causal-edges.js';\n10: import * as sessionManager from '../lib/session/session-manager.js';\n11: import * as intentClassifier from '../lib/search/intent-classifier.js';\n12: // TierClassifier, crossEncoder imports removed — only used by legacy V1 pipeline.\n13: import { isSessionBoostEnabled, isCausalBoostEnabled, isCommunitySearchFallbackEnabled, isDualRetrievalEnabled, isIntentAutoProfileEnabled } from '../lib/search/search-flags.js';\n14: import { searchCommunities } from '../lib/search/community-search.js';\n15: // 4-stage pipeline architecture\n16: import { executePipeline } from '../lib/search/pipeline/index.js';\n17: import type { PipelineConfig, PipelineResult } from '../lib/search/pipeline/index.js';\n18: import type { IntentWeightsConfig } from '../lib/search/pipeline/types.js';\n19: import { initConsumptionLog, logConsumptionEvent } from '../lib/telemetry/consumption-logger.js';\n20: import * as retrievalTelemetry from '../lib/telemetry/retrieval-telemetry.js';\n21: // Artifact-class routing (spec/plan/tasks/checklist/memory)\n22: import { getStrategyForQuery } from '../lib/search/artifact-routing.js';\n23: import { routeQuery } from '../lib/search/query-router.js';\n24: import { createEmptyQueryPlan, type QueryPlan } from '../lib/query/query-plan.js';\n25: import { getGraphReadinessSnapshotFromMarker } from '../lib/code-graph-boundary.js';\n26: import { mapGraphReadinessToTelemetry } from '../lib/search/graph-readiness-mapper.js';\n27: import {\n28:   buildSearchDecisionEnvelope,\n29:   type SearchDecisionEnvelope,\n30: } from '../lib/search/search-decision-envelope.js';\n31: import { recordSearchDecision } from '../lib/search/decision-audit.js';\n32: // Chunk reassembly (extracted from this file)\n33: import { collapseAndReassembleChunkResults } from '../lib/search/chunk-reassembly.js';\n34: // Search utilities (extracted from this file)\n35: import {\n36:   filterByMinQualityScore,\n37:   resolveQualityThreshold,\n38:   buildCacheArgs,\n39:   resolveRowContextType,\n40:   resolveArtifactRoutingQuery,\n41:   applyArtifactRouting,\n42: } from '../lib/search/search-utils.js';\n43: // CacheArgsInput used internally by buildCacheArgs (lib/search/search-utils.ts)\n44: // Eval channel tracking (extracted from this file)\n45: import {\n46:   collectEvalChannelsFromRow,\n47:   buildEvalChannelPayloads,\n48:   summarizeGraphWalkDiagnostics,\n49: } from '../lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.js';\n50: import type { EvalChannelPayload } from '../lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.js';\n51: \n52: // Eval logger — fail-safe, no-op when SPECKIT_EVAL_LOGGING !== \"true\"\n53: import { logSearchQuery, logChannelResult, logFinalResult } from '../lib/eval/eval-logger.js';\n54: import {\n55:   logFeedbackEvents,\n56:   isImplicitFeedbackLogEnabled,\n57: } from '../lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.js';\n58: import type { FeedbackEvent } from '../lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.js';\n59: import { trackQueryAndDetect, logResultCited } from '../lib/feedback/query-flow-tracker.js';\n60: \n61: // Core utilities\n62: import { checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\n63: import { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\n64: import { validateQuery, requireDb, toErrorMessage } from '../utils/index.js';\n65: \n66: // Response envelope + formatters\n67: import { createMCPErrorResponse, createMCPSuccessResponse } from '../lib/response/envelope.js';\n68: import { formatSearchResults } from '../formatters/index.js';\n69: \n70: // Shared handler types\n71: import type { MCPResponse, IntentClassification } from './types.js';\n72: \n73: // Retrieval trace contracts (C136-08)\n74: import { createTrace } from '@spec-kit/shared/contracts/retrieval-trace';\n75: import { buildAdaptiveShadowProposal } from '../lib/cognitive/adaptive-ranking.js';\n76: import { normalizeScopeContext, filterRowsByScope } from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\n77: import {\n78:   attachSessionTransitionTrace,\n79:   type SessionTransitionTrace,\n80: } from '../lib/search/session-transition.js';\n81: \n82: // Mode-Aware Response Shape\n83: import {\n84:   applyProfileToEnvelope,\n85:   isResponseProfileEnabled,\n86: } from '../lib/response/profile-formatters.js';\n87: import {\n88:   buildProgressiveResponse,\n89:   extractSnippets,\n90:   isProgressiveDisclosureEnabled,\n91:   resolveCursor,\n92: } from '../lib/search/progressive-disclosure.js';\n93: import {\n94:   SPEC_DOCUMENT_FILENAMES,\n95:   canClassifyAsSpecDocument,\n96:   normalizeSpecPath,\n97: } from '../lib/config/spec-doc-paths.js';\n98: import {\n99:   getLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot,\n100:   resetLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot,\n101: } from '../lib/search/sqlite-fts.js';\n102: import type { LexicalCapabilitySnapshot } from '../lib/search/sqlite-fts.js';\n103: import { evaluatePublicationGate } from '../lib/context/publication-gate.js';\n104: import {\n105:   deduplicateResults as deduplicateWithSessionState,\n106:   isSessionRetrievalStateEnabled,\n107:   manager as retrievalSessionStateManager,\n108:   refineForGoal,\n109: } from '../lib/search/session-state.js';\n110: \n111: // Type imports for casting\n112: import type { IntentType, IntentWeights as IntentClassifierWeights } from '../lib/search/intent-classifier.js';\n113: import type { RawSearchResult } from '../formatters/index.js';\n114: // RoutingResult, WeightedResult — now used internally by lib/search/search-utils.ts\n115: \n116: // Feature catalog: Semantic and lexical search (memory_search)\n117: // Feature catalog: Hybrid search pipeline\n118: // Feature catalog: 4-stage pipeline architecture\n119: // Feature catalog: Quality-aware 3-tier search fallback\n120: \n121: \n122: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n123:    2. TYPES\n124: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n125: \n126: /**\n127:  * Internal search result row — enriched DB row used within this handler.\n128:  * NOT the same as the canonical SearchResult in shared/types.ts.\n129:  * Self-contained: uses local types instead of the deprecated MemoryRow/MemoryRecord shapes.\n130:  * This can migrate to MemoryDbRow & Record<string, unknown> later without changing the handler contract.\n131:  */\n132: interface MemorySearchRow extends Record<string, unknown> {\n133:   id: number;\n134:   similarity?: number;\n135:   importance_tier?: string;\n136:   contextType?: string;\n137:   context_type?: string;\n138:   attentionScore?: number;\n139:   retrievability?: number;\n140:   stability?: number;\n141:   last_review?: string | null;\n142:   created_at?: string;\n143:   last_accessed?: number;\n144:   content?: string;\n145:   memoryState?: string;\n146:   file_path?: string;\n147:   parent_id?: number | null;\n148:   chunk_index?: number | null;\n149:   chunk_label?: string | null;\n150:   isChunk?: boolean;\n151:   parentId?: number | null;\n152:   chunkIndex?: number | null;\n153:   chunkLabel?: string | null;\n154:   chunkCount?: number | null;\n155:   contentSource?: 'reassembled_chunks' | 'file_read_fallback';\n156:   precomputedContent?: string;\n157: }\n158: \n159: interface DedupResult {\n160:   results: MemorySearchRow[];\n161:   dedupStats: Record<string, unknown>;\n162: }\n163: \n164: interface SearchCachePayload {\n165:   summary: string;\n166:   data: Record<string, unknown>;\n167:   hints: string[];\n168: }\n169: \n170: type SessionAwareResult = Record<string, unknown> & {\n171:   id: number | string;\n172:   score?: number;\n173:   content?: string;\n174: };\n175: \n176: type CanonicalSourceKind = 'spec_doc' | 'continuity' | 'constitutional';\n177: \n178: interface CanonicalSourceStats {\n179:   retained: number;\n180:   dropped: number;\n181:   bySourceKind: Record<CanonicalSourceKind, number>;\n182: }\n183: \n184: const CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID = '_memory.continuity';\n185: const CANONICAL_READER_CACHE_VERSION = 'gate-d-reader-ready-v1';\n186: const CANONICAL_SPEC_DOC_DOCUMENT_TYPES = new Set([\n187:   'spec',\n188:   'plan',\n189:   'tasks',\n190:   'checklist',\n191:   'decision_record',\n192:   'implementation_summary',\n193:   'research',\n194:   'handover',\n195:   'graph_metadata',\n196:   'spec_doc',\n197: ]);\n198: const NON_CANONICAL_DOCUMENT_TYPES = new Set([\n199:   'memory',\n200:   'scratch',\n201: ]);\n202: \n203: function normalizeDocumentType(value: unknown): string | null {\n204:   if (typeof value !== 'string') {\n205:     return null;\n206:   }\n207:   const normalized = value.trim().toLowerCase();\n208:   return normalized.length > 0 ? normalized : null;\n209: }\n210: \n211: function resolveAnchorId(row: Record<string, unknown>): string | null {\n212:   const value = row.anchor_id ?? row.anchorId;\n213:   return typeof value === 'string' && value.trim().length > 0\n214:     ? value.trim()\n215:     : null;\n216: }\n217: \n218: function resolveFilePath(row: Record<string, unknown>): string | null {\n219:   const value = row.file_path ?? row.filePath;\n220:   return typeof value === 'string' && value.trim().length > 0\n221:     ? value\n222:     : null;\n223: }\n224: \n225: function resolveCanonicalSourceKind(row: Record<string, unknown>): CanonicalSourceKind | null {\n226:   const documentType = normalizeDocumentType(row.document_type ?? row.documentType);\n227:   const importanceTier = normalizeDocumentType(row.importance_tier ?? row.importanceTier);\n228:   const anchorId = resolveAnchorId(row);\n229: \n230:   if (importanceTier === 'constitutional' || documentType === 'constitutional') {\n231:     return 'constitutional';\n232:   }\n233: \n234:   if (anchorId === CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID || documentType === 'continuity') {\n235:     return 'continuity';\n236:   }\n237: \n238:   if (documentType && CANONICAL_SPEC_DOC_DOCUMENT_TYPES.has(documentType)) {\n239:     return 'spec_doc';\n240:   }\n241: \n242:   if (documentType && NON_CANONICAL_DOCUMENT_TYPES.has(documentType)) {\n243:     return null;\n244:   }\n245: \n246:   const filePath = resolveFilePath(row);\n247:   if (!filePath) {\n248:     return null;\n249:   }\n250:   const normalizedPath = normalizeSpecPath(filePath);\n251:   const basename = normalizedPath.split('/').filter(Boolean).pop() ?? '';\n252: \n253:   if (\n254:     basename.length > 0 &&\n255:     SPEC_DOCUMENT_FILENAMES.has(basename) &&\n256:     canClassifyAsSpecDocument(normalizedPath)\n257:   ) {\n258:     return anchorId === CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID ? 'continuity' : 'spec_doc';\n259:   }\n260: \n261:   return null;\n262: }\n263: \n264: function filterCanonicalSourceRows<T extends SessionAwareResult>(\n265:   results: T[],\n266: ): { results: T[]; stats: CanonicalSourceStats } {\n267:   const stats: CanonicalSourceStats = {\n268:     retained: 0,\n269:     dropped: 0,\n270:     bySourceKind: {\n271:       spec_doc: 0,\n272:       continuity: 0,\n273:       constitutional: 0,\n274:     },\n275:   };\n276: \n277:   const filtered: T[] = [];\n278:   for (const result of results) {\n279:     const sourceKind = resolveCanonicalSourceKind(result);\n280:     if (!sourceKind) {\n281:       stats.dropped += 1;\n282:       continue;\n283:     }\n284: \n285:     filtered.push({\n286:       ...result,\n287:       canonicalSource: sourceKind,\n288:       canonicalSourceType: sourceKind,\n289:       documentType: sourceKind,\n290:     });\n291:     stats.retained += 1;\n292:     stats.bySourceKind[sourceKind] += 1;\n293:   }\n294: \n295:   return { results: filtered, stats };\n296: }\n297: \n298: // ChunkReassemblyResult — now imported from lib/search/chunk-reassembly.ts\n299: \n300: type IntentWeights = IntentClassifierWeights;\n301: \n302: function toIntentWeightsConfig(weights: IntentWeights | null): IntentWeightsConfig | null {\n303:   if (!weights) return null;\n304:   return {\n305:     similarity: weights.similarity,\n306:     importance: weights.importance,\n307:     recency: weights.recency,\n308:   };\n309: }\n310: \n311: // EvalChannelPayload — now imported from lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.ts\n312: \n313: interface SearchArgs {\n314:   cursor?: string;\n315:   query?: string;\n316:   concepts?: string[];\n317:   specFolder?: string;\n318:   folderBoost?: { folder: string; factor: number };\n319:   tenantId?: string;\n320:   userId?: string;\n321:   agentId?: string;\n322:   limit?: number;\n323:   tier?: string;\n324:   contextType?: string;\n325:   useDecay?: boolean;\n326:   includeContiguity?: boolean;\n327:   includeConstitutional?: boolean;\n328:   includeContent?: boolean;\n329:   anchors?: string[];\n330:   bypassCache?: boolean;\n331:   sessionId?: string;\n332:   enableDedup?: boolean;\n333:   intent?: string;\n334:   autoDetectIntent?: boolean;\n335:   minState?: string;\n336:   applyStateLimits?: boolean;\n337:   rerank?: boolean;\n338:   applyLengthPenalty?: boolean;\n339:   trackAccess?: boolean; // opt-in access tracking (default false)\n340:   includeArchived?: boolean; // Include archived memories in search (default false)\n341:   enableSessionBoost?: boolean;\n342:   enableCausalBoost?: boolean;\n343:   minQualityScore?: number;\n344:   min_quality_score?: number;\n345:   mode?: string; // \"deep\" mode enables query expansion for multi-query RAG\n346:   includeTrace?: boolean;\n347:   sessionTransition?: SessionTransitionTrace;\n348:   /** Presentation profile ('quick'|'research'|'resume'|'debug'). Default: full response. */\n349:   profile?: string;\n350:   /** Dual-level retrieval — 'local' (entity), 'global' (community), 'auto' (local + fallback). */\n351:   retrievalLevel?: 'local' | 'global' | 'auto';\n352: }\n353: \n354: // resolveRowContextType — now imported from lib/search/search-utils.ts\n355: // resolveEvalScore, collectEvalChannelsFromRow — now imported from lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.ts\n356: \n357: function attachTelemetryMeta(\n358:   response: MCPResponse,\n359:   telemetryPayload: Record<string, unknown>,\n360: ): MCPResponse {\n361:   const firstEntry = response?.content?.[0];\n362:   if (!firstEntry || typeof firstEntry.text !== 'string') {\n363:     return response;\n364:   }\n365: \n366:   try {\n367:     const envelope = JSON.parse(firstEntry.text) as Record<string, unknown>;\n368:     const meta = envelope.meta && typeof envelope.meta === 'object'\n369:       ? envelope.meta as Record<string, unknown>\n370:       : {};\n371:     envelope.meta = {\n372:       ...meta,\n373:       _telemetry: telemetryPayload,\n374:     };\n375: \n376:     return {\n377:       ...response,\n378:       content: [{ ...firstEntry, text: JSON.stringify(envelope, null, 2) }],\n379:     };\n380:   } catch (error: unknown) {\n381:     const message = toErrorMessage(error);\n382:     console.warn('[memory-search] Failed to attach telemetry payload:', message);\n383:     return response;\n384:   }\n385: }\n386: \n387: function extractResponseResults(response: MCPResponse): Array<Record<string, unknown>> {\n388:   const firstEntry = response?.content?.[0];\n389:   if (!firstEntry || typeof firstEntry.text !== 'string') {\n390:     return [];\n391:   }\n392: \n393:   try {\n394:     const envelope = JSON.parse(firstEntry.text) as Record<string, unknown>;\n395:     const data = envelope.data && typeof envelope.data === 'object'\n396:       ? envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n397:       : null;\n398:     return Array.isArray(data?.results)\n399:       ? data.results as Array<Record<string, unknown>>\n400:       : [];\n401:   } catch {\n402:     return [];\n403:   }\n404: }\n405: \n406: function extractSearchCachePayload(response: MCPResponse): SearchCachePayload | null {\n407:   const firstEntry = response?.content?.[0];\n408:   if (!firstEntry || typeof firstEntry.text !== 'string') {\n409:     return null;\n410:   }\n411: \n412:   try {\n413:     const envelope = JSON.parse(firstEntry.text) as Record<string, unknown>;\n414:     const summary = typeof envelope.summary === 'string' ? envelope.summary : null;\n415:     const data = envelope.data && typeof envelope.data === 'object'\n416:       ? envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n417:       : null;\n418:     const hints = Array.isArray(envelope.hints)\n419:       ? envelope.hints.filter((hint): hint is string => typeof hint === 'string')\n420:       : [];\n421: \n422:     if (!summary || !data) {\n423:       return null;\n424:     }\n425: \n426:     return { summary, data, hints };\n427:   } catch {\n428:     return null;\n429:   }\n430: }\n431: \n432: function parseResponseEnvelope(\n433:   response: MCPResponse,\n434: ): { firstEntry: { type: 'text'; text: string }; envelope: Record<string, unknown> } | null {\n435:   const firstEntry = response?.content?.[0];\n436:   if (!firstEntry || firstEntry.type !== 'text' || typeof firstEntry.text !== 'string') {\n437:     return null;\n438:   }\n439: \n440:   try {\n441:     return {\n442:       firstEntry,\n443:       envelope: JSON.parse(firstEntry.text) as Record<string, unknown>,\n444:     };\n445:   } catch {\n446:     return null;\n447:   }\n448: }\n449: \n450: function replaceResponseEnvelope(\n451:   response: MCPResponse,\n452:   firstEntry: { type: 'text'; text: string },\n453:   envelope: Record<string, unknown>,\n454: ): MCPResponse {\n455:   return {\n456:     ...response,\n457:     content: [{ ...firstEntry, text: JSON.stringify(envelope, null, 2) }],\n458:   };\n459: }\n460: \n461: function buildSessionStatePayload(sessionId: string): Record<string, unknown> {\n462:   const session = retrievalSessionStateManager.getOrCreate(sessionId);\n463:   return {\n464:     activeGoal: session.activeGoal,\n465:     seenResultIds: Array.from(session.seenResultIds),\n466:     openQuestions: [...session.openQuestions],\n467:     preferredAnchors: [...session.preferredAnchors],\n468:   };\n469: }\n470: \n471: function buildSearchResponseFromPayload(\n472:   payload: SearchCachePayload,\n473:   startTime: number,\n474:   cacheHit: boolean,\n475: ): MCPResponse {\n476:   return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n477:     tool: 'memory_search',\n478:     summary: payload.summary,\n479:     data: payload.data,\n480:     hints: payload.hints,\n481:     startTime,\n482:     cacheHit,\n483:   });\n484: }\n485: \n486: function resolveSearchScore(result: Record<string, unknown>): number | null {\n487:   const candidate = result.score ?? result.similarity ?? result.averageSimilarity ?? result.intentAdjustedScore;\n488:   if (typeof candidate !== 'number' || !Number.isFinite(candidate)) {\n489:     return null;\n490:   }\n491:   return candidate > 1 ? candidate / 100 : candidate;\n492: }\n493: \n494: function computeAverageScore(results: Array<Record<string, unknown>>): number {\n495:   const scores = results\n496:     .map(resolveSearchScore)\n497:     .filter((score): score is number => score !== null);\n498:   if (scores.length === 0) return 0;\n499:   return scores.reduce((sum, score) => sum + score, 0) / scores.length;\n500: }\n501: \n502: function attachLexicalCapabilityMetadata(\n503:   response: MCPResponse,\n504:   snapshot: LexicalCapabilitySnapshot | null,\n505: ): MCPResponse {\n506:   const parsed = parseResponseEnvelope(response);\n507:   if (!parsed) {\n508:     return response;\n509:   }\n510: \n511:   const data = parsed.envelope.data && typeof parsed.envelope.data === 'object'\n512:     ? parsed.envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n513:     : {};\n514: \n515:   if (typeof data.lexicalPath !== 'string' && snapshot) {\n516:     data.lexicalPath = snapshot.lexicalPath;\n517:   }\n518:   if (typeof data.fallbackState !== 'string' && snapshot) {\n519:     data.fallbackState = snapshot.fallbackState;\n520:   }\n521: \n522:   parsed.envelope.data = data;\n523:   return replaceResponseEnvelope(response, parsed.firstEntry, parsed.envelope);\n524: }\n525: \n526: function hasPublicationContractFields(result: Record<string, unknown>): boolean {\n527:   return [\n528:     'certainty',\n529:     'methodologyStatus',\n530:     'schemaVersion',\n531:     'provenance',\n532:     'multiplierAuthorityFields',\n533:   ].some((field) => Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(result, field));\n534: }\n535: \n536: function applyPublicationGateToResponse(response: MCPResponse): MCPResponse {\n537:   const parsed = parseResponseEnvelope(response);\n538:   if (!parsed) {\n539:     return response;\n540:   }\n541: \n542:   const data = parsed.envelope.data && typeof parsed.envelope.data === 'object'\n543:     ? parsed.envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n544:     : null;\n545:   const results = Array.isArray(data?.results)\n546:     ? data.results as Array<Record<string, unknown>>\n547:     : null;\n548: \n549:   if (!data || !results) {\n550:     return response;\n551:   }\n552: \n553:   data.results = results.map((result) => {\n554:     if (!hasPublicationContractFields(result)) {\n555:       return result;\n556:     }\n557: \n558:     const gateResult = evaluatePublicationGate({\n559:       certainty: result.certainty,\n560:       methodologyStatus: result.methodologyStatus as 'provisional' | 'published' | null | undefined,\n561:       schemaVersion: result.schemaVersion as string | null | undefined,\n562:       provenance: Array.isArray(result.provenance) ? result.provenance as string[] : null,\n563:       multiplierAuthorityFields: result.multiplierAuthorityFields as Record<string, unknown> | null | undefined,\n564:     });\n565: \n566:     return gateResult.publishable\n567:       ? {\n568:         ...result,\n569:         publishable: true,\n570:       }\n571:       : {\n572:         ...result,\n573:         publishable: false,\n574:         exclusionReason: gateResult.exclusionReason,\n575:       };\n576:   });\n577: \n578:   parsed.envelope.data = data;\n579:   return replaceResponseEnvelope(response, parsed.firstEntry, parsed.envelope);\n580: }\n581: \n582: // summarizeGraphWalkDiagnostics, buildEvalChannelPayloads — now imported from lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.ts\n583: \n584: // filterByMinQualityScore, resolveQualityThreshold, buildCacheArgs,\n585: // resolveArtifactRoutingQuery, applyArtifactRouting — now imported from lib/search/search-utils.ts\n586: // CacheArgsInput — now imported from lib/search/search-utils.ts\n587: // parseNullableInt, collapseAndReassembleChunkResults — now imported from lib/search/chunk-reassembly.ts\n588: \n589: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n590:    3. CONFIGURATION\n591: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n592: \n593: // Sections 3–5 (STATE_PRIORITY, MAX_DEEP_QUERY_VARIANTS, buildDeepQueryVariants,\n594: // StrengthenOnAccess, applyTestingEffect, filterByMemoryState) removed in\n595: // These were only used by the legacy V1 pipeline.\n596: // The V2 4-stage pipeline handles state filtering (Stage 4), testing effect, and\n597: // Query expansion through its own stages.\n598: \n599: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n600:    6. SESSION DEDUPLICATION UTILITIES\n601: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n602: \n603: function applySessionDedup(results: MemorySearchRow[], sessionId: string, enableDedup: boolean): DedupResult {\n604:   if (!enableDedup || !sessionId || !sessionManager.isEnabled()) {\n605:     return {\n606:       results,\n607:       dedupStats: { enabled: false, sessionId: null }\n608:     };\n609:   }\n610: \n611:   const { filtered, dedupStats } = sessionManager.filterSearchResults(sessionId, results as Parameters<typeof sessionManager.filterSearchResults>[1]);\n612: \n613:   if (filtered.length > 0) {\n614:     sessionManager.markResultsSent(sessionId, filtered as Parameters<typeof sessionManager.markResultsSent>[1]);\n615:   }\n616: \n617:   return {\n618:     results: filtered as MemorySearchRow[],\n619:     dedupStats: {\n620:       ...dedupStats,\n621:       sessionId\n622:     }\n623:   };\n624: }\n625: \n626: // Sections 7–9 (applyCrossEncoderReranking, applyIntentWeightsToResults,\n627: // ShouldApplyPostSearchIntentWeighting, postSearchPipeline) removed in\n628: // These were only used by the legacy V1 pipeline\n629: // Path. The V2 4-stage pipeline handles all equivalent functionality.\n630: \n631: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n632:    10. MAIN HANDLER\n633: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n634: \n635: /** Handle memory_search tool — performs hybrid vector/BM25 search with intent-aware ranking.\n636:  * @param args - Search arguments (query, concepts, mode, specFolder, etc.)\n637:  * @returns MCP response with ranked search results\n638:  */\n639: async function handleMemorySearch(args: SearchArgs): Promise<MCPResponse> {\n640:   await ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized('handler:memory_search');\n641:   const _searchStartTime = Date.now();\n642:   resetLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot();\n643:   // BUG-001: Check for external database updates before processing\n644:   await checkDatabaseUpdated();\n645: \n646:   const {\n647:     cursor,\n648:     query,\n649:     concepts,\n650:     specFolder,\n651:     folderBoost,\n652:     tenantId,\n653:     userId,\n654:     agentId,\n655:     limit: rawLimit = 10,\n656:     tier,\n657:     contextType,\n658:     useDecay: useDecay = true,\n659:     includeContiguity: includeContiguity = false,\n660:     includeConstitutional: includeConstitutional = true,\n661:     includeContent: includeContent = false,\n662:     anchors,\n663:     bypassCache: bypassCache = false,\n664:     sessionId: rawSessionId,\n665:     enableDedup: enableDedup = true,\n666:     intent: explicitIntent,\n667:     autoDetectIntent: autoDetectIntent = true,\n668:     minState,  // No default — memoryState column not yet in schema; defaulting to 'WARM' filters all rows\n669:     applyStateLimits: applyStateLimits = false,\n670:     rerank = true, // Enable reranking by default for better result quality\n671:     applyLengthPenalty: applyLengthPenalty = true,\n672:     trackAccess: trackAccess = false, // opt-in, off by default\n673:     includeArchived: includeArchivedRequested = false, // compatibility-only after Gate B cleanup\n674:     enableSessionBoost: enableSessionBoost = isSessionBoostEnabled(),\n675:     enableCausalBoost: enableCausalBoost = isCausalBoostEnabled(),\n676:     minQualityScore,\n677:     min_quality_score,\n678:     mode,\n679:     includeTrace: includeTraceArg = false,\n680:     sessionTransition,\n681:     profile,\n682:     retrievalLevel: retrievalLevel = 'auto',\n683:   } = args;\n684:   const includeTraceByFlag = process.env.SPECKIT_RESPONSE_TRACE === 'true';\n685:   const includeTrace = includeTraceByFlag || includeTraceArg === true;\n686:   const includeArchived = false;\n687: \n688:   // Validate any caller-supplied sessionId through the server-side session\n689:   // manager to prevent IDOR: a caller must not read or mutate another\n690:   // session's sent-memory dedup state by forging an arbitrary session id.\n691:   // Omitting sessionId stays unchanged (downstream treats it as no-session).\n692:   let sessionId: string | undefined = rawSessionId;\n693:   if (rawSessionId) {\n694:     const trustedSession = sessionManager.resolveTrustedSession(rawSessionId, {\n695:       tenantId,\n696:       userId,\n697:       agentId,\n698:     });\n699:     if (trustedSession.error) {\n700:       return createMCPErrorResponse({\n701:         tool: 'memory_search',\n702:         error: trustedSession.error,\n703:         code: 'E_SESSION_SCOPE',\n704:         details: { requestedSessionId: rawSessionId },\n705:         recovery: {\n706:           hint: 'Omit sessionId to start a new server-generated session, or reuse the effectiveSessionId returned by memory_context.',\n707:         },\n708:       });\n709:     }\n710:     sessionId = trustedSession.effectiveSessionId;\n711:   }\n712: \n713:   const normalizedScope = normalizeScopeContext({ tenantId, userId, agentId, sessionId });\n714:   const progressiveScopeKey = JSON.stringify({\n715:     tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId ?? null,\n716:     userId: normalizedScope.userId ?? null,\n717:     agentId: normalizedScope.agentId ?? null,\n718:     sessionId: normalizedScope.sessionId ?? null,\n719:   });\n720: \n721:   // Validate at least one search input is provided (moved from schema superRefine for GPT compatibility)\n722:   const hasCursor = typeof cursor === 'string' && cursor.trim().length > 0;\n723:   const hasQuery = typeof query === 'string' && query.trim().length > 0;\n724:   const hasConcepts = Array.isArray(concepts) && concepts.length >= 2;\n725:   if (!hasCursor && !hasQuery && !hasConcepts) {\n726:     return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify({ error: 'Either \"query\" (string), \"concepts\" (array with 2-5 items), or \"cursor\" (string) is required.' }) }] };\n727:   }\n728: \n729:   if (hasCursor) {\n730:     const resolved = resolveCursor(cursor.trim(), undefined, { scopeKey: progressiveScopeKey });\n731:     if (!resolved) {\n732:       return createMCPErrorResponse({\n733:         tool: 'memory_search',\n734:         error: 'Cursor is invalid, expired, or out of scope',\n735:         code: 'E_VALIDATION',\n736:         details: { parameter: 'cursor' },\n737:         recovery: {\n738:           hint: 'Retry the original search to generate a fresh continuation cursor',\n739:         },\n740:       });\n741:     }\n742: \n743:     const snippetResults = extractSnippets(resolved.results);\n744:     return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n745:       tool: 'memory_search',\n746:       summary: `Returned ${snippetResults.length} continuation results`,\n747:       data: {\n748:         count: snippetResults.length,\n749:         results: snippetResults,\n750:         continuation: resolved.continuation,\n751:       },\n752:       startTime: _searchStartTime,\n753:       cacheHit: false,\n754:     });\n755:   }\n756: \n757:   const qualityThreshold = resolveQualityThreshold(minQualityScore, min_quality_score);\n758: \n759:   // Validate numeric limit parameter\n760:   const limit = (typeof rawLimit === 'number' && Number.isFinite(rawLimit) && rawLimit > 0)\n761:     ? Math.min(Math.floor(rawLimit), 100)\n762:     : 10;\n763: \n764:   // BUG-007: Validate query first with proper error handling\n765:   let normalizedQuery: string | null = null;\n766:   if (query !== undefined) {\n767:     try {\n768:       normalizedQuery = validateQuery(query);\n769:     } catch (validationError: unknown) {\n770:       if (!concepts || !Array.isArray(concepts) || concepts.length < 2) {\n771:         const message = toErrorMessage(validationError);\n772:         return createMCPErrorResponse({\n773:           tool: 'memory_search',\n774:           error: message,\n775:           code: 'E_VALIDATION',\n776:           details: { parameter: 'query' },\n777:           recovery: {\n778:             hint: 'Provide a valid query string or use concepts array instead'\n779:           }\n780:         });\n781:       }\n782:       normalizedQuery = null;\n783:     }\n784:   }\n785: \n786:   const hasValidQuery = normalizedQuery !== null;\n787:   const hasValidConcepts = Array.isArray(concepts) && concepts.length >= 2;\n788:   const effectiveQuery = normalizedQuery ?? (hasValidConcepts ? concepts.join(', ') : '');\n789:   const searchDecisionRequestId = `memory_search-${_searchStartTime}`;\n790:   let searchDecisionEnvelope: SearchDecisionEnvelope | null = null;\n791: \n792:   if (!hasValidQuery && !hasValidConcepts) {\n793:     return createMCPErrorResponse({\n794:       tool: 'memory_search',\n795:       error: 'Either query (string), concepts (array of 2-5 strings), or cursor (string) is required',\n796:       code: 'E_VALIDATION',\n797:       details: { parameter: 'query' },\n798:       recovery: {\n799:         hint: 'Provide a query string, concepts array with 2-5 entries, or a continuation cursor'\n800:       }\n801:     });\n802:   }\n803: \n804:   if (specFolder !== undefined && typeof specFolder !== 'string') {\n805:     return createMCPErrorResponse({\n806:       tool: 'memory_search',\n807:       error: 'specFolder must be a string',\n808:       code: 'E_VALIDATION',\n809:       details: { parameter: 'specFolder' },\n810:       recovery: {\n811:         hint: 'Provide specFolder as a string path'\n812:       }\n813:     });\n814:   }\n815: \n816:   // Eval logger — capture query at pipeline entry (fail-safe)\n817:   let _evalQueryId = 0;\n818:   let _evalRunId = 0;\n819:   try {\n820:     const evalEntry = logSearchQuery({\n821:       query: effectiveQuery,\n822:       intent: explicitIntent ?? null,\n823:       specFolder: specFolder ?? null,\n824:     });\n825:     _evalQueryId = evalEntry.queryId;\n826:     _evalRunId = evalEntry.evalRunId;\n827:   } catch (_error: unknown) { /* eval logging must never break search */ }\n828: \n829:   const artifactRoutingQuery = resolveArtifactRoutingQuery(\n830:     normalizedQuery,\n831:     hasValidConcepts ? concepts : undefined\n832:   );\n833:   let artifactRouting = getStrategyForQuery(artifactRoutingQuery, specFolder);\n834:   let queryPlan: QueryPlan;\n835:   try {\n836:     queryPlan = routeQuery(effectiveQuery).queryPlan;\n837:   } catch (_error: unknown) {\n838:     queryPlan = createEmptyQueryPlan({\n839:       complexity: 'unknown',\n840:       selectedChannels: ['vector', 'fts', 'bm25', 'graph', 'degree'],\n841:       fallbackPolicy: {\n842:         mode: 'telemetry_only',\n843:         reason: 'QueryPlan telemetry fallback after routeQuery failure',\n844:       },\n845:     });\n846:   }\n847: \n848:   // Intent-aware retrieval\n849:   let detectedIntent: string | null = null;\n850:   let intentConfidence = 0;\n851:   let intentWeights: IntentWeights | null = null;\n852: \n853:   if (explicitIntent) {\n854:     if (intentClassifier.isValidIntent(explicitIntent)) {\n855:       detectedIntent = explicitIntent;\n856:       intentConfidence = 1.0;\n857:       intentWeights = intentClassifier.getIntentWeights(explicitIntent);\n858:     } else {\n859:       console.warn(`[memory-search] Invalid intent '${explicitIntent}', using auto-detection`);\n860:     }\n861:   }\n862: \n863:   if (!detectedIntent && autoDetectIntent && hasValidQuery) {\n864:     const classification: IntentClassification = intentClassifier.classifyIntent(normalizedQuery!);\n865:     detectedIntent = classification.intent;\n866:     intentConfidence = classification.confidence;\n867:     intentWeights = intentClassifier.getIntentWeights(classification.intent as IntentType);\n868: \n869:     if (classification.fallback) {\n870:       console.error(`[memory-search] Intent auto-detected as '${detectedIntent}' (fallback: ${classification.reason})`);\n871:     } else {\n872:       console.error(`[memory-search] Intent auto-detected as '${detectedIntent}' (confidence: ${intentConfidence.toFixed(2)})`);\n873:     }\n874:   }\n875: \n876:   // FIX RC3-B: Intent confidence floor — override low-confidence auto-detections to \"understand\"\n877:   const INTENT_CONFIDENCE_FLOOR = parseFloat(process.env.SPECKIT_INTENT_CONFIDENCE_FLOOR || '0.25');\n878:   if (detectedIntent && intentConfidence < INTENT_CONFIDENCE_FLOOR && !explicitIntent) {\n879:     console.error(`[memory-search] Intent confidence ${intentConfidence.toFixed(3)} below floor ${INTENT_CONFIDENCE_FLOOR}, overriding '${detectedIntent}' → 'understand'`);\n880:     detectedIntent = 'understand';\n881:     intentConfidence = 1.0;\n882:     intentWeights = intentClassifier.getIntentWeights('understand' as IntentType);\n883:   }\n884: \n885:   // Phase C: Intent-to-profile auto-routing.\n886:   // Explicit caller `profile` always takes precedence; auto-detect fills in when absent.\n887:   let effectiveProfile: string | undefined = profile;\n888:   if (!effectiveProfile && detectedIntent && isIntentAutoProfileEnabled()) {\n889:     try {\n890:       const autoProfile = intentClassifier.getProfileForIntent(detectedIntent as IntentType);\n891:       if (autoProfile) {\n892:         effectiveProfile = autoProfile;\n893:         console.error(`[memory-search] Intent-to-profile auto-routing: '${detectedIntent}' → profile '${autoProfile}'`);\n894:       }\n895:     } catch (_autoProfileErr: unknown) {\n896:       // Auto-profile is best-effort — never breaks search\n897:     }\n898:   }\n899:   const adaptiveFusionIntent = effectiveProfile === 'resume'\n900:     ? 'continuity'\n901:     : detectedIntent;\n902: \n903:   // Re-run artifact routing with detected intent for fallback coverage\n904:   if (detectedIntent && artifactRouting?.detectedClass === 'unknown' && artifactRouting?.confidence === 0) {\n905:     artifactRouting = getStrategyForQuery(artifactRoutingQuery, specFolder, detectedIntent);\n906:   }\n907: \n908:   // Create retrieval trace at pipeline entry\n909:   const trace = createTrace(\n910:     effectiveQuery,\n911:     sessionId,\n912:     detectedIntent || undefined\n913:   );\n914: \n915:   // When causal boost is enabled, fold the causal-edges generation\n916:   // counter into the cache key so causal-edge mutations naturally invalidate\n917:   // the affected memory_search entries on the next lookup. We deliberately\n918:   // keep the generation OFF the key when the caller has not opted into causal\n919:   // boost — otherwise unrelated callers would suffer needless cache misses.\n920:   const causalEdgesGenerationForCache = enableCausalBoost\n921:     ? causalEdges.getCausalEdgesGeneration()\n922:     : undefined;\n923: \n924:   // Build cache key args\n925:   const cacheArgs = buildCacheArgs({\n926:     normalizedQuery,\n927:     hasValidConcepts,\n928:     concepts,\n929:     specFolder,\n930:     tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId,\n931:     userId: normalizedScope.userId,\n932:     agentId: normalizedScope.agentId,\n933:     limit,\n934:     mode,\n935:     tier,\n936:     contextType,\n937:     useDecay,\n938:     includeArchived,\n939:     qualityThreshold,\n940:     applyStateLimits,\n941:     includeContiguity,\n942:     includeConstitutional,\n943:     includeContent,\n944:     anchors,\n945:     detectedIntent,\n946:     adaptiveFusionIntent,\n947:     minState: minState ?? '',\n948:     rerank,\n949:     applyLengthPenalty,\n950:     sessionId,\n951:     enableSessionBoost,\n952:     enableCausalBoost,\n953:     includeTrace,\n954:     cacheVersion: CANONICAL_READER_CACHE_VERSION,\n955:     causalEdgesGeneration: causalEdgesGenerationForCache,\n956:   });\n957: \n958:   let _evalChannelPayloads: EvalChannelPayload[] = [];\n959:   const cacheKey = toolCache.generateCacheKey('memory_search', cacheArgs);\n960:   const cacheEnabled = toolCache.isEnabled() && !bypassCache;\n961:   const cachedPayload = cacheEnabled\n962:     ? toolCache.get<SearchCachePayload>(cacheKey)\n963:     : null;\n964: \n965:   let responseToReturn: MCPResponse;\n966:   let goalRefinementPayload: Record<string, unknown> | null = null;\n967: \n968:   if (cachedPayload) {\n969:     responseToReturn = buildSearchResponseFromPayload(cachedPayload, _searchStartTime, true);\n970:   } else {\n971:     // V2 pipeline is the only path (legacy V1 removed from the runtime pipeline)\n972:     const pipelineConfig: PipelineConfig = {\n973:       query: effectiveQuery,\n974:       concepts: hasValidConcepts ? concepts : undefined,\n975:       searchType: (hasValidConcepts && concepts!.length >= 2)\n976:         ? 'multi-concept'\n977:         : 'hybrid',\n978:       mode,\n979:       limit,\n980:       specFolder,\n981:       tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId,\n982:       userId: normalizedScope.userId,\n983:       agentId: normalizedScope.agentId,\n984:       tier,\n985:       contextType,\n986:       includeArchived,\n987:       includeConstitutional,\n988:       includeContent,\n989:       anchors,\n990:       qualityThreshold,\n991:       minState: minState ?? '',\n992:       applyStateLimits,\n993:       useDecay,\n994:       rerank,\n995:       applyLengthPenalty,\n996:       sessionId,\n997:       enableDedup,\n998:       enableSessionBoost,\n999:       enableCausalBoost,\n1000:       trackAccess,\n1001:       detectedIntent,\n1002:       adaptiveFusionIntent,\n1003:       intentConfidence,\n1004:       intentWeights: toIntentWeightsConfig(intentWeights),\n1005:       artifactRouting: artifactRouting as unknown as PipelineConfig['artifactRouting'],\n1006:       queryPlan,\n1007:       trace,\n1008:     };\n1009: \n1010:     const pipelineResult: PipelineResult = await executePipeline(pipelineConfig);\n1011:     let resultsForFormatting = pipelineResult.results as unknown as SessionAwareResult[];\n1012: \n1013:     // Community search fallback — inject community members on weak results\n1014:     let communityFallbackApplied = false;\n1015:     const shouldRunCommunitySearch = (\n1016:       isDualRetrievalEnabled() &&\n1017:       isCommunitySearchFallbackEnabled() &&\n1018:       effectiveQuery.length > 0 &&\n1019:       (retrievalLevel === 'global' || retrievalLevel === 'auto')\n1020:     );\n1021:     if (shouldRunCommunitySearch) {\n1022:       const isWeakResult = resultsForFormatting.length === 0 ||\n1023:         (resultsForFormatting.length < 3 && (retrievalLevel === 'global' || retrievalLevel === 'auto'));\n1024:       if (isWeakResult) {\n1025:         try {\n1026:           const communityResults = searchCommunities(effectiveQuery, requireDb(), 5);\n1027:           if (communityResults.totalMemberIds.length > 0) {\n1028:             // Fetch the actual memory rows for community member IDs\n1029:             const memberIds = communityResults.totalMemberIds.slice(0, 20);\n1030:             const placeholders = memberIds.map(() => '?').join(', ');\n1031:             const db = requireDb();\n1032:             const rawMemberRows = db.prepare(`\n1033:               SELECT id, title, similarity, content, file_path, anchor_id, document_type,\n1034:                      importance_tier, context_type, quality_score, created_at,\n1035:                      tenant_id, user_id, agent_id\n1036:               FROM memory_index\n1037:               WHERE id IN (${placeholders})\n1038:             `).all(...memberIds) as Array<Record<string, unknown> & { id: number }>;\n1039: \n1040:             // Apply governed retrieval scope to the community fallback so it cannot\n1041:             // bypass the tenant/user/agent boundary the canonical pipeline enforces.\n1042:             // sessionId is deliberately excluded — it is a dedup/continuity key, not\n1043:             // a row-access boundary. Unscoped (single-user) callers are unaffected.\n1044:             const hasGovernanceScope = Boolean(\n1045:               normalizedScope.tenantId || normalizedScope.userId || normalizedScope.agentId,\n1046:             );\n1047:             const memberRows = hasGovernanceScope\n1048:               ? filterRowsByScope(rawMemberRows, {\n1049:                   tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId,\n1050:                   userId: normalizedScope.userId,\n1051:                   agentId: normalizedScope.agentId,\n1052:                 })\n1053:               : rawMemberRows;\n1054: \n1055:             if (memberRows.length > 0) {\n1056:               // Calibrate score from community match quality, bounded below pipeline threshold\n1057:               const communityScoreScale = 0.02; // aligns with pipeline's minimum quality floor\n1058:               const avgMatchScore = communityResults.results.length > 0\n1059:                 ? communityResults.results.reduce((sum, r) => sum + r.matchScore, 0) / communityResults.results.length\n1060:                 : 0.5;\n1061:               const calibratedScore = Math.max(0.001, avgMatchScore * communityScoreScale);\n1062:               // Mark community-sourced results and assign calibrated score\n1063:               const communityRows = memberRows.map((row) => ({\n1064:                 ...row,\n1065:                 similarity: typeof row.similarity === 'number' ? row.similarity : 0.5,\n1066:                 score: calibratedScore,\n1067:                 _communityFallback: true,\n1068:               }));\n1069:               // Merge: append community results not already in pipeline results\n1070:               const existingIds = new Set(resultsForFormatting.map((r) => (r as Record<string, unknown>).id as number));\n1071:               const newRows = communityRows.filter((r) => !existingIds.has(r.id));\n1072:               if (newRows.length > 0) {\n1073:                 resultsForFormatting = [...resultsForFormatting, ...newRows as unknown as SessionAwareResult[]];\n1074:                 communityFallbackApplied = true;\n1075:               }\n1076:             }\n1077:           }\n1078:         } catch (err: unknown) {\n1079:           const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n1080:           console.warn(`[memory-search] Community search fallback failed (fail-open): ${msg}`);\n1081:         }\n1082:       }\n1083:     }\n1084: \n1085:     // Apply folder boost — multiply similarity for results matching discovered folder\n1086:     if (folderBoost && folderBoost.folder && folderBoost.factor > 1) {\n1087:       let boostedCount = 0;\n1088:       for (const r of resultsForFormatting) {\n1089:         const filePath = (r as Record<string, unknown>).file_path as string | undefined;\n1090:         if (filePath && filePath.includes(folderBoost.folder)) {\n1091:           const raw = (r as Record<string, unknown>);\n1092:           if (typeof raw.similarity === 'number') {\n1093:             raw.similarity = Math.min(raw.similarity * folderBoost.factor, 1.0);\n1094:             boostedCount++;\n1095:           }\n1096:         }\n1097:       }\n1098:       // Re-sort by similarity after boosting\n1099:       if (boostedCount > 0) {\n1100:         resultsForFormatting.sort((a, b) => {\n1101:           const sa = (a as Record<string, unknown>).similarity as number ?? 0;\n1102:           const sb = (b as Record<string, unknown>).similarity as number ?? 0;\n1103:           return sb - sa;\n1104:         });\n1105:       }\n1106:     }\n1107: \n1108:     // Eval channel attribution should reflect the retrieval pipeline output\n1109:     // before canonical source filtering drops rows for response formatting.\n1110:     _evalChannelPayloads = buildEvalChannelPayloads(\n1111:       pipelineResult.results as unknown as Array<Record<string, unknown>>,\n1112:     );\n1113: \n1114:     const canonicalFilter = filterCanonicalSourceRows(resultsForFormatting);\n1115:     resultsForFormatting = canonicalFilter.results;\n1116:     const avgScore = computeAverageScore(resultsForFormatting as Array<Record<string, unknown>>);\n1117:     const requestQualityLabel = pipelineResult.metadata.stage4.evidenceGapDetected ? 'gap' : 'weak';\n1118:     const qualityGapRouting = routeQuery(effectiveQuery, undefined, {\n1119:       quality: requestQualityLabel,\n1120:       avgScore,\n1121:     });\n1122:     const qualityFallback = qualityGapRouting.qualityFallback;\n1123:     if (qualityFallback.engaged) {\n1124:       queryPlan = qualityGapRouting.queryPlan;\n1125:     }\n1126: \n1127:     if (sessionId && isSessionRetrievalStateEnabled()) {\n1128:       const activeGoal = effectiveQuery.trim().length > 0 ? effectiveQuery : null;\n1129:       if (activeGoal) {\n1130:         retrievalSessionStateManager.updateGoal(sessionId, activeGoal);\n1131:       }\n1132:       if (Array.isArray(anchors) && anchors.length > 0) {\n1133:         retrievalSessionStateManager.setAnchors(sessionId, anchors);\n1134:       }\n1135: \n1136:       const goalRefinement = refineForGoal(resultsForFormatting, sessionId);\n1137:       resultsForFormatting = goalRefinement.results as SessionAwareResult[];\n1138:       goalRefinementPayload = {\n1139:         activeGoal: goalRefinement.metadata.activeGoal,\n1140:         applied: goalRefinement.metadata.refined,\n1141:         boostedCount: goalRefinement.metadata.boostedCount,\n1142:       };\n1143:     }\n1144: \n1145:     // Build extra data from pipeline metadata for response formatting\n1146:     const lexicalCapability = getLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot();\n1147:     if (lexicalCapability) {\n1148:       console.error(\n1149:         `[memory-search] Lexical capability path '${lexicalCapability.lexicalPath}' (fallbackState: ${lexicalCapability.fallbackState})`\n1150:       );\n1151:     }\n1152: \n1153:     const extraData: Record<string, unknown> = {\n1154:       stateStats: pipelineResult.annotations.stateStats,\n1155:       featureFlags: {\n1156:         ...pipelineResult.annotations.featureFlags,\n1157:       },\n1158:       pipelineMetadata: pipelineResult.metadata,\n1159:       qualityGapFallback: qualityFallback,\n1160:     };\n1161:     if (lexicalCapability) {\n1162:       extraData.lexicalPath = lexicalCapability.lexicalPath;\n1163:       extraData.fallbackState = lexicalCapability.fallbackState;\n1164:     }\n1165: \n1166:     if (pipelineResult.annotations.evidenceGapWarning) {\n1167:       extraData.evidenceGapWarning = pipelineResult.annotations.evidenceGapWarning;\n1168:     }\n1169: \n1170:     if (detectedIntent) {\n1171:       extraData.intent = {\n1172:         type: detectedIntent,\n1173:         confidence: intentConfidence,\n1174:         description: intentClassifier.getIntentDescription(detectedIntent as IntentType),\n1175:         weightsApplied: pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.intentWeightsApplied,\n1176:       };\n1177:     }\n1178: \n1179:     if (artifactRouting) {\n1180:       extraData.artifactRouting = artifactRouting;\n1181:       extraData.artifact_routing = artifactRouting;\n1182:     }\n1183: \n1184:     if (pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.feedbackSignalsApplied === 'applied') {\n1185:       extraData.feedbackSignals = { applied: true };\n1186:       extraData.feedback_signals = { applied: true };\n1187:     }\n1188: \n1189:     if (pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.graphContribution) {\n1190:       extraData.graphContribution = pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.graphContribution;\n1191:       extraData.graph_contribution = pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.graphContribution;\n1192:     }\n1193: \n1194:     if (pipelineResult.metadata.stage3.rerankApplied) {\n1195:       extraData.rerankMetadata = {\n1196:         reranking_enabled: true,\n1197:         reranking_requested: true,\n1198:         reranking_applied: true,\n1199:       };\n1200:     }\n1201: \n1202:     if (pipelineResult.metadata.stage3.chunkReassemblyStats.chunkParents > 0) {\n1203:       extraData.chunkReassembly = pipelineResult.metadata.stage3.chunkReassemblyStats;\n1204:       extraData.chunk_reassembly = pipelineResult.metadata.stage3.chunkReassemblyStats;\n1205:     }\n1206:     extraData.sourceContract = {\n1207:       version: CANONICAL_READER_CACHE_VERSION,\n1208:       archivedTierEnabled: false,\n1209:       legacyFallbackEnabled: false,\n1210:       includeArchivedCompatibility: includeArchivedRequested === true ? 'ignored' : 'not_requested',\n1211:       preferredDocumentTypes: ['spec_doc', 'continuity'],\n1212:       retainedResults: canonicalFilter.stats.retained,\n1213:       droppedNonCanonicalResults: canonicalFilter.stats.dropped,\n1214:       countsBySourceKind: canonicalFilter.stats.bySourceKind,\n1215:     };\n1216: \n1217:     if (includeTrace && pipelineResult.trace) {\n1218:       extraData.retrievalTrace = pipelineResult.trace;\n1219:     }\n1220:     const degradedReadiness = mapGraphReadinessToTelemetry(\n1221:       getGraphReadinessSnapshotFromMarker(),\n1222:     );\n1223:     searchDecisionEnvelope = buildSearchDecisionEnvelope({\n1224:       requestId: searchDecisionRequestId,\n1225:       tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId,\n1226:       userId: normalizedScope.userId,\n1227:       agentId: normalizedScope.agentId,\n1228:       queryPlan,\n1229:       trustTreeInput: {\n1230:         responsePolicy: {\n1231:           state: 'live',\n1232:           decision: 'memory_search_response',\n1233:         },\n1234:       },\n1235:       degradedReadiness,\n1236:       pipelineTiming: pipelineResult.metadata.timing,\n1237:       timestamp: new Date(_searchStartTime).toISOString(),\n1238:       latencyMs: Date.now() - _searchStartTime,\n1239:     });\n1240:     extraData.searchDecisionEnvelope = searchDecisionEnvelope;\n1241:     extraData.search_decision_envelope = searchDecisionEnvelope;\n1242:     try {\n1243:       const adaptiveShadow = buildAdaptiveShadowProposal(\n1244:         requireDb(),\n1245:         effectiveQuery,\n1246:         resultsForFormatting as Array<Record<string, unknown> & { id: number }>,\n1247:       );\n1248:       if (adaptiveShadow) {\n1249:         extraData.adaptiveShadow = adaptiveShadow;\n1250:         extraData.adaptive_shadow = adaptiveShadow;\n1251:       }\n1252:     } catch (_error: unknown) {\n1253:       // Adaptive proposal logging is best-effort only\n1254:     }\n1255: \n1256:     const appliedBoosts: Record<string, unknown> = {\n1257:       session: { applied: pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.sessionBoostApplied },\n1258:       causal: { applied: pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.causalBoostApplied },\n1259:     };\n1260:     if (folderBoost && folderBoost.folder) {\n1261:       appliedBoosts.folder = { applied: true, folder: folderBoost.folder, factor: folderBoost.factor };\n1262:     }\n1263:     if (communityFallbackApplied) {\n1264:       appliedBoosts.communityFallback = { applied: true, retrievalLevel };\n1265:     }\n1266:     extraData.appliedBoosts = appliedBoosts;\n1267:     extraData.applied_boosts = appliedBoosts;\n1268: \n1269:     let formatted = await formatSearchResults(\n1270:       resultsForFormatting as RawSearchResult[],\n1271:       pipelineConfig.searchType,\n1272:       includeContent,\n1273:       anchors,\n1274:       null,\n1275:       null,\n1276:       extraData,\n1277:       includeTrace,\n1278:       normalizedQuery,   // pass query for recovery + confidence context\n1279:       specFolder ?? null // pass specFolder for recovery narrowing detection\n1280:     );\n1281: \n1282:     // Prepend evidence gap warning if present\n1283:     if (pipelineResult.annotations.evidenceGapWarning && formatted?.content?.[0]?.text) {\n1284:       try {\n1285:         const parsed = JSON.parse(formatted.content[0].text) as Record<string, unknown>;\n1286:         if (typeof parsed.summary === 'string') {\n1287:           parsed.summary = `${pipelineResult.annotations.evidenceGapWarning}\\n\\n${parsed.summary}`;\n1288:           formatted.content[0].text = JSON.stringify(parsed, null, 2);\n1289:         }\n1290:       } catch (_error: unknown) {\n1291:         // Non-fatal\n1292:       }\n1293:     }\n1294:     if (isProgressiveDisclosureEnabled()) {\n1295:       const parsedFormatted = parseResponseEnvelope(formatted);\n1296:       if (parsedFormatted) {\n1297:         const data = parsedFormatted.envelope.data && typeof parsedFormatted.envelope.data === 'object'\n1298:           ? parsedFormatted.envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n1299:           : {};\n1300:         data.progressiveDisclosure = buildProgressiveResponse(\n1301:           resultsForFormatting,\n1302:           undefined,\n1303:           effectiveQuery,\n1304:           { scopeKey: progressiveScopeKey },\n1305:         );\n1306:         parsedFormatted.envelope.data = data;\n1307:         formatted = replaceResponseEnvelope(formatted, parsedFormatted.firstEntry, parsedFormatted.envelope);\n1308:       }\n1309:     }\n1310: \n1311:     formatted = applyPublicationGateToResponse(formatted);\n1312: \n1313:     const cachePayload = extractSearchCachePayload(formatted);\n1314:     if (cachePayload && cacheEnabled) {\n1315:       toolCache.set(cacheKey, cachePayload, { toolName: 'memory_search' });\n1316:     }\n1317: \n1318:     responseToReturn = cachePayload\n1319:       ? buildSearchResponseFromPayload(cachePayload, _searchStartTime, false)\n1320:       : formatted;\n1321:   }\n1322: \n1323:   responseToReturn = applyPublicationGateToResponse(responseToReturn);\n1324: \n1325:   if (sessionId && isSessionRetrievalStateEnabled() && !sessionManager.isEnabled()) {\n1326:     const parsedResponse = parseResponseEnvelope(responseToReturn);\n1327:     const data = parsedResponse?.envelope.data && typeof parsedResponse.envelope.data === 'object'\n1328:       ? parsedResponse.envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n1329:       : null;\n1330:     const existingResults = Array.isArray(data?.results) ? data.results as SessionAwareResult[] : null;\n1331: \n1332:     if (parsedResponse && data && existingResults && existingResults.length > 0) {\n1333:       const deduped = deduplicateWithSessionState(existingResults, sessionId);\n1334:       data.results = deduped.results as SessionAwareResult[];\n1335:       data.count = deduped.results.length;\n1336:       data.sessionDedup = deduped.metadata;\n1337:       parsedResponse.envelope.data = data;\n1338:       responseToReturn = replaceResponseEnvelope(responseToReturn, parsedResponse.firstEntry, parsedResponse.envelope);\n1339:     }\n1340:   }\n1341: \n1342:   // Apply session deduplication AFTER cache\n1343:   if (sessionId && enableDedup && sessionManager.isEnabled()) {\n1344:     let resultsData: Record<string, unknown> | null = null;\n1345:     if (responseToReturn?.content?.[0]?.text && typeof responseToReturn.content[0].text === 'string') {\n1346:       try {\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1346. Use offset=1347 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Search\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   1. DEPENDENCIES\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nimport * as toolCache from '../lib/cache/tool-cache.js';\nimport * as causalEdges from '../lib/storage/causal-edges.js';\nimport * as sessionManager from '../lib/session/session-manager.js';\nimport * as intentClassifier from '../lib/search/intent-classifier.js';\n// TierClassifier, crossEncoder imports removed — only used by legacy V1 pipeline.\nimport { isSessionBoostEnabled, isCausalBoostEnabled, isCommunitySearchFallbackEnabled, isDualRetrievalEnabled, isIntentAutoProfileEnabled } from '../lib/search/search-flags.js';\nimport { searchCommunities } from '../lib/search/community-search.js';\n// 4-stage pipeline architecture\nimport { executePipeline } from '../lib/search/pipeline/index.js';\nimport type { PipelineConfig, PipelineResult } from '../lib/search/pipeline/index.js';\nimport type { IntentWeightsConfig } from '../lib/search/pipeline/types.js';\nimport { initConsumptionLog, logConsumptionEvent } from '../lib/telemetry/consumption-logger.js';\nimport * as retrievalTelemetry from '../lib/telemetry/retrieval-telemetry.js';","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts","text":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Search\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   1. DEPENDENCIES\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nimport * as toolCache from '../lib/cache/tool-cache.js';\nimport * as causalEdges from '../lib/storage/causal-edges.js';\nimport * as sessionManager from '../lib/session/session-manager.js';\nimport * as intentClassifier from '../lib/search/intent-classifier.js';\n// TierClassifier, crossEncoder imports removed — only used by legacy V1 pipeline.\nimport { isSessionBoostEnabled, isCausalBoostEnabled, isCommunitySearchFallbackEnabled, isDualRetrievalEnabled, isIntentAutoProfileEnabled } from '../lib/search/search-flags.js';\nimport { searchCommunities } from '../lib/search/community-search.js';\n// 4-stage pipeline architecture\nimport { executePipeline } from '../lib/search/pipeline/index.js';\nimport type { PipelineConfig, PipelineResult } from '../lib/search/pipeline/index.js';\nimport type { IntentWeightsConfig } from '../lib/search/pipeline/types.js';\nimport { initConsumptionLog, logConsumptionEvent } from '../lib/telemetry/consumption-logger.js';\nimport * as retrievalTelemetry from '../lib/telemetry/retrieval-telemetry.js';\n// Artifact-class routing (spec/plan/tasks/checklist/memory)\nimport { getStrategyForQuery } from '../lib/search/artifact-routing.js';\nimport { routeQuery } from '../lib/search/query-router.js';\nimport { createEmptyQueryPlan, type QueryPlan } from '../lib/query/query-plan.js';\nimport { getGraphReadinessSnapshotFromMarker } from '../lib/code-graph-boundary.js';\nimport { mapGraphReadinessToTelemetry } from '../lib/search/graph-readiness-mapper.js';\nimport {\n  buildSearchDecisionEnvelope,\n  type SearchDecisionEnvelope,\n} from '../lib/search/search-decision-envelope.js';\nimport { recordSearchDecision } from '../lib/search/decision-audit.js';\n// Chunk reassembly (extracted from this file)\nimport { collapseAndReassembleChunkResults } from '../lib/search/chunk-reassembly.js';\n// Search utilities (extracted from this file)\nimport {\n  filterByMinQualityScore,\n  resolveQualityThreshold,\n  buildCacheArgs,\n  resolveRowContextType,\n  resolveArtifactRoutingQuery,\n  applyArtifactRouting,\n} from '../lib/search/search-utils.js';\n// CacheArgsInput used internally by buildCacheArgs (lib/search/search-utils.ts)\n// Eval channel tracking (extracted from this file)\nimport {\n  collectEvalChannelsFromRow,\n  buildEvalChannelPayloads,\n  summarizeGraphWalkDiagnostics,\n} from '../lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.js';\nimport type { EvalChannelPayload } from '../lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.js';\n\n// Eval logger — fail-safe, no-op when SPECKIT_EVAL_LOGGING !== \"true\"\nimport { logSearchQuery, logChannelResult, logFinalResult } from '../lib/eval/eval-logger.js';\nimport {\n  logFeedbackEvents,\n  isImplicitFeedbackLogEnabled,\n} from '../lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.js';\nimport type { FeedbackEvent } from '../lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.js';\nimport { trackQueryAndDetect, logResultCited } from '../lib/feedback/query-flow-tracker.js';\n\n// Core utilities\nimport { checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\nimport { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\nimport { validateQuery, requireDb, toErrorMessage } from '../utils/index.js';\n\n// Response envelope + formatters\nimport { createMCPErrorResponse, createMCPSuccessResponse } from '../lib/response/envelope.js';\nimport { formatSearchResults } from '../formatters/index.js';\n\n// Shared handler types\nimport type { MCPResponse, IntentClassification } from './types.js';\n\n// Retrieval trace contracts (C136-08)\nimport { createTrace } from '@spec-kit/shared/contracts/retrieval-trace';\nimport { buildAdaptiveShadowProposal } from '../lib/cognitive/adaptive-ranking.js';\nimport { normalizeScopeContext, filterRowsByScope } from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\nimport {\n  attachSessionTransitionTrace,\n  type SessionTransitionTrace,\n} from '../lib/search/session-transition.js';\n\n// Mode-Aware Response Shape\nimport {\n  applyProfileToEnvelope,\n  isResponseProfileEnabled,\n} from '../lib/response/profile-formatters.js';\nimport {\n  buildProgressiveResponse,\n  extractSnippets,\n  isProgressiveDisclosureEnabled,\n  resolveCursor,\n} from '../lib/search/progressive-disclosure.js';\nimport {\n  SPEC_DOCUMENT_FILENAMES,\n  canClassifyAsSpecDocument,\n  normalizeSpecPath,\n} from '../lib/config/spec-doc-paths.js';\nimport {\n  getLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot,\n  resetLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot,\n} from '../lib/search/sqlite-fts.js';\nimport type { LexicalCapabilitySnapshot } from '../lib/search/sqlite-fts.js';\nimport { evaluatePublicationGate } from '../lib/context/publication-gate.js';\nimport {\n  deduplicateResults as deduplicateWithSessionState,\n  isSessionRetrievalStateEnabled,\n  manager as retrievalSessionStateManager,\n  refineForGoal,\n} from '../lib/search/session-state.js';\n\n// Type imports for casting\nimport type { IntentType, IntentWeights as IntentClassifierWeights } from '../lib/search/intent-classifier.js';\nimport type { RawSearchResult } from '../formatters/index.js';\n// RoutingResult, WeightedResult — now used internally by lib/search/search-utils.ts\n\n// Feature catalog: Semantic and lexical search (memory_search)\n// Feature catalog: Hybrid search pipeline\n// Feature catalog: 4-stage pipeline architecture\n// Feature catalog: Quality-aware 3-tier search fallback\n\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   2. TYPES\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\n/**\n * Internal search result row — enriched DB row used within this handler.\n * NOT the same as the canonical SearchResult in shared/types.ts.\n * Self-contained: uses local types instead of the deprecated MemoryRow/MemoryRecord shapes.\n * This can migrate to MemoryDbRow & Record<string, unknown> later without changing the handler contract.\n */\ninterface MemorySearchRow extends Record<string, unknown> {\n  id: number;\n  similarity?: number;\n  importance_tier?: string;\n  contextType?: string;\n  context_type?: string;\n  attentionScore?: number;\n  retrievability?: number;\n  stability?: number;\n  last_review?: string | null;\n  created_at?: string;\n  last_accessed?: number;\n  content?: string;\n  memoryState?: string;\n  file_path?: string;\n  parent_id?: number | null;\n  chunk_index?: number | null;\n  chunk_label?: string | null;\n  isChunk?: boolean;\n  parentId?: number | null;\n  chunkIndex?: number | null;\n  chunkLabel?: string | null;\n  chunkCount?: number | null;\n  contentSource?: 'reassembled_chunks' | 'file_read_fallback';\n  precomputedContent?: string;\n}\n\ninterface DedupResult {\n  results: MemorySearchRow[];\n  dedupStats: Record<string, unknown>;\n}\n\ninterface SearchCachePayload {\n  summary: string;\n  data: Record<string, unknown>;\n  hints: string[];\n}\n\ntype SessionAwareResult = Record<string, unknown> & {\n  id: number | string;\n  score?: number;\n  content?: string;\n};\n\ntype CanonicalSourceKind = 'spec_doc' | 'continuity' | 'constitutional';\n\ninterface CanonicalSourceStats {\n  retained: number;\n  dropped: number;\n  bySourceKind: Record<CanonicalSourceKind, number>;\n}\n\nconst CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID = '_memory.continuity';\nconst CANONICAL_READER_CACHE_VERSION = 'gate-d-reader-ready-v1';\nconst CANONICAL_SPEC_DOC_DOCUMENT_TYPES = new Set([\n  'spec',\n  'plan',\n  'tasks',\n  'checklist',\n  'decision_record',\n  'implementation_summary',\n  'research',\n  'handover',\n  'graph_metadata',\n  'spec_doc',\n]);\nconst NON_CANONICAL_DOCUMENT_TYPES = new Set([\n  'memory',\n  'scratch',\n]);\n\nfunction normalizeDocumentType(value: unknown): string | null {\n  if (typeof value !== 'string') {\n    return null;\n  }\n  const normalized = value.trim().toLowerCase();\n  return normalized.length > 0 ? normalized : null;\n}\n\nfunction resolveAnchorId(row: Record<string, unknown>): string | null {\n  const value = row.anchor_id ?? row.anchorId;\n  return typeof value === 'string' && value.trim().length > 0\n    ? value.trim()\n    : null;\n}\n\nfunction resolveFilePath(row: Record<string, unknown>): string | null {\n  const value = row.file_path ?? row.filePath;\n  return typeof value === 'string' && value.trim().length > 0\n    ? value\n    : null;\n}\n\nfunction resolveCanonicalSourceKind(row: Record<string, unknown>): CanonicalSourceKind | null {\n  const documentType = normalizeDocumentType(row.document_type ?? row.documentType);\n  const importanceTier = normalizeDocumentType(row.importance_tier ?? row.importanceTier);\n  const anchorId = resolveAnchorId(row);\n\n  if (importanceTier === 'constitutional' || documentType === 'constitutional') {\n    return 'constitutional';\n  }\n\n  if (anchorId === CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID || documentType === 'continuity') {\n    return 'continuity';\n  }\n\n  if (documentType && CANONICAL_SPEC_DOC_DOCUMENT_TYPES.has(documentType)) {\n    return 'spec_doc';\n  }\n\n  if (documentType && NON_CANONICAL_DOCUMENT_TYPES.has(documentType)) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const filePath = resolveFilePath(row);\n  if (!filePath) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  const normalizedPath = normalizeSpecPath(filePath);\n  const basename = normalizedPath.split('/').filter(Boolean).pop() ?? '';\n\n  if (\n    basename.length > 0 &&\n    SPEC_DOCUMENT_FILENAMES.has(basename) &&\n    canClassifyAsSpecDocument(normalizedPath)\n  ) {\n    return anchorId === CONTINUITY_ANCHOR_ID ? 'continuity' : 'spec_doc';\n  }\n\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction filterCanonicalSourceRows<T extends SessionAwareResult>(\n  results: T[],\n): { results: T[]; stats: CanonicalSourceStats } {\n  const stats: CanonicalSourceStats = {\n    retained: 0,\n    dropped: 0,\n    bySourceKind: {\n      spec_doc: 0,\n      continuity: 0,\n      constitutional: 0,\n    },\n  };\n\n  const filtered: T[] = [];\n  for (const result of results) {\n    const sourceKind = resolveCanonicalSourceKind(result);\n    if (!sourceKind) {\n      stats.dropped += 1;\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    filtered.push({\n      ...result,\n      canonicalSource: sourceKind,\n      canonicalSourceType: sourceKind,\n      documentType: sourceKind,\n    });\n    stats.retained += 1;\n    stats.bySourceKind[sourceKind] += 1;\n  }\n\n  return { results: filtered, stats };\n}\n\n// ChunkReassemblyResult — now imported from lib/search/chunk-reassembly.ts\n\ntype IntentWeights = IntentClassifierWeights;\n\nfunction toIntentWeightsConfig(weights: IntentWeights | null): IntentWeightsConfig | null {\n  if (!weights) return null;\n  return {\n    similarity: weights.similarity,\n    importance: weights.importance,\n    recency: weights.recency,\n  };\n}\n\n// EvalChannelPayload — now imported from lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.ts\n\ninterface SearchArgs {\n  cursor?: string;\n  query?: string;\n  concepts?: string[];\n  specFolder?: string;\n  folderBoost?: { folder: string; factor: number };\n  tenantId?: string;\n  userId?: string;\n  agentId?: string;\n  limit?: number;\n  tier?: string;\n  contextType?: string;\n  useDecay?: boolean;\n  includeContiguity?: boolean;\n  includeConstitutional?: boolean;\n  includeContent?: boolean;\n  anchors?: string[];\n  bypassCache?: boolean;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  enableDedup?: boolean;\n  intent?: string;\n  autoDetectIntent?: boolean;\n  minState?: string;\n  applyStateLimits?: boolean;\n  rerank?: boolean;\n  applyLengthPenalty?: boolean;\n  trackAccess?: boolean; // opt-in access tracking (default false)\n  includeArchived?: boolean; // Include archived memories in search (default false)\n  enableSessionBoost?: boolean;\n  enableCausalBoost?: boolean;\n  minQualityScore?: number;\n  min_quality_score?: number;\n  mode?: string; // \"deep\" mode enables query expansion for multi-query RAG\n  includeTrace?: boolean;\n  sessionTransition?: SessionTransitionTrace;\n  /** Presentation profile ('quick'|'research'|'resume'|'debug'). Default: full response. */\n  profile?: string;\n  /** Dual-level retrieval — 'local' (entity), 'global' (community), 'auto' (local + fallback). */\n  retrievalLevel?: 'local' | 'global' | 'auto';\n}\n\n// resolveRowContextType — now imported from lib/search/search-utils.ts\n// resolveEvalScore, collectEvalChannelsFromRow — now imported from lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.ts\n\nfunction attachTelemetryMeta(\n  response: MCPResponse,\n  telemetryPayload: Record<string, unknown>,\n): MCPResponse {\n  const firstEntry = response?.content?.[0];\n  if (!firstEntry || typeof firstEntry.text !== 'string') {\n    return response;\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const envelope = JSON.parse(firstEntry.text) as Record<string, unknown>;\n    const meta = envelope.meta && typeof envelope.meta === 'object'\n      ? envelope.meta as Record<string, unknown>\n      : {};\n    envelope.meta = {\n      ...meta,\n      _telemetry: telemetryPayload,\n    };\n\n    return {\n      ...response,\n      content: [{ ...firstEntry, text: JSON.stringify(envelope, null, 2) }],\n    };\n  } catch (error: unknown) {\n    const message = toErrorMessage(error);\n    console.warn('[memory-search] Failed to attach telemetry payload:', message);\n    return response;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction extractResponseResults(response: MCPResponse): Array<Record<string, unknown>> {\n  const firstEntry = response?.content?.[0];\n  if (!firstEntry || typeof firstEntry.text !== 'string') {\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const envelope = JSON.parse(firstEntry.text) as Record<string, unknown>;\n    const data = envelope.data && typeof envelope.data === 'object'\n      ? envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n      : null;\n    return Array.isArray(data?.results)\n      ? data.results as Array<Record<string, unknown>>\n      : [];\n  } catch {\n    return [];\n  }\n}\n\nfunction extractSearchCachePayload(response: MCPResponse): SearchCachePayload | null {\n  const firstEntry = response?.content?.[0];\n  if (!firstEntry || typeof firstEntry.text !== 'string') {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const envelope = JSON.parse(firstEntry.text) as Record<string, unknown>;\n    const summary = typeof envelope.summary === 'string' ? envelope.summary : null;\n    const data = envelope.data && typeof envelope.data === 'object'\n      ? envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n      : null;\n    const hints = Array.isArray(envelope.hints)\n      ? envelope.hints.filter((hint): hint is string => typeof hint === 'string')\n      : [];\n\n    if (!summary || !data) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    return { summary, data, hints };\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction parseResponseEnvelope(\n  response: MCPResponse,\n): { firstEntry: { type: 'text'; text: string }; envelope: Record<string, unknown> } | null {\n  const firstEntry = response?.content?.[0];\n  if (!firstEntry || firstEntry.type !== 'text' || typeof firstEntry.text !== 'string') {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  try {\n    return {\n      firstEntry,\n      envelope: JSON.parse(firstEntry.text) as Record<string, unknown>,\n    };\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction replaceResponseEnvelope(\n  response: MCPResponse,\n  firstEntry: { type: 'text'; text: string },\n  envelope: Record<string, unknown>,\n): MCPResponse {\n  return {\n    ...response,\n    content: [{ ...firstEntry, text: JSON.stringify(envelope, null, 2) }],\n  };\n}\n\nfunction buildSessionStatePayload(sessionId: string): Record<string, unknown> {\n  const session = retrievalSessionStateManager.getOrCreate(sessionId);\n  return {\n    activeGoal: session.activeGoal,\n    seenResultIds: Array.from(session.seenResultIds),\n    openQuestions: [...session.openQuestions],\n    preferredAnchors: [...session.preferredAnchors],\n  };\n}\n\nfunction buildSearchResponseFromPayload(\n  payload: SearchCachePayload,\n  startTime: number,\n  cacheHit: boolean,\n): MCPResponse {\n  return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n    tool: 'memory_search',\n    summary: payload.summary,\n    data: payload.data,\n    hints: payload.hints,\n    startTime,\n    cacheHit,\n  });\n}\n\nfunction resolveSearchScore(result: Record<string, unknown>): number | null {\n  const candidate = result.score ?? result.similarity ?? result.averageSimilarity ?? result.intentAdjustedScore;\n  if (typeof candidate !== 'number' || !Number.isFinite(candidate)) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return candidate > 1 ? candidate / 100 : candidate;\n}\n\nfunction computeAverageScore(results: Array<Record<string, unknown>>): number {\n  const scores = results\n    .map(resolveSearchScore)\n    .filter((score): score is number => score !== null);\n  if (scores.length === 0) return 0;\n  return scores.reduce((sum, score) => sum + score, 0) / scores.length;\n}\n\nfunction attachLexicalCapabilityMetadata(\n  response: MCPResponse,\n  snapshot: LexicalCapabilitySnapshot | null,\n): MCPResponse {\n  const parsed = parseResponseEnvelope(response);\n  if (!parsed) {\n    return response;\n  }\n\n  const data = parsed.envelope.data && typeof parsed.envelope.data === 'object'\n    ? parsed.envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n    : {};\n\n  if (typeof data.lexicalPath !== 'string' && snapshot) {\n    data.lexicalPath = snapshot.lexicalPath;\n  }\n  if (typeof data.fallbackState !== 'string' && snapshot) {\n    data.fallbackState = snapshot.fallbackState;\n  }\n\n  parsed.envelope.data = data;\n  return replaceResponseEnvelope(response, parsed.firstEntry, parsed.envelope);\n}\n\nfunction hasPublicationContractFields(result: Record<string, unknown>): boolean {\n  return [\n    'certainty',\n    'methodologyStatus',\n    'schemaVersion',\n    'provenance',\n    'multiplierAuthorityFields',\n  ].some((field) => Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(result, field));\n}\n\nfunction applyPublicationGateToResponse(response: MCPResponse): MCPResponse {\n  const parsed = parseResponseEnvelope(response);\n  if (!parsed) {\n    return response;\n  }\n\n  const data = parsed.envelope.data && typeof parsed.envelope.data === 'object'\n    ? parsed.envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n    : null;\n  const results = Array.isArray(data?.results)\n    ? data.results as Array<Record<string, unknown>>\n    : null;\n\n  if (!data || !results) {\n    return response;\n  }\n\n  data.results = results.map((result) => {\n    if (!hasPublicationContractFields(result)) {\n      return result;\n    }\n\n    const gateResult = evaluatePublicationGate({\n      certainty: result.certainty,\n      methodologyStatus: result.methodologyStatus as 'provisional' | 'published' | null | undefined,\n      schemaVersion: result.schemaVersion as string | null | undefined,\n      provenance: Array.isArray(result.provenance) ? result.provenance as string[] : null,\n      multiplierAuthorityFields: result.multiplierAuthorityFields as Record<string, unknown> | null | undefined,\n    });\n\n    return gateResult.publishable\n      ? {\n        ...result,\n        publishable: true,\n      }\n      : {\n        ...result,\n        publishable: false,\n        exclusionReason: gateResult.exclusionReason,\n      };\n  });\n\n  parsed.envelope.data = data;\n  return replaceResponseEnvelope(response, parsed.firstEntry, parsed.envelope);\n}\n\n// summarizeGraphWalkDiagnostics, buildEvalChannelPayloads — now imported from lib/telemetry/eval-channel-tracking.ts\n\n// filterByMinQualityScore, resolveQualityThreshold, buildCacheArgs,\n// resolveArtifactRoutingQuery, applyArtifactRouting — now imported from lib/search/search-utils.ts\n// CacheArgsInput — now imported from lib/search/search-utils.ts\n// parseNullableInt, collapseAndReassembleChunkResults — now imported from lib/search/chunk-reassembly.ts\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   3. CONFIGURATION\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\n// Sections 3–5 (STATE_PRIORITY, MAX_DEEP_QUERY_VARIANTS, buildDeepQueryVariants,\n// StrengthenOnAccess, applyTestingEffect, filterByMemoryState) removed in\n// These were only used by the legacy V1 pipeline.\n// The V2 4-stage pipeline handles state filtering (Stage 4), testing effect, and\n// Query expansion through its own stages.\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   6. SESSION DEDUPLICATION UTILITIES\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nfunction applySessionDedup(results: MemorySearchRow[], sessionId: string, enableDedup: boolean): DedupResult {\n  if (!enableDedup || !sessionId || !sessionManager.isEnabled()) {\n    return {\n      results,\n      dedupStats: { enabled: false, sessionId: null }\n    };\n  }\n\n  const { filtered, dedupStats } = sessionManager.filterSearchResults(sessionId, results as Parameters<typeof sessionManager.filterSearchResults>[1]);\n\n  if (filtered.length > 0) {\n    sessionManager.markResultsSent(sessionId, filtered as Parameters<typeof sessionManager.markResultsSent>[1]);\n  }\n\n  return {\n    results: filtered as MemorySearchRow[],\n    dedupStats: {\n      ...dedupStats,\n      sessionId\n    }\n  };\n}\n\n// Sections 7–9 (applyCrossEncoderReranking, applyIntentWeightsToResults,\n// ShouldApplyPostSearchIntentWeighting, postSearchPipeline) removed in\n// These were only used by the legacy V1 pipeline\n// Path. The V2 4-stage pipeline handles all equivalent functionality.\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   10. MAIN HANDLER\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\n/** Handle memory_search tool — performs hybrid vector/BM25 search with intent-aware ranking.\n * @param args - Search arguments (query, concepts, mode, specFolder, etc.)\n * @returns MCP response with ranked search results\n */\nasync function handleMemorySearch(args: SearchArgs): Promise<MCPResponse> {\n  await ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized('handler:memory_search');\n  const _searchStartTime = Date.now();\n  resetLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot();\n  // BUG-001: Check for external database updates before processing\n  await checkDatabaseUpdated();\n\n  const {\n    cursor,\n    query,\n    concepts,\n    specFolder,\n    folderBoost,\n    tenantId,\n    userId,\n    agentId,\n    limit: rawLimit = 10,\n    tier,\n    contextType,\n    useDecay: useDecay = true,\n    includeContiguity: includeContiguity = false,\n    includeConstitutional: includeConstitutional = true,\n    includeContent: includeContent = false,\n    anchors,\n    bypassCache: bypassCache = false,\n    sessionId: rawSessionId,\n    enableDedup: enableDedup = true,\n    intent: explicitIntent,\n    autoDetectIntent: autoDetectIntent = true,\n    minState,  // No default — memoryState column not yet in schema; defaulting to 'WARM' filters all rows\n    applyStateLimits: applyStateLimits = false,\n    rerank = true, // Enable reranking by default for better result quality\n    applyLengthPenalty: applyLengthPenalty = true,\n    trackAccess: trackAccess = false, // opt-in, off by default\n    includeArchived: includeArchivedRequested = false, // compatibility-only after Gate B cleanup\n    enableSessionBoost: enableSessionBoost = isSessionBoostEnabled(),\n    enableCausalBoost: enableCausalBoost = isCausalBoostEnabled(),\n    minQualityScore,\n    min_quality_score,\n    mode,\n    includeTrace: includeTraceArg = false,\n    sessionTransition,\n    profile,\n    retrievalLevel: retrievalLevel = 'auto',\n  } = args;\n  const includeTraceByFlag = process.env.SPECKIT_RESPONSE_TRACE === 'true';\n  const includeTrace = includeTraceByFlag || includeTraceArg === true;\n  const includeArchived = false;\n\n  // Validate any caller-supplied sessionId through the server-side session\n  // manager to prevent IDOR: a caller must not read or mutate another\n  // session's sent-memory dedup state by forging an arbitrary session id.\n  // Omitting sessionId stays unchanged (downstream treats it as no-session).\n  let sessionId: string | undefined = rawSessionId;\n  if (rawSessionId) {\n    const trustedSession = sessionManager.resolveTrustedSession(rawSessionId, {\n      tenantId,\n      userId,\n      agentId,\n    });\n    if (trustedSession.error) {\n      return createMCPErrorResponse({\n        tool: 'memory_search',\n        error: trustedSession.error,\n        code: 'E_SESSION_SCOPE',\n        details: { requestedSessionId: rawSessionId },\n        recovery: {\n          hint: 'Omit sessionId to start a new server-generated session, or reuse the effectiveSessionId returned by memory_context.',\n        },\n      });\n    }\n    sessionId = trustedSession.effectiveSessionId;\n  }\n\n  const normalizedScope = normalizeScopeContext({ tenantId, userId, agentId, sessionId });\n  const progressiveScopeKey = JSON.stringify({\n    tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId ?? null,\n    userId: normalizedScope.userId ?? null,\n    agentId: normalizedScope.agentId ?? null,\n    sessionId: normalizedScope.sessionId ?? null,\n  });\n\n  // Validate at least one search input is provided (moved from schema superRefine for GPT compatibility)\n  const hasCursor = typeof cursor === 'string' && cursor.trim().length > 0;\n  const hasQuery = typeof query === 'string' && query.trim().length > 0;\n  const hasConcepts = Array.isArray(concepts) && concepts.length >= 2;\n  if (!hasCursor && !hasQuery && !hasConcepts) {\n    return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify({ error: 'Either \"query\" (string), \"concepts\" (array with 2-5 items), or \"cursor\" (string) is required.' }) }] };\n  }\n\n  if (hasCursor) {\n    const resolved = resolveCursor(cursor.trim(), undefined, { scopeKey: progressiveScopeKey });\n    if (!resolved) {\n      return createMCPErrorResponse({\n        tool: 'memory_search',\n        error: 'Cursor is invalid, expired, or out of scope',\n        code: 'E_VALIDATION',\n        details: { parameter: 'cursor' },\n        recovery: {\n          hint: 'Retry the original search to generate a fresh continuation cursor',\n        },\n      });\n    }\n\n    const snippetResults = extractSnippets(resolved.results);\n    return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n      tool: 'memory_search',\n      summary: `Returned ${snippetResults.length} continuation results`,\n      data: {\n        count: snippetResults.length,\n        results: snippetResults,\n        continuation: resolved.continuation,\n      },\n      startTime: _searchStartTime,\n      cacheHit: false,\n    });\n  }\n\n  const qualityThreshold = resolveQualityThreshold(minQualityScore, min_quality_score);\n\n  // Validate numeric limit parameter\n  const limit = (typeof rawLimit === 'number' && Number.isFinite(rawLimit) && rawLimit > 0)\n    ? Math.min(Math.floor(rawLimit), 100)\n    : 10;\n\n  // BUG-007: Validate query first with proper error handling\n  let normalizedQuery: string | null = null;\n  if (query !== undefined) {\n    try {\n      normalizedQuery = validateQuery(query);\n    } catch (validationError: unknown) {\n      if (!concepts || !Array.isArray(concepts) || concepts.length < 2) {\n        const message = toErrorMessage(validationError);\n        return createMCPErrorResponse({\n          tool: 'memory_search',\n          error: message,\n          code: 'E_VALIDATION',\n          details: { parameter: 'query' },\n          recovery: {\n            hint: 'Provide a valid query string or use concepts array instead'\n          }\n        });\n      }\n      normalizedQuery = null;\n    }\n  }\n\n  const hasValidQuery = normalizedQuery !== null;\n  const hasValidConcepts = Array.isArray(concepts) && concepts.length >= 2;\n  const effectiveQuery = normalizedQuery ?? (hasValidConcepts ? concepts.join(', ') : '');\n  const searchDecisionRequestId = `memory_search-${_searchStartTime}`;\n  let searchDecisionEnvelope: SearchDecisionEnvelope | null = null;\n\n  if (!hasValidQuery && !hasValidConcepts) {\n    return createMCPErrorResponse({\n      tool: 'memory_search',\n      error: 'Either query (string), concepts (array of 2-5 strings), or cursor (string) is required',\n      code: 'E_VALIDATION',\n      details: { parameter: 'query' },\n      recovery: {\n        hint: 'Provide a query string, concepts array with 2-5 entries, or a continuation cursor'\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  if (specFolder !== undefined && typeof specFolder !== 'string') {\n    return createMCPErrorResponse({\n      tool: 'memory_search',\n      error: 'specFolder must be a string',\n      code: 'E_VALIDATION',\n      details: { parameter: 'specFolder' },\n      recovery: {\n        hint: 'Provide specFolder as a string path'\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Eval logger — capture query at pipeline entry (fail-safe)\n  let _evalQueryId = 0;\n  let _evalRunId = 0;\n  try {\n    const evalEntry = logSearchQuery({\n      query: effectiveQuery,\n      intent: explicitIntent ?? null,\n      specFolder: specFolder ?? null,\n    });\n    _evalQueryId = evalEntry.queryId;\n    _evalRunId = evalEntry.evalRunId;\n  } catch (_error: unknown) { /* eval logging must never break search */ }\n\n  const artifactRoutingQuery = resolveArtifactRoutingQuery(\n    normalizedQuery,\n    hasValidConcepts ? concepts : undefined\n  );\n  let artifactRouting = getStrategyForQuery(artifactRoutingQuery, specFolder);\n  let queryPlan: QueryPlan;\n  try {\n    queryPlan = routeQuery(effectiveQuery).queryPlan;\n  } catch (_error: unknown) {\n    queryPlan = createEmptyQueryPlan({\n      complexity: 'unknown',\n      selectedChannels: ['vector', 'fts', 'bm25', 'graph', 'degree'],\n      fallbackPolicy: {\n        mode: 'telemetry_only',\n        reason: 'QueryPlan telemetry fallback after routeQuery failure',\n      },\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Intent-aware retrieval\n  let detectedIntent: string | null = null;\n  let intentConfidence = 0;\n  let intentWeights: IntentWeights | null = null;\n\n  if (explicitIntent) {\n    if (intentClassifier.isValidIntent(explicitIntent)) {\n      detectedIntent = explicitIntent;\n      intentConfidence = 1.0;\n      intentWeights = intentClassifier.getIntentWeights(explicitIntent);\n    } else {\n      console.warn(`[memory-search] Invalid intent '${explicitIntent}', using auto-detection`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (!detectedIntent && autoDetectIntent && hasValidQuery) {\n    const classification: IntentClassification = intentClassifier.classifyIntent(normalizedQuery!);\n    detectedIntent = classification.intent;\n    intentConfidence = classification.confidence;\n    intentWeights = intentClassifier.getIntentWeights(classification.intent as IntentType);\n\n    if (classification.fallback) {\n      console.error(`[memory-search] Intent auto-detected as '${detectedIntent}' (fallback: ${classification.reason})`);\n    } else {\n      console.error(`[memory-search] Intent auto-detected as '${detectedIntent}' (confidence: ${intentConfidence.toFixed(2)})`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // FIX RC3-B: Intent confidence floor — override low-confidence auto-detections to \"understand\"\n  const INTENT_CONFIDENCE_FLOOR = parseFloat(process.env.SPECKIT_INTENT_CONFIDENCE_FLOOR || '0.25');\n  if (detectedIntent && intentConfidence < INTENT_CONFIDENCE_FLOOR && !explicitIntent) {\n    console.error(`[memory-search] Intent confidence ${intentConfidence.toFixed(3)} below floor ${INTENT_CONFIDENCE_FLOOR}, overriding '${detectedIntent}' → 'understand'`);\n    detectedIntent = 'understand';\n    intentConfidence = 1.0;\n    intentWeights = intentClassifier.getIntentWeights('understand' as IntentType);\n  }\n\n  // Phase C: Intent-to-profile auto-routing.\n  // Explicit caller `profile` always takes precedence; auto-detect fills in when absent.\n  let effectiveProfile: string | undefined = profile;\n  if (!effectiveProfile && detectedIntent && isIntentAutoProfileEnabled()) {\n    try {\n      const autoProfile = intentClassifier.getProfileForIntent(detectedIntent as IntentType);\n      if (autoProfile) {\n        effectiveProfile = autoProfile;\n        console.error(`[memory-search] Intent-to-profile auto-routing: '${detectedIntent}' → profile '${autoProfile}'`);\n      }\n    } catch (_autoProfileErr: unknown) {\n      // Auto-profile is best-effort — never breaks search\n    }\n  }\n  const adaptiveFusionIntent = effectiveProfile === 'resume'\n    ? 'continuity'\n    : detectedIntent;\n\n  // Re-run artifact routing with detected intent for fallback coverage\n  if (detectedIntent && artifactRouting?.detectedClass === 'unknown' && artifactRouting?.confidence === 0) {\n    artifactRouting = getStrategyForQuery(artifactRoutingQuery, specFolder, detectedIntent);\n  }\n\n  // Create retrieval trace at pipeline entry\n  const trace = createTrace(\n    effectiveQuery,\n    sessionId,\n    detectedIntent || undefined\n  );\n\n  // When causal boost is enabled, fold the causal-edges generation\n  // counter into the cache key so causal-edge mutations naturally invalidate\n  // the affected memory_search entries on the next lookup. We deliberately\n  // keep the generation OFF the key when the caller has not opted into causal\n  // boost — otherwise unrelated callers would suffer needless cache misses.\n  const causalEdgesGenerationForCache = enableCausalBoost\n    ? causalEdges.getCausalEdgesGeneration()\n    : undefined;\n\n  // Build cache key args\n  const cacheArgs = buildCacheArgs({\n    normalizedQuery,\n    hasValidConcepts,\n    concepts,\n    specFolder,\n    tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId,\n    userId: normalizedScope.userId,\n    agentId: normalizedScope.agentId,\n    limit,\n    mode,\n    tier,\n    contextType,\n    useDecay,\n    includeArchived,\n    qualityThreshold,\n    applyStateLimits,\n    includeContiguity,\n    includeConstitutional,\n    includeContent,\n    anchors,\n    detectedIntent,\n    adaptiveFusionIntent,\n    minState: minState ?? '',\n    rerank,\n    applyLengthPenalty,\n    sessionId,\n    enableSessionBoost,\n    enableCausalBoost,\n    includeTrace,\n    cacheVersion: CANONICAL_READER_CACHE_VERSION,\n    causalEdgesGeneration: causalEdgesGenerationForCache,\n  });\n\n  let _evalChannelPayloads: EvalChannelPayload[] = [];\n  const cacheKey = toolCache.generateCacheKey('memory_search', cacheArgs);\n  const cacheEnabled = toolCache.isEnabled() && !bypassCache;\n  const cachedPayload = cacheEnabled\n    ? toolCache.get<SearchCachePayload>(cacheKey)\n    : null;\n\n  let responseToReturn: MCPResponse;\n  let goalRefinementPayload: Record<string, unknown> | null = null;\n\n  if (cachedPayload) {\n    responseToReturn = buildSearchResponseFromPayload(cachedPayload, _searchStartTime, true);\n  } else {\n    // V2 pipeline is the only path (legacy V1 removed from the runtime pipeline)\n    const pipelineConfig: PipelineConfig = {\n      query: effectiveQuery,\n      concepts: hasValidConcepts ? concepts : undefined,\n      searchType: (hasValidConcepts && concepts!.length >= 2)\n        ? 'multi-concept'\n        : 'hybrid',\n      mode,\n      limit,\n      specFolder,\n      tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId,\n      userId: normalizedScope.userId,\n      agentId: normalizedScope.agentId,\n      tier,\n      contextType,\n      includeArchived,\n      includeConstitutional,\n      includeContent,\n      anchors,\n      qualityThreshold,\n      minState: minState ?? '',\n      applyStateLimits,\n      useDecay,\n      rerank,\n      applyLengthPenalty,\n      sessionId,\n      enableDedup,\n      enableSessionBoost,\n      enableCausalBoost,\n      trackAccess,\n      detectedIntent,\n      adaptiveFusionIntent,\n      intentConfidence,\n      intentWeights: toIntentWeightsConfig(intentWeights),\n      artifactRouting: artifactRouting as unknown as PipelineConfig['artifactRouting'],\n      queryPlan,\n      trace,\n    };\n\n    const pipelineResult: PipelineResult = await executePipeline(pipelineConfig);\n    let resultsForFormatting = pipelineResult.results as unknown as SessionAwareResult[];\n\n    // Community search fallback — inject community members on weak results\n    let communityFallbackApplied = false;\n    const shouldRunCommunitySearch = (\n      isDualRetrievalEnabled() &&\n      isCommunitySearchFallbackEnabled() &&\n      effectiveQuery.length > 0 &&\n      (retrievalLevel === 'global' || retrievalLevel === 'auto')\n    );\n    if (shouldRunCommunitySearch) {\n      const isWeakResult = resultsForFormatting.length === 0 ||\n        (resultsForFormatting.length < 3 && (retrievalLevel === 'global' || retrievalLevel === 'auto'));\n      if (isWeakResult) {\n        try {\n          const communityResults = searchCommunities(effectiveQuery, requireDb(), 5);\n          if (communityResults.totalMemberIds.length > 0) {\n            // Fetch the actual memory rows for community member IDs\n            const memberIds = communityResults.totalMemberIds.slice(0, 20);\n            const placeholders = memberIds.map(() => '?').join(', ');\n            const db = requireDb();\n            const rawMemberRows = db.prepare(`\n              SELECT id, title, similarity, content, file_path, anchor_id, document_type,\n                     importance_tier, context_type, quality_score, created_at,\n                     tenant_id, user_id, agent_id\n              FROM memory_index\n              WHERE id IN (${placeholders})\n            `).all(...memberIds) as Array<Record<string, unknown> & { id: number }>;\n\n            // Apply governed retrieval scope to the community fallback so it cannot\n            // bypass the tenant/user/agent boundary the canonical pipeline enforces.\n            // sessionId is deliberately excluded — it is a dedup/continuity key, not\n            // a row-access boundary. Unscoped (single-user) callers are unaffected.\n            const hasGovernanceScope = Boolean(\n              normalizedScope.tenantId || normalizedScope.userId || normalizedScope.agentId,\n            );\n            const memberRows = hasGovernanceScope\n              ? filterRowsByScope(rawMemberRows, {\n                  tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId,\n                  userId: normalizedScope.userId,\n                  agentId: normalizedScope.agentId,\n                })\n              : rawMemberRows;\n\n            if (memberRows.length > 0) {\n              // Calibrate score from community match quality, bounded below pipeline threshold\n              const communityScoreScale = 0.02; // aligns with pipeline's minimum quality floor\n              const avgMatchScore = communityResults.results.length > 0\n                ? communityResults.results.reduce((sum, r) => sum + r.matchScore, 0) / communityResults.results.length\n                : 0.5;\n              const calibratedScore = Math.max(0.001, avgMatchScore * communityScoreScale);\n              // Mark community-sourced results and assign calibrated score\n              const communityRows = memberRows.map((row) => ({\n                ...row,\n                similarity: typeof row.similarity === 'number' ? row.similarity : 0.5,\n                score: calibratedScore,\n                _communityFallback: true,\n              }));\n              // Merge: append community results not already in pipeline results\n              const existingIds = new Set(resultsForFormatting.map((r) => (r as Record<string, unknown>).id as number));\n              const newRows = communityRows.filter((r) => !existingIds.has(r.id));\n              if (newRows.length > 0) {\n                resultsForFormatting = [...resultsForFormatting, ...newRows as unknown as SessionAwareResult[]];\n                communityFallbackApplied = true;\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        } catch (err: unknown) {\n          const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n          console.warn(`[memory-search] Community search fallback failed (fail-open): ${msg}`);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Apply folder boost — multiply similarity for results matching discovered folder\n    if (folderBoost && folderBoost.folder && folderBoost.factor > 1) {\n      let boostedCount = 0;\n      for (const r of resultsForFormatting) {\n        const filePath = (r as Record<string, unknown>).file_path as string | undefined;\n        if (filePath && filePath.includes(folderBoost.folder)) {\n          const raw = (r as Record<string, unknown>);\n          if (typeof raw.similarity === 'number') {\n            raw.similarity = Math.min(raw.similarity * folderBoost.factor, 1.0);\n            boostedCount++;\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      // Re-sort by similarity after boosting\n      if (boostedCount > 0) {\n        resultsForFormatting.sort((a, b) => {\n          const sa = (a as Record<string, unknown>).similarity as number ?? 0;\n          const sb = (b as Record<string, unknown>).similarity as number ?? 0;\n          return sb - sa;\n        });\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Eval channel attribution should reflect the retrieval pipeline output\n    // before canonical source filtering drops rows for response formatting.\n    _evalChannelPayloads = buildEvalChannelPayloads(\n      pipelineResult.results as unknown as Array<Record<string, unknown>>,\n    );\n\n    const canonicalFilter = filterCanonicalSourceRows(resultsForFormatting);\n    resultsForFormatting = canonicalFilter.results;\n    const avgScore = computeAverageScore(resultsForFormatting as Array<Record<string, unknown>>);\n    const requestQualityLabel = pipelineResult.metadata.stage4.evidenceGapDetected ? 'gap' : 'weak';\n    const qualityGapRouting = routeQuery(effectiveQuery, undefined, {\n      quality: requestQualityLabel,\n      avgScore,\n    });\n    const qualityFallback = qualityGapRouting.qualityFallback;\n    if (qualityFallback.engaged) {\n      queryPlan = qualityGapRouting.queryPlan;\n    }\n\n    if (sessionId && isSessionRetrievalStateEnabled()) {\n      const activeGoal = effectiveQuery.trim().length > 0 ? effectiveQuery : null;\n      if (activeGoal) {\n        retrievalSessionStateManager.updateGoal(sessionId, activeGoal);\n      }\n      if (Array.isArray(anchors) && anchors.length > 0) {\n        retrievalSessionStateManager.setAnchors(sessionId, anchors);\n      }\n\n      const goalRefinement = refineForGoal(resultsForFormatting, sessionId);\n      resultsForFormatting = goalRefinement.results as SessionAwareResult[];\n      goalRefinementPayload = {\n        activeGoal: goalRefinement.metadata.activeGoal,\n        applied: goalRefinement.metadata.refined,\n        boostedCount: goalRefinement.metadata.boostedCount,\n      };\n    }\n\n    // Build extra data from pipeline metadata for response formatting\n    const lexicalCapability = getLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot();\n    if (lexicalCapability) {\n      console.error(\n        `[memory-search] Lexical capability path '${lexicalCapability.lexicalPath}' (fallbackState: ${lexicalCapability.fallbackState})`\n      );\n    }\n\n    const extraData: Record<string, unknown> = {\n      stateStats: pipelineResult.annotations.stateStats,\n      featureFlags: {\n        ...pipelineResult.annotations.featureFlags,\n      },\n      pipelineMetadata: pipelineResult.metadata,\n      qualityGapFallback: qualityFallback,\n    };\n    if (lexicalCapability) {\n      extraData.lexicalPath = lexicalCapability.lexicalPath;\n      extraData.fallbackState = lexicalCapability.fallbackState;\n    }\n\n    if (pipelineResult.annotations.evidenceGapWarning) {\n      extraData.evidenceGapWarning = pipelineResult.annotations.evidenceGapWarning;\n    }\n\n    if (detectedIntent) {\n      extraData.intent = {\n        type: detectedIntent,\n        confidence: intentConfidence,\n        description: intentClassifier.getIntentDescription(detectedIntent as IntentType),\n        weightsApplied: pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.intentWeightsApplied,\n      };\n    }\n\n    if (artifactRouting) {\n      extraData.artifactRouting = artifactRouting;\n      extraData.artifact_routing = artifactRouting;\n    }\n\n    if (pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.feedbackSignalsApplied === 'applied') {\n      extraData.feedbackSignals = { applied: true };\n      extraData.feedback_signals = { applied: true };\n    }\n\n    if (pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.graphContribution) {\n      extraData.graphContribution = pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.graphContribution;\n      extraData.graph_contribution = pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.graphContribution;\n    }\n\n    if (pipelineResult.metadata.stage3.rerankApplied) {\n      extraData.rerankMetadata = {\n        reranking_enabled: true,\n        reranking_requested: true,\n        reranking_applied: true,\n      };\n    }\n\n    if (pipelineResult.metadata.stage3.chunkReassemblyStats.chunkParents > 0) {\n      extraData.chunkReassembly = pipelineResult.metadata.stage3.chunkReassemblyStats;\n      extraData.chunk_reassembly = pipelineResult.metadata.stage3.chunkReassemblyStats;\n    }\n    extraData.sourceContract = {\n      version: CANONICAL_READER_CACHE_VERSION,\n      archivedTierEnabled: false,\n      legacyFallbackEnabled: false,\n      includeArchivedCompatibility: includeArchivedRequested === true ? 'ignored' : 'not_requested',\n      preferredDocumentTypes: ['spec_doc', 'continuity'],\n      retainedResults: canonicalFilter.stats.retained,\n      droppedNonCanonicalResults: canonicalFilter.stats.dropped,\n      countsBySourceKind: canonicalFilter.stats.bySourceKind,\n    };\n\n    if (includeTrace && pipelineResult.trace) {\n      extraData.retrievalTrace = pipelineResult.trace;\n    }\n    const degradedReadiness = mapGraphReadinessToTelemetry(\n      getGraphReadinessSnapshotFromMarker(),\n    );\n    searchDecisionEnvelope = buildSearchDecisionEnvelope({\n      requestId: searchDecisionRequestId,\n      tenantId: normalizedScope.tenantId,\n      userId: normalizedScope.userId,\n      agentId: normalizedScope.agentId,\n      queryPlan,\n      trustTreeInput: {\n        responsePolicy: {\n          state: 'live',\n          decision: 'memory_search_response',\n        },\n      },\n      degradedReadiness,\n      pipelineTiming: pipelineResult.metadata.timing,\n      timestamp: new Date(_searchStartTime).toISOString(),\n      latencyMs: Date.now() - _searchStartTime,\n    });\n    extraData.searchDecisionEnvelope = searchDecisionEnvelope;\n    extraData.search_decision_envelope = searchDecisionEnvelope;\n    try {\n      const adaptiveShadow = buildAdaptiveShadowProposal(\n        requireDb(),\n        effectiveQuery,\n        resultsForFormatting as Array<Record<string, unknown> & { id: number }>,\n      );\n      if (adaptiveShadow) {\n        extraData.adaptiveShadow = adaptiveShadow;\n        extraData.adaptive_shadow = adaptiveShadow;\n      }\n    } catch (_error: unknown) {\n      // Adaptive proposal logging is best-effort only\n    }\n\n    const appliedBoosts: Record<string, unknown> = {\n      session: { applied: pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.sessionBoostApplied },\n      causal: { applied: pipelineResult.metadata.stage2.causalBoostApplied },\n    };\n    if (folderBoost && folderBoost.folder) {\n      appliedBoosts.folder = { applied: true, folder: folderBoost.folder, factor: folderBoost.factor };\n    }\n    if (communityFallbackApplied) {\n      appliedBoosts.communityFallback = { applied: true, retrievalLevel };\n    }\n    extraData.appliedBoosts = appliedBoosts;\n    extraData.applied_boosts = appliedBoosts;\n\n    let formatted = await formatSearchResults(\n      resultsForFormatting as RawSearchResult[],\n      pipelineConfig.searchType,\n      includeContent,\n      anchors,\n      null,\n      null,\n      extraData,\n      includeTrace,\n      normalizedQuery,   // pass query for recovery + confidence context\n      specFolder ?? null // pass specFolder for recovery narrowing detection\n    );\n\n    // Prepend evidence gap warning if present\n    if (pipelineResult.annotations.evidenceGapWarning && formatted?.content?.[0]?.text) {\n      try {\n        const parsed = JSON.parse(formatted.content[0].text) as Record<string, unknown>;\n        if (typeof parsed.summary === 'string') {\n          parsed.summary = `${pipelineResult.annotations.evidenceGapWarning}\\n\\n${parsed.summary}`;\n          formatted.content[0].text = JSON.stringify(parsed, null, 2);\n        }\n      } catch (_error: unknown) {\n        // Non-fatal\n      }\n    }\n    if (isProgressiveDisclosureEnabled()) {\n      const parsedFormatted = parseResponseEnvelope(formatted);\n      if (parsedFormatted) {\n        const data = parsedFormatted.envelope.data && typeof parsedFormatted.envelope.data === 'object'\n          ? parsedFormatted.envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n          : {};\n        data.progressiveDisclosure = buildProgressiveResponse(\n          resultsForFormatting,\n          undefined,\n          effectiveQuery,\n          { scopeKey: progressiveScopeKey },\n        );\n        parsedFormatted.envelope.data = data;\n        formatted = replaceResponseEnvelope(formatted, parsedFormatted.firstEntry, parsedFormatted.envelope);\n      }\n    }\n\n    formatted = applyPublicationGateToResponse(formatted);\n\n    const cachePayload = extractSearchCachePayload(formatted);\n    if (cachePayload && cacheEnabled) {\n      toolCache.set(cacheKey, cachePayload, { toolName: 'memory_search' });\n    }\n\n    responseToReturn = cachePayload\n      ? buildSearchResponseFromPayload(cachePayload, _searchStartTime, false)\n      : formatted;\n  }\n\n  responseToReturn = applyPublicationGateToResponse(responseToReturn);\n\n  if (sessionId && isSessionRetrievalStateEnabled() && !sessionManager.isEnabled()) {\n    const parsedResponse = parseResponseEnvelope(responseToReturn);\n    const data = parsedResponse?.envelope.data && typeof parsedResponse.envelope.data === 'object'\n      ? parsedResponse.envelope.data as Record<string, unknown>\n      : null;\n    const existingResults = Array.isArray(data?.results) ? data.results as SessionAwareResult[] : null;\n\n    if (parsedResponse && data && existingResults && existingResults.length > 0) {\n      const deduped = deduplicateWithSessionState(existingResults, sessionId);\n      data.results = deduped.results as SessionAwareResult[];\n      data.count = deduped.results.length;\n      data.sessionDedup = deduped.metadata;\n      parsedResponse.envelope.data = data;\n      responseToReturn = replaceResponseEnvelope(responseToReturn, parsedResponse.firstEntry, parsedResponse.envelope);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Apply session deduplication AFTER cache\n  if (sessionId && enableDedup && sessionManager.isEnabled()) {\n    let resultsData: Record<string, unknown> | null = null;\n    if (responseToReturn?.content?.[0]?.text && typeof responseToReturn.content[0].text === 'string') {\n      try {","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":1346,"totalLines":1347,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts","time":{"start":1780738219150,"end":1780738219164}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_076c916f5a177fda016a23e8aaf3588191a252eb151aec77ad"}},"id":"prt_e9c44dc80001eT4GhfhtQy1gOL","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","messageID":"msg_e9c44b8f8001v2rOknVCFoX4el"}}
