{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738253885,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_uq2ZVA01UWnSVv6Qb8YlvjiH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"memory_delete|retention-sweep|health|dashboard|audit|mutation ledger|doctor|ownership","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 236 matches (showing first 100)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md:\n  Line 288: 6. Reduces evidence into a dimensional dashboard with convergence detection (per SKILL canonical stopReason enum: converged | maxIterationsReached | blockedStop | manualStop | error | stuckRecovery)\n\n  Line 320: | Dynamic | `--dynamic` | Any agent (generated on-the-fly) | Evaluating arbitrary agents, integration health checks |\n\n  Line 366: 6. Reduce state, refresh dashboard\n\n  Line 372: - `{spec_folder}/improvement/agent-improvement-dashboard.md` — dimensional progress + stop status\n\n  Line 479:   Dashboard: specs/041/008/improvement/agent-improvement-dashboard.md\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/agent.md:\n  Line 154:    │    Format: kebab-case (e.g., quality-gate, security-audit)     │\n\n  Line 444: /create:agent security-audit --mode primary\n\n  Line 446: → Creates `[runtime_agent_path]/security-audit.md`\n\n  Line 471: /create:agent security-audit --mode primary :confirm\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md:\n  Line 2: description: Install or repair MCP servers via /doctor:mcp <install|debug> sub-action routing.\n\n  Line 17: >    - `install` → `doctor_mcp_install.yaml`\n\n  Line 18: >    - `debug`   → `doctor_mcp_debug.yaml`\n\n  Line 29: - **STANDALONE COMMAND**: this is not part of `/doctor`'s subsystem-diagnostic family. It handles MCP infrastructure repair, which is upstream of every subsystem's database.\n\n  Line 31: > **Format:** `/doctor:mcp <install|debug> [flags]`\n\n  Line 32: > Examples: `/doctor:mcp install --server mk-spec-memory`, `/doctor:mcp debug --fix`\n\n  Line 40: | Alternative | Per-server install guides + `mcp-doctor.sh` health probes; rollback by deleting the offending dir and reinstalling from canonical guide     |\n\n  Line 70:      EMIT \"Unknown sub-action '<sub_action>'. Valid: install, debug. Try `/doctor:mcp install` or `/doctor:mcp debug`.\"\n\n  Line 75:      install) yaml_asset = \"doctor_mcp_install.yaml\" ;;\n\n  Line 76:      debug)   yaml_asset = \"doctor_mcp_debug.yaml\"   ;;\n\n  Line 96:      EMIT \"Flag '--fix' is only valid for `debug`. Did you mean `/doctor:mcp debug --fix`?\"\n\n  Line 99:      EMIT \"Flag '--runtime' is only valid for `install`. Did you mean `/doctor:mcp install --runtime <name>`?\"\n\n  Line 104: 8. HAND OFF to .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/<yaml_asset>.\n\n  Line 113: `/doctor:mcp` bundles two MCP infrastructure operations:\n\n  Line 115: - **`debug`** — Diagnose and repair broken MCP servers. Runs `mcp-doctor.sh --json`, cross-references each failure with its install guide, offers targeted repair (`--fix`), re-verifies, and reports a final status.\n\n  Line 117: These are the only two operations on MCP infrastructure itself. Every other `/doctor*` workflow runs INSIDE the working MCP layer; if MCP is broken, run `/doctor:mcp debug --fix` first.\n\n  Line 126: - `STATUS=OK` — install or debug completed (final state in mcp-doctor.sh report)\n\n  Line 132: - `install` → `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml`\n\n  Line 133: - `debug` → `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_debug.yaml`\n\n  Line 136: - `.opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/mcp-doctor.sh` — JSON diagnostic\n\n  Line 137: - `.opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/mcp-doctor-lib.sh` — shared lib\n\n  Line 145: /doctor:mcp install                   