 mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_scan, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_apply, mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__session_health\n\n  Line 8: > **Code Graph ownership:** The code-graph tier now uses `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite` by default (skill-local, shared across runtimes via the `.opencode/skills` symlink), with `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR` as the DB-dir override.\n\n  Line 19: >    - -> `doctor_update.yaml` (per-phase prompt)\n\n  Line 24: - **ONLY MODE ()**: this doctor command is always interactive by design; deleted mode suffixes are invalid.\n\n  Line 29: - **RESTART CONTRACT**: if runtime bootstrap changes layout or build artifacts during `/doctor:update`, stop with `STATUS=RESTART_REQUIRED`; start a fresh OpenCode process and rerun with `--resume-bootstrap`.\n\n  Line 34: - **LOCK SCOPE**: acquire `mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.flock` before probing or mutating any database.\n\n  Line 35: - **STATE LOG REQUIRED**: every terminal path writes `mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json`.\n\n  Line 37: > **Format:** `/doctor:update` [flags]\n\n  Line 38: > Example: `/doctor:update`\n\n  Line 44: | Location    | Runtime databases under `mcp_server/database/` plus `.doctor-update.*` lock/state files                   |\n\n  Line 54:    - Always: execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\", yaml = \"doctor_update.yaml\"\n\n  Line 71:    /doctor:update rebuilds ALL spec-kit databases in dependency order with\n\n  Line 200: action: lock -> probe -> migrate -> snapshot -> dashboard -> execute DAG -> validate -> rollback/finalize\n\n  Line 205: `/doctor:update` is the one-shot maintenance path for bringing the spec-kit runtime databases back into alignment with the repository. It coordinates the individual doctor surfaces, but adds cross-database safety that a single subsystem command cannot provide: one lock, one snapshot set, one dependency DAG, one rollback policy, and one state log.\n\n  Line 207: Use it after upgrading spec-kit, after large packet moves, after a stale startup graph warning, or when multiple doctor commands would otherwise need to be run by hand. The command is intentionally conservative because a partial rebuild can leave memory, graph, advisor, and eval state disagreeing with each other.\n\n  Line 214: | context-index | `mcp_server/database/context-index__*.sqlite` active profile DB    | `memory_health`, `memory_stats`      | `memory_index_scan`                    | `memory_search` representative queries |\n\n  Line 215: | vector-index  | `mcp_server/database/context-index__*.sqlite` active profile DB    | `memory_health`, `memory_stats`      | `memory_index_scan`                    | embedding-backed `memory_search`       |\n\n  Line 220: | eval          | `mcp_server/database/speckit-eval.db`                              | `session_health`, eval probes        | `eval_run_ablation`                    | ablation run completes                 |\n\n  Line 267: | `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite` and `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite.pre-doctor-update.*.bak`                                       | structural graph DB + snapshots        |\n\n  Line 268: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/context-index__*.sqlite` and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/context-index__*.sqlite.pre-doctor-update.*.bak`                               | memory records, FTS, causal edges, vectors |\n\n  Line 269: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite` and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite.pre-doctor-update.*.bak`                                         | skill graph DB                         |\n\n  Line 270: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` and `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite.pre-doctor-update.*.bak`                                                               | deep research/review graph DB          |\n\n  Line 271: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/speckit-eval.db` and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/speckit-eval.db.pre-doctor-update.*.bak`                                               | eval DB                                |\n\n  Line 272: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.flock`                                                                                                                                            | primary concurrent-dispatch lock       |\n\n  Line 273: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.lock`                                                                                                                                             | PID-file fallback with stale detection |\n\n  Line 274: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json`                                                                                                                                    | state log                              |\n\n  Line 287: | 4     | Execute in dependency order with tier prompts                                          | `phase_4_status_dashboard` + `phase_5_dependency_order_execute` |\n\n  Line 293: | 10    | Write `.doctor-update.last-run.json`; release flock; cleanup old snapshots unless kept | `phase_10_state_log_unlock_cleanup`                             |\n\n  Line 297: `mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json` is written on success, failure, rollback, and cancellation.\n\n  Line 301:   \"command\": \"/doctor:update\",\n\n  Line 314:       \"snapshot_path\": \"mcp_server/database/context-index__hf-local__onnx-community-embeddinggemma-300m-onnx__768__q8.sqlite.pre-doctor-update.3.4.1.0.20260509T130100Z.bak\"\n\n  Line 337: State log: mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json\n\n  Line 347: - `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"...\"` — see state log `.doctor-update.last-run.json` for details\n\n  Line 349: When `STATUS=RESTART_REQUIRED`, no database rebuild has started yet. Start a fresh OpenCode process so the MCP launcher can register the now-built `mk-spec-memory` surface, then rerun `/doctor:update --resume-bootstrap`.\n\n  Line 353: - `/doctor memory` - isolated context-index/vector-index health and rebuild.\n\n  Line 354: - `/doctor causal-graph` - isolated causal edge coverage and add-only repair.\n\n  Line 355: - `/doctor deep-loop` - isolated research/review coverage graph rebuild.\n\n  Line 356: - `/doctor code-graph` - isolated structural graph diagnosis and confirm workflow.\n\n  Line 357: - `/doctor skill-advisor` - advisor and skill-graph optimization pass.\n\n  Line 358: - `/doctor skill-budget` - advisor budget/status helper.\n\n  Line 363: 2. Load the selected `assets/doctor_update.yaml` file and execute it as the source of truth.\n\n  Line 367: 7. In Phase 4, render the cross-subsystem dashboard before deciding which dependency steps to run. skips this decision and runs the full chain.\n\n  Line 372: 12. Always write `.doctor-update.last-run.json`, release the flock, and remove snapshots older than 30 days unless `--keep-snapshots` is true.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md:\n  Line 2: description: Router for /doctor <target>; dispatches per-subsystem diagnostic to the right YAML via the _routes.yaml manifest.\n\n  Line 4: allowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_status, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_scan, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_apply, mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__embedder_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status\n\n  Line 17: > 2. Look `target` up in `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml`. Resolve `yaml`, `setup_vars`, `allowed_flags`, `mutating`, `mcp_tools`, and any `script_invocations`.\n\n  Line 18: > 3. Run the per-target flag parser (Tier 2) using ONLY that target's `allowed_flags`. Any unknown or cross-target flag MUST raise a clear error pointing to the correct command (e.g. \"`--confidence-threshold` is not a flag for `memory`; did you mean `/doctor causal-graph --confidence-threshold=0.8`?\").\n\n  Line 32: - **NO YAML MODIFICATIONS**: the 10 YAML assets under `assets/doctor_*.yaml` are stable and untouched by this router.\n\n  Line 35: > **Format:** `/doctor <target> [flags]` | `/doctor list` | `/doctor ?`\n\n  Line 36: > Examples: `/doctor memory --dry-run`, `/doctor causal-graph --confidence-threshold=0.8`\n\n  Line 50: | `skill-budget`  | n/a (read-only audit)                                                                     | **read-only**  | No mutations; report-only                                         | Diagnostic output only                                       |\n\n  Line 58: | `memory`        | `doctor_memory.yaml`            | execution_mode, intent, incremental, no_snapshot, dry_run               | read-only      | Diagnose the memory continuity index; report drift and recommend action   |\n\n  Line 59: | `embeddings`    | `doctor_embeddings.yaml`        | execution_mode                                                          | read-only      | Inspect provider selection and hf-local model-server status               |\n\n  Line 60: | `causal-graph`  | `doctor_causal-graph.yaml`      | execution_mode, intent, confidence_threshold, no_snapshot, dry_run      | read-only      | Diagnose causal-edge integrity; sample drift and recommend candidates     |\n\n  Line 61: | `code-graph`    | `doctor_code-graph.yaml`        | execution_mode, scope                                                   | read-only      | Diagnose code-graph index; report stale / missed / bloat findings         |\n\n  Line 62: | `deep-loop`     | `doctor_deep-loop.yaml`         | execution_mode, intent, scope, no_snapshot, dry_run                     | read-only      | Diagnose deep-loop coverage graphs (research / review)                    |\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 236 matches (136 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":236,"truncated":true},"title":"memory_delete|retention-sweep|health|dashboard|audit|mutation ledger|doctor|ownership","time":{"start":1780738253862,"end":1780738253883}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06fef252c6ca1472016a23e8cd2d3c8191ba11f32071c7b1d4"}},"id":"prt_e9c4563c30012OR3VOJ038qbnB","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","messageID":"msg_e9c453ddd001QL6YKVN6nbPJ50"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780738254308,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"id":"prt_e9c4565e20015o6XXY1NQjDV6m","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"50685c2a6a1e950fed2bf1ad78e4e0894695ddde","messageID":"msg_e9c453ddd001QL6YKVN6nbPJ50","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":139522,"input":11229,"output":241,"reasoning":52,"cache":{"write":0,"read":128000}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780738256461,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"id":"prt_e9c456e4b001d2ceaI2rsvFyl7","messageID":"msg_e9c456709001HKosgL39QLExeZ","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","snapshot":"a3409d1a0332cf6deefc1eb4c8abacbe74e63714","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738327130,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","part":{"id":"prt_e9c45f549001iXq5AgkF82hIdH","messageID":"msg_e9c456709001HKosgL39QLExeZ","sessionID":"ses_163bcc50affeyxhkrz48ouVc7l","type":"text","text":"## Per-behavior UX design\n\n- **source_kind tagging**: default · infer automatically from caller/context: `/memory:save` agent-authored canonical continuity = `agent`, enrichment/reconsolidation/retention = `system`, imports/scans = `import`, feedback ledger = `feedback`, explicitly user-authored protected docs = `human`; surfacing · hidden on hot-path save/search, exposed in `data.sourceKind`/trace/debug and `/memory:manage` or `/doctor memory` diagnostics; friction-budget · zero prompts, zero required params; opt-out · no opt-out for recording, only hide/show via trace/debug profile; errors · \"Automated update skipped human-authored fields; safe fields were still saved.\" Grounding: `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts`.\n\n- **idempotency (retry-safe save)**: default · server derives receipt from normalized operation/content fingerprint; caller never supplies an operation id; surfacing · first save says normal `Memory indexed/updated successfully`, retry only adds a quiet line like `Retry recognized; returned prior save #<id>` plus `data.idempotency.replayed=true`; friction-budget · retry is just running the same save again; opt-out · no normal opt-out, `force:true` keeps its current meaning of intentional re-index, not \"disable safety\"; errors · distinguish \"same retry replayed\" from \"same content already exists\" using current duplicate/unchanged style from `buildSaveResponse`. Grounding: `.opencode/commands/memory/save.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/response-builder.ts`.\n\n- **advisory near-duplicate hint**: default · compute only when embeddings already exist and only surface deterministic high-confidence/borderline cases; surfacing · save response only when actionable, using existing `data.assistiveRecommendation` shape and one hint, not a modal: `Possible related record #<id>; saved normally`; friction-budget · never blocks save, never creates a review queue; opt-out · hide hints by default in compact profile or env/config flag such as near-duplicate advisories off; errors · if embeddings are pending, say nothing by default or debug-only `Near-duplicate check skipped; embedding pending`. Grounding: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/response-builder.ts`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts`.\n\n- **feedback-event capture + diagnostics**: default · capture `search_shown`, query-flow, and `result_cited` as shadow-only events when enabled; no ranking/retention mutation; surfacing · not in search results, only in `/memory:search dashboard`, `/memory:search history`, or `/memory:manage feedback diagnostics`; friction-budget · no rating buttons, no \"was this useful?\" prompt on the hot path; opt-out · local privacy kill switch, e.g. implicit feedback logging disabled; errors · fail silently with debug/doctor visibility only: feedback logging must never break search. Grounding: `.opencode/commands/memory/search.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts`.\n\n- **automated-mutation audit**: default · append compact audit/ledger rows for automated save, delete, supersede, reconsolidation, feedback reducer candidates, and retention actions; surfacing · only show in normal output if audit append fails, matching existing `Mutation ledger append failed; audit trail may be incomplete.` warnings; `/memory:manage audit` and `/doctor memory` show full history; friction-budget · no confirmation, no audit summaries after every success; opt-out · no opt-out for safety ledger, only verbosity controls; errors · warning severity, not alarm, unless the mutation depends on audit for rollback/compliance. Grounding: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/response-builder.ts`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-delete.ts`.\n\n- **tombstone delete**: default · `memory_delete` becomes soft-delete/tombstone first, preserving first delete timestamp; repeat delete is idempotent and does not extend retention; surfacing · command says `Tombstoned 1 spec-doc record` and gives restore/purge hint only when useful, while retention sweep keeps its dry-run-first output; friction-budget · same delete command, same `confirm:true` contract, no extra \"soft or hard?\" question; opt-out · hard purge only via explicit retention/admin purge path, not regular delete; errors · `Already tombstoned at <timestamp>; no change made` and `Purge not due yet; use retention sweep dry-run to inspect`. Grounding: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-delete.ts`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-retention-sweep.ts`.\n\n- **stale-exclusion in search**: default · normal `/memory:search` excludes tombstoned/purgeable and truly archived rows, but should audit whether deprecated/superseded relevant rows are silently lost; surfacing · compact search stays as documented: folder, score, id, title only; add omission metadata only in `includeTrace`, debug profile, dashboard, or when results are empty/weak and stale rows would have matched; friction-budget · no filters required for normal search; opt-out · explicit diagnostics mode to include omitted stale/deprecated candidates, not a default toggle; errors · helpful non-alarming message: `Active results shown; 2 stale/deprecated candidates omitted. Use diagnostics if investigating history.` Grounding: `.opencode/commands/memory/search.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts`.\n\n- **MCP tool-ownership map**: default · static ownership/stability map generated from the 37-tool MCP surface and maintained by system-spec-kit/system-code-graph ownership boundaries; surfacing · `/memory:manage help`, `/doctor memory`, `/doctor list`, and unknown/deprecated tool diagnostics, not every MCP response; friction-budget · developer never chooses owner or stability class while saving/searching; opt-out · none needed, it is documentation/diagnostic metadata; errors · route mistakes should say `This is a code-graph tool; use code_graph_*` or `memory_search owns retrieval; memory_save owns canonical continuity writes`. Grounding: `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md`, `.opencode/commands/memory/search.md`.\n\n## UX principles for this integration\n\n- Infer, do not ask: `source_kind`, idempotency keys, audit actor, and stale state should be server-derived.\n- Surface on exception, not success: normal save/search output should stay compact unless something changes the user's next action.\n- Save/search hot paths must remain one-step: safety features run behind the command, not as follow-up chores.\n- Diagnostics are pull-based: dashboards, `/doctor`, `includeTrace`, and `/memory:manage` carry detail.\n- Advisory means advisory: duplicate, stale, and feedback signals should not block or mutate canonical truth without explicit measured promotion.\n- Use plain language: \"retry recognized\", \"saved normally\", \"omitted stale candidates\", \"audit incomplete\" beats internal provenance jargon.\n\n## Friction anti-patterns to avoid\n\n- Asking the developer to choose `source_kind`; zero-friction alternative: infer it from tool/caller and only expose it in diagnostics.\n- Requiring user-provided idempotency tokens; zero-friction alternative: server receipt from content/request fingerprint and replay on identical retry.\n- Turning near-duplicates into hard rejects or review queues; zero-friction alternative: save normally and show at most one advisory hint.\n- Showing feedback widgets after every search; zero-friction alternative: passive shadow event capture and dashboard-only diagnostics.\n- Printing audit rows on every mutation; zero-friction alternative: append silently, warn only when audit failed.\n- Making delete ask \"soft delete or hard delete?\"; zero-friction alternative: normal delete tombstones, retention sweep purges later.\n- Hiding stale/deprecated matches without traceability; zero-friction alternative: default active results plus debug/weak-result omission diagnostics.\n- Consolidating MCP tools into a generic operation dispatcher; zero-friction alternative: keep discoverable tools, add an ownership map for maintainers and `/doctor` routing.\n\nDELTA_JSON: {\"iteration\":\"004\",\"focus\":\"UX-first design\",\"findingsCount\":8,\"newInfoRatio\":0.82,\"impacts\":[\"source_kind tagging -> infer from caller/context and hide unless diagnostic\",\"idempotency -> server-derived retry receipt with replay-only hint\",\"near-duplicate -> deterministic advisory saved normally\",\"feedback events -> shadow capture diagnostics only\",\"automated audit -> append silently warn only on failure\",\"tombstone delete -> regular delete soft-deletes idempotently\",\"stale-exclusion -> active default with omission diagnostics on demand\",\"MCP tool map -> maintenance/doctor surface not hot-path output\"],\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md\",\".opencode/commands/memory/save.md\",\".opencode/commands/memory/search.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/response-builder.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-delete.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-retention-sweep.ts\"]}","time":{"start":1780738291017,"end":1780738327127},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0195c68912b0bfa5016a23e8f2ffd88191b37330f53c9eab3c","phase":"final_answer"}}}}
